{"_id":"ZsZapS4lKEue2V2w","name":"bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen","pages":[{"_id":"PML9hY16iYBRL4dF","name":"PDF local","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h1>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen</h1><p><strong>Archivo:</strong> bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf</p><p><strong>Paginas:</strong> 30</p><p><a href=\"systems/broken-tales/assets/source-pdfs/bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen-2022-06-29.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Abrir PDF dentro de Foundry</a></p>","markdown":""},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241731,"modifiedTime":1783973241731,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"bPIlgUYxdbR4lOVJ","name":"Pagina 1","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 1</h2><p>Informations on the Sheet.<br> ◆ A brief background is introduced under the Hunter’s <br>name, explaining who the Hunter is and why they joined <br>the Order.<br> ◆ Descriptors indicate what the Hunter does best and <br>what their flaws are. Incorporating a Descriptor into <br>the narration of a Hunter’s actions allows a Position or <br>Defense Check to start from 3 Base Successes. Getting in <br>trouble during the narrative, thanks to the Descriptor’s <br>Downside, allows you to check them off and gain XP .<br> ◆ Gifts are powerful special abilities that only Hunters of the <br>Order possess. They can be used whenever the opportunity <br>arises, following the rules and limitations of the Gift itself.<br> ◆ The Dark Ego  represents their essence and bond to the <br>fairytale world, what the Hunter was before their Breaking <br>Point. Y ou can activate the Dark Ego whenever the <br>Activator’s condition is triggered, or when the Hunter <br>suffers or decides to inflict 1 Wound on themselves. The <br>effect of the Dark Ego persists throughout the course of <br>the Scene.<br> ◆ Equipment indicates what gear the Hunter possesses and <br>can use in order to perform their mission on behalf of the <br>Order.<br> ◆ The Soma value represents the Hunter’s inner strength and <br>ability to tap into the true essence of a Broken Fairytale. <br>Spending Soma increases the chances of a positive <br>Outcome in any Position and Defense Check, or allows <br>the activation of certain Gifts.<br>Player’s Sheet<br>When the Storyteller asks for a <br>Position or Defense Check…<br>Check if one of the Hunter’s Descriptors can help them in the action being <br>performed. If so, the Hunter starts with 3 Base Successes. If no Descriptor <br>is relevant, only 1 Base Success  is obtained. It’s possible to obtain <br>Additional Successes (for example, as a result of a Gift) or Penalties (to <br>be subtracted from the total), to modify the number of Base Successes. Once <br>this is done, the number of  Successes  is compared with the NPC’s or <br>Threat’s Opposition Level declared by the Storyteller. <br>There are 3 Levels of Opposition:<br>Easy 3, Medium 5, Hard 7<br>For an action to have a positive Outcome, you must obtain a total of <br>Successes (given by the sum of Base Successes and Additional Successes) <br>that is at least equal to the Opposition Level you are facing.<br>To get ADDITIONAL <br>SUCCESSES you can...<br> ◆ Spend Soma from the Hunter’s reserve to obtain 1 Additional <br>Success for each point.<br> ◆ Decide to roll one or more 6-sided dice. Y ou gain an Additional <br>Success for each die rolled. However, if even a single die rolls <br>a 1, the entire Check fails. All other results (2-6) count as <br>Additional Successes.<br>How many dice can you roll?<br>Rolling dice is a gamble. Y ou can roll as many dice as you wish to <br>reach the Outcome you desire. However, each additional die rolled <br>increases the chances of rolling a 1, even one of which results in a <br>Failure. Even when aiming for the best Outcome (Outcome with <br>Increment) the total number of Successes needed will never exceed <br>the Opposition Level + 2.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241731,"modifiedTime":1783973241731,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"HfFhLgnJqlBe5bFe","name":"Pagina 2","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 2</h2><p>Find out how it all turns out...<br>If the result is equal to the Opposition Level:  you’ll get <br>an Outcome with a Cost. The Hunter gets what they want but <br>at a Cost chosen by the Storyteller. If it makes sense, the Hunter <br>can also inflict 1 Wound. In a Defense Check the incoming <br>problem is avoided, but with a complication decided by the <br>Storyteller.<br>By scoring 1 point above the Opposition Level:  you’ll <br>get a Standard Outcome. The Hunter gets what they want. <br>In a Defense Check, the problem is handled without any <br>complications. If it makes sense, the Hunter can also inflict 1 <br>Wound.<br>By scoring 2 points above the Opposition Level:  you’ll <br>get an Outcome with an Increment. The Hunter succeeds better <br>than expected and gains an Increment in addition to what they <br>wanted. The Storyteller decides on the additional effect or, <br>alternatively, the special Increment of one of the Hunter’s Gifts <br>can be activated. In the case of a Defense Check, the problem is <br>avoided perfectly and an Increment is also obtained. If it makes <br>sense, the Hunter can also inflict 1 Wound.<br>Once upon a time...<br>If during the Scenario the Hunter gets into trouble and highlights <br>the Downside of one of their Descriptors, the corresponding <br>box must be marked. During an Interlude, each box marked is <br>converted into 1 XP.<br>Declaring an Interlude<br>If Hunters need to catch their breath, a Player can ask <br>the Storyteller for an Interlude between Scene changes. <br>During the Interlude, it is possible to recover 1 Wound <br>or, alternatively, recover 2 Soma. Each Hunter can ask a <br>question of another Hunter to learn more about their past.<br>During an Interlude XP may be spent to obtain <br>additional effects:<br> ◆ Recover 2 Soma for each XP spent.<br> ◆ Recover 1 Wound for each XP spent.<br> ◆ Evolve a Descriptor into a Specialization. For the <br>rest of the Scenario, this will grant 1 Additional <br>Success in each Scene in which it is used for the first <br>time (1 XP).<br> ◆ Obtain a Scenario Gift for the duration of the <br>Scenario (1 XP).<br>Each Interlude, however, represents a use of time. <br>Remember that the Scenario, and the NPCs, may continue <br>to act even when the Hunters aren’t paying attention.A Wound is inflicted...<br>As an effect of a failed Defense Check or as a Cost for an <br>action. Each Wound must be described and annotated in <br>the Bookmark. The Wound narratively affects what the <br>Hunter can do and the Opposition Level of what they <br>face. Whenever you suffer 1 Wound, you can activate your <br>Dark Ego power for the duration of the Scene. A Player <br>may decide to voluntarily inflict a Wound on the Hunter to <br>instantly activate their Dark Ego.<br>When they suffer a third Wound, the Hunter is out of <br>the game or dead. The Storyteller will reveal their fate <br>according to the situation.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241731,"modifiedTime":1783973241731,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"6XyRE3U121QlumAw","name":"Pagina 3","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 3</h2><p>James  <br>the Swordsman</p>","markdown":""},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241731,"modifiedTime":1783973241731,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"dh1mLNUf0bgd8hg0","name":"Pagina 4","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 4</h2><p>Descriptors and Gifts<br>I am a skilled swordsman and possess fine manners, which is why <br>the Order considers me an excellent candidate to move among <br>High Society. I love indulging in good food and dissolute company.<br>• With a Sword or a Smile:  Once per Scene you may <br>perform a gesture of extreme precision with your weapon, such as <br>slipping an object off someone or writing something on a surface. The <br>person observing your skill will either be impressed or intimidated, <br>depending on the Storyteller’s decision. Y ou receive 1 Additional <br>Success when you use the emotion you have aroused to your advantage.<br>I have learned to face monsters and aberrations without being <br>intimidated. The Beast is on my trail because, having tasted my <br>flesh, it can no longer do without it… <br>• Tick-Tock, Here Comes The Beast: While outdoors, you <br>may ask the Storyteller for the Beast to come in search of your flesh.<br>The Beast is a monstrous NPC with the following characteristics: <br>OL Hard 7 – (4 Wounds) <br>Descriptor: I am a great and mighty beast. I overwhelm everything I <br>come across on my way to snatch my prey. <br>Gift – Ravenous Madness: The Beast has an insane craving for your <br>flesh, and will unleash its rage on anyone standing in its way. With its <br>titanic strength, it can tear down trees and walls, and hurl a man away <br>with a single swipe of its huge paws. The Beast is also quite stupid <br>and will leave the Scene as soon as you are out of sight. Y ou receive <br>2 Additional Successes to any Defense Check against it. If the Beast <br>suffers the fourth Wound, it will dissolve. However, it will regenerate <br>and can be used in the next Scene.<br>I have been a lot of things in my life: ship captain, duellist of great <br>renown, and lover of the most beautiful noblewomen. After years of <br>successes and victories, a mysterious child defeated me with deception. <br>This despicable boy led me into the lair of a dangerous beast and, after <br>imprisoning me, left me to be eaten by the monster. I survived, though <br>I lost a hand... I know for certain he who I seek is no human, and I <br>joined the Order to hunt down the child I hate above all else, and thus <br>have my revenge.<br>James<br>the Swordsman<br>I am a man of the world and nothing can really surprise me <br>anymore. I never question myself. After all, I’m the best at <br>what I do.<br>• Dark Ego – I Will have my Satisfaction: When you <br>choose an opponent, there is no escape for them. Once per Scene, you <br>can take an additional action against the target of your challenge (even <br>if you had already acted during this Exchange) to anticipate their move <br>and stop their action with yours. If an opponent inflicts a Wound on <br>you, you savor the taste of the challenge and receive 1 Additional <br>Success at each Check against them for the rest of the Scenario. <br>Activator: You challenge an enemy or otherwise make clear who and <br>how skilled you are.<br>XP<br>Soma<br> 7<br>Equipment <br>A fine dueling blade / A black powder gun / <br>A finely crafted hook / A purple-red cloak / <br>Traveling boots / A precious pair of binoculars <br>/ Valuable rings.<br>Wounds <br>1.<br>2.<br>3.<br>Extra <br>Wound.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241731,"modifiedTime":1783973241731,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"cv6kqbs2wA620gHh","name":"Pagina 5","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 5</h2><p>Garou  <br>the Old Wolf</p>","markdown":""},"sort":500000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241731,"modifiedTime":1783973241731,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"loiwzONZdCgVdj78","name":"Pagina 6","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 6</h2><p>Garou  <br>the Old Wolf<br>Descriptors and Gifts<br>My senses are unfailing. Nothing can escape my sense of <br>smell and that is why the Order uses me as a guardian. I <br>hate strong smells and loud noises because they feel like <br>burning irons to acute senses.<br>• Find Them Forever After: Once you catch someone’s <br>scent, you never forget it. During a Scene, you can spend 1 Soma to <br>memorize the scent of a person you are interacting with. Y ou will <br>always recognize it and it will be easy for you to follow its traces <br>even after some time. If you concentrate, you can hear a noise even <br>at great distances. When someone approaches you, the Storyteller <br>will warn you long before anyone else in the Scene would notice.<br>A true predator knows how to appear as the most helpless <br>of lambs. I know how to disguise myself. My confidence is <br>boundless and I often tend to underestimate danger, ready <br>to risk anything for a tasty bite.<br>• Wolf Among the Lambs: Y ou may spend 1 Soma to <br>assume the shape of a common human. Create a Descriptor that <br>represents you and includes at least one of these words: Old, <br>Helpless, Weak. In your human form you can speak and act <br>without problems, but, as soon as you use your Dark Ego, you will <br>immediately lose the effect of Wolf Among the Lambs. Y ou receive <br>1 Additional Success when you use the Descriptor you created to <br>deceive someone and catch them off guard.<br>I am a mountain wolf and far more cunning than the stupid villagers who <br>tremble at the mere sight of me. I have lived proudly at the head of my pack, <br>leading a thousand raids and eating succulent, tender morsels of human flesh. <br>But I am not so old I cannot face those who hate me the most, though I may be <br>hunted and reviled. Now that I’m part of the Order, I use my strength to defend <br>the weak hunters who are my companions, knowing that with a single bite I <br>could end their insignificant lives.<br>I am fiercer and more powerful than any human and my fangs <br>can pierce even metal. My proud wolf spirit is everything to me.<br>• Dark Ego - The Big Bad Wolf: Y ou are hardened by a lifetime <br>in the great mountains and your skill is matched only by your courage. <br>When you unleash your rage, create a Descriptor for it that includes <br>at least one of these words: Strong, Fierce, Unstoppable. Y ou can <br>employ the strength of three men, gnaw through stone as easily as flesh, <br>or break down any barrier. When you act using this special Descriptor <br>for Position Checks, you get 1 Additional Success. Once per Scene, you <br>can unleash your rage and receive 3 Additional Successes instead of 1.<br>Activator: You assume the form of a Wolf or reveal yourself for what you <br>really are, scaring off weak humans.<br>Equipment <br>A necklace of stones and wood that I carry in a paw, <br>a token of the only human I do not consider food / <br>Knick-knacks, keys and other junk that I sometimes <br>vomit up from my large stomach.<br>Wounds <br>1.<br>2.<br>3.<br>Extra <br>Wound.<br>XP<br>Soma<br> 6</p>","markdown":""},"sort":600000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241731,"modifiedTime":1783973241731,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"0gmRxTUQZnq0Ok1q","name":"Pagina 7","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 7</h2><p>The Astonishing<br>Pied Piper     Without a Name</p>","markdown":""},"sort":700000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241731,"modifiedTime":1783973241731,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"oaflGEqCLfnPpQGN","name":"Pagina 8","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 8</h2><p>Descriptors and Gifts<br>With my pipe I can play any melody and touch the hearts of <br>living beings. Art needs time to express itself.<br>• Soul Music: When you play your pipes you can spend 1 <br>Soma to sing a special melody. Choose from:<br>1. Imparting an emotion:  Create a Descriptor that represents <br>the emotional state you wish to convey. Everybody present will <br>receive that Descriptor for the current Scene. Y ou may have to <br>make a Position Check to affect opponents.<br>2. Bewitching animals: Y ou may give simple commands to <br>animals that hear your melody. If they show an aggressive attitude, <br>you have to make a successful Position Check for your melody to <br>take effect. As long as you are playing, you may ask the animals to <br>do simple actions such as moving or following a simple command.<br>I am a skilled acrobat and musician. My talent is unrivaled <br>and the Order has chosen me for my ability to capture people’s <br>attention and stimulate their emotions. When I am in the grip <br>of artistic inspiration, I am totally divorced from reality.<br>• Skilled Acrobat: When you sing, dance, or move with <br>grace, you always put on a great show. As an additional action, you <br>can spend 1 Soma and decide on one of the following effects:<br>1. Y ou can make an incredible leap, many feet high, without <br>anyone being able to stop you.<br>2. Y ou may take an object, even if it is worn by an enemy.<br>3. Y ou can perform a minor action with a stunt, such as opening <br>a door or flipping a switch, and then return exactly to where you <br>started.<br>As an artist I have traveled to many places and I know many <br>myths and legends. I’m hungry for knowledge and I’m fascinated <br>by everything I don’t know.<br>• Dark Ego - The Power of Music:  Once per Scene, you <br>can make a sound that can be heard by whomever you wish,<br>even from a great distance. Everyone who hears it suffers 1 Wound, <br>fragile objects break, and frightened animals flee. Alternatively, you <br>can play a gentle melody and the wind itself will obey you, carrying <br>your message to whomever you wish, wherever they are. When using <br>The Power of Music, you can also activate a Soul Music effect on one <br>or more targets of your choice.<br>Activator: Demonstrate your art to its fullest extent, with a show that <br>cannot be ignored.<br>XP<br>Soma<br> 5<br>Equipment <br>A precious pipe of the finest workmanship <br>/ A theater mask / A cloak of many colors / <br>Multicolored chalks and powders / An old ocarina, <br>the first instrument I ever played / Hamelin, my <br>faithful trained mouse.<br>Wounds <br>1.<br>2.<br>3.<br>Extra <br>Wound.<br>  <br>The Astonishing<br>Pied Piper       Without a Name<br>I have always made my art my reason for living. I can play so skillfully that it might as well be magic. I <br>have learned to use the power of music to reach into the souls of both humans and animals. Unfortunately, <br>I have lost count of the number of times I have performed dishonorable acts while pursuing the perfect <br>melody. Having been guilty of various crimes and having taken revenge on those who mocked my sincere <br>love for music, I serenely waited for my execution. The Order freed me in exchange for a promise to <br>serve them and put my skills to work in the fight against Darkness. It was in the darkest moments that I <br>glimpsed the perfect melody, so perhaps as a Hunter, I can find it and make it my own.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":800000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241731,"modifiedTime":1783973241731,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"sH7QbaiuFvjkZnW0","name":"Pagina 9","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 9</h2><p>Babayaga<br>The Child Witch</p>","markdown":""},"sort":900000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241731,"modifiedTime":1783973241731,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"yihSyqrAGgJgSLud","name":"Pagina 10","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 10</h2><p>I  am a child witch, and my power is equal only to my ambition. I did not have a childhood, for I was born <br>already aware of my abilities. To most, I seem cynical and cruel. That is because they do not understand <br>that they are pawns, insignificant pieces in the bloody games that witches and warlocks play. The Order <br>does not look down on my age, which is why it has given me the leadership I deserve.<br>Like any respectable sorceress, I carry my trusty bag full of herbs, <br>poisons, and all kinds of magic tools. My childlike appearance is often <br>useful, but sometimes it leads others to underestimate me. I hate that.<br>• Dark Ego - The Evil Witch: Receive 1 Additional Success on any <br>Check when you use one of your spells, either through the Magic Gift or by <br>inserting it into your narrative through the Descriptors. Moreover, you can <br>unleash your evil aura to gain one or more of the following effects:<br>1. Animals and ordinary people are tormented by your presence and will <br>flee in terror. <br>2. Y ou gain 1 Additional Success if you use your magic to punish someone <br>for breaking a promise or agreement you made earlier.<br>3. In the area around you, you can summon daylight or darkness.<br>Activator: Scare ordinary people or dispense punishment through your <br>magic.<br>XP<br>Soma<br> 5<br>Equipment <br>An old and worn-out black cloak/ A bag of magical <br>ingredients / A small, curved dagger / A rag doll / The <br>Ring of the Order / A lucky elderberry branch / The <br>keys of a strange hut in a tree, which is always in my <br>vicinity.<br>Wounds <br>1.<br>2.<br>3.<br>Extra <br>Wound.<br>Baba yaga<br>       The Child Witch<br>Descriptors and Gifts<br>I am a sorceress and my magical powers allow me to do <br>whatever I want. I need the right amount of time to cast my <br>spells.<br>• Magic: When you want to achieve something, you may <br>use witchcraft. Choose what you want with a sentence like: I want <br>to fly on that old broom, or I want to look like a demon in the <br>eyes of those fools. Y our spell must be focused on an object in <br>your possession, such as a broom to fly or a mask you can wear <br>to look like a demon. Pay a cost from 0 to 2 Soma, decided by <br>the Storyteller, to activate your spell for the duration of a Scene. <br>Remember that you can’t ask for someone’s sudden death, but you <br>can inflict Wounds with your actions through magic.<br>I am very skilled at reading people, that is why the Order has <br>chosen me as leader of the Hunters. I love manipulating people <br>and I often do it merely to amuse myself.<br>• Listen to my Words: Once per Scene, when you talk to <br>someone, you can ask the Storyteller a question about them. The <br>question must be regarding their behaviour, such as any vices or <br>their desires they might have. Y ou gain 1 Additional Success in any <br>action where you exploit what you’ve discovered.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":1000000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241731,"modifiedTime":1783973241731,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"20IwaSCha1Qx8kMR","name":"Pagina 11","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 11</h2><p>Regina<br>The Thief Of Hearts</p>","markdown":""},"sort":1100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241731,"modifiedTime":1783973241731,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"LY3FDobvkx7wdt6x","name":"Pagina 12","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 12</h2><p>I was born to be a leader and I have always surrounded myself with faithful followers ready <br>to satisfy my every whim. Lacking the benefit of noble birth, the power I held was pried from the <br>hands of those less deserving to wield it, no matter the cost. I ruled armies of thugs, and broke <br>the hearts of both men and women. After each conquest, I set out in search of a bigger challenge. <br>Because there is still so much out there that should be rightfully mine, I always want more. The <br>Order has given me a new purpose, a new perspective, and new creatures to enslave.<br>I have an enviable charm and love to dress up to fit the role I have <br>chosen. Even when I try to restrain myself, I never go unnoticed.<br>• Dark Ego - As I Want!:  Y ou know that your way is the only <br>right way to do things. During the Scene, as an additional action, you can <br>choose another character who will be issued a <br>command. In the case of <br>an ally, if they do exactly what you tell them, they will receive 1 Additional <br>Success to their action or increase their Opposition Level by 1. If you give <br>a peremptory order to ensnare an enemy, they will lower their Opposition <br>Level by 1 or, if you’ve already seen it in action, you can prevent them <br>from using one of their Gifts. Once per Scene, you can shout, drawing <br>everyone’s attention to you. For a few moments, they will pause to listen <br>to what you have to say.<br>Activator: Take control of a situation and impose your decisions by <br>dramatically drawing attention to yourself.<br>XP<br>Soma<br> 6<br>Equipment <br>A long leather whip with metal studs and spikes / <br>A beautiful fan behind which to hide your face / <br>Dresses for every occasion / A long burgundy cape / <br>Gold and jewels, gifts from my countless suitors / A <br>sharp stiletto that I use as a hairpin.<br>Wounds <br>1.<br>2.<br>3.<br>Extra <br>Wound.<br>Regina<br>   The Thief Of Hearts<br>Descriptors and Gifts<br>I am determined to get what I want, and nothing will get in <br>my way. I will kill, humiliate, or conquer anything that stands <br>between me and my objective. As you can imagine, I sincerely <br>hate being told no!<br>• I Want It!: When you act with clear and direct intention to <br>achieve an objective, you get 1 Additional Success on each Position <br>Check. Once per Session, you can turn a Failure into an Outcome <br>with Increment. Describe how you grit your teeth and fight to get <br>what you want.<br>Thanks to my contacts and charisma, I always have an ace <br>up my sleeve: followers ready to help me and allies who owe <br>me favors. Maintaining an empire of beneficial connections <br>requires commitment and resources.<br>• The Queen: During a Scene you always have a couple of <br>trusted servants with you, ready to execute your every order. <br>Create a Descriptor for each, which represents the skill for which <br>you hold them in your service. Y our servants will do their best to <br>satisfy your every wish. Decide how you pay them. The Storyteller, <br>when and if they deem it necessary, will ask you to honor their <br>services so as not to lose the use of this Gift for the rest of the <br>Scene. Y ou can check this Descriptor multiple times to get XP .</p>","markdown":""},"sort":1200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241731,"modifiedTime":1783973241731,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"MUm1IEtnH1YiT7Ww","name":"Pagina 13","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 13</h2><p>Babai the Judge</p>","markdown":""},"sort":1300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241731,"modifiedTime":1783973241731,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"5STuCDLjI9Lbfuxr","name":"Pagina 14","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 14</h2><p>XP<br>Soma<br> 6<br>Equipment <br>A precious elegant black dress / A cape and a top hat <br>/ A sturdy cane with a hidden blade / A monocle lens <br>/ An exquisitely crafted Larva (typical mask of the <br>Venice Carnival) / An accurate pocket watch.<br>Wounds <br>1.<br>2.<br>3.<br>Extra <br>Wound.<br>After years of honorable service as State Inquisitor of the Republic of Venice, my body and <br>spirit have undergone a rare mutation and fear is now unknown to me. People have always <br>called me Bogeyman, fearing the justice that I represented. Perhaps my own absence of <br>fear made me even more terrifying in the eyes of mortals. The Order has given me a new <br>assignment because even in the fight against darkness, someone needs to be ready to judge <br>what is right and what is wrong.<br>My presence intimidates people, touching the fear that dwells deep in <br>their hearts. The presence of children and their innocent way of looking <br>at the world makes me uneasy.<br>• Dark Ego - If you don’t Stop, I’ll Call the Bogeyman!: <br>Y ou are like a sinuous shadow that can reach anywhere. During a Scene, <br>you can arrive at a location by covering any distance and overcoming <br>any obstacle if one of your allies or an NPC calls your name. When you <br>manifest your true nature, everyone who witnesses it will be frightened <br>and will not act against you unless you threaten them first. The Storyteller <br>may ask you for a Position Check to frighten particularly powerful <br>characters. Receive 1 Additional Success on all Defense Checks you make <br>against the actions of someone who is now fearful.<br>Activator: Enter or leave a shadow by manifesting your true nature and <br>scaring someone.<br>Descriptors and Gifts<br>I am good at understanding, evaluating, and grasping every <br>hidden detail, which is why the Order wanted me as a judge. <br>I am cold, methodical, and cannot stand when plans change <br>abruptly.<br>• Eye of the Judge:  Once per Scene, when you meet a <br>group of NPCs you will immediately understand who is the most <br>and the least capable of them. Moreover, the Storyteller will also <br>reveal to you if there are relationships such as love, hate, or fidelity <br>between two NPCs of your choice. Receive 1 Additional Success <br>when you use the information you have discovered to intimidate <br>or question someone.<br>My body is made of pure shadow and I can become intangible <br>for brief moments. I hate sunlight and cannot properly focus <br>when not surrounded by a comforting shadow.<br>• Like a Shadow: Y ou can spend 1 Soma to manipulate the <br>shadows to your advantage, choose from:<br>1. Acquire a small object, even if it is held by someone, as long as <br>you can see it. <br>2. Make an object in your immediate vicinity topple down. <br>3. Stretch a shadow and manipulate its shape to make it look <br>different.<br>Additionally, you always receive 1 Additional Success on any <br>Defense Check you make while in a shaded area. If you get a <br>successful Outcome, as an additional effect you can move from <br>one shadow to another and no one can prevent it.<br>Babai<br>the Judge</p>","markdown":""},"sort":1400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241731,"modifiedTime":1783973241731,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"UEXjtpuJshKxvGPS","name":"Pagina 15","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 15</h2><p>The Woman<br>    from the Wood</p>","markdown":""},"sort":1500000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241731,"modifiedTime":1783973241731,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"5VXO9UIxvs16al1N","name":"Pagina 16","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 16</h2><p>Descriptors and Gifts<br>I am incredibly strong. Despite my petite looks, I am tougher than <br>the sturdiest of men. I struggle to control my strength and often <br>end up damaging things unintentionally.<br>• The Woman from the Wood:  Y ou receive 1 Additional <br>Success to any Position Check that requires you to resort to your <br>strength. If you eliminate a living being by causing a Wound, you can <br>do it in an extremely disturbing way. Anyone who witnesses it, at the <br>discretion of the Storyteller, will lower their Opposition Level by 1 for <br>the next action.<br>Sometimes I manifest strange abilities, the legacy of a past that I <br>no longer remember. But, when I need it, the world around me <br>shapes itself to protect and shelter me. I hate being out in the open <br>and being the center of attention.<br>• Home Sweet Home: Y ou can spend 1 Soma to draw on the <br>strange powers of the witch you once were. When you do so, choose <br>one of the following effects.<br>1. Create a shelter for one person, perfectly camouflaged within the <br>environment. It is very difficult to discover your shelter, though some <br>NPCs can come close. At the Storyteller’s discretion, a Defense Check <br>may be made to see if you’re discovered.<br>2. Reshape a plant. Y ou can, for instance, create a ladder with the <br>branches of a tree or weave branches to act as a shield.<br>3. Make something disgusting/rotten edible, giving it a sweet and <br>enticing appearance. Anyone other than you who consumes your <br>sweet recovers 1 Wound.<br>My memory is gone. The first thing I remember is the Order finding me, wandering in <br>the woods naked and covered in blood. I possess extraordinary strength and a feral instinct, <br>such that any civilized society ought to chain me like a monster. I know that in my past is a sin <br>so great, my memory could not bear the weight of it. But, I want to remember and perhaps <br>by serving the Order I will be able to do so. I have a natural soft spot for children, and I can’t <br>stand to see them get hurt. The Order uses me as a weapon in the most serious matters when <br>it is necessary to act decisively and demonstrate that a Hunter is a force to be reckoned with.<br>The Woman<br>from the Wood<br>I love human flesh and can gain insight about people just <br>looking at them. I am helplessly attracted to those who have a <br>particular physical trait that stimulates my appetite, such as a <br>good smell or velvety skin.<br>• Dark Ego - Soft and Succulent Flesh: The truth is that you crave human flesh , especially when raw and taken from evil <br>people. When you inflict a Wound through violent action on someone <br>you deem evil, and if you reach an Outcome with an Increment, you <br>may inflict 1 additional Wound. Once per Scene when you consume <br>human flesh , you recover 1 Wound and the Storyteller will reveal <br>some memories of the victim, giving you contextualized information <br>about what you are looking for. <br>Activator: Blatantly manifest your desire to devour human flesh , regardless of the consequences.<br>XP<br>Soma<br> 6<br>Equipment <br>A doll and a little wooden soldier, the only items I had <br>with me when I was found. I don’t know where they come <br>from, but I treasure them / A worn out, gray travel dress, <br>on which one can see bloodstains / A sharp butcher’s <br>knife / A hair ribbon, a gift from a Hunter of the Order / <br>A cookbook with recipes for cakes and sweets.<br>Wounds <br>1.<br>2.<br>3.<br>Extra <br>Wound.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":1600000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241732,"modifiedTime":1783973241732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Kf5zTQB5WMvVrOab","name":"Pagina 17","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 17</h2><p>TheImmortal</p>","markdown":""},"sort":1700000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241732,"modifiedTime":1783973241732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"PQghY2Y4PdCSUhmS","name":"Pagina 18","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 18</h2><p>TheImmortal<br>Descriptors and Gifts<br>I have knowledge and wisdom drawn from centuries of <br>existence, which I can conjure to mind when needed. <br>I often get lost in the memories of my past glories, <br>forgetting about the world around me.<br>• Memories of an Infinite Life: Y ou have been <br>alive for an indefinite time and know almost everything. <br>Once per Scene, you may ask for information about the <br>past or a specific subject or place, which is only available <br>to you due to your long history. The Storyteller will provide <br>relevant and useful details that may be available to you due <br>to your experiences. Once per Scene, you may change the <br>above Descriptor associated with this Gift (but not the <br>Drawback) to one that represents a skill you have conjured <br>to your immortal mind. This new Descriptor is yours until <br>the end of the Scene and you receive 1 Additional Success <br>the first time you use it for a Check.<br>The Order uses my powers for their own purposes and <br>I have had to become skilled at understanding and <br>supporting the needs of my allies as a result. Although <br>I hate to admit it, over time I have begun to take some <br>pleasure in doing good deeds.<br>• The Servant: Once per Scene, as an additional <br>action, you can grant 1 Additional Success to an ally’s action <br>if you can narratively support them. Y ou can also always <br>spend your Soma to pay the activation cost of your allies’ <br>Gifts.<br>I m a sorcerer who has found the key to immortality. Long life has only whetted my appetite for power <br>and in its pursuit, I have been stained by every sin.  The secret behind my unending existence is that I <br>have hidden my soul, removing it from my body. Unfortunately, the Order found its hiding place and now <br>it is held beyond my reach in a fortified church, leaving me no choice but to submit to their commands. <br>Guilty of one thousand and one crimes, the Order demands I balance each with one thousand and one acts <br>of virtue. According to those foolish preachers, they are leading me down the path of redemption. In truth, <br>the Order treats me as a servant, giving to me only the most thankless tasks, knowing that I can not be <br>subdued by death. I remain humble and silent, waiting for the day when I will discover where they have <br>hidden my soul. Then I will unleash my revenge and annihilate the entire Papacy...<br>My body is but a tool which I can manipulate at will, far beyond common <br>human limits. In spite of my old and emaciated appearance, I feel neither fatigue <br>nor pain. With matters of the flesh no longer of concern, I value beautiful things <br>and works of art above anything else.<br>• Dark Ego - The Immortal:  When you suffer 1 Wound, you can <br>immediately spend 1 Soma to remain conscious, allowing you to suffer many <br>Wounds without dying. Y ou are in full control of your body, even parts that have <br>been cut off. Y ou can see through a torn eye or continue to use your severed hand, <br>so don’t skimp on describing a Wound when you suffer it. At the end of the Scene <br>in which you activated your Dark Ego, you recover all the Wounds suffered except <br>the first one. Y our body regenerates and the severed parts are reattached in a horrid <br>spectacle that few have the stomach to watch.<br>Activator: Use your indifference to pain or death to your advantage, revealing your <br>true nature for anyone to see.<br>Equipment <br>Poor clothes / A worn out sickle, a reminder of times past / A <br>small bag with some precious items that you have collected <br>in your adventures / A key that opens the door of one of your <br>many secret refuges / A papal ring, symbol of your indenture <br>to the Church / A little toy, given to you by whoever you <br>helped with your first good deed.<br>Wounds <br>1.<br>2.<br>3.<br>Extra <br>Wound.<br>XP<br>Soma<br> 7</p>","markdown":""},"sort":1800000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241732,"modifiedTime":1783973241732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"3mCfkFXzPwKCz5be","name":"Pagina 19","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 19</h2><p>Marina <br>the Sea <br>Explorer</p>","markdown":""},"sort":1900000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241732,"modifiedTime":1783973241732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"6UGWlBj7BlUNZ9nQ","name":"Pagina 20","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 20</h2><p>I am a traveler, and, over the years, I have visited every location known to man. Being a <br>traveling merchant has allowed me to easily hide my talents as a witch from prying eyes. Year <br>after year, I have accumulated all kinds of magical and mundane wealth. But the Order found <br>me and forced me to sign the most one-sided contract of my entire career as a trader. Now <br>I must put my skills and my charisma at the service of the Order, trying to earn as much as <br>possible to redeem the enormous debt that they have made me incur through deceit.<br>I have a massive collection of magical relics and treasures. I am very <br>stingy with my collection and constantly seeking to add to my wealth <br>so I can redeem my freedom.<br>• Dark Ego - Treasures of the Sea:  At the beginning of <br>the Scenario, you receive 2 Treasure Tokens. When you show off your <br>Treasures, spend 1 Treasure Token and 1 Soma, and create a Descriptor <br>that represents it such as Wolf-Slaying Dagger or Lens of Truth. Receive 1 <br>Additional Success for any Check in which your Treasure may be helpful. <br>Alternatively, spend 1 Token to draw a Potion from your pouch to give <br>to someone. Create a Descriptor to represent its magical effect such as <br>Seeing in the dark or Extraordinary strength. Whoever drinks it will be <br>granted the Descriptor you created for 1 Scene, plus 1 Additional Success <br>on the first action in which they use the advantage given by the potion. <br>When you obtain a new treasure or close a favorable deal, you receive 1 <br>Treasure Token.<br>Activator: Turn a request for help or a conversation into a negotiation, <br>making it clear how amazing your treasures are.<br>XP<br>Soma<br> 6<br>Equipment <br>Exotic and colorful dresses / A large bag full of treasures / A <br>travel bag / Rings and fine jewelry made out of seashells / <br>A vial of sea water / Cosmetics and perfumes.<br>Wounds <br>1.<br>2.<br>3.<br>Extra <br>Wound.<br>Marina <br>the Sea <br>Explorer<br>Descriptors and Gifts<br>I am a sea witch, and as such, I have the power to shape water <br>and move it at will. I hate enclosed places, cut off from the <br>presence of my beloved sea.<br>• Sea Magic:  Y ou can unleash your witch powers and <br>control seawater, manipulating it as if it were solid. Y ou can use <br>it as a weapon or as an object to support your actions, giving it the <br>consistency of a whip that can reach up to thirty feet. When you <br>act, you can take a second supporting action, such as picking up <br>something, moving someone you want to defend, or hindering an <br>enemy’s movement thanks to the water you manipulate. Y ou can <br>also use this Gift with fresh water, but you will need to spend 1 <br>Soma to do so.<br>Nobody knows my true form, which I hide under an appearance <br>of eternal youth. I can change shape to some extent, while still <br>remaining in human form. I am hopelessly attracted to all <br>forms of beauty and I often get lost in contemplating it.<br>• Mutable Appearance: Once per Scene you can change <br>your appearance. Create a Descriptor that represents your new <br>appearance. Nobody can pierce your deception, except through <br>magical means or Gifts that allow one to discover the truth. In <br>addition, you may spend 1 Soma to take the specific appearance of <br>a person you have already met, mimicking their voice and manners <br>as well. Y ou can keep your new appearance until the Scene is over.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":2000000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241732,"modifiedTime":1783973241732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"mlNGfYhpn6kxkwpY","name":"Pagina 21","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 21</h2><p>Niklaus<br>   von Krampus</p>","markdown":""},"sort":2100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241732,"modifiedTime":1783973241732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"xLBbZOdd9wTmFAaD","name":"Pagina 22","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 22</h2><p>Niklaus<br>von Krampus<br>Descriptors and Gifts<br>I am a skilled exorcist. I know how to identify and fight <br>evil through prayer and the sacred arts. Despite what I <br>am, I hate holy places and manifestations of faith and <br>religion, as they cause the demon inside me to stir.<br>• Exorcist: When you face a clearly supernatural being, <br>you gain 1 Additional Success on all Checks. Y ou can also <br>invoke sacred rites and prayers to disturb the evil you face. If a <br>subject, artifact, or supernatural manifestation uses a Gift that <br>you know of or have already seen in action, you can spend 1 <br>Soma to prevent its use. Each time you activate this Gift, roll 1 <br>die. If you roll a 5 or a 6, you gain 1 Devil Token.<br>I am good at understanding people and helping them. <br>Now, thanks to the demon that dwells in me, I can even <br>perceive the dark side of people. Every so often, however, <br>the demon takes over, making me behave strangely in <br>front of ordinary people.<br>• The Inner Demon: Once per Scene, you can release <br>the inner demon, whether that’ d be yours or someone else’s. In <br>your case, create a Descriptor that represents an emotion that <br>includes the word Anger, Envy, or Wickedness. Y ou receive 2 <br>Additional Successes the first time you use this Descriptor for <br>a Position Check. If you unleash someone else’s inner demon, <br>the Storyteller will create a Descriptor for them that showcases <br>their hidden, dark side. When using this Gift on particularly <br>powerful individuals, the Storyteller may request a Position <br>Check from you to succeed. Each time you use this Gift, you <br>receive 1 Devil Token.<br>I am a devoted clergyman who has always dedicated his life to helping others. Over the years I have <br>become a talented exorcist and this vocation of mine led me to the remote village of Borgo Maleanime. <br>There, I fought a particularly insidious demon, who concealed itself among the ranks of a gang of young <br>thugs who merely pretended to be demons to scare people. It was a tough fight, but I finally got the better <br>of the fiend. Or so I thought. Something in the exorcism did not go as expected and now the demon dwells <br>inside me, sowing fear and pain whenever it re-emerges. The Order welcomed me into its ranks as an <br>exorcist and I gladly accepted this role, with the hope that the missions entrusted to me would allow me to <br>find a way to rid myself, once and for all, of that which hides within me.<br>The demon in me grants me its power, allowing me to act with savage strength <br>and speed. It is not easy to contain this ferocity and, often, I end up hurting or <br>destroying things I did not wish to.<br>• Dark Ego - The Demon Revealed: While generally retaining control, <br>every now and then you have to allow the demon to manifest and unleash its <br>anger. Create a Descriptor that represents your demonic form and that includes <br>at least one of these words: Monstrous , Fierce, Beastly. Y our physical abilities go <br>far beyond those of a mere mortal, but you will behave like a devil, enjoying the <br>evil and fear you inspire. When you act using this special Descriptor, you gain 1 <br>Additional Success. Y ou can spend 1 Devil Token to inflict 1 additional Wound or <br>to spend as Soma for a Check. Once per Scenario, the Storyteller can spend 1 Devil <br>Token to activate this Gift against your will.<br>Activator: Give free rein to your demonic side or listen to the sound of bells or cowbells <br>for at least one minute.<br>Equipment <br>An old cassock, worn out by many travels / Exorcism vestments <br>and tools / An old pouch where you find things that the demon <br>takes when it is in control (often, things with unclear origins <br>you don’t wish to know about) / A shepherd’s curved staff of <br>wood and iron to beat the devil with / Precious and small relics <br>received as offerings / An old and time-worn bible.<br>XP<br>Soma<br> 6<br>Wounds <br>1.<br>2.<br>3.<br>Extra <br>Wound.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":2200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241732,"modifiedTime":1783973241732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"YCzLq5hWO6jf9YgH","name":"Pagina 23","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 23</h2><p>George<br>The Holy<br>Dragon <br>Slayer</p>","markdown":""},"sort":2300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241732,"modifiedTime":1783973241732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"V4FZmLz9LupliCro","name":"Pagina 24","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 24</h2><p>Descriptors and Gifts<br>I have dedicated my life to slaying monsters and <br>aberrations, honing my body and my skill for that <br>purpose. My strict discipline makes me rarely inclined to <br>forgive the mistakes of others.<br>• The Dragon Slayer:  Y ou’re skilled at slaying <br>monsters and demonic creatures in the name of faith. Y ou <br>start each Scenario with 1 Fervor Token. When facing an <br>enemy that is obviously monstrous, if you get a successful <br>Outcome on a Position Check, you can spend 1 Fervor Token <br>to inflict 1 additional Wound. When such an enemy attempts <br>to overwhelm you using one of their Gifts, you can spend <br>1 Fervor Token to receive 2 Additional Successes to your <br>Defense Check. When you suffer 1 Wound, you receive 1 <br>Fervor Token.<br>I have vowed to eradicate all evil from this world and <br>nothing can escape my inquisitive gaze. I hate all secrets, <br>for I know that the seed of evil may grow within anyone.<br>• Agent of the Papacy: When you speak to a crowd  <br>you can infuse their hearts with the light of faith. Spend 1 <br>Fervor Token and you can create a Descriptor that represents <br>a feeling of faith, anger, and a desire for justice against evil. <br>Alternatively, create a Descriptor that represents trust and <br>submission in such faith. The crowd will act accordingly for <br>the rest of the Scene, but particularly powerful NPCs may be <br>immune to your words. Receive 1 Additional Success on any <br>Check you make using the sentiment you inspired. When you <br>publicly expose evil, you receive 1 Fervor Token.<br>I am the most skilled and trusted agent of the Papacy and as such, it is my responsibility <br>to make sure that the fight against darkness never falters. As a child, I fell into a river and <br>almost drowned, but was saved by a creature that I later discovered was a dragon. When I <br>grew up, I took holy vows and joined the Church. In doing so, I discovered that what I believed <br>to be my savior was actually a creature of darkness, ready to steal my soul. I vowed to fight <br>the darkness, suppressing the feeling of gratitude toward the dragon that saved me, which has <br>always plagued me. Such weakness represents a crack through which evil could slither in. No <br>mercy for monsters, no forgiveness for those who would join and serve the forces of evil.<br>George The Holy<br>Dragon Slayer<br>I am a saint in the eyes of ordinary people and no door remains closed <br>for me. My word is that of the Church itself. What I say is not to be <br>questioned.<br>• Dark Ego - The Saint:  When you channel sacred divine power, <br>everyone bows their heads. Ordinary people will show you reverence, while <br>weaker enemy NPCs (at the Storyteller’s discretion) won’t target you unless <br>you’re the only available option, nor will they try to get in your way. In <br>your presence, anyone possessing powers linked to the supernatural lowers <br>their Opposition Level by 1. Y our holy aura emits an intense light that can <br>illuminate the whole area around you at your will.  <br>Activator: Invoke holy divine power by reproaching all sinners and providing <br>an example of purity and righteousness.<br>XP<br>Soma<br> 6<br>Equipment <br>My sacred armor / A sword and a spear blessed by the Pope <br>himself / My proud war stallion / A cross with the Keys of Saint <br>Peter engraved, as a universal symbol of power / <br>Aldebrand, <br>my trusty squire and servant / Papal papers and seals / A cloak <br>of fine workmanship.<br>Wounds <br>1.<br>2.<br>3.<br>Extra <br>Wound.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":2400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241732,"modifiedTime":1783973241732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"nDUjQzKwkclXdZq1","name":"Pagina 25","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 25</h2><p>Sun<br>Wukong<br>the Amazing <br>Monkey</p>","markdown":""},"sort":2500000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241732,"modifiedTime":1783973241732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"5l7Qa3D1DtL9Az4h","name":"Pagina 26","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 26</h2><p>Sun Wukong<br>the Amazing Monkey<br>Descriptors and Gifts<br>I am a skilled guardian. My body is strong and hardened, <br>my senses sharp and alert. Years of captivity have made me <br>submissive, and I struggle not to follow every order I am <br>given.<br>• Guardian Disciple: Y ou can intercept a danger before it <br>overwhelms your ally. Y ou may spend 1 Soma to get between an <br>ally and a danger by standing in their place. Receive 1 Additional <br>Success to any Defense Check you have to perform doing so. Once <br>per Scenario, you can ignore 1 Wound you suffer.<br>I am stronger and faster than any human and I am a highly <br>skilled fighter. I don’t shy away from a challenge because I <br>always believe I can win.<br>• Monkey King: Y ou are able to perform athletic feats <br>unthinkable to a mere mortal. Y ou may spend 1 Soma and choose <br>an effect:<br>1. Y ou can jump incredibly far, up to thirty feet. Y ou can bring <br>another person with you by carrying them on your shoulders. Y ou <br>also ignore any damage related to a fall. <br>2. Use your tail to manipulate an object and perform an additional <br>action.<br>3. Ignore any physical impediments to movement by using your <br>impressive skills.<br>I have no memory of my life before my captivity, although I often dream of the forests <br>and snow-capped peaks of my beloved China. I grew up as a circus animal at London’s <br>Royal Circus but, deep within I carry the conviction that I am destined for something else. I <br>rebelled by killing all my captors, fleeing across a vast and labyrinthine city. When the Order <br>reached me, I thought it was the end, but the Hunters took me with them as their guardian and <br>defender. The more I live as a Hunter, the closer I draw to transcendence. Now I am aware <br>that, someday, I will discover who I really am.<br>My essence is magical, and this makes me resistant to enchantments that <br>might snare stupid humans. My spiritual presence is imposing, and I struggle <br>to hide what I am, especially in the eyes of those accustomed to magic.<br>• Dark Ego - Descendant of the Awakening of the Void and <br>the Emptiness: When you release your true power, your body emits <br>a divine light and no one can stop you. Take 1 Wound to get 2 Additional <br>Successes to any physical Checks you have to perform. For the rest of the <br>Scene spells have little effect on you and you get 2 Additional Successes to any <br>Defense Check you make to protect yourself from arcane effects. When you <br>deal a hit to someone, you can spend 1 Soma to inflict 1 additional Wound. <br>The effects of this Gift cease if you behave in a composed and obedient <br>manner, as your role as guardian dictates.<br>Activator: Act with passion and strength, showing everyone the incredible <br>power that lies within your body.<br>Equipment <br>A circus stick with three segments that I can extend / Old <br>and worn circus clothes / An old golden diadem so tight <br>on my forehead that it cannot be removed / A sheet with <br>the drawing of a Chinese landscape, gift from a child who <br>watched one of my shows.<br>XP<br>Soma<br> 6<br>Wounds <br>1.<br>2.<br>3.<br>Extra <br>Wound.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":2600000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241732,"modifiedTime":1783973241732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"RjpLVgVnFdCYEFUu","name":"Pagina 27","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 27</h2><p>Verdoux Bluebeard</p>","markdown":""},"sort":2700000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241732,"modifiedTime":1783973241732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"k2Q2nxZMEGhGVKwH","name":"Pagina 28","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 28</h2><p>I am a French aristocrat, called upon by my sovereign to manage the most devious and disreputable <br>matters. I have lived an unconventional life, between accomplishing impossible tasks and keeping <br>unspeakable secrets. It has opened my eyes to the world beyond the prosaic limits to which most are <br>accustomed. In an effort to escape my adventurous life, I have more than once tried to start a family. <br>However, my efforts have always ended in ruin, a price I must pay for the secrets I keep. I have lost six <br>lovers, each killed by enemies and dangers that I naively hoped I could exclude from my life. That is why I <br>volunteered for the Order, took an oath to weed out the darkness in this world, and sought revenge for the <br>lives that were stolen from me.<br>Under the facade of a respectable man hides a skilled, unscrupulous <br>problem-solver. I know how to kill and how to act with decisiveness. <br>Everyone has done something they are not proud of and I can’t stand <br>seeing the hypocrites who pretend as if they are morally superior to <br>others.<br>• Dark Ego - The Unscrupulous Assassin:  Y ou may appear as a civilized gentleman, but appearances can be deceiving. When <br>necessary, you will not hesitate to kill. If you eliminate an NPC by inflicting <br>a final Wound, you can also immediately eliminate a second Minor NPC. <br>When you successfully defend yourself from a violent action, you can <br>immediately eliminate a Minor NPC in response. Either way, the target <br>must be within range of your wrath. After inflicting 1 Wound to someone, <br>you can move freely as an additional action, allowing you to reach your <br>true goal without anyone preventing you from doing so.<br>Activator: Reveal your dark side by injuring someone or acting aggressively <br>despite your outwardly calm and staid appearance.<br>XP<br>Soma<br> 6<br>Equipment <br>Nobleman’s clothes / A long black cape / A large <br>bunch of keys / A fine dueling blade / Snuff of <br>excellent quality / A few doses of deadly Aqua <br>Tofana / A large amount of coins and precious <br>trinkets / A heart-shaped locket hanging from a gold <br>chain, within which are engraved the names of my <br>lost loves.<br>Wounds <br>1.<br>2.<br>3.<br>Extra <br>Wound.<br>Verdoux<br>Bluebeard<br>Descriptors and Gifts<br>My specialty is problem solving and I have a talent for analyzing <br>every situation, allowing me to find resources and discover <br>clues. Managing danger requires calm and concentration, <br>and so I hate acting precipitously.<br>• Problem Solver: If you’ve seen it once, you can do it <br>yourself even better. Y ou may spend 1 Soma to replicate the effect <br>of a Gift from a Hunter or NPC you witnessed during the Scenario. <br>Particular Gifts may still be off limits or only yield a part of their <br>effect at the Storyteller’s discretion. Y ou cannot replicate more than <br>one Gift at a time. Once per Scene, you may ask the Storyteller to <br>reveal to you a Gift of an NPC that you had time to study.<br>I am an educated man who has studied the arts and sciences. <br>I use this knowledge to uncover truths and reveal mysteries. I <br>hate secrets, but only when I don’t know them.<br>• The Key to Each Door: Once per Scene, you can use one <br>of the magic keys you own. Choose an effect. <br>1. Open a closed door, no matter how many locks or defenses it <br>has.<br>2. If a subject touches your key, discover the strongest feeling they <br>are experiencing. <br>3. Close and lock a door so that no conventional methods will be <br>able to open it. <br>4. If you put your key in the mouth of a dead person you will see <br>some of their memories. The Storyteller will describe them to you, <br>focusing on your areas of interest.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":2800000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241732,"modifiedTime":1783973241732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"2wu6HL3gYqYh2rkR","name":"Pagina 29","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 29</h2><p>Yukie Onn<br>the Traveling<br>Artist</p>","markdown":""},"sort":2900000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241732,"modifiedTime":1783973241732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"FFaSkLg2tjfFAAFw","name":"Pagina 30","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 30</h2><p>I am a traveling artist who has known fame and honor in my homeland, Japan. That prestige meant nothing, <br>however, when I found true love with Akihiro, son of a powerful noble family. When they forbade him from seeing <br>me, we fled together to the remote region of Ezo. Even there we were not beyond the reach of Akihiro’s family and <br>they pursued us into the high, snow-capped mountains. We had escaped every assassin, but could not outwit the <br>snowstorm that trapped us. I survived, but only because Akihiro sacrificed the warmth of his life to save mine.  <br>But the cold has left me changed. It has become part of me and now the only thing that can make me feel warm <br>is the hot blood of others. After taking revenge on all those who took Akihiro from me, I fled far away, using my <br>talent for art to gain prestige and the protection of wealthy western nobles. Now, in the service of the Order, I <br>save others from suffering the injustice that I have experienced, by punishing selfishness and wickedness.<br>My body is pure ice and, because of this, I can manipulate ice as I please. <br>However, I hate to manifest my power because it is dangerous to those <br>around me and, as an artist, my purpose is to make people smile.<br>• Dark Ego - Ice-Cold: Y ou have control over your body temperature <br>and, consequently, you can freeze the environment or objects in your <br>immediate vicinity. When you manipulate ice, choose an effect by creating <br>a Descriptor that represents it such as: Frozen Door or Aura of Frost and <br>spend 1 Soma to manifest it for the whole Scene. As an additional effect, <br>your frost can inflict 1 Wound on those who interact with it or make what <br>you freeze incredibly fragile or incredibly hard. Whoever exploits the effects <br>of frost in their favor gains 1 Additional Success for their action. Y our frost <br>has no direct effect on living things.<br>Activator: Shed your disguise as a simple artist and reveal your true, bitterly <br>cold form or react passionately when fear and intimidation are used for selfish <br>reasons.<br>XP<br>Soma<br> 6<br>Equipment <br>A travel kimono / Stage kimono, make-up, and stage effects / A <br>small ice sphere that never melts / A butterfly-shaped hair clip, <br>a reminder of my lost love Akihiro / A finely crafted Shamisen, <br>a traditional stringed instrument / Several daggers hidden in the <br>Kimono / A pair of fine fans.<br>Wounds <br>1.<br>2.<br>3.<br>Extra <br>Wound.<br>Yukie Onn<br>the Traveling<br>Artist<br>Descriptors and Gifts<br>I am a highly skilled artist. Music, dance, and painting hold no <br>mysteries for me. My otherworldly charm captivates ordinary <br>people, always drawing attention to me.<br>• Otherworldly Charm:  When you perform or flaunt <br>your talents, all eyes will be on you. Receive 1 Additional Success <br>for each Position Check you make to attract attention or charm <br>someone. If you get an Outcome with an Increment, you may <br>declare that a subject who has seen you has fallen in love with you. <br>The Storyteller will create a specific Agenda for them that leads <br>them to seek your attention.<br>I cannot feel pain and my frail appearance hides surprising <br>physical abilities. Blood is the only thing that can warm me <br>and its smell alone makes me shiver.<br>• Blood-Hot: Once per Scene, you can consume a person’s <br>blood when inflicting 1 non-fatal Wound. Y ou recover 1 Wound, <br>1 Soma and receive some information about your victim such as a <br>memory, an emotion or their heart’s desire. When you drink blood <br>roll a die: if you roll a 1, you lose control and you will kill your <br>victim by draining their blood, unless someone stops you.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":3000000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241732,"modifiedTime":1783973241732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"librarySlug":"bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen-2022-06-29","category":"Core Book","sourceFile":"bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","sourcePath":"C:\\Users\\Gamer\\Documents\\Broken Tales KS [ENG]\\bt-cb-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf"}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241732,"modifiedTime":1783973241732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"N5lfad8HzCyTdWBd","name":"bt-cb-foxcat-sheet-eng-final-screen","pages":[{"_id":"OvudRJ7DMGbz1fsx","name":"PDF local","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h1>bt-cb-foxcat-sheet-eng-final-screen</h1><p><strong>Archivo:</strong> bt-cb-foxcat-sheet-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf</p><p><strong>Paginas:</strong> 2</p><p><a href=\"systems/broken-tales/assets/source-pdfs/bt-cb-foxcat-sheet-eng-final-screen-2022-06-29.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Abrir PDF dentro de Foundry</a></p>","markdown":""},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241732,"modifiedTime":1783973241732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"vFYuRZPpcvokL010","name":"Pagina 1","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-foxcat-sheet-eng-final-screen - Pagina 1</h2><p>Cunning Machiavelli the Fox <br>and Sly Bischeri<br>the Cat</p>","markdown":""},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241732,"modifiedTime":1783973241732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"0yNCk8uXv4ZVMtik","name":"Pagina 2","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-cb-foxcat-sheet-eng-final-screen - Pagina 2</h2><p>We are two boys who survived and thrived on the street through trickery and deceit. <br>Unfortunately, we made a terrible mistake by choosing a weird old lady as a mark. She <br>turned out to be a goddamn witch. The witch cursed us… And from that day on, every twelve <br>hours, one becomes a Fox and the other a Cat. Bound by this spell, we found a way to make <br>a lot of money, deceiving stupid nobles and rich merchants. The Order has noticed us and <br>taken us under its wing, with the promise of breaking the curse that afflicts us.<br>Cunning Machiavelli <br>the Fox and Sly <br>Bischeri the Cat<br>Cunning’s exclusive Descriptor and Gift<br>I have a natural talent for telling lies, which the Order often uses to its <br>advantage. In spite of my origins, I know a great deal about many things <br>because lying requires planning and preparation. I’m so used to spinning <br>nonsense that I often lie even when I shouldn’t.<br>• Believe in Miracles:  Statements are true until proven otherwise. <br>Once per Scene, you can tell everyone something that will be accepted <br>without question, until the lie is uncovered. The deception will be obvious to <br>your victims at the end of the Scene or once exposed. Receive 1 Additional <br>Success on any Check in which you exploit the lie you have created.<br>Sly’s exclusive Descriptor and Gift<br>A life on the road has taught me to be a skilled thief, which is why <br>the Order uses me to do its dirty work. If I can make a profit out of a <br>situation, I’ll try to. “Everyone for themselves” is my motto.<br>• Rogue: Y ou always make sure you go unnoticed. By pretending to <br>be weak during a Scene, NPCs will overlook you as a target unless you have <br>previously acted against them. By spending 1 Soma, you can flee a Scene or a <br>situation wherever there is a crowd. No one will be able to stop you.<br>Soma<br> 6<br>Note: During the night, use Cunning’s Descriptor, Gift, and equipment, while Sly will be a cat. During the day, use <br>Sly’s Descriptor, Gift, and equipment, while Cunning will be a fox.<br>Common Descriptors and Gifts<br>I will stop at nothing to get what I want, and it only takes me a few seconds <br>to evaluate what is happening and find the right way to take advantage of it. I <br>hate acting alone because there’s no one to take the blame.<br>• Partner in Crime: Y ou are always ready to seize the right opportunity. <br>Once per Scene, if one of your allies acts with your support, they receive 1 <br>Additional Success to their Check. Additionally, once per Scene, if one of your <br>allies achieves an Outcome with an Increment after they have completed their <br>action, you may immediately take an additional action.<br>Like it or not, we are bound by magic. We can share thoughts, each see <br>what the other sees, and thanks to this we can work together to cheat others. <br>Whoever is in animal form hates not being able to communicate and often <br>annoys the other out of spite.<br>• Dark Ego - The Fox and the Cat:  The curse that binds you makes <br>you a perfect team. At night as Cunning or during the day as Sly, you are a human <br>and make use of the full support of your partner in his animal form. Y our <br>partner can act individually to accomplish the task you give him. Y ou share the <br>same Wounds and the same Soma. Whoever is in human form can spend 1 Soma <br>to use the Gift of his accomplice. Once per Scene, if your partner is there to help <br>you, you receive 2 Additional Successes on a Position Check.<br>Activator: Trick or deceive someone, taking advantage of the support of your <br>trusted partner in crime.<br>XP<br>Cunning’s Equipment<br>Comfortable and light clothes / A set of small knives that I hide everywhere <br>/ Cards, stamps, and other counterfeit objects / Some completely fake coins and jewelry / A volume of the famous Biblioteca Universale Sacro-<br>Profana Encyclopedia, which always reveals what I need to know.<br>Sly’s Equipment<br>Worn-out and lived-in clothes / A long, sharp knife / An old stick to <br>pretend to be blind / An old purse with a hole in it / A sack full of junk <br>that I collect while thieving.<br>Wounds <br>1.<br>2.<br>3.<br>Extra <br>Wound.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241732,"modifiedTime":1783973241732,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"librarySlug":"bt-cb-foxcat-sheet-eng-final-screen-2022-06-29","category":"Core Book","sourceFile":"bt-cb-foxcat-sheet-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","sourcePath":"C:\\Users\\Gamer\\Documents\\Broken Tales KS [ENG]\\bt-cb-foxcat-sheet-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf"}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241733,"modifiedTime":1783973241733,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"4yOY40LTdtSlr6F8","name":"Broken Europe Map","pages":[{"_id":"Bcghkm3OiA7SG8lB","name":"PDF local","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h1>Broken Europe Map</h1><p><strong>Archivo:</strong> Broken Europe Map.pdf</p><p><strong>Paginas:</strong> 1</p><p><a href=\"systems/broken-tales/assets/source-pdfs/broken-europe-map.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Abrir PDF dentro de Foundry</a></p>","markdown":""},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241733,"modifiedTime":1783973241733,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"sOyP6GKISvnvjkJ8","name":"Pagina 1","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>Broken Europe Map - Pagina 1</h2><p>Map<br>Broken Europe<br>City<br>Settlement<br>Bridge<br>Forest<br>Naples<br>Rome<br>Paris Prague<br>London<br>York<br>Martana Island<br>Sinalunga<br>Borgo <br>Maleanime<br>Valea Viilor<br>Durfort<br>Whitehaven<br>Vík í Mýrdal<br>Borgholm<br>Stegeborg<br>Malbork<br>Lohr<br>Nijmegen<br>ZugarramurdiVigo<br>Devil's <br>Bridge<br>Black <br>Forest<br>Devil's <br>Bridge<br>Devil's <br>Bridge<br>BEAUTIFUL A SUNNY <br>DAY! THE SPELL IS BROKEN A SMALL ROAD IN THE WOODS DARK BEARD MEMORIES WHY?<br> FAIRYTALE A GENTLE CARESS A SMALL TOY SOMETHING OF VALUE</p>","markdown":""},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241733,"modifiedTime":1783973241733,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"librarySlug":"broken-europe-map","category":"Sheets and Support","sourceFile":"Broken Europe Map.pdf","sourcePath":"C:\\Users\\Gamer\\Documents\\Broken Tales KS [ENG]\\Broken Europe Map.pdf"}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241733,"modifiedTime":1783973241733,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"p9YXV9rPD1gWlLML","name":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen","pages":[{"_id":"mAgEObVgPeN7b7ye","name":"PDF local","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h1>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen</h1><p><strong>Archivo:</strong> bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf</p><p><strong>Paginas:</strong> 176</p><p><a href=\"systems/broken-tales/assets/source-pdfs/bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen-2022-06-29.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Abrir PDF dentro de Foundry</a></p>","markdown":""},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241733,"modifiedTime":1783973241733,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"uHrvYip0BXEz4r60","name":"Pagina 1","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 1</h2><p><em>Page has no extractable text. Use the local PDF linked on the first Journal page.</em></p>","markdown":""},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241733,"modifiedTime":1783973241733,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"i89CTcbZXubcTjJM","name":"Pagina 2","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 2</h2><p>Game Design and Texts: Alberto Tronchi<br>Editing: Natascia Cortesi, Alberto Tronchi, Sean Newton, <br>Tommaso De Benetti, Luca Vanin<br>Translations: Tommaso De Benetti, Y oann Stordeur<br>Graphics and Illustrations: Daniel Comerci<br>Layout: Daniel Comerci<br>Crowdfunding Manager: Tommaso De Benetti<br>History Consultant: Stefano Maioli<br>Playtest and Thanks:  Tommaso De Benetti, Luca <br>Vanin, Daniel Comerci, Giacomo Jack Gordesco, Federico <br>Scattolin, Enrico Ronconi, Fabiana Gasperini, Alberto <br>Lolli, Gianpaolo Benedetti, Attilio Bravi, Fabio Bianchetti, <br>Matteo Mazzoli, Valerio Votadoro, Giorgio Catenacci, <br>Rikch, Fabrizio Infusino, Jane Toikka, Stefano Maioli, <br>Elvis Lupo, Matteo Petrangeli, Gabriele Tacito, Alessandro <br>Prometeo Di Pastena, Marco D’ Ascenzo, Fumble GDR, <br>Tebra Hansing, Y oann Stordeur, Sean Newton, Nix, Eric <br>Verspoor, Jerry Boucher, Ciro Lamberti.<br>Alberto Tronchi Copyright (c) 2022<br>The Broken Ones is a work of fiction. Names, characters, <br>locations, and incidents either are products of the author’s <br>imagination or are used fictitiously. Any resemblance to <br>actual events or locales or persons, living or dead, is entirely <br>coincidental. The work, including all its parts, is protected <br>by copyright law. Unless expressly authorized, reproductions <br>are forbidden in any way or form, including photocopying, <br>scanning, and electronic storage. Any violation will be <br>prosecuted to the full extent of the copyright law.<br>Web: https://theworldanvil.com<br>Discord: bit.ly/discord-twa<br>Facebook: facebook.com/theworldanvil<br>Twitter: twitter.com/theworldanvil<br>Printed in the month of July 2022 in Türkiye at KÜLTÜR SANAT<br>Printing House<br>The Broken Ones Book HARDCOVER ENG ISBN: 979-12-80387-13-4<br>The Broken Ones Book PDF ENG ISBN: 979-12-80387-12-7</p>","markdown":""},"sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241733,"modifiedTime":1783973241733,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"cRBu8fjRHR9CXLls","name":"Pagina 3","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 3</h2><p>SOMMARIO<br>3 Introduction<br>5 The Order’s Treasury<br>29 Untold Stories<br>51 The Village<br>75 Spoiler<br>76 The Broken Ones during a Campaign<br>80 I Don’t Believe<br>92 Hunger Island<br>108 Bloodwhite’s Heart<br>122 The House of Roses<br>134 Stegeborg’s Quiet<br>150 In your Eyes, with your Feet<br>162 I Will Stay with You Always<br>175 Villager’s Sheet</p>","markdown":""},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241733,"modifiedTime":1783973241733,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"BwPyQF4xkwCuQS7T","name":"Pagina 4","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 4</h2><p>3<br>Introduction<br>This book introduces the Broken Ones, the “heroes” from the original tales <br>who were turned into the main antagonists in the world of Broken Tales, and later <br>subdued by the Order into new Hunters following the events of the Core Book. <br>Y ou won’t find any difference in the mechanics compared to regular Hunters, <br>but it is important to take a few things into consideration when adding <br>Broken Ones to the game.<br>Creating a Broken One Hunter<br>The creation of a Hunter from a Broken One follows the rules <br>presented on page 69 of Broken Tales’ Core Book. The difference <br>is that the story used to bring them to their breaking point <br>won’t be the original tale, but rather the one in the Scenario <br>they come from. In fact, creating a Broken One means <br>“breaking a story that has already been broken. ” In some <br>ways, this is easier and faster since one doesn’t have to <br>reimagine the whole background story of a classic <br>Hunter. In short: to create a Broken One, there <br>needs to be a Scenario or a Broken story involving <br>them.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241733,"modifiedTime":1783973241733,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"nIatOEjGJ4NRFkLx","name":"Pagina 5","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 5</h2><p>4<br>Broken Ones during a Broken <br>Tales’ Campaign<br>A Broken One is a natural fit for a long-term Campaign <br>because Players need to have solved a given Scenario to <br>unlock the new Hunter tied to it. Keeping in mind that <br>the Players may not want to leave their original Hunters <br>behind, there are a few ways to introduce the Broken Ones <br>in the game.<br>An Alternative Group of Hunters<br>During the Campaign, an interesting clue may emerge <br>from one of the Broken Ones captured by the Hunters. The <br>new lead may be located far away from the group’s position, <br>and the Order could instruct a second group of Hunters <br>that includes a few Broken Ones. The Storyteller can then <br>offer to let the Players play one or more Sessions with this <br>different group of Hunters. At the end of those Scenarios, <br>all the earned XP can be transferred to the Players’ main <br>Hunters. <br>Apprentice Hunters<br>Once they have been defeated in their Scenario and <br>integrated into the Order, the Advancement option Have <br>an apprentice Hunter in tow (page 259 of the Broken Tales <br>Core Book) is perfect to introduce a Broken One in the <br>game as a Hunter. <br>Broken Ones as NPCs<br>It should be easy for the Storyteller to convert a Broken One <br>Hunter into an Ally Dark Presence with a little adaptation <br>so they can join the Hunters during their journey.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":500000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241733,"modifiedTime":1783973241733,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"P9U6c6IspBxKmMwV","name":"Pagina 6","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 6</h2><p>5<br>The Order’s <br>Treasury<br>In its frantic quest for control over the Broken Tales, the <br>Order established the Treasury shortly after its foundation. In the <br>Principality of Transylvania, the fortified church of Valea Viilor was <br>chosen for its series of secret rooms, perfect for storing objects and <br>magic that would be incomprehensible to the common man. The <br>management of the Treasury is entrusted to Hansen, known as the <br>Swineherd. He is a nobleman fallen into disgrace, but very skilled <br>at making items with incredible properties. An order of knights <br>faithful to the Papacy watches over Valea Viilor so that only the <br>Hunters and the most trusted agents of the Church can enter the <br>secret halls, where all kinds of artifacts are accumulated and kept <br>hidden from the world. The most daring Hunters often take one of <br>the Treasures, one that may help them in their mission based on its <br>properties. Possession of an Order’s Treasure is only ever temporary, <br>except in rare cases when a particularly deserving Hunter will be <br>able to keep the Treasure for themselves permanently.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":600000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241733,"modifiedTime":1783973241733,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"LqkjAvUl7T9UJ7SE","name":"Pagina 7","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 7</h2><p>6<br>Hansen known as the Swineherd<br>Inspired by The Swineherd (Neutral)<br>Once upon a time, there was a young nobleman with a great passion for craftsmanship and the <br>creation of miraculous objects. Unfortunately, no matter how hard he worked, his creations were <br>never as successful as he had hoped, or perhaps the problem was that the acclaim he received <br>always fell short of what he thought he deserved. Over the years, Hansen squandered all his <br>wealth, refusing offers of marriage and requests for his work, driven mad by his dream of the <br>“perfect creation. ” With a new-found resolve, Hansen disguised himself as a humble swineherd, <br>traveling from city to city to experiment with his creations, often with deadly results for the <br>poor souls who happened to be within range. Captured by the Order, the Papacy gave <br>Hansen a new purpose as a Hunter, deciding to put his talent at the service of the <br>fight against darkness. Since that day, obsessed with all the wonders of the Treasury, <br>Hansen studies every object that is delivered by the Hunters, frantically searching <br>for a perfection that can never be achieved.<br>Descriptor: I am a skilled craftsman and I know every Order’s Treasure down <br>to the smallest detail. I can dismantle any object with a few precise gestures of my <br>hand.<br>3 Wounds<br>Opposition Level: Medium 5<br>Agenda: To thoroughly study every object the Treasury holds, as well as any Hunter <br>who comes through.<br>Gift - Master Craftsman: Given a few minutes of study, Hansen can understand <br>the functionality of any object related to the Broken Tales. His deep knowledge of <br>magic allows him to understand the abilities of those in front of him, enabling him <br>to figure out their Descriptors and Gifts after a short time. A Hunter can make a <br>Defense Check to prevent Hansen from deducing certain facts about them, <br>but it will be impossible to hide everything from the watchful eye of the <br>Swineherd.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":700000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241733,"modifiedTime":1783973241733,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"7wO9AlERvvw3ANy4","name":"Pagina 8","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 8</h2><p>7<br>Karen the Mannequin <br>Guardian of the Treasury<br>Inspired by Red Shoes (Neutral / Opponent)<br>Once upon a time, there was a beautiful girl <br>named Karen. Despite being born a <br>peasant, the girl won the affection <br>of the young heir to a wealthy <br>family. Before too much time had <br>passed, she was a rich and happy <br>bride. Freed from any responsibilities, <br>Karen fell into a dissolute life devoted to <br>pleasure, wasting her husband’s fortune. <br>He soon regretted having taken her as his <br>wife. The rich scion sought out a witch, who <br>offered him an easy way to get rid of her. <br>Returning from a distant journey, the <br>man handed Karen a pair of beautiful <br>red slippers, bright enough to dazzle <br>the eyes. But those cursed shoes hid <br>a fearsome secret. The shoes woke <br>envy in the hearts of those that saw <br>them, but it was only a fraction of <br>the envy felt by the one wearing the <br>shoes. Karen began to desire every <br>beautiful thing she saw. She set out <br>on a journey, leaving her husband <br>behind in her relentless search for <br>the beautiful things she craved. <br>Over the years, Karen has stained <br>herself with many crimes to <br>obtain what she desired. Standing at the gallows, a messenger <br>of the Order made her a proposal that she could not refuse. She <br>would forever keep an eye on the most beautiful objects in the <br>world.<br>Descriptor: I am obsessed with magical objects and anything <br>that meets my standards of beauty. My body bears the wounds <br>of all the punishments I have suffered for my greed, but the only <br>pain I truly feel is that of waiting for a new treasure.<br>3 Wounds<br>Opposition Level: Medium 5<br>Agenda: To acquire any object that I consider special and <br>wonderful, to keep it safe in the Treasury.<br>Special Agenda (Object Obsession): I can’t stand the idea <br>of Hunters borrowing my precious Treasury items. I must watch <br>over them and the sooner the Hunter dies, the sooner I will have <br>the opportunity to bring my precious treasure back.<br>Note: This Agenda transforms Karen the Mannequin from <br>Neutral to Opponent.<br>Gift - The Human Mannequin: Karen has suffered through <br>torture and abuse. The girl has had her feet cut off to remove <br>the damned red shoes and has lost her hands as a punishment <br>for everything she has stolen over the years. Karen’s legs and <br>arms are now metal and wood prostheses that allow her to <br>move freely. During a Scene, thanks to her legs, Karen can <br>move on vertical surfaces and anchor herself, ignoring any <br>penalty to movement. Karen’s arms can also stretch to reach a <br>range of nine feet.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":800000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241733,"modifiedTime":1783973241733,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"h0ozzpCFHjBHgWyt","name":"Pagina 9","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 9</h2><p>8<br>Using the Order’s Treasures<br>To the Hunters who cross the sacred threshold <br>of Valea Viilor, remember this warning: In this <br>place, priceless treasures are kept that must not <br>be released upon the common world. God and <br>his emissaries watch over the Treasury so that <br>the power enclosed within it is used to fight the <br>darkness.<br>Evil against Evil, the strength of the shadow <br>turned against itself.<br>If you receive the honor of wielding one of the <br>Treasures of the Order, remember the three <br>rules by which you must abide:<br>1. Do not reveal the power of your treasure <br>within view of the commons.<br>2. Do not use your treasure to harm a <br>representative of the Church or the Order.<br>3. Do not abuse the power of the treasure <br>and return it at the end of your task.<br>As a Hunter you are aware that one of your <br>duties is to deliver any potential Treasure to the <br>Order, so that it can be studied, cataloged, and <br>made available to other brave Hunters in the <br>fight against evil.<br>Obtaining and using an Order’s Treasure<br>The Order’s Treasury contains a series of iconic items that, <br>like the Hunters and the Broken Tales, come from a wide <br>variety of stories. Each Treasure has a story and grants <br>those who wield it a Gift linked to its powers. There are <br>several ways for a Hunter to use an Order’s Treasure:<br>Replace a Gift:  A Hunter chooses a Treasure that will <br>replace one of their Gifts (they cannot replace the Dark <br>Ego). They will then have the possibility to use the Treasure <br>for the duration of the Scenario and will have to rewrite one <br>of their Descriptors so it relates to the Treasure. This option <br>is particularly useful to spice up the Hunters, especially the <br>pre-generated ones.<br>Special Experience Reward:  During a Campaign, <br>through the Advancement Permanently acquire an Order’s <br>Treasure. At this point, the Treasure becomes a permanent <br>Descriptor and a permanent Gift. The Gift “set aside” for <br>the Scenario is recovered, granting the Hunter a fourth <br>Descriptor and a fourth Gift. The Hunter can still take <br>other Treasures temporarily with the Replace a Gift option.<br>Mission Requirement from the Order:  A Scenario <br>may require the use of an Order’s Treasure as part of it, <br>or the Storyteller may grant a Treasure as support to a <br>small group of Hunters, in a similar fashion to receiving <br>the support of an Allied Dark Presence. In this case, the <br>use of the Treasure is to be considered as a Scenario Gift, <br>and Hunters can freely pass on the Treasure between them <br>without adding a connected Descriptor.<br>TREASURES</p>","markdown":""},"sort":900000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241733,"modifiedTime":1783973241733,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"chXkqQFXRTWmOsHH","name":"Pagina 10","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 10</h2><p>9<br>Campaign Event’s Discovery: By playing a Campaign, <br>Order Treasures can be found as part of an Event. Each <br>Treasure comes with a Broken story of how it came into <br>existence, which can inspire the Storyteller to create an ad <br>hoc Event.<br>Treasure’s Descriptor<br>Whoever wields a Treasure must create a related Descriptor, <br>like for any other Gift. Each Treasure comes with a series <br>of Keywords that can help the Player create the Descriptor. <br>Even better, the Treasure’s Descriptor can be mixed with <br>some of the Hunter’s defining aspects. When creating a <br>Drawback for the Treasure refer to at least one of these <br>Order rules:<br> ◆ Do not reveal the power of your Treasure in the eyes of <br>the commons.<br> ◆ Do not use your Treasure to harm a representative of <br>the Church or the Order.<br> ◆ Do not abuse the power of the Treasure.<br>Example: James the Swordsman is getting ready for a <br>mission in the city of Paris. James’ Player believes that his Gift <br>“Tick-Tock, Here Comes the Beast” may not be very useful, <br>since it specifies “while outdoors”, which is not always easy <br>in a big city. James’ Player decides, therefore, to replace this <br>Gift with an Order’s Treasure and chooses The Old Sword <br>(inspired by the Arthurian Myth).<br>Looking at the Keywords of the Old Sword we have: Weapon <br>/ Hilt / Rock / Impact / Vibration / Power / Might. James’s <br>Player then revises his Descriptor with:<br>I have learned to face monsters and aberrations of all <br>kinds, using every weapon and power possible. The Old <br>Sword is what I need, even if the abuse of its power has <br>turned it against me more than once.<br>Treasure’s Gift<br>The Gift granted by an Order’s Treasure is considered a <br>normal Gift of the Hunter wielding it: all activation costs <br>and benefits refer to them. If the Treasure is instead the <br>requirement of a Scenario, the Gift will be considered usable <br>by whoever is wielding the Treasure during the Scene.<br>TREASURES</p>","markdown":""},"sort":1000000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241733,"modifiedTime":1783973241733,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"oU5YvJZVOqj42ebs","name":"Pagina 11","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 11</h2><p>Durend<br>10<br>The Order’s Treasures<br>Durend the Broken Blade<br>Inspired by Orlando Furioso<br>Once upon a time, there was a justice-obsessed Paladin who asked God for a sword that <br>could not be destroyed. But through some strange mockery of fate, he received Durend, a <br>fragile sword that broke with every hit landed. Every night, Durend’s blade reassembled <br>itself, because to be indestructible doesn’t mean to never fall, but to always stand back <br>up afterward. Unable to understand the true essence of that boon, the Paladin threw <br>Durend at the wall of the cathedral of Rocamadour in a fit of rage, where it remained <br>embedded until the Order came along. Only those who are pure enough to understand <br>its true value can wield the Broken Blade’s full power.<br>Keywords: Sword / Shards / Fury / Blessing / Faith / Metal<br>Gift - The Broken Blade: Durend will always have a Descriptor that determines <br>its status, either Whole or Shattered. Whoever wields the Whole Durend can <br>decide at any time to have it become Shattered. Later on, when acting with <br>Shattered Durend, an attack can be made using either what remains of the <br>sword or by wielding one of the blade shards. If this attack catches the opponent <br>by surprise, gain 1 Additional Success for the Position Check. Durend’s owner can <br>spend 1 Soma to make it Whole again at any time. When gaining an Outcome with <br>an Increment by defending themselves with Whole Durend, its wielder can decide <br>to have it become Shattered and inflict 1 Wound to the enemy with the metal <br>shards generated by the impact. At the end of each Scene, Durend is made Whole <br>again.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":1100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241733,"modifiedTime":1783973241733,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"gfNaAIDccuW29oCF","name":"Pagina 12","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 12</h2><p>The Prodigious Beanstalks<br>Durend<br>11<br>The Prodigious <br>Beanstalks<br>Inspired by Jack and the Beanstalk<br>As all Hunters know, there are many magical edibles with <br>prodigious effects. These strange beanstalks can grow on <br>command, allowing whoever uses them to manipulate the <br>vegetation. It is said that the Prodigious Beanstalks were <br>delivered to the Order by a young boy whose eyes were <br>filled with madness. Among tales of man-eating giants and <br>treasures in the clouds, the boy said that the magic stalks <br>had been given to him by an old man, but that their use <br>had proven to be a true curse. The Order took the crazed <br>youngster to its healers and safely stored the magic stalks in <br>the Treasury.<br>Keywords: Seeds / Plants / Growth / Vegetation / Flowers <br>/ Tree.<br>Gift - Plant Growth:  This Gift grants the Player 5 Bean <br>Tokens per Scenario. Spending 1 Token, the Hunter can <br>throw 1 Bean into the bare earth, activating its power. <br>This allows the Hunter to manipulate the vegetation of <br>the immediate vicinity, making it grow. This Gift can be <br>activated in a Controlled way by spending 1 Soma. This <br>way, the Hunter has full control of plant growth and can <br>create a Descriptor that makes it useful, such as a Climbing <br>Ladder or a Bark Wall. The first time the Hunter acts by <br>exploiting the created Descriptor, they gain 1 Additional <br>Success to their action. The second method of activation <br>is called Wild and differs from the first on two levels: <br>there isn’t a Soma cost, but the growth is not fully under <br>the control of the Hunter. After the Descriptor is created, <br>the Storyteller will create a second one that represents the <br>problem generated by the uncontrolled plant growth after <br>using the Beanstalks.<br>Special Effect (Ambrose the Sorcerer known as <br>Old Merlin): No one is aware of the fact that the old man <br>who traded the Beanstalks with the poor crazy boy was, in <br>fact, Merlin. The Prodigious Beanstalks are just yet another <br>magical means for the sorcerer to manipulate the destiny of <br>others. If Merlin is present in the Scenario, during a Wild <br>use of the Gift, the Descriptor created by the Storyteller will <br>not be a disadvantage to the Hunter. It will instead open the <br>way to a special Scene that, if completed, will be beneficial <br>to Merlin himself. The effect should lead to a creature’s lair <br>or a potential trap, but it will also free or allow the Hunter <br>to find someone or something useful for the sorcerer. <br>When this effect is activated, the owner of this Gift and <br>their companions will receive 2 XP if they choose to follow <br>the new path suggested by Merlin.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":1200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241733,"modifiedTime":1783973241733,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"7PT0PcZQViCBqSVO","name":"Pagina 13","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 13</h2><p>The Clothes of the Late Emperor<br>12<br>The Clothes of the Late <br>Emperor<br>Inspired by The Emperor’s New Clothes<br>Once upon a time, a vain nobleman was looking for new clothes to show off. Confident <br>he would look magnificent in any dress, the nobleman accepted the challenge of a <br>strange tailor who offered to let him wear a particular piece of clothing, apparently <br>invisible to the human eye. It was, unfortunately, a scam. However, a very disturbing <br>piece of clothing is featured in the Order’s Treasury, said to be made of human skin. <br>The garment has always been hungry for flesh and blood, and whoever wears it <br>becomes invisible to those who do not know how to look carefully. Legend has it <br>that it is made with the skin of the tailor, skinned alive by the vain nobleman as <br>punishment for his lies.<br>Keywords: Dress / Leather / Blood / Invisible / Cloak / Color<br>Gift - Invisible Cloak: Whoever wears the Clothes of the Late Emperor becomes <br>invisible throughout the course of the Scene, obtaining the additional Descriptor: <br>I am invisible to the human eye and only children see through the deception of <br>my clothes. Whoever is made invisible because of this Gift receives all the narrative <br>advantages of being unseen and 2 Additional Successes to each Defense Check in <br>which being invisible represents a tangible advantage. Activating the power of the <br>Invisible Cloak inflicts 1 Wound to the one wearing it, as the Clothes of the Late <br>Emperor try to feast on their flesh and blood.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":1300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241733,"modifiedTime":1783973241733,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"vQVda0t7SejJL6xM","name":"Pagina 14","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 14</h2><p>Eden’s Fruit<br>The Clothes of the Late Emperor<br>13<br>Eden’s Fruit<br>Inspired by Snow White<br>The magic power of the apple reaches back to the myth of <br>Eden and to a power that God himself denied to man. For <br>this reason, apples are the fruits most easily enchanted by <br>wizards and witches. The most famous enchanted fruit is <br>preserved in the Order’s Treasury, where scholars try to <br>understand its apparent imperishability. The juicy red apple <br>called Eden’s Fruit, in fact, does not decay with the passage of <br>time and regenerates in a few hours after being bitten or even <br>completely eaten. Those who feed on Eden’s Fruit see their <br>body mutate or, in some cases, fall into a deep sleep because <br>of the malignant effect of the mutagenic power of the fruit on <br>their metabolism.<br>Keywords: Apple / Red / Good smell / Flavor / Mutation <br>/ Sleep<br>Gift - Mutagenic Fruit:  Whoever eats part of Eden’s <br>Fruit can choose one of the two effects. 1. Mutation: Yo u  <br>may change a part of your body throughout the Scene and <br>create a specific Descriptor such as Membranous wings or <br>Gills. The mutation will always be difficult to conceal and <br>grants 1 Additional Success in all the actions in which it can <br>be of help; 2. Torpor: This puts the body of those who ate <br>the Fruit into a state of apparent death, in which, however, <br>their cognitive ability is not lost. Whoever has eaten the <br>apple will seem dead for all intents and purposes, even to <br>the most in-depth medical investigations, while keeping all <br>five senses active. One may only wake up from the Torpor <br>at the end of the Scene. If Eden’s Fruit is given to a subject <br>unaware of its power, whoever gave it to them will choose <br>the effect to be activated. It is possible to attempt a Defense <br>Check to resist the power of either of Eden’s Fruit effects. <br>Once bitten, the apple will take the rest of the Scene to <br>regenerate. A second use in the same Scene will make it <br>useless for the rest of the current Scenario. <br>Special Effect (Bloodwhite): Y our special metabolism <br>rejects the power of Eden’s Fruit and you can only choose <br>the Torpor effect. Y ou can recover from it whenever you <br>want, without having to wait for the end of the Scene.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":1400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241733,"modifiedTime":1783973241733,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"7XVinTo1AQKRQBoh","name":"Pagina 15","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 15</h2><p>The <br>Golem<br>14<br>There was a time when alchemists and sorcerers used magic and dark arts to gain power <br>with impunity. In those days, the Church was not yet aware of the true power of darkness, <br>which thrived on the ambition of those who were foolish enough to rely on strange magical <br>practices. Among the many blasphemies produced by alchemy, Golems are one of the most <br>incredible, considering they are animated giants composed of whatever materials came to <br>hand. The Order also uses Golems as tireless minions, bestowing them with the dignity that <br>suits every servant of God.<br>Keywords: Giant / Force / Mindless / Resistant / Clay / Bond<br>Gift - The Immortal Guardian: A Golem is at the service of the Hunter, executing all <br>their orders at a slow, methodical pace. The Golem has the following profile.<br>Descriptor: I am a mighty and resilient Golem. I act only when prompted to carry out an <br>order by my master.<br>3 Wounds<br>Opposition Level: Medium 5 <br>Gift - Immortal Body:  When suffering its third Wound, the Golem crumbles to a <br>thousand pieces to regenerate in the next Scene. The only way to eliminate it permanently <br>is to kill its master. Being animated by magic, an opponent versed in such arts can use <br>their powers to try to temporarily take control of the Golem or prevent it from acting. The <br>Hunter controlling the Golem may attempt a Defense Check to prevent the interference <br>through the strength of their bond with the Golem. The Golem acts only at the command <br>of its creator and giving it an order during an active Scene takes time. For every action, <br>the Golem performs, the Hunter receives 1 Penalty in the next action. The bond, however, <br>provides several advantages. During a Scene, the Hunter can use each of these effects.  <br>1. Protect me!:  The Golem takes 1 Wound in place of its master; 2. Deep Bond: The <br>Hunter can consider the Golem as a “relay” of their presence and activate the effects of their <br>Gifts, using them as if they occupied the Golem’s space. Not all Gifts fit this effect and the <br>Hunter, in agreement with the Storyteller, must create an effect consistent with the narrative;  <br>3. Come to me!: If not present in the Scene, the Golem will arrive as soon as possible and <br>use the fastest shortcut (literally breaking through walls and obstacles!) to reach its master’s <br>side.<br>The Golem Inspired by Jewish Mythology</p>","markdown":""},"sort":1500000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241733,"modifiedTime":1783973241733,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"7IORHGWYh0icm0Tk","name":"Pagina 16","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 16</h2><p>The Wind Carpet<br>15<br>The Wind Carpet<br>Inspired by the One Thousand and One Nights<br>Many special objects were created during antiquity and often <br>preserved in the personal collections of wealthy merchants <br>and spoiled nobles. The Order is ruthlessly efficient at <br>feigning interest in purchasing items and then seizing them. <br>The history of the Wind Carpet has its roots in the eastern <br>lands where, apparently, it passed through many hands, <br>sometimes stained with the blood of its previous owner. For <br>years, the Order’s scholars believed that the Carpet had no <br>special quality, only to discover that it could actually fly, but <br>only if not under the gaze of anyone skeptical of it. After that <br>revelation, it was easy to understand why the artifact was so <br>dangerous.<br>Keywords: Wind / Carpet / Large / Oriental / Strange <br>scriptures / Dust<br>Gift - The Flying Carpet:  The Wind Carpet can fly, <br>carrying up to six people or very heavy loads. This power <br>can be used at will by the Hunter but will dissipate as <br>soon as someone who does not believe in magic looks at <br>the Carpet for a few moments. If this happens, the Carpet <br>immediately loses its power, causing its passengers to fall to <br>the ground. The Wind Carpet is magically indestructible, <br>allowing the Hunter to use it as a wall or shield against a <br>potential hazard, such as fire, arrows, or anything else that <br>could be blocked by it. Once per Scene, the Hunter can <br>take advantage of this protection to receive 2 Additional <br>Successes on their Defense Check. This bonus applies to <br>anyone under the Carpet’s protection, but, as with flight, <br>it cannot be used if a nonbeliever observes the Carpet in <br>action.<br>NB: Magical creatures, witches, the Church, and the Broken <br>Tales, in general, believe in magic and are not considered <br>skeptical of the power of the Wind Carpet. What the item <br>really reacts to are the doubting gazes of ordinary people.<br>Special Effect (Baba Yaga the Child Witch): Even if <br>no one believes your story, the Wind Carpet is actually your <br>creation, and the Order has put its dirty hands on it. As <br>proof, once per Scene, when the stupid humans lay their <br>eyes on it, you can spend 1 Soma to ensure that the power <br>of the Carpet does not fizzle, leaving those poor fools <br>speechless.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":1600000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241734,"modifiedTime":1783973241734,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"fTJEJiTEpqmm0SZP","name":"Pagina 17","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 17</h2><p>The Wind Fan<br>16<br>The Wind Fan<br>Inspired by Journey to the West<br>The East seems to hide incredible treasures, all forged in <br>metal, which represents firmness, discipline, strength, and <br>determination throughout Chinese mythology. In the cycle of <br>elements, however, metal also represents decline and decay, <br>concepts that are well suited to the dark parts of the world. <br>This small metal fan is an ancient heirloom, said to have been <br>forged at the dawn of time. Wave the fan and the wind will <br>respond to the call by obeying the will of its new master.<br>Keywords: Metal / Antique / Wind / Air / Fan / Balance<br>Gift - Dominating the Wind:  Whoever owns the Fan <br>can wave it to invoke the power of the wind and create <br>a Descriptor that deals with the wind, such as A strong <br>breeze or A powerful ascending air current. Using this Gift <br>requires an expense of Soma from 0 to 2 points (decided by <br>the Storyteller), based on the power of the invoked effect. <br>Whoever owns the Fan can wave it to move the wind in <br>their defense, gaining 1 Additional Success in each Defense <br>Check in which the wind could help. <br>Special Effect (Sun WuKong): When the power of the <br>fan is released for the first time in the Scenario, you feel your <br>blood boil as the ancestral spirit inside of you awakens. Y ou <br>can activate your Dark Ego - Descendant of the Awakening <br>of the Void and the Emptiness without paying the required <br>Wound.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":1700000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241734,"modifiedTime":1783973241734,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"TDqx1aipGCD0Nby7","name":"Pagina 18","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 18</h2><p>The Needle of Living Shadows17<br>The Needle of Living <br>Shadows<br>Inspired by Peter and Wendy<br>Since ancient times, there has been a belief that a person’s shadow is nothing more than the <br>extension of their soul and that it remains attached to the body only because it is forced <br>to do so. However, there is an artifact that can separate the shadow from its owner, thus <br>granting it freedom. The Needle of Living Shadows, as it is called, allows one to “unweave” <br>the shadow from a body so that it can act independently. In the same way, a shadow can <br>only be sewn back to its original body using the Needle, which is important because, after <br>twenty-four hours of separation, neither one nor the other would survive...<br>Keywords: Shadow / Darkness / Light / Spite / Mimicking / Joking<br>Gift - Mischievous Shadow: Once per Scene, the Hunter who uses the Needle of <br>the Living Shadows can mime a gesture as if undoing their own shadow. The shadow <br>will then become alive, taking with it 1 of the owner’s Wounds. From that moment, <br>the Hunter will be able to act independently through either their own body or their <br>shadow. The shadow becomes solid and can be hit with weapons or other physical <br>means, possesses all the Gifts, Descriptors, and equipment of the original body, but <br>cannot speak. As soon as it suffers its only Wound, the shadow reattaches to its owner. <br>The only other way to restore one’s shadow is to mime the gesture of sewing it back on <br>with the Needle. However, the shadow, enjoying its freedom, will usually oppose this, <br>unaware that exceeding 24 hours of separation will lead to both its and its owner’s end. <br>This mischievous attitude may require the Hunter to do one or more Position Checks <br>to restore things to their proper order.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":1800000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241734,"modifiedTime":1783973241734,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"pfR2JH4nQskQiGcv","name":"Pagina 19","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 19</h2><p>The Magic Wand18<br>The Magic Wand<br>Inspired by Cinderella<br>Wizards and witches possess many objects of power. Most common among those are wands, <br>genuine catalysts of energy. A wand allows one to express their latent mystical force at its highest <br>levels, permitting whoever wields it to unleash the power of magic. But as the most cautious <br>know, magic is pure chaos and often escapes the control of those who are foolish enough to evoke <br>its power. Over the years, many witches have been captured by the Order, but despite torture <br>and interrogations, none have ever revealed the inner works of their wands.<br>Keywords: Magic / Wood / Wish / Wand / Formula / Light<br>Gift - Magic Transmutation:  Whoever wields the Magic Wand can invoke its power <br>to change the shape of one object into another. Just point the Wand and say the formula <br>“[Target object Name] changes to [New object name]” and spend 0 to 2 Soma points for the <br>spell. The exact value of the cost is decided by the Storyteller, in proportion to the difference <br>between the starting object and what you want to obtain. The mutation lasts until the end of <br>a Scene and can be maintained during the following Scenes at the cost of 1 Soma per Scene. <br>Using the Wand on a living being does not generate mutations, but the magical force destroys <br>the living matter in a vain attempt to manipulate it. For this reason, the Magic Wand can be <br>used to attack an enemy even at great distances, ignoring obstacles and normal defenses. <br>Using the Wand in this way costs 1 Soma point for each attack, but gives 1 Additional Success <br>in the action and, in the event of an Outcome with an Increment, the Hunter can spend the <br>Increment to inflict 1 Additional Wound.<br>Special Effect (Baba Yaga the Child Witch, Marina the Sea Explorer, and <br>Morgana of the Lake):  The Magic Wand perceives your witch aura and shuns it, since <br>it is not in your nature to do good deeds for others. Once per Scenario, when using the <br>transmutation power of the Magic Wand, the Storyteller can decide on a retaliatory effect <br>between the following. 1. Mutating Backfire: Something in your body changes for the <br>rest of the Scene, the Storyteller creates a relevant Descriptor; 2. Explosion: The Magic <br>Wand spits fire and sparks, inflicting 1 Wound to you; 3. Reject: Y ou will no longer be able <br>to use the Magic Wand to transform something until the next Interlude. Y ou can still use it <br>as a weapon.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":1900000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241734,"modifiedTime":1783973241734,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"yLGN0Vm21uZDUT8m","name":"Pagina 20","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 20</h2><p>The Newcomer’s Crown<br>19<br>Once upon a time, an old and dissipated king was served by a <br>company of knights, also old and tired. Although in the past the <br>kingdom had been an example of courage and righteousness, <br>now it was nothing more than a land lost to pleasure and <br>laziness. To fight his ennui, the king called a tournament in <br>which anyone could participate. The dissolute ruler’s intent was <br>to cruelly laugh while his knights were beating on some poor <br>peasant attracted by the idea of becoming a noble. On the day <br>of the tournament, however, only the knights had entered. The <br>people were discouraged by fear, despite the fact that the grand <br>prize, nobility, could change their lives forever. However, shortly <br>before the start of the tournament, a mysterious challenger <br>appeared, a small boy with a wooden sword. The king and <br>his knights laughed heartily, warning the fool not to enter his <br>name. In response, the young man said he wanted to become a <br>knight, and what better way to achieve his dream than winning <br>a tournament?<br>Taking pity, the king sought an excuse to prevent the young <br>man’s death at the edge of some random blade. “If you don’t <br>have a helmet to protect your head, I’m afraid you can’t <br>participate. ” The young man did not lose heart. Instead, he took <br>a small wicker basket, like those used as cradles, and put it on <br>his head. “I am ready, Your Majesty, ” replied the young man.<br>The king began the tournament… and the knights fell one after <br>the other. With absolute courage, against all expectations, the <br>young man defeated all the challengers before the stunned gaze <br>of the king. “ And now that I have demonstrated my bravery, can <br>you make me a knight?”<br>The king, visibly amazed, smiled. He thought about it for a <br>moment and then shouted, “ Arrest this young man! He’s the <br>Devil himself!” The guards grabbed him. Realizing the danger, <br>the boy begged the king for mercy. But the king certainly could <br>not allow true courage and purity of heart to sprout in his <br>kingdom, proving how unworthy he was to sit at its head. <br>And so it was that the young man’s head was lopped off by the <br>headsman’s ax, leaving the small basket as the only memory of <br>his courage and his purity, soiled with blood.<br>Keywords: Purity / Attempt / Challenge / Tournament / <br>Courage / Unexpected<br>Gift - The Newcomer’s Crown:  The Hunter who wears <br>the small basket as a helmet is infused with purity and <br>courage. When facing a threat for the first time, the Hunter <br>gets 1 Additional Success at both the first Position Check and <br>the first Defense Check they must perform. Once per Scene, <br>when they take an action where they do not have a relevant <br>Descriptor, they still get 3 Base Successes. Once per Scene, <br>when the Hunter fails a Position Check, they gain back 1 <br>Soma.<br>The Newcomer’s Crown<br>Inspired by the Arthurian Myth</p>","markdown":""},"sort":2000000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241734,"modifiedTime":1783973241734,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"pAjB1ExtVoRNfoSl","name":"Pagina 21","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 21</h2><p>The Hair Rope20<br>The Hair Rope<br>Inspired by Rapunzel<br>Once upon a time, there was a young woman who, due to an unfortunate event, had ended <br>up in the clutches of a powerful witch. The old hag locked the girl at the top of a tower with <br>no stairs or door and cast a spell on her hair. Thanks to the spell, the girl’s long hair could <br>move and grow impossibly long, becoming a rope that could be climbed. Every day, the witch <br>went to visit the young woman in the tower, bringing her food and gifts. Over the years, <br>she began to regard her as a daughter and not a prisoner. The young woman, however, <br>had met an attractive young man from the nearby village. At night, he went up along the <br>braid of hair to meet her and consummate with her a forbidden love. “The next time the <br>witch asks you to come up, ” said the boy, “coil your hair around her neck and kill her, so we <br>will be free. ” The girl agreed, eager to regain her freedom. But a guardian owl warned the <br>witch of the deception and she, heartbroken, prepared her revenge. She bewitched the boy <br>and took him by day to the foot of the tower, then she called the girl. The young woman did <br>not think twice, animating her hair and, unknowingly, strangled her beloved. Realizing her <br>terrible mistake, she jumped from the tower. Fate had her fall right on the old witch, killing <br>them both instantly. Only the hair, still animated by magic, remained to witness this absurd <br>tragedy.<br>Keywords: Hair / Rope / Crawl / Whip / Strangle / Animate<br>Gift - The Hair Rope: The Hunter who owns the Hair Rope can spend 1 Soma to animate <br>it and move it for all its 30 feet of length. The rope can grab and drag objects, tie itself to <br>a ledge, or execute any other order that comes to its master’s mind. Once animated, the <br>Hair Rope will act for the entire duration of the Scene, being able to perform its action at <br>any time at the order of the Hunter. Once per Scene, the Rope can hinder a danger that <br>threatens its master, granting 2 Additional Successes on a Defense Check.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":2100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241734,"modifiedTime":1783973241734,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"KpfhiYDeN3chDICS","name":"Pagina 22","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 22</h2><p>The Old Sword<br>The Hair Rope 21<br>The Old Sword<br>Inspired by the Arthurian Myth<br>Once upon a time, there was a powerful magic sword stuck in <br>a rock that no one could pull out. According to the prophecy <br>shared by the old sage Merlin, only someone destined to reign <br>over all England would be worthy to wield the sword in the stone. <br>In fact, Merlin himself had enchanted the weapon, merging it <br>with the rock in which it was set. Following the dark plans of <br>the magician, the prophecy attracted nobles, knights, and even <br>ordinary people, all eager for the power and status derived from <br>being the chosen one. But as Merlin had plotted, no one could <br>really draw the sword, which should have remained forever <br>in the rock, distracting the mortal fools from the true aims of <br>the wizard. What Merlin had not considered, however, was <br>the power of people’s desire. At every attempt, at every failure <br>to draw the weapon, the sword was charged with a spark of <br>magical power, growing more powerful by the day. Finally, <br>after a hundred long years, the sword had reached immense <br>power but remained inextricable. Merlin stopped basking in his <br>deception when the Order came. The Hunters did not hesitate <br>to break the stone around the sword, taking it away, under the <br>astonished gaze of its creator.<br>Keywords: Weapon / Hilt / Rock / Impact / Vibration / Power <br>/ Might</p>","markdown":""},"sort":2200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241734,"modifiedTime":1783973241734,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"1EqGOQDatJtTxbdZ","name":"Pagina 23","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 23</h2><p>22<br>Gift - The Sword of the Myth: The Old Sword does not <br>have a blade, being nothing more than a block of rock with <br>a hilt to hold it. The weapon’s power is strong and tangible, <br>but also incredibly unstable. Whoever holds it must roll a <br>die every time they use it to see how the latent energy in the <br>Old Sword manifests. <br>1. Heavy as a rock: The power does nothing but increase <br>the weight of the weapon, so actions receive 1 Penalty <br>because of the cumbersome block; <br>2. The Nothingness:  The Old Sword loses all power, <br>resulting in a common piece of rock; <br>3. Spark of Power: A flash of power gives 1 Additional <br>Success to the action; <br>4. Impact: The Old Sword releases a shock wave that hits <br>the enemy upon impact. If the action inflicts 1 Wound, and <br>the target is thrown several feet away as an additional effect; <br>5. Devastation: The Old Sword falls upon the target to <br>pulverize it into a thousand pieces. If the action causes 1 <br>Wound, it will also cause 1 additional Wound; <br>6. The True Excalibur:  For a moment, the Old Sword <br>manifests all its true power. Whoever wields it inflicts <br>1 additional Wound and can cut through anything, <br>even rock or metal. The enemies are dazzled by the <br>power of the Old Sword and whoever wields it receives <br>1 Additional Success on the next Defense Check they <br>make to defend themselves from an enemy attack.  <br>Once per Scene, whoever wields the Old Sword can spend <br>1 Soma before rolling the dice to choose the desired effect. <br>Special Effect (Ambrose the Sorcerer known as <br>Old Merlin): Merlin hates the Old Sword, as it represents <br>his greatest failed deception. Whoever wields the Old <br>Sword will never benefit from Merlin’s help but will also <br>receive 2 Additional Successes to defend against any effect <br>generated directly or indirectly by the sorcerer’s magic.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":2300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241734,"modifiedTime":1783973241734,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"OJLIPfNAZbX5C1uG","name":"Pagina 24","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 24</h2><p>The Dead Bandits’ Jars<br>23<br>The Dead Bandits’ Jars<br>Inspired by the One Thousand and One Nights<br>There is an old story that tells of a group of bandits that was <br>deceived by a brave boy who, with the help of his family, <br>vanquished the whole band of scoundrels. Hidden in jars, <br>the bandits were burned alive one by one, dying with a last <br>curse between their lips. A hundred years passed and the <br>jars shattered. But still, today, when throwing a piece of the <br>jars to the ground, the curse lives on, bringing one of those <br>unfortunate spirits into our world.<br>Keywords: Bandits / Undead / Boulder / Sabers / Sand / <br>Turbans<br>Gift - The Forty Immortal Thieves: Whoever has this <br>Gift receives 5 Jar Tokens at the beginning of a Scenario. <br>During a Scene, spending one Jar Token to throw one of <br>the pieces to the ground, roll a dice to see how many Dead <br>Bandits are summoned: 1-2 1 Bandit 3-4 2 Bandits 5-6 3 Bandits.<br>Descriptor: I am the animated corpse of a bandit and I <br>execute every order of whoever summoned me.<br>1 Wound<br>Opposition Level: Easy 3<br>A Bandit can act independently or sacrifice themselves to <br>help their master, suffering 1 Wound to grant 1 Additional <br>Success to the Hunter’s action.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":2400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241734,"modifiedTime":1783973241734,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"TKLLapAZY28Jzphx","name":"Pagina 25","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 25</h2><p>The Carnival Masks24<br>The Carnival Masks<br>Inspired by the Italian Tradition<br>Some treasures are born from legend, others become legends thanks to popular belief. The <br>Order’s studies and research have led to the discovery of an incredible truth: the power <br>of belief in something unreal can make it real. And just as monsters are born from man’s <br>fears, the Carnival Masks were born from the strange characters that man has created <br>to mock the vices and flaws of society. It is said that the oldest masks have taken on a <br>consciousness of their own, fuelled by the popular belief that has made those grotesque <br>characters a reality.<br>Keywords: Mask / Voice / Carnival / Laughter / Theater / Deception<br>Gift - The Carnival Masks:  Whoever owns this set of four masks can wear them <br>during a Scene to receive the attached benefit. Each Mask can be used 1 time per <br>Scenario. All additional Descriptors conferred by the Masks can be marked to obtain <br>extra XP .<br>Pantaloon: Whoever wears it receives the Descriptor I am an expert merchant, <br>skilled at evaluating anything. I am greedy and crave wealth. Simply by observing <br>a place or a person, the Hunter will be able to identify the thing of the highest value, <br>deciding whether to measure it by monetary value, emotional value, or spiritual value.<br>Pulcinella: Whoever wears it receives the Descriptor I am a skilled and elusive <br>scoundrel. I love to do wrong. The Hunter can leave a Scene without anyone noticing <br>them, even in a guarded or closed place. Those present will notice their absence only <br>at the end of the Scene.<br>Colombina: Whoever wears it receives the Descriptor I am a skilled servant who, <br>however, wants to be flattered. There’s no job I can’t do. In addition to a normal <br>action, the Hunter can add 2 Additional Successes to an ally’s action when they need <br>it most, once per Scene.<br>Rugantino: Whoever wears it receives the Descriptor No one can stand up to me <br>in a duel. I am easily angered when my worth is questioned. While performing an <br>action that involves a fight or duel, the Hunter can turn an Outcome with a Cost into <br>an Outcome with an Increment.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":2500000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241734,"modifiedTime":1783973241734,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"WKRDEBA5Ww3D0oMk","name":"Pagina 26","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 26</h2><p>The Razor-sharp Glass Slippers25<br>The Razor-sharp Glass Slippers<br>Inspired by Cinderella<br>Once upon a time, there was a young girl, the youngest of three sisters. When the mother <br>of the three decided to offer them in marriage to a rich noble, the youngest girl was <br>immediately discarded because of the color of her hair, which did not please the noble. <br>Wounded in her pride, the young woman turned to a powerful witch who gave her a <br>pair of magic shoes. While wearing the glass shoes, each click of the heels clouded the <br>minds of those who were close to her, forgetting the most insignificant details. “Thanks <br>to these shoes, ” said the witch, “you can approach your beloved and make yourself <br>known for your inner beauty, while he will not remember the hair that he does not <br>appreciate. ” But the young woman’s heart was not as pure as the old witch believed. <br>Drunk with the power of the slippers, she set out to trick men and women, stealing <br>gold and precious items. When the old witch returned to the city, she wept with sadness <br>seeing what the young woman had become. Now a rich and greedy noblewoman, she <br>refused to return the shoes and accused the witch of blasphemy, condemning her to <br>burn at the stake. With her last breath, the witch invoked one last spell, and the shoes <br>animated, leading the young woman towards the flames. Everyone watched, horrified <br>but unable to intervene since at every click of the heel the power of the shoes clouded <br>their mind. The glass slippers, shiny and unmarked, were all that remained once the fire <br>was extinguished.<br>Keywords: Bright / Precise / Clicking / Reflective / Dazed / Attention<br>Gift - Glass Heels:  Whoever wears the shoes can click the glass heels and create <br>a resonance that confuses subjects within 40 feet. Once per Scene, the Hunter can <br>create a Descriptor that contains the words Focused (for example, Everyone’s eyes <br>are focused on me and my royal gait) or Distracted (Everyone is distracted  by <br>the clicking of my heels ) and manipulate the NPCs around them. The Descriptor’s <br>effect lasts throughout the Scene and reduces the Opposition Level of each NPC by 1. <br>Once per Scenario, the Hunter can decide to break the heels to inflict 1 Wound on all <br>enemies who can hear the noise. The Glass Slippers will thereafter be unusable until <br>the next Interlude.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":2600000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241734,"modifiedTime":1783973241734,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"d1IuIAZUcY0irYDT","name":"Pagina 27","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 27</h2><p>The Mirror of a Thousand Wishes26<br>The Mirror of a Thousand Wishes<br>Inspired by Snow White<br>Once upon a time, there was a queen so obsessed with her appearance that she never stopped <br>admiring her reflection. She was a beautiful woman, the most beautiful of her time, but <br>despite this, she could not stop scrutinizing herself in search of the slightest defect. Her worried <br>spouse turned for help to a powerful wizard, asking for a mirror that could show what was <br>most desired. The wizard took advantage of that gesture of love to dispose of a cursed mirror <br>of which he himself was a victim. “The Mirror of a Thousand Wishes can show anything, ” said <br>the wizard to the poor man, “but only if it’s in the past or the future. ” Even better, thought the <br>man, the one I love will see her perfection before and after, enjoying her present with me. The <br>queen was happy with the gift, but she began to spend even more time in front of her new <br>mirror. She saw her future and past selves, two perfect women, identical and beautiful. But <br>why couldn’t she see herself at this very instant? Maybe the mirror was hiding something from <br>her? The queen stopped doing anything else, asking the mirror to show her what she was like at <br>that very moment. Insistence became obsession; obsession became desperation. Then one day, <br>for a second, the mirror showed her the present. The last thing the queen saw was her beloved <br>with a knife in his hand and, in his eyes, the pain of those who have forever lost their love.<br>Keywords: Reflection / Blur / Mirror / Vanity / Glass / Gold<br>Gift - Mirror Mirror on the Wall:  Those who use the Mirror of a Thousand Wishes <br>can ask to see the near past or the imminent future of a subject they have met at least once. <br>After spending 1 Soma, the Mirror will show a few moments of the target by displaying <br>them on its surface. The observer will not know if what they see is the past or the future. <br>The Storyteller secretly rolls a die: with 1-3, they will see the past, with 4-6 the future. <br>The same subject cannot be observed more than once during a Scene. Alternatively, before <br>attempting a specific task, the owner of the mirror can look into it and spend 1 Soma. <br>Roll a die. If it’s a 4+ they will see a few moments of their imminent future. Thanks to <br>this premonition they will receive 3 Additional Successes for the first action attempting to <br>perform the task.  <br>Special Effect (Bloodwhite): Y ou cannot hide your true nature from the Mirror of a <br>Thousand Wishes, it will always reveal what you really are. Reflecting yourself in the Mirror <br>of a Thousand Wishes is considered an Activator of your Dark Ego.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":2700000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241734,"modifiedTime":1783973241734,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"FRUWY07b28W6rucS","name":"Pagina 28","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 28</h2><p>The Tetsubo of the Oni27<br>The Tetsubo of the Oni<br>Inspired by Japanese Mythology<br>The Order has never been interested in the Dark Presences roaming the distant <br>lands of the East, but – as it happens – evil always finds a way to hunt its prey. The <br>Tetsubo of the Oni is a long spiked club with a strange shape, which seems to rouse <br>the most hostile part of those who wield it. The Tetsubo was brought to the West by <br>inexperienced Hunters. Now, the Order fears that the artifact is nothing less than <br>a key for the variety of Demons called Oni to invade our world. But as dangerous <br>as the Tetsubo is, it is also a weapon of incredible value, which more than once has <br>allowed the Hunters to gain the upper hand over monsters and aberrations.<br>Keywords: Mace / Power / Fury / Smash / Lightning / Steel<br>Gift - Rage of the Oni: Whoever wields the Tetsubo of the Oni experiences fits <br>of uncontrolled anger, which becomes the source of a devastating force. Should <br>the Hunter obtain an Outcome with an Increment during a Tetsubo attack, they <br>can spend the Increment to inflict 1 additional Wound on their target. Once <br>per Scene after an attack, the Hunter can decide between 1 of these effects.  <br>1. Smash: An object or part of the environment is completely shattered by <br>the blow the Tetsubo inflicts; 2. Kill: Even if the attack is a Failure, the target <br>suffers 1 Wound inflicted by the incredible energy released by the Tetsubo;  <br>3. Sweep: The Tetsubo attack can hit up to a total of 3 targets within range. <br>For each target, a different Position Check must be made. The Tetsubo makes its <br>owner overly aggressive and agitated. As a result, the Hunter receives 1 less Base <br>Success on all Defense Checks.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":2800000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241734,"modifiedTime":1783973241734,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"rFRcTLqDSj0q2XaP","name":"Pagina 29","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 29</h2><p>28</p>","markdown":""},"sort":2900000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241734,"modifiedTime":1783973241734,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"2fYrsut8hZaNHurO","name":"Pagina 30","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 30</h2><p>29<br>This chapter expands Broken Tales with a solo play <br>mode, without the need for a Storyteller or other Players. <br>This type of experience will look much more like a creative <br>writing exercise than a usual role-playing Session. Due <br>to its more introspective nature, Untold Stories  will allow <br>you to glimpse into the Hunters’ past, living intense and <br>engaging adventures and bringing out different facets of <br>each Hunter and their relationship to the Order.<br>That way, you can explore novel elements of each Hunter’s <br>past, based on their background and their Descriptors. <br>Who really is the mysterious little boy who deceived James <br>the Swordsman? Is Baba Y aga really the most powerful <br>witch of them all? These and other adventures await you in <br>the Untold Stories.<br>Initial Setup<br>The first step is to choose the Hunter protagonist of your <br>story. Hunters have a personal list of 3 possible narrative <br>hooks linked to their past, each giving some hints useful to <br>determine the ultimate goal of the Hunter. <br>Keywords are thematic elements linked to the possible <br>storylines and clues available to the Hunter. Their use <br>is relevant for the Key Scenes, as explained in the Initial <br>Situation Table on page 44.  <br>Alice of Other Worlds<br>1-2 Beyond the mirror:  Alice wakes up in front of <br>the great mirror of Wonder. Facing her reflection, she <br>unexpectedly activated her mental control ability. However, <br>the body she took over isn’t hers, but that of a young girl <br>named Alix. The young woman is locked in a house full of <br>mirrors and is tortured by a jailer whose face is shrouded. <br>Only Alice can save her.<br>3-4 The trial: Alice has been summoned to London’s court <br>to be part of the jury in an important trial. Along with her, <br>on the jury, there is a strange inventor named Hatta Carter <br>and an arrogant noblewoman named Regina the Thief of <br>Hearts. Alice quickly understands that the old soldier called <br>Jack Hearts, accused of murder, is a scapegoat while the true <br>culprit is one of those judging him...<br>5-6 The diary: Alice recovers a diary from when she was <br>little more than a teenager. While reading it, she realizes that <br>there are notes about travels she does not remember. To cure <br>such severe amnesia, she will have to visit those places again.<br>Keywords: Truth merges with madness / Journey into <br>memories / Injustice / Reason turned upside down / <br>Accusation / Underground / Strange food / The den / The <br>playground / The house that no one sees.<br>Untold Stories</p>","markdown":""},"sort":3000000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241734,"modifiedTime":1783973241734,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"hQT4uG3yQzlhkLrT","name":"Pagina 31","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 31</h2><p>30<br>Baba Yaga the Child Witch<br>1-2 The challenger:  Baba Yaga receives a visit from a <br>young witch. It is quite a surprise when the clueless girl tries <br>to hurt Yaga with one of her spells. After being defeated, the <br>young woman reveals that she is one of Circe’s students, a <br>witch who claims to be the best in the trade.<br>3-4 The awakening: The power of Baba Yaga also derives <br>from an ancient agreement made with Merlin, as she agreed <br>to eliminate all those who are endowed with great magical <br>power. After crippling Morgana, relegating her to a Hunter <br>of the Order, a fairy animal reveals to Yaga terrible news. <br>The Snow Queen, her bitter and ancient rival, has awakened <br>from the magical sleep in which Yaga and Merlin sealed her <br>ten years ago.<br>5-6 The little girl:  Even Yaga does not know the true <br>identity of the body of the child she occupies. As far back <br>as she can remember, she has always been like this. What <br>mystery lies behind her birth? Who condemned her to eternal <br>childhood?<br>Keywords: Magic and rituals / Power games / Evil / House <br>on the tree / Secrets not to be revealed / The mirror of eternity <br>/ Merlin / Broken memories / The secret of magic / True <br>power.<br>Babai the Judge<br>1-2 Whispers from the light:  Babai was not always <br>such a dark character. There was a time when he lived in the <br>sunlight and a beloved woman smiled at him. But one day <br>she broke the law and, like all the others, she was judged. New <br>evidence has now emerged, after so many years, casting doubt <br>on the judgment and leading Babai to investigate further.<br>3-4 Whispers from the shadows:  There was a <br>time when Babai’s body wasn’t a shadow and was instead <br>made of flesh and bones. Interestingly, criminals are now <br>plaguing Venice and it appears that their bodies are made <br>of pure darkness. By investigating them, perhaps Babai will <br>understand something more about the gift darkness has <br>bestowed upon him.<br>5-6 The judge: In a small village in the French countryside, <br>a little girl of ten killed her whole family by slaughtering them <br>in their sleep. Although the entire village would like to put <br>little Selene on the gallows, Babai cannot help but give the <br>defendant a fair trial and try to understand what really <br>happened.<br>Keywords: Accusation / Light / Shadows / Unbearable <br>guilt / Hard to believe innocence / Envy / Dormant grudge / <br>Sanction / Country rumors / Goodnight kiss.<br>Beauty and her Beast<br>1-2 The beast hunter: A mysterious and skilled monster <br>slayer is tracking down Dionysus to eliminate him, but <br>Bellina cannot allow it because of the bond that binds her life <br>to that of the Beast.<br>3-4 The miracle of true love:  An old acquaintance of <br>the Gonsalva family proposes an arranged marriage between <br>the rich and young Dolcinea and Dionysus. Bellina must <br>remove the rival or risk remaining forever the servant of <br>the Beast. But Dolcinea is different from all the others, and <br>because of her purity, she is able to look beyond the beastly <br>aspect of Dionysus. This time, Bellina will have to prevent a <br>real love miracle from happening.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":3100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241735,"modifiedTime":1783973241735,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"t5WfPSAhTl1X33pZ","name":"Pagina 32","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 32</h2><p>31<br>5-6 The poor father: After the fall of the House of Roses, <br>the good name of Antonio, Bellina’s father, was forever <br>disgraced. The old merchant tried to get out of debt by offering <br>Bellina’s hand to a greedy crime lord who is now claiming his <br>bride. <br>Keywords: Purity / Beastly violence / Opportunity / Hunt <br>for the Beast / Debt / Looking beyond appearances / Dark <br>soul / The hidden truth / Bond / Made for each other.<br>Bloodwhite<br>1-2 Heart eater:  A strange creature feeds on the hearts <br>of its victims and terrorizes a small village in Germanic <br>Bavaria. Bloodwhite is sent by the Order to investigate since <br>whatever creature is responsible for these crimes seems to <br>share similarities with the young Hunter.<br>3-4 The stepmother:  Elsa Karenmann is missing, and <br>her husband Karl immediately remarries a mysterious <br>noblewoman. The peaceful village of Lohr soon becomes a <br>rich trading hub, rejecting the quiet life that many of the <br>inhabitants had built through commitment and sacrifice. <br>When Bianca returns to the village to understand what <br>happened, it is clear to her that her new stepmother is no <br>ordinary person, but a dangerous rival who aims to destroy <br>everything she holds dear.<br>5-6 Into the mine:  During the period when she lived <br>hidden in the mine, Bianca forged a close relationship with <br>a group of Hessian mercenaries, crude dwarves with great <br>team spirit. But as the dwarves dug into the mine to make <br>it their new home, something that sleeps in the depths of the <br>earth awakened, searching for new prey.<br>Keywords: Heart and blood / Motherly love / Envy / <br>Mutant / Friendship / Village / Pure heart / Kindness / <br>Hidden / Looks can be deceiving.<br>Carlo the Living Puppet<br>1-2 The whale: A fishing boat has not returned to the <br>port, and an old sailor tells of a fearsome sea monster that <br>swallows entire boats in one gulp. While the fishermen’s <br>children mourn their fathers, Carlo decides to seek out the <br>monster and save the poor sailors.<br>3-4 A big problem: Carlo is convinced by two other <br>Hunters, Cunning Machiavelli and Sly Bischeri, to undertake <br>a mission for the Order. While Carlo checks that no one <br>is watching, the two Hunters steal a relic from St. Peter’s <br>Basilica in Rome and when the papal guards arrive, Carlo <br>realizes that he has trusted the wrong Hunters.<br>5-6 The guard: After inadvertently freeing all the chickens <br>of a poor farmer, Carlo begins to work on the farm to make <br>up for the disasters he has caused. While guarding the field, <br>he will discover a secret kept far from the prying eyes of the <br>Order.<br>Keywords: Bandits / Secrets and lies / Redeem one’s <br>mistakes / Monster / Naivety / Debt / Unexpected help / <br>Trouble / Lost / Promise.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":3200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241735,"modifiedTime":1783973241735,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"fdg8bca2yZforQ1R","name":"Pagina 33","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 33</h2><p>UNTOLD STORIES<br>32<br>Garou the Old Wolf<br>1-2 The hunter: Of all the many humans in the world, <br>only one truly deserves the respect of Garou. There is an <br>old huntsman, the only one who has ever prevailed against <br>the wolf. Now, the huntsman has learned that Garou was <br>not executed for all his wrongdoings, but rehabilitated as a <br>member of the Order. And that’s not fair. The hunt is on.<br>3-4 The impostor: Garou’s name still echoes in the <br>countryside, and it seems that the fierce wolf has resumed <br>his raids. But the real Garou knows that this is an impostor, <br>and he will certainly not allow them to exploit his name for <br>much longer.<br>5-6 The only human I don’t consider food: Only one <br>human is dear to Garou, a young female farmer who took <br>care of him when everything seemed lost. Garou paid his <br>debt by eliminating the girl’s violent father, but now she is in <br>danger once more and Garou will not leave behind someone <br>he considers part of his pack.<br>Keywords: Wolves and howlers / Rifle / Hunting trophy / <br>Kids and houses / Stones and ponds / You can’t teach an old <br>dog new tricks / Enraged survivors / A gentle caress / The <br>pack / Hunting trip.<br>James the Swordsman<br>1-2 Monster hunt: Tired of being hunted by the creature <br>that craves his flesh, James decided to put an end to this <br>eternal hunt. But the monster has shown over and over again <br>that it can come back to life. What secret does it hide? And <br>why did it choose James as its prey?<br>3-4 Old comrades: One of his former crewmates contacts <br>James for help. An impostor has taken the name of James the <br>Captain and now sails the sea, leading raids and terrorizing <br>seafarers. James certainly cannot allow his good name to be <br>tarnished like this.<br>5-6 The gang of the lost: A gang of young criminals sows <br>panic in London, carrying out acts of vandalism and then <br>disappearing into thin air under the noses of their pursuers. <br>A crescent-moon-shaped dagger that is found after every <br>attack is a clear message to James. It is indeed the same blade <br>wielded by the mysterious boy who deceived him.<br>Keywords: A place that is not there / Monstrosity / Crew <br>/ A duel / Honor and bravery / The dark half / The curse / <br>Youthful cruelty / Revenge / The monster slayer.<br>George the Holy Dragon Slayer<br>1-2 The false dragon: A dragon has been sighted in the <br>English countryside, but something about the reports does <br>not convince the Dragon Slayer. Is the dragon real or just a <br>clever scam?<br>3-4 Return home: George returns to the village where <br>he was born, taking a short rest from fighting the forces of <br>evil. During the first night, strange noises draw his attention. <br>Perhaps in the depths of the forest lies another creature like <br>the one that the Saint has already eradicated in the name of <br>God?<br>5-6 The traitor: A champion of the Church has betrayed <br>the cause and fled, taking with him a Treasure of the Order. <br>Theodomir has always been a knight of duty, and George is <br>convinced that there is something more than a simple escape <br>behind his actions.<br>Keywords: For the greater good / Sacred / Profane / <br>Monster heart / Hidden truth / Past wrongs / Discipline and <br>duty / Monstrosity / Innocents in danger / Devotion and <br>honor.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":3300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241735,"modifiedTime":1783973241735,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"2D3gcvvT0yADnI53","name":"Pagina 34","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 34</h2><p>UNTOLD STORIES<br>33<br>Hatta Carter<br>1-2 From the top: While working on the Groundhog, a <br>new automaton, Hatta realizes that he is always at the same <br>point. It’s always Monday, he’s always still in the moment of <br>staring at the last bolt that he can’t find... when everything <br>starts again. What is actually happening?<br>3-4 The Expo: That time when Hatta Carter participated <br>in the first London Universal Exposition, without knowing <br>that it was the year 1851.<br>5-6 A tea in peace: Hatta has organized an afternoon <br>tea with his best friends when he suddenly realizes he has no <br>friends. He only has three hours to get three guests to share a <br>nice cup of tea with him. <br>Keywords: Loop / An old friend / A new enemy / So insane <br>that it is real / Automata / Invention / Nonsense / Paradox <br>/ The hat of wishes / This keyword (which was the most <br>important and useful) was forgotten by Hatta and replaced <br>with one of the following: Shrimp, Dodecahedron or Ropeway. <br>The Astonishing Pied Piper Without a Name<br>1-2 The kidnapper: A mysterious criminal who uses <br>music to charm people has kidnapped the son of a wealthy <br>nobleman to ask for a large ransom. And there is only one <br>person to whom the Astonishing Pied Piper Without a Name <br>has taught his art...<br>3-4 The perfect melody: Walking through the streets of <br>Vienna, the Astonishing Pied Piper Without a Name hears <br>the most perfect of melodies coming from the instrument of a <br>young street artist. The Pied Piper has felt such urges before, <br>but this song is one he cannot let go. He’ll have that music, no <br>matter what.<br>5-6 The masks of Notre Dame: A company of acrobats <br>has set up shop near the cathedral of Notre Dame, bewitching <br>the public with skilled performances and musical tales. Soon, <br>however, several disappearances begin to take place in the <br>neighborhood. Is someone using art with evil intentions?<br>Keywords: Perfection / Charming / Notes like blades / The <br>secret note / Teachers and students / Concert / The price of <br>art / Eternal life through art pieces / Blood feuds / Rumors.<br>The Knight with a Hundred Heads<br>1-2 Echoes from the past: The Knight with a Hundred <br>Heads awakens on an old, abandoned bridge. Near him, the <br>decapitated body of a soldier with the head a few steps away. <br>Ordog grins, amused, as he invites the Knight to “wear” the <br>head and understand what happened.<br>3-4 Ordog’s secret: The Knight with a Hundred Heads <br>has always been accompanied by the strange talking horse <br>Ordog. But what is this creature’s true nature? Arriving at <br>the top of a rugged mountain, the Knight hopes that the holy <br>man who lives there will have an answer.<br>5-6 The last line of defense: The Knight with a Hundred <br>Heads wakes up in a small village in the Black Forest. As <br>always, he does not remember how he got there, but he is <br>“wearing” the head of someone whom all the inhabitants of <br>the village are relying on to defeat an imminent dark threat.<br>Keywords: Former comrade in arms / The pact / Revenge / <br>My lost family / The duty of a soldier / Barnabas my eternal <br>rival / War wounds / Will beyond death / A promise / The <br>Devil has many forms.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":3400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241735,"modifiedTime":1783973241735,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"REav7WdxpKWn1JXj","name":"Pagina 35","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 35</h2><p>34<br>Iskra the Young Wolf<br>1-2 History repeats itself: Iskra returns to her old village <br>to cherish the memories of her previous life. But Irena, her <br>dearest childhood friend, has disappeared… lost in the great <br>forest where she had ventured searching for herbs. <br>3-4 The old woman in the woods: A small village has <br>seen many of its children disappear. Desperate parents tell of <br>an old witch who attracts innocent young people to her house <br>in the woods and then devours them mercilessly.<br>5-6 The pack: Although no longer part <br>of Greskar’s pack, Iskra cannot remain <br>motionless to the news that her former <br>pack has been targeted by a group of <br>unscrupulous poachers.<br>Keywords: Poacher / Cottage in the woods / Grandmother’s <br>smile / Young girls / The hidden predator / Fangs / The pack’s <br>call / Tracks / Dark forest / The wolf among the lambs.<br>The Gang of Three Pigs<br>1-2 The wolf that threatens the houses: The Gang <br>arrives in a small village harassed by a mysterious creature <br>that, every night, destroys one of the houses and devours its <br>inhabitants. The Gang decides to solve the problem, not so <br>much because it is the duty of a Hunter, but because of the <br>challenge that this phantom “house wrecker” represents. <br>3-4 The new lair: In his travels, the youngest of the Gang <br>has come across what could become the perfect secret lair. <br>The only problem is that a whole crew of smugglers now lives <br>there. <br>5-6 The fortress: That damned nuisance, Saint George, <br>has discovered the power of the flesh of the God Under the <br>Mine and now wants to deliver it to the scholars of the Order. <br>The Gang took refuge in an old, abandoned castle, preparing <br>to repel the assault of Saint George and his Paladins. <br>Keywords: To build / Fierce wolf / Traps / House / Shelter / <br>Secret passage / Tear down / The flesh of God Under the Mine <br>/ Pretend / Fireplace.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":3500000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241735,"modifiedTime":1783973241735,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Su9aQQJadps2y8lG","name":"Pagina 36","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 36</h2><p>35<br>The Woman from the Wood<br>1-2 History repeats itself: The Woman from the Wood <br>wakes up in the middle of the countryside, completely covered <br>with blood. Near her, the dismembered bodies of five men and <br>the bloody tracks of a couple of children heading for the nearby <br>forest. What happened here? <br>3-4 The abandoned house: A Hunter’s report to the <br>Order reveals that, in the thick of the Black Forest, they have <br>come across a haunted house. The Woman from the Wood feels <br>a strange nostalgia hearing this. Are there hidden clues to her <br>past within that house? <br>5-6 The survivor: News has come of the eruption of the <br>Laki volcano in the islands of the far north. Only one survivor <br>has returned to the mainland, carried by the fury of the sea. <br>Miraculously unharmed, the strange individual vanished <br>without a trace, escaping from the hospital where he was <br>hospitalized. The Woman from the Wood feels a strange <br>excitement at hearing the man’s description, including physical <br>traits similar to her own. Perhaps she is also native to those <br>islands. Only by finding the fugitive will she get an answer.<br>Keywords: Lost memories / Smell of freshly baked cake / <br>Little house in the woods / Children’s laughter / Fleeing from <br>the past / The power to trigger mutations / Blood and sugar / <br>Fire / Home sweet home / The sweet taste of raw meat.<br>The Immortal<br>1-2 The retrieval: After years of investigation, the Immortal <br>is now convinced that there is a map in Valea Viilor that leads <br>to the place where the needle storing his soul is kept. The <br>objective of the old sorcerer is to make a copy of the map to <br>retrieve the precious heirloom later when he is safe from the <br>Order’s gaze.<br>3-4 The young Dragomira: The old Immortal has <br>fallen in love with a young noblewoman from the East, but <br>unfortunately he is no longer the great sorcerer who could <br>make himself look handsome with magic. Dragomira came <br>to Rome from Freiburg to marry a local nobleman, but the <br>Immortal discovered that the young woman mourns another <br>love, left behind in her native land. The Immortal must decide <br>whether to help her escape, doing a good deed, or stop her in <br>order to satisfy his own frustrated ego. <br>5-6 A strange memory: Every now and then, some <br>thousand-year-old memory resurfaces in the Immortal’s mind. <br>There is a recurring one showing him naked among a circle <br>of big menhirs while reciting a magic formula. What was he <br>doing? And who were the other sorcerers and witches there <br>with him? Finding the magic circle may yield some answers.<br>Keywords: Ancient magic / Beauty and youth / Distant <br>memories / Wounded bodies / Fortified churches / Compelled <br>obedience / Former glories / Selfishness and generosity / <br>Atonement / Guilt.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":3600000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241735,"modifiedTime":1783973241735,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"vcJKS6mpinvlK8m8","name":"Pagina 37","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 37</h2><p>36<br>Marina the Sea Explorer<br>1-2 The stolen treasure: Once upon a time, there was <br>a fascinating merchant named Armand who acquired one <br>of Marina’s treasures through deception. The treasure could <br>allow the wielder to force others to agree with them, allowing <br>for some very profitable business deals. Armand used the <br>treasure against Marina allowing him to get away while <br>paying next to nothing. But now the merchant is in Paris for <br>a great fair and it is time for Marina to have him pay in full, <br>with interest. <br>3-4 Marina’s true form: A mysterious letter is delivered <br>to the Order. Inside is the portrait of a woman. Marina is <br>deeply affected by this because that portrait shows her true <br>appearance. Who would know of her identity? And why <br>would they want Marina to know they have such secret <br>knowledge?<br>5-6 The call of the sea: A Sea Fairy sends a message to <br>Marina. A fearsome monster is waking up in the abyss and <br>will bring disaster to the depths. Now used to a comfortable <br>life among humans, Marina is not very interested in the fate <br>of the sea. But when the Fairy explains that the water will no <br>longer be salty, Marina decides to leave at once, intent on not <br>losing the very source of her magical powers.<br>Keywords: A good deal / A bad deal / Elixirs and potions <br>/ Mirror / The sea / The magic of the sea / Sea fairies and <br>creatures / The big market / Hidden treasure / Love can’t be <br>bought.<br>Morgana of the Lake<br>1-2 The knight: A well-built young man named Accolon <br>reaches out to Morgana claiming to be her lover. He says <br>he never stopped searching for his lost lady. The young <br>man looks familiar to Morgana but also evokes unpleasant <br>emotions. Following Accolon could allow her mind to access <br>lost memories, but at what price?<br>3-4 The mysterious island: More and more ships are <br>disappearing into thin air off the coast of the island of Sicily. <br>Morgana is sent by the Order because it is feared that a spell is <br>at work there, cast a hundred years ago by a powerful fairy...<br>5-6 The delivery: Morgana is entrusted with the Old <br>Sword, a relic of the Order that must be taken to safekeeping <br>in Valea Viilor. But the more Morgana holds the weapon, the <br>more she feels it is tied to her past. <br>Keywords: Magical places / Illusions / Lost memory / <br>Family feud / Merlin / Baba Yaga / Magic that changes reality <br>/ Fairy / Knight / Round table.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":3700000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241735,"modifiedTime":1783973241735,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"0w7BDPtBST8gOxko","name":"Pagina 38","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 38</h2><p>37<br>OZena the Afflicted<br>1-2 The first witch: Everything has a beginning. Dorothea’s <br>story starts in the village of Schiltach, in the eastern part of <br>the Black Forest. There Dorothea killed the witch Johanne <br>and was reborn as OZena the witch killer. But how did things <br>really go?<br>3-4 The gang: During her crusade against the witches of <br>the Black Forest, OZena saved and took under her wing three <br>faithful followers: Hirnloser the madman, Dose the leper, and <br>Lowe the coward. This is the story of their meeting.<br>5-6 The only friend who ever loved me: Dorothea <br>did not arrive alone from the future in 1780. With her was <br>her faithful dog Toto, but he was lost in the magical vortex <br>evoked by Henkle. During a traveling circus show, Dorothea <br>recognizes her dog among the beasts that a fierce tamer uses <br>to give a show. But what lies behind the creepy Emerald <br>Circus and its grim members?<br>Keywords: Lost / Respect / A common cause / Brain / <br>Heart / Courage / Witchcraft / Solitude / Away from home / <br>United in destiny.<br>Regina the Thief of Hearts<br>1-2 The price of power: Regina has trampled and <br>destroyed anyone in her way, even her beloved sister, to reach <br>the top. Now that she is undoubtedly the best, she suddenly <br>regrets some of her actions, particularly consigning her sister <br>to slavery in a fit of pique. After so many years, perhaps it is <br>time to do something for someone else.<br>3-4 The unexpected legacy: For Regina, it seems normal <br>to have a dozen husbands scattered throughout Europe, silly <br>nobles that she left after having squeezed them properly. But <br>now that one of them has passed away, a bunch of greedy <br>relatives can’t wait to silence Regina forever and prevent her <br>from collecting a notable inheritance.<br>5-6 You’ll die when I decide!: Jack Hearts, one of the <br>most debauched servants of the Queen, was captured by a <br>gang of crazy cutthroats who call themselves the Jabberwock. <br>But Jack had a very important task, which was to bring <br>Regina a precious box of her favorite chocolates. No one can <br>play with the life of her servant, except Regina herself. It is <br>time to save those precious chocolates from the cutthroats, <br>and maybe even that disappointment Jack Hearts.<br>Keywords: The gang / Crushed feelings / Gold and <br>pleasures / An order to execute / Obsession / The title of <br>Queen / Former loves and broken hearts / The drive to excel <br>/ The word given / Madness.<br>Verdoux Bluebeard<br>1-2 The lost bride: Strange news comes to Verdoux’s <br>ear from one of his many informants. A beautiful woman <br>named Adeline will soon be marrying an elderly and wealthy <br>nobleman, an arranged marriage that has nothing to do with <br>love. Perhaps a meaningless piece of news, except that the <br>young woman is identical in appearance to Bluebeard’s sixth <br>wife, who died during a shipwreck.<br>3-4 The secret of death: Strange disappearances are <br>occurring within the slums of Amsterdam. Bodies with pierced <br>skulls are sometimes found among the rubbish. It seems that <br>a thriving trade has been born in the city, involving secrets <br>and information which someone takes directly from the brain <br>of the victims. And if there’s a mystery to figure out, Verdoux <br>Bluebeard will solve it.<br>5-6 The house of a thousand doors: Verdoux got his <br>magic bunch of keys on a business trip, exploring a cursed <br>house that everyone calls the House of a Thousand Doors.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":3800000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241735,"modifiedTime":1783973241735,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"x8p5yhE33cJyy9yb","name":"Pagina 39","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 39</h2><p>38<br>Every year, Verdoux needs to recharge the power of his <br>magical keys. To do so, he must explore new rooms of the <br>cursed house. <br>Keywords: Unmentionable secrets / Lookalike / The room <br>of memories / Ruthless / The price of truth / Love at first sight <br>/ The missing key / Doors / Business and intrigue / Enemies <br>everywhere.<br>Sherazade the Weaver of Tales<br>1-2 The djinn: Rumors come to Sherazade of a strange <br>creature, a shadow with a turban that deceives people, <br>promising to fulfill their wishes in exchange for their soul. <br>Sherazade has used such a shadow before. Could it have <br>escaped her control to roam free?<br>3-4 Traveling with Sinbad: At the court of a wealthy <br>nobleman, Sherazade meets Sinbad the Traveler of a <br>Thousand Seas who invites her to embark with him on his <br>next journey. With the promise of learning an incredible <br>story, Sherazade accepts, aware that the shrewd sailor hides a <br>secret he does not want to reveal. <br>5-6 The greedy nobleman: Sherazade is contacted by <br>the messengers of a rich nobleman who has heard rumors of <br>an incredible storyteller. The nobleman wants Sherazade all <br>to himself, revealing himself as the same sort of man as the <br>Sultan. Determined to prevent the past from repeating itself, <br>Sherazade does not flee, instead imparting an exemplary <br>punishment to the nobleman.<br>Keywords: Fireside stories / Obligations and secrets / <br>Moving shadows / Imprisonment and blackmail / Sea and <br>distant islands / Storytelling / Twist / Appearances and <br>protagonists / Curtain / Archetypes.<br>Sun Wukong the Amazing Monkey<br>1-2 Fight between spirits: A strange creature of <br>incredible power spreads panic among the small villages on <br>the Aneto Peak, in the Pyrenees. An ancestral call guides <br>Wukong to the large snow-covered forests, in search of a spirit <br>with which he feels he has a great deal in common.<br>3-4 Journey to the West: Wukong is assigned as a <br>personal guard to a young novice nun. He must secretly <br>escort the devout Sanzia from Rome to Westminster Abbey <br>in England. But why does a common novice make a Hunter <br>of the Order so uncomfortable? Who really is Sanzia? <br>5-6 Human cubs: Three little brothers roam the streets <br>of London in despair. Because of a power struggle between <br>underworld leaders, their mother was abducted and put on <br>a ship to Paris. Entertained by the three little “cubs, ” Sun <br>Wukong embarks on a journey to help them reunite with <br>their mother. <br>Keywords: Dangerous journey / Compulsion / Awakening <br>/ Spite / Someone to defend / Wild animals / Rebellion / <br>Understanding humans / Rough / Spirits of nature.<br>Talia the Sleeper<br>1-2 A prince’s dream: While she was secluded in her <br>castle, Talia had recurring visions of a young nobleman in <br>the same situation. Now that she’s a Hunter of the Order, it’s <br>time to go and find him. <br>3-4 The miracle: One morning, Talia suddenly opens her <br>eyes. She is awake and can finally interact with the world as a <br>normal person. But how long will this miracle last? And who <br>made it happen?</p>","markdown":""},"sort":3900000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241735,"modifiedTime":1783973241735,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"POzneoMDdUbSRIy7","name":"Pagina 40","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 40</h2><p>39<br>5-6 The last link: Talia found a diary among the treasures <br>of her ancestral castle belonging to an aunt she did not know <br>she had. Reading it, Talia learns that her parents had a <br>younger sister and that she was the one who incited them <br>into a blasphemous union. This mysterious aunt, named <br>Edwige, seems a diabolical person who enjoys manipulating <br>the minds of others. If she’s still alive, Talia needs to find her <br>and prevent her from doing to others what she did to Talia.<br>Keywords: Curse / Will / Dream / Castle / Painful <br>memories / Blood ties / Ignore reality / Prison / Journal / <br>Countdown.<br>Yukie Onn the Traveling Artist<br>1-2 Bloodlust: A strange creature spreads terror through <br>the nighttime streets of Prague, bleeding its victims dry. <br>Intrigued by a monster that could have similar powers to <br>hers, Yukie Onn begins an investigation into the city’s dark <br>alleys.<br>3-4 The suitor: A scion of a noble family fell hopelessly <br>in love with Yukie after her performance at the court of the <br>Bourbons. What at first was an insistent suitor soon turned <br>out to be a madman obsessed with the beautiful artist. Yukie <br>will now have to prove that love cannot be bought or taken <br>by force.<br>5-6 The lake of spirits: A legend says that lost in the <br>mountains of Northern Europe is a magical lake where the <br>spirits of the dead appear to talk to the living. Yukie needs to <br>find it to see her beloved Akihiro one last time.<br>Keywords: Love tears / Warm blood / Snowstorm / <br>Vampire / Toxic love / Spirits / Vanity / Spilled blood / A <br>great show / A gallant encounter.<br>Yvonne of the Dark<br>1-2 Orphans: Yvonne has grown fond of a group of <br>Parisian foundlings, living hand-to-mouth on the streets. But <br>winter is coming and the ghost must find accommodation for <br>her young friends so that they do not succumb to the cold and <br>hardships in the catacombs. <br>3-4 The witch stakes: In a small country village, an <br>overzealous prelate started his own witch hunt, setting two <br>young girls ablaze. Yvonne has to find out where the real guilt <br>lies.<br>5-6 Exploitation: Jerome, a powerful lord of the <br>underworld in Paris, exploits young orphans to gather money <br>through alms, but leaves almost nothing to those who serve <br>him. Yvonne wants to teach him a lesson he won’t forget. <br>Keywords: Fire / Abandonment / Alms / Society’s outcasts <br>/ Cold / Selfishness / No consideration / Church / Grace of <br>God / Injustice.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":4000000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241735,"modifiedTime":1783973241735,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"BszkEG1ArENa5YOh","name":"Pagina 41","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 41</h2><p>40<br>Managing a <br>Session<br>An Untold Stories Session unfolds broadly like a regular <br>Broken Tales Session, with a few changes due to the solo <br>game mode:<br> ◆ The Player plays both the role of Hunter and of <br>Storyteller, using a series of tables to randomly <br>determine some events and to get guidance in times of <br>uncertainty. The Initial Situation Table will be used <br>to determine if what happens during a Scene will bring <br>into play a Keyword, which will significantly alter the <br>plot towards the Hunter’s goal.<br> ◆ Each Scene is set through a series of rolls on various <br>tables, after which the Player describes the actions <br>of the Hunter and imagines how the surrounding <br>environment could consistently react. In case of doubt <br>about how a situation can be resolved, formulate a <br>simple Yes/No question.<br>Whenever a question would normally be asked of the <br>Storyteller, the question must instead be put so that the <br>answer can only be Y es or No:<br>The Hunter scans the alley. Is someone lurking here? After <br>seeing the Hunter’s magic in action, is the NPC frightened?<br>The Player rolls 2 dice and adds the results. Consulting <br>table on page 43 will reveal the answer, sometimes with <br>variations.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":4100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241735,"modifiedTime":1783973241735,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"j22USfUiUJdw2Z1K","name":"Pagina 42","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 42</h2><p>41<br>No, and...  In addition to denial ( no), something goes <br>wrong and the situation turns against the Hunter.<br>No. The answer to the question is no.<br>No, but...  The answer is no, but an element can be <br>introduced in the Scene that, if dealt with, could transform <br>the answer into a yes.<br>Maybe. The Player can decide between the Yes or No <br>effect, but each time after that, they will have to choose the <br>option they didn’t choose on the previous occurrence.<br>Yes, but…  The answer to the question is yes, but like <br>an Outcome with a Cost, a negative element of some kind <br>must be introduced.<br>Yes. The answer to the question is yes.<br>Yes, and... The answer to the question is yes, but like an <br>Outcome with an Increment, a further positive element of <br>some kind can be introduced.<br>On the side of the Question Table you’ll find two lists of <br>Keywords that can be used to inspire additional elements <br>for No/Yes, but... and No/Yes, and... <br>Clearly depict each Scene<br>Just like in a Scenario, each Scene should have:<br> ◆ An Initial Situation.<br> ◆ A Place.<br> ◆ A list of NPCs (if any).<br> ◆ A clear set of information for the Hunter. <br>It is possible to determine each of these elements through a <br>dedicated table, or by choosing options that are consistent <br>with the developing story.<br>In addition, it is useful to determine the Purpose of the <br>Scene, which is decided by the Player. This will be the <br>“guideline” to decide who or what to include in the Scene, <br>according to the final goal of the Hunter.<br>A Scene must be played until the stated Purpose is achieved <br>or until it is clear that it is no longer achievable. Keeping <br>track of the Scenes will help keep track of the mood and the <br>playing time, and it is also critical to the use of some Gifts. <br>If an Interlude is called, after resolving it you must roll on <br>the Complication Table, which will add a future problem <br>for the Hunter (page 48). <br>Managing Scene consistency<br>Obstacles, clues, and reactions of the NPCs will emerge <br>naturally from the Player’s decisions and from the random <br>elements generated by the tables. A fundamental task is to <br>call the Position and Defense Checks each time the most <br>plausible resolution to a situation involves a potential <br>failure. <br>Consistency, however, is more important than introducing <br>randomness. If during a Scene, it occurs to you that “it <br>would be nice if X happened right now” , it makes sense for <br>X to happen, period. There is no need to be afraid to lead <br>the story, introducing an event, NPC, or a Threat.<br>As a general rule, each Scene should engage the <br>Hunter in at least a couple of Position or Defense <br>Checks.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":4200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241735,"modifiedTime":1783973241735,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Lpjvx3XNcgSLhAHB","name":"Pagina 43","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 43</h2><p>42<br>The easiest way to do this is to never take the result of an <br>action for granted. There isn’t a Storyteller to manage NPC <br>Descriptors, Gifts, and Agendas or use them to oppose <br>you. Instead, it makes more sense to rely on Checks when <br>determining if an action is successful or which option an <br>NPC may choose.<br>Typical actions that require a Check can be:<br> ◆ Convince, get attention from, or scare <br>someone. Unless the introduced NPCs openly fear <br>the Hunter, important NPC interactions require a <br>Check to determine the outcome. However, it’s often <br>wise to leave open an alternative that doesn’t require a <br>Check. Frequently, the Hunter must fulfill a request to <br>earn the NPC’s favor .<br> ◆ Fighting or using force.  Fights will feel less <br>like a natural part of the narrative, since there is no <br>Storyteller making decisions for the NPCs. With a <br>couple of adjustments, it is still possible to generate <br>interesting situations. The Player must roll or decide <br>a result from the Opponents’ Strategy Table and <br>the Opponents’ Objective Table. These tables will <br>provide a course of action and a purpose to the NPCs, <br>allowing for more interesting situations than a mere <br>exchange of blows.<br> ◆ Noticing a clue or a detail. Unlike with the normal <br>rules (which never include a Check to get information), <br>in this solo game mode it is necessary for the Hunter <br>to perform a Check to notice details or gather <br>information. In most cases, the Question Table will <br>provide something for your Hunter to discover in a <br>Scene, but you may need a Check to better understand <br>the situation. Hunters’ Gifts that provide information <br>should be used to provide information to the Hunter’s <br>benefit, without going through a Check.<br> ◆ Overcoming an obstacle or facing a Threat.  As <br>per the rules, any situation with a risk of failure and that <br>does not directly involve an NPC must be formalized <br>into a Threat. The Player can create one or roll on the <br>Danger Table.<br>Story Tables<br>The Story Tables cover the most varied situations and <br>events. While setting up a Scene, it is always good to <br>keep the tables close at hand so you can determine any <br>unexpected elements on the fly.<br>Getting to the epilogue<br>After experiencing at least 3 Keywords, the story can move <br>towards its conclusion. The sum of the 3 Keywords allows <br>the Player to set a final Scene that solves the Scenario’s <br>objective. If some issues are still unsolved, they can all be <br>used during the epilogue.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":4300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241735,"modifiedTime":1783973241735,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"zk6AmYGaYypgBKNv","name":"Pagina 44","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 44</h2><p>43<br>Question Table<br>Whenever you need an answer to determine how the world <br>around you behaves, set up a question that you can <br>answer with a Yes or No. Roll 2 dice and follow the <br>result.<br>2: No, and...<br>3-4: No.<br>5-6: No, but...<br>7: Maybe (The first time this is rolled, choose No, but... or <br>Yes, but... In the course of a single Scene, each time this <br>happens, you have to choose the opposite result to the <br>previous one).<br>8-9: Y es, but...<br>10-11: Y es.<br>12: Y es, and...<br>Additional positive elements<br>Notice a hidden detail / Drop something / Uncover something <br>about yourself / Find a secret / Somebody arrives / Change <br>perspective / A new path is revealed / Introduce a new NPC <br>/ Introduce a new place / Gain time / Get a future advantage <br>/ Break a promise / Reveal a Gift / Reveal a Treasure / It is <br>linked to a Dark Presence / Someone is watching the scene / <br>They are willing to accept a deal / Gain a resource.<br>Negative additional elements<br>Reveal something about yourself / Reinforcements are coming <br>/ Someone is coming / Something remains unsolved / Change <br>perspective / Introduce a new NPC / Introduce a new place / <br>Waste time / A guarantee is needed / Make a promise / Reveal <br>a Gift / Reveal a Treasure / It is linked to a Dark Presence / <br>You went back on your trail / Someone is watching the scene <br>/ They see you / They hear you / Lose resources.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":4400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241735,"modifiedTime":1783973241735,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"mRwHhnOImEk0R0G9","name":"Pagina 45","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 45</h2><p>44<br>Story Tables<br>The first four tables are the basis on which to create and set <br>the Scenes. All the other tables are to be considered optional. <br>If the story seems to come to a halt during the Session, or <br>you are up a blind alley, you can roll the dice for each of the <br>tables and try to integrate the result with the information <br>already in place. This way, you will get unexpected or <br>inspirational elements, or sense of the situation that could <br>give new life to the story (a new NPC appears and opposes <br>the Hunter, an old friend runs to help, etc.)<br>Story Table 1 - Initial Situation<br>Choose according to the plot or roll 1 die to determine <br>which Scene is presented to the Hunter. If you rely entirely <br>on chance, add +1 to the roll for each Scene you play until a <br>Key Scene comes out, then reset the bonus count.<br>1-2 Agitated or dramatic Scene: Things get worse <br>for the Hunter, something gets in the way and hinders <br>them. Y ou can roll on the Danger Table or the Event <br>Table to figure out what.<br>3 Unexpected Scene:  The situation is not as the <br>Hunter expected. Y ou can roll on the Event Table.<br>4-5 Connection Scene:  The story follows its natural <br>course in line with the previous Scenes, you can roll on <br>the Table of Encounters  and the Table of Typical <br>Situations.<br>6 Key Scene: The story follows its natural course and <br>will introduce a Keyword. After collecting 3 Keywords, the <br>next Scene can be the Epilogue. <br>Story Table 2 - Place<br>Choose according to the plot or roll a die 2 times to <br>determine the positive and negative characteristics of a <br>location the Hunter visits.<br>URBAN PLACES<br>1: Secluded, away from prying eyes / A potential danger to <br>the Hunter is lurking.<br>2: Rich in resources and benefits / Controlled by someone <br>who decides everything.<br>3: A mystery is linked to the place or to someone who inhabi-<br>ts it / A Broken Tale lives in or uses this place.<br>4: Crowded, is home to parties or gatherings / Someone takes <br>advantage of the confusion to commit illicit acts.<br>5: Fortified and defended against danger / Well guarded and <br>secure, it is not easy to enter and exit without being seen.<br>6: Comfortable and optimal for rest / Very difficult not to <br>leave tracks and traces of your presence.<br>WILD PLACES<br>1: Isolated and far from human presence / Natural hazards <br>and predators.<br>2: The “home” of a Broken Tale / The territory of an entity <br>that does not want intruders.<br>3: No-man’s land, where anyone can walk around without <br>worry / A crucible of magical power.<br>4: Devastated by a menace / Intricate, where one can easily <br>get lost.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":4500000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241736,"modifiedTime":1783973241736,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"1Ll5m1k3KAjMgLwo","name":"Pagina 46","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 46</h2><p>45<br>5: Abandoned and lost / Point of passage where it is easy to <br>run into a Threat.<br>6: Unknown and full of secrets / Full of traps.<br>Story Table 3 - List of NPCs<br>Y ou can roll several times on the tables to generate details <br>of an NPC and formalize a Descriptor. For Minor NPCs, it <br>is not advisable to waste too much time on the details, apart <br>from choosing a Quality and an Attitude, which are the <br>most useful pieces of    information to include in the story. <br>More than in other cases, you will have to thoroughly <br>evaluate what is useful to establish before rolling to keep <br>the narrative consistent.<br>DISTINCTIVE ELEMENT<br>Roll one or more dice to determine distinctive elements in <br>the various categories of an NPC.<br>Physique - Hair - Eyes - Face - Clothing <br>1: Tall / Thick hair / Tired eyes / Well-kept teeth / Poor and <br>worn appearance.<br>2: Small / Bald / Sincere Eyes / Dirty and broken teeth / A <br>symbol of belonging.<br>3: Overweight / Gray hair / Inquiring eyes / Well-kept beard <br>and mustache / A religious jewel.<br>4: Underweight / Strange hairstyle / Sad eyes / A big scar / <br>Clothes typical of a trade.<br>5: Handicapped / Hair braids / Cynical eyes / Scent of oil and <br>essences / Fine clothes.<br>6: Trained / Dirty and ruffled hair / Lustful eyes / Scent of <br>dirt and sweat / Armed. <br>Defects - Voice - Benefits - Attitude - Quality<br>1: Nervous tics / Calm voice / Multilingual / Available to tho-<br>se in need / Skilled in exploiting weaknesses.<br>2: Fearful / Thunderous voice / Master of an art / Busy sol-<br>ving a problem / Stubborn and ready to fight.<br>3: Poor memory / Whispering voice / Affinity to a Broken <br>Tale / Desperately searching for something / Benefit derived <br>from knowledge. <br>4: Shy / Strong voice / Master of a particular weapon / Ap-<br>prehended by someone / A useful resource. <br>5: Rude / Hoarse, coughing voice / Knows the area / Seeking <br>a challenge / Protected by someone who matters.<br>6: Greedy / Melodious voice / Loved by all / Trusted / Strug-<br>gling to handle a situation / Accurate and able to notice de-<br>tails.<br>PROFILE<br>If necessary, you can generate an NPC profile.<br>1-2 Weak: OL Easy 3 – 1 Wound – 0/1 Gift<br>3-5 Capable: OL Medium 5 – 1 to 3 Wounds – 1/2 Gifts<br>6 Paragon: OL Difficult 7 – 3 to 6 Wounds – 2 Gifts</p>","markdown":""},"sort":4600000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241736,"modifiedTime":1783973241736,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"nnhfotGwX3W9S5Uw","name":"Pagina 47","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 47</h2><p>46<br>AGENDA<br>It is not necessary for every NPC to have an Agenda, simply <br>because there is no Storyteller to manage it. However, <br>it may be useful to have a general idea of what the most <br>important NPCs would like to achieve, in relation to the <br>Hunter’s objective. Roll a die:<br>1: The NPC’s Agenda is in total contrast with that of the Hun-<br>ter, and achieving one excludes the other. The NPC can be <br>considered a main opponent of the Scenario and will be wil-<br>ling to do anything to stop the Hunter.<br>2-3: The NPC’s Agenda is opposite to the Hunter’s, but only <br>due to a connection to other NPCs and situations. The NPC <br>hinders the Hunter, but they do so in the name of the bond <br>they hold and not out of direct hatred for the Hunter. <br>4-5: The NPC’s Agenda intersects with that of the Hunter. <br>The NPC may be an ally or an enemy, in relation to what <br>happens/what they crave for themselves. The objective of the <br>NPC is connected to the story of the Hunter and is influenced <br>by the decisions of the latter.<br>6: The NPC’s Agenda is aligned with that of the Hunter. The <br>NPC will be a genuine ally, to the best of their ability.<br>Story Table 4 - Clear information for <br>the Hunter<br>To get useful information to progress in the story, you often <br>need a Check. Y ou can roll on this table to understand <br>where the information is and who holds it.<br>1: The information is in the hands of an NPC who intends to <br>share it at a high price.<br>2: The information is contained in something (a tome or in <br>possession of an NPC) that anyone can reach. First come, first <br>served.<br>3: The information is protected by several Threats.<br>4: The information is in the hands of an NPC willing to pro-<br>vide it and unable to defend themselves from threats.<br>5: The information is hidden and should be sought with time <br>and attention.<br>6: The information can be accessed by killing a very dange-<br>rous creature/NPC.<br>Once the information is obtained, it will often open the way <br>to the next Scene. Sometimes it will instead act as a bridge <br>to the resolution of the Scene itself.<br>As an optional rule, you can add unpredictability with false <br>information. <br>When you find a new piece of information, you don’t <br>always know if it’s accurate until you follow where it leads. <br>To provide that ambiguity in a solo game, you can use a <br>die, a deck of cards, or another tool. Roll a die, then hide <br>the result without looking. Alternatively, draw a card from <br>the deck and don’t look at it. When you follow up on the <br>information in the next Scene, you can decide that an <br>even roll means it was true, while an odd roll means the <br>information was false, or vice versa. Alternatively, a red <br>suited card could mean correct information while a black <br>suit means it was a false lead. Y ou can then reveal the result <br>(flipping the card over or uncovering the die) to discover if <br>the information was true or false. If it was true, the Scene <br>continues. If the information was false, you can introduce <br>an unexpected element or roll on the Event Table.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":4700000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241736,"modifiedTime":1783973241736,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"vhZTw3uKFg8v7DYy","name":"Pagina 48","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 48</h2><p>47<br>Additional Tables<br>All the tables below are not a must for the construction of <br>the story but can provide interesting ideas to enrich each <br>situation.<br>Danger Table<br>Dangers are NPC and Threats that will try to harm the <br>Hunter.<br>1: A group of Minor NPCs on mission on behalf of an NPC / <br>A natural phenomenon that puts everyone in danger.<br>2: A group of Minor NPCs led by a Main NPC / A skillfully <br>set trap.<br>3: A Dark Presence / A crowd out of control.<br>4: A Hunter with opposite or intersecting objectives / One or <br>more dangerous animals.<br>5: A Main NPC prepared to deal with the Hunter / A threat <br>based on a natural element (e.g., a fire).<br>6: A Main Broken Tale NPC / Someone (to whom the Hunter <br>is bound) whose life is at stake. <br>Event Table<br>Events are sudden incidents that overturn the status quo of <br>the Scene.<br>1: A group of NPCs takes control of the situation by force.<br>2: The arrival of a new faction in the Scenario with a neutral <br>Agenda.<br>3: A Dark Presence that crashes into the Scene, roll 1 die (1-3 <br>They seek revenge against the Hunter on behalf of someone <br>else, 4-6 They are intrigued by the Hunter and their abilities).<br>4: An incident that attracts general attention.<br>5: An NPC that is eliminated in a mysterious way, roll 1 die <br>(1-3 an allied NPC, 4-6 an opponent NPC).<br>6: A Broken Tale manifests itself for the first time.<br>Typical Situations Table<br>Situations are great introductions to a Scene with which <br>to integrate the Initial Situation. It is possible to generate a <br>Scene opening and a situation or place.<br>1: Someone on the run / A village festival.<br>2: A request for help / A mass.<br>3: A tournament / A market day.<br>4: A search / A night round.<br>5: A looming threat/ A place considered cursed.<br>6: A summons / At sunset.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":4800000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241736,"modifiedTime":1783973241736,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"HJb7ZQtNaClsNET3","name":"Pagina 49","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 49</h2><p>48<br>Encounter Table<br>The encounters are great for introducing new NPCs into <br>the story. Y ou can determine who you meet and a potential <br>situation that affects them.<br>1: A Broken Tale / Wounded.<br>2: An old person / In pursuit.<br>3: A person / Fleeing.<br>4: A young person / In danger.<br>5: A couple / On a mission.<br>6: A group / Deceased recently or long ago.<br>Opponent’s Strategy Table<br>During a fight, you can change up the NPCs’ actions <br>by rolling on this table. The first result is for individual <br>opponents, the second for groups, and the third for the <br>Broken Tales. During a fight, only apply each result once, <br>rerolling the die if necessary.<br>1: They try to exploit the environment to attack / Exploit <br>numerical superiority / They reveal a new Gift and use it <br>against the Hunter.<br>2: They try to take advantage of the environment to defend <br>themselves / Only one engages the Hunter, while the others <br>block every escape / They go straight for the kill.<br>3: They try to hit an ally of the Hunter / They threaten so-<br>mething the Hunter cares about to distract them, while some <br>companions attack / They use a Gift.<br>4: They pretend to be struggling, then counterattack / They <br>surround the Hunter / They call for an ally. <br>5: They call for one or more underlings / They call for their <br>leader / They try to understand the Hunter’s intentions while <br>fighting them.<br>6: They use a Gift / They attack all together without conside-<br>ring the risk / They move away to attack at a distance.<br>Complication Table<br>After an Interlude, roll twice on this table to find out <br>what happened while the Hunter rested. Each result has a <br>narrative effect and a possible mechanical effect.<br>1: An NPC, resource or situation that the Hunter cares about, <br>ends up at the mercy of an opponent / What the Hunter ye-<br>arns for is used as bait to distract them and force them to <br>perform Checks to keep it safe while the enemy acts.<br>2: The Hunter arrives late on the Scene, leaving time for their <br>opponents to prepare / Add or introduce Minor NPCs as op-<br>ponents.<br>3: The enemy has time to devise a strategy / Give a new Gift  <br>to an opponent.<br>4: The place where the Hunter arrives turns out to be a trap / <br>Delete one or more piece of the Hunter’s equipment. <br>5: The enemy has learned something about the Hunter / In-<br>troduce something that hinders the use of one of the Hunter’s <br>Gifts.<br>6: The enemy has become more powerful / Improves the pro-<br>file of an enemy by increasing the Opposition Level or their <br>Wounds.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":4900000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241736,"modifiedTime":1783973241736,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"l7nrOccJI3oQ61d3","name":"Pagina 50","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 50</h2><p>49<br>Discovery Table<br>Y ou can determine a finding or discovery and how it affects <br>the situation.<br>1: A valuable object / Alter the status quo.<br>2: A Treasure of the Order / Procures wealth.<br>3: A building / Brings desolation.<br>4: A secret / Generates interest.<br>5: A document / Removes limitations of some kind (prohibi-<br>tions, laws, accusations).<br>6: A substance / Corrupts.<br>Traveling Table<br>If the Hunter covers long distances from one Scene to <br>another, you can roll to see what happens along the way.<br>1: An enemy hired by a rival NPC intercepts the Hunter to <br>stop them.<br>2: A group of NPCs in a perilous situation they can’t cope <br>with.<br>3: Lost along the way, the Hunter comes to a mysterious pla-<br>ce that hides something.<br>4: A Dark Presence crosses the path of the Hunter.<br>5: The journey continues smoothly.<br>6: The Hunter arrives early, gaining time to plan and prepare <br>before enemies and troubles arise.<br>In Media Res Table<br>If there are no particular ideas on how to set up a Scene it <br>is possible to start it “in media res, ” meaning “in the middle <br>of things”: the Hunter is already engaged with something <br>and what happened before will be determined by the tables. <br>This is a great way to create twists and turns in the story.<br>1: The Hunter is hunted by an enemy or a multitude of thre-<br>ats. <br>2: The Hunter is trapped in a place by a threat or ended up <br>there by mistake.<br>3: The Hunter is lost and far from what was their original <br>destination, thrown into a completely new situation.<br>4: The Hunter is hiding while watching some NPC plot so-<br>mething.<br>5: The Hunter is interviewing an important person who can <br>help them.<br>6: The Hunter is at the gates of a mysterious place full of <br>dangers.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":5000000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241736,"modifiedTime":1783973241736,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"G7kE9sgo2ecA9lQh","name":"Pagina 51","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 51</h2><p>50</p>","markdown":""},"sort":5100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241736,"modifiedTime":1783973241736,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Q6kP0trPmF7Czg7u","name":"Pagina 52","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 52</h2><p>51<br>The Village is a variant of the game that will put <br>the Players in the shoes of ordinary people who have <br>crossed paths with the Broken Tales. Scarred by their <br>dark encounter, regular people can no longer live a normal <br>existence. Instead, they fall into a spiral of confusion, <br>driven by a fascination with the macabre to investigate the <br>mysteries of Broken Europe.<br>This mode is designed for a game with a strong OSR (Old <br>School Renaissance) atmosphere, a game philosophy <br>movement that highlights groups of less heroic protagonists, <br>often desperately poor, who try to survive in a dangerous <br>and hostile world. The protagonists will find themselves <br>investigating the same Scenarios as the Hunters of the <br>Order but, because their abilities are not the same as the <br>Hunters’ , their experiences will be profoundly different. <br>Rule Variations<br>The Village is played exactly like a normal Broken Tales <br>Session, but with some tweaks both in the organization of <br>the game and its rules.<br>A reason to investigate the <br>shadows of the Broken Tales<br>Based on the chosen Scenario, the Storyteller decides why <br>a group of Villagers gets involved in the investigation. If <br>the idea is to play a continuous Campaign, the group of <br>Villagers could be formed at the request of some authority <br>or a Hunter. Given the shortage of Hunters of the Order, <br>someone else has to step in. In the preparation phase, the <br>Storyteller will have to consider rewriting the background <br>of the Scenario to adapt it to the Villagers.<br>The Horror of the Broken Tales<br>The Villagers’ abilities are nothing like those of the Hunters <br>of the Order. Any Position or Defense Check against a NPC <br>or Threat that is clearly linked to the Broken Tales will have <br>its Opposition Level increased by 1. This disadvantage can <br>be eliminated in future Checks as soon as a Villager is able <br>The Village</p>","markdown":""},"sort":5200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241736,"modifiedTime":1783973241736,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"d65P1TSz7E5bNcW5","name":"Pagina 53","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 53</h2><p>52<br>to inflict 1 Wound to whatever is threatening them, or <br>overcome it entirely. This simple change significantly shifts <br>the level of difficulty of each Check, putting the Villagers <br>in a constant state of insecurity. The application of this rule <br>must be strongly anchored to what happens during the <br>Scenario. The Storyteller can decide when not to apply it. <br>If, for example, the Villagers face a creature for the second <br>time, it is plausible that its sight no longer rouses such <br>horror in the Villagers as to affect their actions.<br>Mortality<br>When a Villager suffers their last Wound, they will die or, <br>more rarely, be put aside for the rest of the Scenario. The <br>Player can immediately create a new Villager by choosing <br>them from a Bond on the Sheet, or by creating them from <br>scratch if the Scenario offers interesting ideas from among <br>the NPCs they have encountered. The Storyteller will <br>arrange for the new Villager to enter the Scene as soon as <br>possible.<br>Resting and experience<br>Villagers can ask for Interludes as described on page 11 of <br>the Broken Tales core book. <br>In the case of a Campaign, as with Hunters, it isn’t possible <br>to advance a Descriptor into a Specialization during <br>Scenario Interludes.<br>During the Scenario’s end Interlude, they recover every <br>Wound suffered and every Soma point spent. Experience <br>can be spent on:<br> ◆ Acquiring a new Gift: (a Villager can never have more <br>than 3 Gifts) 5 XP .<br> ◆ Evolve a Descriptor into a Specialization: Granting <br>1 Additional Success once per Scene, when the <br>Descriptor is used. 5 XP .<br> ◆ Obtain additional Soma for the following Scenario: <br>1 point per XP spent. Soma obtained in this way can <br>exceed the Villager’s normal maximum threshold.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":5300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241736,"modifiedTime":1783973241736,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"tbFmUsTXSBci6uBC","name":"Pagina 54","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 54</h2><p>53<br>Roll Age Wounds Gifts Soma Possessions<br>1 Child (up to 16 years) 1 1 6 +1<br>2-3 Y oung adult (up to 22 years) 2 2 4 +2<br>4-5 Adult (up to 42 years) 2 2 3 +3<br>6 Elderly (over 42 years) 1 2 5 +4<br>Creation of <br>the Villager<br>The creation of the Villager is different <br>from that of the Hunters and follows a <br>series of steps to establish the Villager’s <br>past and abilities.<br>2 - Role<br>Roll two dice to create one of the combinations available <br>from page 60, determining the Role assigned to <br>the Villager. Each Role provides guidance for creating <br>Descriptors, a specific Gift that can be selected, a list of <br>Possessions, and a Bond.<br>Optional rule: To give more choice to the Players, you can <br>have them roll twice and choose between the two results.<br>3 - Descriptors<br>Each Role provides a list of 3 possible options for initial <br>contact with the Broken Tales. These represent an event in <br>the past of the Villager that has led them to the fringes of <br>society, in search of what is hiding in the darkness. Each <br>Player rolls a die to determine the past event (or, as an <br>optional rule, chooses the one that inspires them the most) <br>and marks it on the Sheet along with the Role Keywords. <br>As a last option, each Player may decide to roll on the <br>Distinguishing Features table one or more times.<br>At this point, it is necessary to create the 2 Descriptors that <br>characterize the Villager:<br> ◆ The first Descriptor must concern the past of the <br>Villager, which must always contain elements of <br>darkness and a connection with the Broken Tales. The <br>Villager is an outcast, or, at least, someone who has <br>missed their shot at having a normal life. <br> ◆ The second Descriptor must be concerned with how <br>the Villager fights the Broken Tales and what abilities <br>they can rely on in their fight against darkness. This <br>Descriptor can be created by mutual agreement <br>between the Players so that a motivation that keeps the <br>group of Villagers together is outlined.<br>1 - Age<br>Roll a die to decide the Villager’s Age. Their age group will <br>determine how many Wounds they can endure, their Soma <br>point pool, and their number of Gifts and Possessions.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":5400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241736,"modifiedTime":1783973241736,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"pgfHNDpgAWDhFkkt","name":"Pagina 55","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 55</h2><p>54<br>4 - Bond<br>Each Role provides a list of three possible Bonds that <br>represent an NPC connected in some way to the Villager <br>who will worry about their fate. In game, if the Villager dies <br>or is knocked out for the rest of the Scenario, the Player <br>controlling them will be able to immediately create a new <br>Villager using one of the Bonds from a Sheet, either theirs <br>or another Player’s. This will immediately provide a new <br>protagonist with a valid and reasonable connection to the <br>Scenario. <br>During the Session, it’s possible to create additional Bonds <br>with the NPCs encountered. The Storyteller has the final say <br>on whether or not to create a Bond based on the purpose of <br>the NPC in the story.<br>Note: During the Session, it may happen that a Villager <br>forges a Bond with a Hunter of the Order. If this happens <br>and the Villager is eliminated, the Player can select the <br>Hunter and bring them into play. In the case of a Campaign, <br>the Hunter will exit the game at the end of the Scenario and <br>the Player will have to create a new Villager afterward.<br>Some suggestions for group motivation: At the service of an <br>agent of the Church / At the service of a Hunter of the Order <br>/ A company that solves mysteries for reward / A group of <br>devotees, sponsored by an anonymous client who presents <br>mysterious cases to be solved / At the service of a wealthy <br>nobleman who wants to manage mysteries without drawing <br>the attention of the Order.<br>Each Descriptor must have its own Drawback, as usual. <br>For the creation of the Descriptors, each Player can use as <br>inspiration the Keywords present in the Role, their contact <br>with the Broken Tales, any Distinguishing Features, and the <br>name of the Role itself which, in fact, gives a clear idea of <br>what the Villager does for a living.<br>DISTINGUISHING FEATURES<br>Roll 2 dice to cross the results in the table. Both <br>combinations are considered to obtain 2 Distinctive Traits <br>and decide which one to keep.<br>Roll 1 2 3 4 5 6<br>1 A visible scar. A trembling <br>voice. A constant hum. Bald. Sniffles. Thin fingers.<br>2<br>Eyes of different <br>colors.<br>The smell of an <br>animal.<br>The laughter of a <br>hyena. A severe gaze. Eyes of ice. Cold skin.<br>3<br>Skin riddled by <br>a disease. A limp. A grin. Barefoot. Cadaverous. Well-kept beard or hair.<br>4<br>Dirtied with <br>ash. Deep eye-circles. Missing two <br>fingers. Bright smile. Hairless. Smells of berries and <br>plants.<br>5 Aquiline nose.<br>A burn scar in <br>the shape of a <br>cross.<br>Prays to God. Sulky face. Chews tobacco. Impressive physique.<br>6 Golden tooth. Noisy breathing. Bandages on the <br>face. Albinism. Fragrance. Small frame.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":5500000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241736,"modifiedTime":1783973241736,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"r2FXBN7Oa2jEZJkB","name":"Pagina 56","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 56</h2><p>55<br>5 - Possessions<br>The available equipment will be much more important for <br>the Villagers than for Hunters. Their possessions confer <br>useful narrative possibilities to aid in Checks. They can also <br>supplement the use of resources such as Wounds and Soma, <br>which are generally very limited. Each Role provides a list <br>of possessions. The Player will add to those a number of <br>Possessions equal to the bonus in the Age Table, generating <br>them from the Table of Possessions.<br>Table of Possessions<br>Roll 2 dice, pick the first result for the vertical column <br>and the second for the horizontal row and cross-check the <br>result in the table. If you get the same combination twice, <br>or something repeats too much amongst party members, <br>reroll the dice. <br>ROLL 1 2 3 4 5 6<br>1<br>An old saber that <br>belonged to a <br>soldier.<br>An old, stubborn <br>mule.<br>A lighter and a few <br>candles. <br>A bottle of good <br>wine. A holy book.<br>A worn, old gun <br>with everything <br>you need for a few <br>shots.<br>2 A rag doll or a <br>carved wooden toy. Good quality snuff.<br>A noble coat of <br>arms won at a <br>game.<br>An oil lantern. An ash stake and a <br>garlic crown.<br>An old greatcoat <br>that is full of    <br>pockets.<br>3<br>A pocket watch <br>that is always ten <br>minutes behind.<br>A pair of fine boots. A rosary with beads <br>of wood and gold.<br>A beautiful jewel <br>recovered from a <br>corpse.<br>A slightly cracked <br>hand mirror.<br>A couple of old, <br>rusty knives. <br>4<br>An old, sick cat <br>that follows you <br>everywhere.<br>A finely carved <br>wooden mask.<br>A key with the <br>initials T.A.<br>A good walking <br>stick.<br>A pair of thick <br>leather gloves. A pitchfork. <br>5 A slingshot with a <br>bag of glass beads. A shovel. Cards and dice. <br>A book written by <br>the Marquis De <br>Sade.<br>A sharp stiletto. A bag full of fruit <br>and dried meat.<br>6 An old lute. A large copper <br>frying pan.<br>A heavy militia <br>halberd.<br>An old, locked <br>wooden box.<br>A silver jewel <br>obtained as a sign <br>of gratitude from <br>a Hunter of the <br>Order.<br>A Treasure of the <br>Order.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":5600000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241736,"modifiedTime":1783973241736,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"m2cJJLQ5WNzqtyRO","name":"Pagina 57","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 57</h2><p>56<br>6 - Gifts<br>Each Villager obtains the number of Gifts indicated in <br>the Age Table. Gifts can be chosen from the generic list in <br>addition to the exclusive Gift conferred by the Villager’s <br>Role. <br>GENERIC GIFTS<br>Accustomed to Horror:  Y ou have already fought the <br>horrors that hide in the shadows several times. Ignore the <br>penalties of the Horror of the Broken Tales rule. Reduce <br>your Soma cap by 1.<br>Animal Friend: An animal is faithful to you and follows <br>you wherever you go. Y our Animal Friend is a Minor NPC <br>under the control of the Storyteller, but it does its best to <br>help you. Create a Descriptor to characterize it.<br>Die Hard: It’s not easy to knock you out. Once per Scenario, <br>you can return at the end of a Scene after you suffered your <br>last Wound. Tell everyone how you survived and recovered <br>from your Wound.<br>Lucky: Y ou’ve done well more than once thanks to your <br>incredible luck. Once per Scene, when you don’t have any <br>Descriptor that fits the action you are doing, gain 3 Base <br>Successes.<br>Old Friendships:  When you arrive in a new place, <br>you can spend 1 Soma to create a Bond with an NPC (in <br>agreement with the Storyteller) that your Villager knows <br>and with whom you have some kind of relationship. The <br>nature of the Bond is decided by the Storyteller, or chosen <br>by you if you pay 1 additional Soma.<br>One-Time Remedies: Y ou know how to treat wounds <br>and ailments with simple means. Once per Scene, if you <br>take enough time to treat a wound, roll 1 die. 1-2: Y ou have <br>the wrong remedy and nothing happens. 3-4: Y ou do not <br>cure the problem, but you lift the spirits of your patient, <br>who recovers 1 Soma. 5-6: Y ou got it right and cured 1 of <br>your patient’s Wounds. Once per Scenario, you can decide <br>the outcome without rolling the dice.<br>Savings: Y ou have saved up a decent amount and use it <br>to the fullest. Once per Scene you can take out or procure <br>an object you need, simply by spending a portion of your <br>resources. Get 2 additional Possessions.<br>Sixth Sense: Y ou can easily sense when the situation is <br>going south. Receive 2 Additional Successes for the first <br>Defense Check you make against a sudden threat.<br>Status: Y ou are related to some important organization, <br>such as the Papacy or a noble family. Once per Scene, you <br>can appeal to your connections to receive 1 Additional <br>Success when you deal with or ask for favors from high-<br>ranking people. Once per Scene, you gain 1 Additional <br>Success when you threaten or manipulate low-ranking <br>people.<br>Veteran: Y ou have many years of experience on your <br>shoulders. Once per Scene, you can raise the Outcome of <br>an action by one rank. Y ou can also turn a Failure into an <br>Outcome with a Cost, but you must spend 1 Soma to do so.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":5700000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241736,"modifiedTime":1783973241736,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"4Mg4gwUVczjeQuUd","name":"Pagina 58","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 58</h2><p>57<br>Tips for the <br>Storyteller<br>A game in Village mode varies considerably in tones and <br>atmospheres compared to one involving the Hunters of <br>the Order, who can guide the situation and turn the tide of <br>each story with their skills. Villagers are the exact opposite: <br>ordinary people who have to endure the power of the Broken <br>Tales without really having the skills. Given the total reversal <br>of perspective, here is a list of useful tips to manage the <br>Session.<br>Use a Check only when you really need it<br>Villagers, compared to a Hunter, are definitely at a <br>disadvantage when it comes to Position and Defense Checks <br>because they will face increased Opposition Levels most of the <br>time. It is good to point out to the Players that changing the <br>narration can lead to avoiding a Check, and that studying <br>a situation might reduce the opponent’s Opposition <br>Level by 1 precious point. They don’t want to be heroes <br>and fewer Checks mean a smaller chance of getting <br>hurt. However, the Storyteller must not hesitate to <br>call for a Position or Defense Check when necessary. <br>They must strike mercilessly even using Wounds as <br>possible Costs. A Scenario played by Villagers must <br>always maintain a sense of hardship and insecurity.<br>Intelligence and preparation<br>Clever use of the Villagers’ Possessions must be <br>rewarded. Each Check is a situation of <br>potential danger, which is why it’s <br>a good habit to always pay attention to the “alternative” <br>plans of the Villagers. It’s rarely a good idea to face the most <br>dangerous situations head-on. A skirmish for a group of <br>Hunters could become a genuine slaughter for the Villagers. <br>Avoiding a problem often means solving it later, when you <br>have brought resources to spend.<br>Shrouding all in darkness<br>In this mode, the perception of the Broken Tales is very <br>different from the usual. The Hunters are aware and prepared <br>for the dark part of the world, while the Villagers have only <br>tasted a small sample of it in their past. Giving a different <br>vibe to the descriptions can significantly vary the overall <br>mood of the Session. A group of hungry werewolves is <br>simply a problem to be managed for a group of experienced <br>Hunters. To Villagers, they would be a nightmare made flesh. <br>The Horror of the Broken Tales rule serves to highlight this <br>aspect, which can be reinforced by the Storyteller giving <br>weight to descriptions and dwelling more on the monstrous <br>aspects of the Broken Tales and how different they are <br>from what is conceived as normality.<br>Hunters as NPCs<br>In addition to rewriting the background of the <br>Scenario to suit Villagers, a good option may be <br>to drop in one or more Hunters as NPCs. Even <br>if they have other things to do, Villagers may <br>ask the Hunter for help at certain times in the <br>Scenario and even create a Bond of some kind. <br>The presence of a Hunter in the Scenario can <br>act as an anchor of salvation for a distressed <br>group of Villagers.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":5800000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241736,"modifiedTime":1783973241736,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"41TVu8629QBWTAve","name":"Pagina 59","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 59</h2><p><em>Page has no extractable text. Use the local PDF linked on the first Journal page.</em></p>","markdown":""},"sort":5900000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241736,"modifiedTime":1783973241736,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"7yNVG91tG0HchM1q","name":"Pagina 60","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 60</h2><p>LIST OF ROLES<br>The Village</p>","markdown":""},"sort":6000000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241736,"modifiedTime":1783973241736,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"dldoJCi3i4w7Tm0Z","name":"Pagina 61","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 61</h2><p>60<br>List of Roles<br>11 Witch<br>You have received esoteric teachings from another witch. <br>You are aware of the existence of the occult world and that <br>strange beings move with evil intentions in the shadow of <br>civilization.<br>Keywords: Latent power / Herbs and poisons / Witch’s <br>gaze / Dark aura / Cats and owls / Blood / Cauldron / Little <br>house / Evil eye.<br>Possessions: Healing herbs and ointments / a small bag <br>/ bones of small animals / stones and crystals / a short, sharp <br>knife / a small animal that follows me everywhere.<br>Gift - Witch Rituals: Y ou know ancient rituals that have <br>been handed down to you by other witches. Y ou can use <br>each of these powers by spending 1 Soma. 1. Reading the <br>soul: Y ou are good at understanding other <br>people. When you interact with a subject <br>and can observe their behavior, the <br>Storyteller will reveal to you what emo-<br>tion they are feeling; 2. Witch remedy: <br>Y ou can apply herbs and ointments to so-<br>othe a Wound that your patient will reco-<br>ver at the end of the Scene; 3. Evil eye: <br>Y ou can leverage people’s superstition <br>by openly showing that you are a witch. <br>Anyone who is superstitious lowers <br>their Opposition Level by 1 in every <br>action against you until the end <br>of the Scene.<br>YOUR CONTACT WITH THE BROKEN TALES<br>1-2: A Hunter of the Order saved you from ending up at <br>the stake because they are also a witch. Y ou’re looking for <br>them to discover who they really are.<br>3-4: An emissary of the Church knows who you are and, <br>using blackmail, forces you to investigate the occult forces.<br>5-6: Y ou saw real magic in action at the hands of a strange <br>creature and now you want that power for yourself.<br>YOUR BOND<br>1-2: A daughter you had to abandon (Street Orphan).<br>3-4: The offspring of a relationship with a monster (Half <br>Fae).<br>5-6: Someone you saved thanks to your remedies (Penitent <br>Prelate).<br>12 Occult Researcher<br>You always had a passion for the occult arts, although this <br>could lead you straight to the gallows. You know there’s <br>a world beyond the one you see and you want to study it, <br>whatever the costs.<br>Keywords: Old books / Glasses / Certificates / Multilingual <br>/ Money / Strange objects / Sixth sense / Symbols / Brand <br>mark.<br>Possessions: Tomes about pagan rites / a small <br>magnifying glass / a sturdy stick / chalk and ashes / a good <br>lantern / an old idol purchased from a merchant of exotic <br>objects.<br>Gift - Occult Knowledge:  Y ou have studied strange vo-<br>lumes for a long time and possess uncommon knowledge. <br>Once per Scene, you can create a Descriptor that represents <br>dark knowledge or some ritual that you have learned throu-<br>gh research. Get 1 Additional Success in the first action <br>where you use your special knowledge. During a Scenario,</p>","markdown":""},"sort":6100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241736,"modifiedTime":1783973241736,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"t4ZLZk3J98xCEO9j","name":"Pagina 62","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 62</h2><p>61<br>whenever you put your hands on forbid-<br>den knowledge, you gain 2 XP .<br>YOUR CONTACT WITH THE <br>BROKEN TALES<br>1-2: Y ou own a book detailing the <br>whereabouts of a magical place, but the <br>page with the exact location has been torn <br>out.<br>3-4: A fellow student of yours disappeared <br>after they laid hands on an ancient, forbidden <br>volume.<br>5-6: Y ou have seen a monstrous creature <br>rage against your master and fear that <br>you are next.<br>YOUR BOND<br>1-2: An old friend who brings you forbidden treasures <br>(Grave Robber).<br>3-4: An old flame that now creates art deemed <br>blasphemous (Mad Artist).<br>5-6: Someone who provides you with exotic merchandise <br>(Smuggler).<br>13 Grave Robber<br>Whether they are doctors looking for corpses to practice on <br>or relatives dissatisfied with a poorly divided legacy, many <br>would rather not leave the dead to rest in their graves. You <br>wouldn’t blink at the idea of opening a tomb and facing what <br>it hides.<br>Keywords: Cold Blood / Silent / Climbing / Digging / <br>Slayer of the dead / Stink of dead / Light / Prayer / Keys.<br>Possessions: A shovel and a bucket / a long and heavy <br>leather coat / a truncheon / a bunch of old rusty keys / a dark <br>scarf to cover my face / rope and hammer.<br>Gift - Of Treasures and Tombs:  Y ou are used to dea-<br>ling with corpses. While in a basement or cemetery, you <br>receive 1 Additional Success for each action you take. <br>Once per Scene, if you lay hands on a treasure, you re-<br>gain 1 Soma.<br>YOUR CONTACT WITH THE BROKEN <br>TALES<br>1-2: Y ou went to clear a tomb, but something <br>had arrived before you and it wasn’t human.<br>3-4: Y ou have found a magical object inside <br>a tomb and the Order is hunting you down <br>for it.<br>5-6: Once, after opening a tomb, what you <br>found inside was still alive. Y ou closed it in a hurry, but <br>you’ll never forget what you saw.<br>YOUR BOND<br>1-2: A sloppy alchemist who owes you money (Alchemist).<br>3-4: An ambitious physician for whom you procure <br>corpses to dissect (Renegade Physician).<br>5-6: A blacksmith who refurbishes your <br>equipment (Blacksmith).</p>","markdown":""},"sort":6200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241737,"modifiedTime":1783973241737,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"eYXG5VvYUdx3J9xB","name":"Pagina 63","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 63</h2><p>62<br>14 Renegade Physician<br>It is not easy for a representative of the noble medical <br>art to practice on fresh bodies. Only the richest and <br>most highly ranked doctors have this privilege, but <br>the stupid social conventions won’t be enough to <br>quench your thirst for knowledge. By opposing the <br>darkness, you can shift attention from what you do <br>to something worse.<br>Keywords: Anatomist / Impassive / Cold / <br>Analysis / Accurate / Safe / Rare texts / Operating <br>tools / Wound.<br>Possessions: A scalpel and <br>tools to operate / a worn medical <br>bag / leather gloves and glasses / <br>anesthetic and disinfectant solutions / an old medical book / <br>needle and thread / some sharp knives.<br>Gift - Medical Art: Y ou know how to treat a wound and <br>take care of a patient. Once per Session, you can cure 1 <br>Wound from a subject by taking care of them. If you assist <br>them in the Scene in which they suffer their last Wound, <br>at the discretion of the Storyteller, you may prevent their <br>death. If you save a life with your care, you recover 1 Soma.<br>YOUR CONTACT WITH THE BROKEN TALES<br>1-2: Y ou met a very skilled doctor who used unconventional <br>methods. Be it magic or something else, you need to obtain <br>that knowledge.<br>3-4: Y ou have cured unnatural wounds and now you want <br>to know what kind of creatures can inflict them.<br>5-6: Y ou are looking for the discovery of the century <br>hidden among the shadows of superstition, to resell it and <br>get the funds you need for your own studies.<br>YOUR BOND<br>1-2: A butcher who let you practice on the meat in his shop <br>for years (Butcher).<br>3-4: A swordsman you treated for a major wound (Military <br>Veteran).<br>5-6: A sick person whom you have not yet been able to <br>heal (Afflicted).<br>15 Village Militia<br>You are dedicated to people’s safety, walking nightly patrols <br>to keep shadows and madmen at bay. You know how to use <br>a gun and you don’t fear the night, so you have decided to <br>patrol the borders of the normal world and fight what lies <br>beyond. <br>Keywords: Fighter / Attentive / Night watchman / Contacts <br>/ Benevolent / Leadership / Calm / Reassuring voice / Armor.<br>Possessions: A long halberd / a good lantern / a thick <br>cloak to keep the biting night cold at bay / dice and cards for <br>a game at the inn / a bottle of cheap wine.<br>Gift - Night Round: Y ou are skilled at moving and facing <br>dangers at night. Ignore any penalty resulting from the lack <br>of lighting. Furthermore, when you face danger at night, <br>you get 1 Additional Success to any Defense <br>Check you have to make.<br>YOUR CONTACT WITH THE <br>BROKEN TALES<br>1-2: Y ou are determined to put a face on <br>the strange shadows that move in the night <br>between the alleys of the city.<br>3-4: Y ou witnessed a murder, and those <br>involved were certainly not ordinary humans. <br>However, no one believes you.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":6300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241737,"modifiedTime":1783973241737,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"m1x5YBjbogQy2SKF","name":"Pagina 64","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 64</h2><p>63<br>5-6: Y ou live at night because you hate daylight and <br>human interactions. Y ou know there is something in you <br>that is connected to the realm of the dark.<br>YOUR BOND<br>1-2: A murderer you let escape because they killed in <br>the name of justice (Assassin).<br>3-4: A hunter with whom you shared patrols <br>at the edge of the city (Poacher).<br>5-6: A bizarre occultist for whom you act as a <br>bodyguard during their long nights of research <br>(Occult Researcher).<br>16 Military Veteran<br>You lived through the war as a hero, but <br>a bad wound forced you to retreat. You <br>now put your experience to good use by <br>selling it to the many simpletons <br>in the country who always need <br>someone who can handle danger <br>and who won’t quail at the first hint of devilry.<br>Keywords: Expert / Art of war / Leader / Hard to kill / <br>Memories / War-time loot / Discipline / Fame / Marksman.<br>Possessions: A rifle or a gun / a saber in its worn sheath <br>/ a memento of a comrade fallen on the battlefield / drugs <br>and alcohol to endure the specters of war / an old tricorn and <br>my uniform.<br>Gift - War Veteran:  Y ou have fought on many battle-<br>fields and you never lose your temper. Once per Scene, you <br>can use one of the following effects.  1. Aimed Shot: If <br>you take enough time to prepare, in case of an Outcome <br>with an Increment, you can inflict 1 additional Wound;  <br>2. Soldier’s Eye: If you take a few moments to study an <br>enemy, the Storyteller will reveal one of their Gifts that you <br>do not yet know of; 3. Maintain Position:  Y ou gain 2 <br>Additional Successes at a Defense Check.<br>YOUR CONTACT WITH THE BROKEN TALES<br>1-2: Y our war wound was inflicted by a being not of this <br>world and now you want your revenge.<br>3-4: Y ou’ve been in the service of a good patron for a long <br>time and his sudden disappearance doesn’t seem right to <br>you. Y ou know he was courting a strange woman that <br>many accuse of being a witch.<br>5-6: Y ou want to enter the ranks of the Order and to do <br>so you must win a fight against something unnatural.<br>YOUR BOND<br>1-2: A member of the village militia you have trained <br>(Village Militia).<br>3-4: An old comrade, now a deserter, whom you <br>helped escape (Deserter).<br>5-6: A strange woman you served for a short time <br>before she shamefully ran away without paying you <br>(Identity Thief).</p>","markdown":""},"sort":6400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241737,"modifiedTime":1783973241737,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"DkaQ98i9niGMFET9","name":"Pagina 65","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 65</h2><p>64<br>22 Blacksmith <br>You have learned a good trade and <br>work iron for an almost-decent <br>wage. You handle weapons with <br>skill because you’ve learned to test <br>their sturdiness. Over time, <br>you have discovered how to <br>forge weapons that the Church <br>uses to fight monsters and <br>aberrations, and that is why you <br>have decided to put your knowledge at the <br>service of those who fight against the darkness. <br>Keywords: Strength / Weapons / Metal / Fire / Resistance <br>/ Eye for business / Chain / Keys / Burn. <br>Possessions: A heavy hammer / tinder and tools to light <br>a good fire / a heavy leather apron / a finely forged weapon <br>/ a homemade ointment against burns / pliers, spikes, and <br>other work tools.<br>Gift - Craftsman: Y ou are skilled in working metals and <br>have extensive knowledge of weapons. Once per Scene, if <br>you take enough time, you can repair any object that has <br>metal in it. With enough time and the necessary resour -<br>ces (decided in agreement with the Storyteller), you can <br>modify or create weapons that can harm the Broken Ta-<br>les. Create a Descriptor that represents the specific quality <br>infused into the weapon. Whoever wields your creation <br>gains 1 Additional Success for each action in which the <br>Descriptor is relevant. <br>YOUR CONTACT WITH THE BROKEN <br>TALES<br>1-2: Y ou have forged a special weapon for <br>a member of the Order who, however, has <br>not returned. What happened to them? <br>3-4: When you beat the burning metal, strange voices <br>come from the tongues of fire and rumble in your mind, <br>leaving you restless.<br>5-6: Y ou have forged a strange knife that you fear will be <br>used for dark rites. Y ou can’t shake that feeling of guilt.<br>YOUR BOND<br>1-2: An old acquaintance who has become quite a good <br>friend, and to whom you have supplied black market <br>weapons (Assassin).<br>3-4: Y our apprentice or your teacher (Blacksmith).<br>5-6: A soldier who pays well for repairs (Military Veteran).<br>23 Butcher<br>You have learned a good trade and practiced it with <br>commitment and dedication. Working with meat requires <br>a strong stomach, which has made you less fearful of death <br>and gore. That is why you are inclined to face the darkness; <br>you know for certain that everything that has a body can be <br>butchered.<br>Keywords: Strength / Clean cut / Blood / Meat / Appraising <br>the goods / Accurate blow / Accustomed to blood / Skinning <br>/ Cooking.<br>Possessions: A cleaver and butcher’s knives / knitted <br>gloves to protect my hands / a long leather gown / a <br>small bag with offal and processing waste.<br>Gift - Butcher:  Y ou know how to cut meat <br>and kill a beast quickly. When you reach <br>an Outcome with an Increment, you <br>can spend the Increment to inflict 1 <br>additional Wound, but only against <br>living targets. If you want to, the</p>","markdown":""},"sort":6500000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241737,"modifiedTime":1783973241737,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"slCdflG8veb2nXdg","name":"Pagina 66","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 66</h2><p>65<br>Wounds you inflict will be especially bloody. They leave <br>traces and are difficult to conceal until they are treated.<br>YOUR CONTACT WITH THE BROKEN TALES<br>1-2: A mysterious customer made you butcher the body of <br>a fawn, but you’re not sure it really was an animal… <br>3-4: When you sink your cleaver into flesh you feel a fit <br>of strange anger grow in you, along with the desire to shed <br>more blood.<br>5-6: A skilled hunter brings you a lot of game, too much, <br>way too much. How can they be so good?<br>YOUR BOND<br>1-2: A good friend who brings you their cattle (Shepherd).<br>3-4: A customer you have been working with for a long <br>time (Poacher).<br>5-6: A weird girl to whom you sell scraps and offal <br>(Alchemist). <br>24 Shepherd<br>You are used to a simple, unforgiving life, always spent on the <br>move with your flock in search of a good pasture. You learned <br>early on that the perfect hiding place for the Broken Tales is <br>outside of towns, at the edge of civilization. Even if you are a <br>simple soul, your knowledge of nature can make a difference <br>in protecting humanity.<br>Keywords: Night / Long Walk / Careful / Clubbing / <br>Protecting the herd / Singing / Forest / Simple Soul / Resistant.<br>Possessions: A shepherd’s crook / a cloak and winter <br>clothes / a large bottle / two trusted dogs / an ocarina that I <br>play to keep myself company / a sharp knife.<br>Gift - Seeking the Path: When you lead your flock, you <br>are accustomed to always finding the right path. When you <br>arrive at a place, the Storyteller will always tell you the best <br>way in and out, even if exits are camouflaged and hidden <br>from a common eye. Receive 1 Additional Success when <br>you move in or out of a place.<br>YOUR CONTACT WITH THE BROKEN TALES<br>1-2: Y ou are aware that something is watching you, hidden <br>among the brush, when traveling with your flock through <br>the woods.<br>3-4: Y ou have found some of your flock slain, completely <br>bled out but with no other wounds.<br>5-6: Y ou are convinced that a strange creature has hidden <br>within your flock, using it as a safe means of traveling.<br>YOUR BOND<br>1-2: A fugitive whom you escorted to the village for some <br>money, passing them off as a shepherd (Deserter).<br>3-4: A beautiful and strange person you fell in love with <br>(Witch).<br>5-6: A childhood friend of yours who seems to talk to <br>animals (Half Fae).</p>","markdown":""},"sort":6600000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241737,"modifiedTime":1783973241737,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"yTlYjdC2fMJNky8E","name":"Pagina 67","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 67</h2><p>66<br>25 Smuggler<br>You’re a pirate and, for <br>governments, one of the worst <br>scourges of the 18th century. <br>You have chosen a life of raids <br>and freedom, always on the <br>edge between a lucky assault <br>and ending up on the gallows. <br>Whether it’s to be pardoned <br>or to get a hefty commission, <br>you have realized that hunting <br>down monsters can be very <br>lucrative. <br>Keywords: Arrest / Merciless <br>/ Gunman / Low blow / <br>Treasure / Wanted / Companion / Navigator / Gambling.<br>Possessions: A sword / a series of knives / a bag with <br>various precious items, the result of my raids / a good bottle <br>of liquor / an old gun that often jams.<br>Gift - Raid: Y ou are skilled at looting and using gang tacti-<br>cs. Receive 1 Additional Success when you act to overwhelm <br>an enemy and have at least one teammate supporting you. <br>Once per Scene, you can spend 1 Soma to redirect a threat <br>towards a companion in your immediate vicinity.<br>YOUR CONTACT WITH THE BROKEN TALES<br>1-2: A prized object was cursed, leading to the death of all <br>who possessed it. <br>3-4: A member of the Order is on your trail and <br>seems to be moving through the shadows.<br>5-6: During one of your voyages, you can swear <br>you saw a siren, and that memory haunts you.<br>YOUR BOND<br>1-2: A former companion who has now settled in the city <br>(Thief).<br>3-4: A child you abandoned (Street Orphan).<br>5-6: A rich eccentric to whom you bring the strangest <br>things you find (Occult Researcher).<br>26 Thief<br>You make a living day after day, stealing what you can. <br>What was once a necessity merely to eat is now your private <br>rebellion against an uncaring world. Living on the fringes, <br>you have glimpsed secrets and hidden treasures that you can <br>exploit and resell.<br>Keywords: Stealth / Burglary / Dexterous hands / Evaluate <br>/ Escape / Secret passage / Stun / Steal / Friendships.<br>Possessions: A heavy club / burglar tools / a long knife / <br>a hood to cover my face / two large bags / a beautiful jewel <br>that I stole from a rich man / chalk and stones to leave signs <br>for my gang.<br>Gift - Rogue: Y ou can spend 1 Soma to put your thieving <br>skills to good use, choose from: 1. Having a small object <br>vanish (even if worn by someone) without arousing any <br>suspicion. Particularly powerful subjects can require a Po-<br>sition Check; 2. Opening doors and locks with extreme <br>speed and without damaging them; 3. Receiving 3 Addi-<br>tional Successes to a Po-<br>sition Check you make <br>to escape a threat.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":6700000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241737,"modifiedTime":1783973241737,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"R3FtkVaa5bsVm8NT","name":"Pagina 68","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 68</h2><p>67<br>YOUR CONTACT WITH THE BROKEN TALES<br>1-2: Moving through the poor neighborhoods of the city, <br>you noticed a strange creature disguising itself as an elderly <br>beggar.<br>3-4: Y ou stole an object from a witch and now she haunts <br>you in your dreams.<br>5-6: Y ou know that the rumors of a murderer feeding on <br>human flesh in the slums of the city are real.<br>YOUR BOND<br>1-2: A gang mate (Thief).<br>3-4: A guard you’ve bribed several times to get away <br>(Village Militia).<br>5-6: A gravedigger to whom you occasionally lend a hand <br>for a share of the loot (Grave Robber).<br>33 Identity Thief <br>In a world where you are what you say you are, you’ve <br>learned to impersonate others, and you know the fools out <br>there are ready to be fooled. You’ve forgotten who you really <br>are to embrace a life of feigned success and well-constructed <br>lies. You are attracted to magic and darkness because they <br>allow you to reach ever greater success.<br>Keywords: Counterfeit / Acting / Makeup / Nerve / <br>Warm / Fugitive / Opportunist / Pleasant / Liar.<br>Possessions: Clothes of different shapes / a small bag <br>with some coins / falsified documents/ a fake noble ring <br>/ a saber with a military coat of arms / a valuable mask <br>/ perfumes and makeup / a pair of glasses / a pair of <br>exotic objects to show off.<br>Gift - They Don’t Know Who I Am:  Y ou can spend 1 <br>Soma to disguise yourself and pass for someone else. Crea-<br>te a Descriptor that represents your disguise and your new <br>identity. Y ou gain 1 Additional Success when you try to de-<br>ceive someone by using your fake identity.<br>YOUR CONTACT WITH THE BROKEN TALES<br>1-2: Y ou took the identity of a wealthy noble, only to find <br>out that they had signed a pact with a dark entity.<br>3-4: Y ou have been forced to impersonate the role of the <br>victim to attract a monster, and this experience has marked <br>you forever.<br>5-6: Y ou met another impostor like you, but they could <br>change their appearance with magic. Y ou want that power.<br>YOUR BOND<br>1-2: An eccentric painter for whom you have modeled <br>several times (Mad Artist).<br>3-4: An old friend who knows your true identity <br>(Smuggler).<br>5-6: An acquaintance you helped escape from the clutches <br>of the Church (Witch).</p>","markdown":""},"sort":6800000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241737,"modifiedTime":1783973241737,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"DNIJgIB3x7StOaPb","name":"Pagina 69","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 69</h2><p>68<br>34 Deserter<br>You served the army for several years, <br>earning respect and esteem. Then, <br>something in you broke and all you <br>wanted was to escape from your life <br>of war and violence. But it is not easy <br>to abandon your comrades without <br>being accused of cowardice. Doing <br>the dirty work by hunting down the <br>Broken Tales is a good way to keep <br>out-of-sight, as it’s easy to remain <br>hidden when you hunt secrets.<br>Keywords: Fugitive / Soldier / Unscrupulous / Stolen <br>weapons / Expert / Determined / Low profile / Wanted / <br>Disciplined.<br>Possessions: A rifle or a gun / a saber in its worn sheath / <br>old and worn clothes to look like a common traveler / a stolen <br>military document / supplies / a small trench shovel.<br>Gift - Survival Instinct:  Y ou are used to coping with <br>adversity. Once per Session, you can ignore the first Wound <br>you receive. When you do this, you receive 2 Additional <br>Successes to any attack you make against those who at-<br>tacked you.<br>YOUR CONTACT WITH THE BROKEN TALES<br>1-2: Y our regiment was dismantled by a creature <br>that, whatever it was, looked nothing like a <br>human.<br>3-4: Y ou were convicted of murdering <br>an officer who, in fact, was a monstrous <br>creature in disguise.<br>5-6: Y ou are haunted by nightmares in <br>which a war is fought at the gates of hell.<br>YOUR BOND<br>1-2: A poor outcast who, however, has helped you without <br>regret (Afflicted).<br>3-4: An old friend who gave you shelter in a time of need <br>(Renegade Physician).<br>5-6: A companion with whom you fled (Deserter).<br>35 Assassin<br>After a lifetime of hardship and poverty, you’ve lost all <br>scruples, and taking a life doesn’t upset you anymore. The <br>law of the wild is the only one you live by, and you are paid <br>handsomely for this quality. As a professional living on the <br>fringes of society, you have soon learned that “special” targets <br>like the Broken Tales have generous bounties on their heads.<br>Keywords: Shadow / Slaying / Stalking / Merciless / <br>Watcher / Fast / Shadow in the crowd / Poison / Quick blade.<br>Possessions: A sharp knife / a garrotte / a long dark cloak <br>/ a cloth mask to cover my face / an easily concealable small <br>crossbow / a few doses of poison and sleeping pills.<br>Gift - Assassin: When you surprise a target with a vio-<br>lent action, inflict 1 additional Wound. Receive 1 Additio-<br>nal Success when you move or hide using the shadows to <br>your advantage.<br>YOUR CONTACT WITH THE BROKEN TALES<br>1-2: Y ou were commissioned to assassinate someone, <br>but when you stabbed your target, it disappeared before <br>your eyes.<br>3-4: Y ou found a strange book full of magic formulas on <br>the body of a victim.<br>5-6: Sometimes, you wake up feeling like you have been <br>wandering all night and you are afraid you have hurt <br>someone.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":6900000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241737,"modifiedTime":1783973241737,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"G8ULmws34y3IfcH3","name":"Pagina 70","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 70</h2><p>69<br>YOUR BOND<br>1-2: A kind-hearted person whose love you murdered, <br>and whom you now help to alleviate your own guilt <br>(Penitent Prelate).<br>3-4: A bounty hunter on your trail (Military Veteran).<br>5-6: A renegade physician who has commissioned many <br>jobs from you (Renegade Physician).<br>36 Penitent Prelate<br>You are a man of the Church and faith has guided <br>your life. Unfortunately, you have committed a sin of <br>which you are ashamed, and the Church has driven <br>you away so that you may find your redemption. <br>Fighting the Broken Tales is the best way to prove that you <br>are still worthy of God’s grace.<br>Keywords: Faith / Preacher / Punishment / Wisdom / <br>Suspicious / Charity / Righteous Words / Church Authority <br>/ Blessing.<br>Possessions: A cassock / a bowl for offerings / a rosary of <br>wood and gold / a walking stick / a holy text / a bag of coins <br>/ parchments, pen, and inkwell.<br>Gift - Strength of the Faith:  In your presence, peo-<br>ple’s hearts are strengthened against the darkness. When a <br>Broken Tale reveals itself, you can spend 1 Soma to cancel <br>the effect of the Horror of the Broken Tales’ rule. Only tho-<br>se who have faith in God or hold you in high esteem <br>can take advantage of this Gift by relying on your <br>words. Faith in God protects you, granting you 1 <br>Additional Success when you defend yourself <br>from a manifestly supernatural threat.<br>YOUR CONTACT WITH THE <br>BROKEN TALES<br>1-2: The sin you committed is linked to a <br>dark and elusive figure, so you could not <br>prove your innocence. <br>3-4: Y ou have visions in which the Saints <br>speak to you of dark presences living on the <br>fringes of society.<br>5-6: Y ou have stolen a sacred text in which <br>you are convinced you can find the map for <br>a secret place run by the Order.<br>YOUR BOND<br>1-2: An old friend with whom you <br>spend your evenings drinking wine <br>and talking about theology (Occult Researcher).<br>3-4: A thug who has paid you well to access the cemetery <br>(Grave Robber).<br>5-6: Y our superior who believes in your innocence <br>(Penitent Prelate).<br>44 Afflicted<br>You have survived a terrible disease and your body bears <br>its indelible marks. Between superstition and fear, society <br>has marginalized you, calling you a plague-bearer. Perhaps, <br>through the Broken Tales and their power, you could find a <br>cure for your condition.<br>Keywords: Fear / Resilient / Anger / Insensitive to <br>pain / Nothing to lose / Dirty / Keep your distance / <br>Corpse-carrier / Sick.<br>Possessions: Old and dirty clothes / a heavy <br>winter cloak / bandages covering my hands <br>and face / soothing herbs / a few charity <br>coins / a stick to defend myself.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":7000000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241737,"modifiedTime":1783973241737,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Fy9ajU5tjiSXodFa","name":"Pagina 71","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 71</h2><p>70<br>Gift - Repulsive:  Ordinary people fear you and they <br>avoid approaching you. If you reveal the ravages of your <br>illness, any opponent who is not a Broken Tale will avoid <br>attacking you directly except to defend themselves. Y ou can <br>move through others without fear that they would block <br>your path and receive 2 Additional Successes to intimidate <br>or scare them by menacing them with contagious diseases. <br>During the Scene in which you manifest this Gift, you can-<br>not have positive social interactions with someone who is <br>scared by your condition.<br>YOUR CONTACT WITH THE BROKEN TALES<br>1-2: Someone saved you from death by halting the <br>progression of your illness with the touch of their hand. <br>3-4: Y ou are convinced that your illness derives from a <br>curse and that, with the help of a witch, you could be cured.<br>5-6: Cast out for your monstrous appearance, you <br>discovered that true monsters are hiding among the poor <br>and desperate.<br>YOUR BOND<br>1-2: A friend who meets you outside the city and asks no <br>question (Shepherd).<br>3-4: A kind woman who is not afraid of your illness and <br>tries to soothe it (Witch).<br>5-6: A group of orphans who are grateful to you for <br>defending them from a bully (Street Orphan).<br>45 Mad Artist<br>You have dedicated your whole life to art, earning a living <br>in salons and wealthy churches. However, you soon began to <br>feel a strange attraction for macabre art and for the darker <br>corners of the human mind. Your creations now being <br>beyond understanding, you were relegated to the limbo of <br>cursed artists.<br>Keywords: Madness / Eye of the artist / Capture the <br>details / Eccentric / Artist’s charm / Intuition / Charismatic <br>/ Drawing / Art.<br>Possessions: Paints and canvases / a small knife / colored <br>chalk / one or two doses of drugs / some jewels taken as <br>payment for a job / a small, unfinished painting that lacks <br>the spark of true inspiration.<br>Gift - Genius and Madness: Y ou see the world through <br>a different lens, and this allows you to see things ordinary <br>people cannot even imagine. Y our gaze cannot be deceived <br>by the magic or powers of the Broken Tales. When a Broken <br>Tale acts, the Storyteller will clearly tell you that something <br>seems wrong to your piercing gaze, giving you a useful clue. <br>Y our intuition may allow you to grasp a detail that no one <br>has noticed or to have specific information that allows you <br>to unveil the supernatural. Y ou gain 1 Additional Success <br>on the first action you take using your intuition.<br>YOUR CONTACT WITH THE BROKEN TALES<br>1-2: Strange creatures that move at the edges of civilization <br>have always inhabited your dreams. In your paintings, you <br>give life to these dreams, making anyone who looks at them <br>uneasily. <br>3-4: Y ou made a painting, a completely black canvas that <br>a strange client commissioned. The client complimented <br>you on your work, before taking it and vanishing before <br>your eyes.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":7100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241737,"modifiedTime":1783973241737,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"YTmO2Rr6RYVE59Im","name":"Pagina 72","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 72</h2><p>71<br>5-6: Y ou are obsessed with a picture where, when you look <br>at it, elements seem to change every day.<br>YOUR BOND<br>1-2: A fellow student who is now a researcher and provides <br>you with quality colors (Alchemist).<br>3-4: A rich noble who often comes to see your works, but <br>then never buys anything (Identity Thief).<br>5-6: A raid partner who provided you with work in dire <br>times (Thief).<br>46 Poacher<br>You love the silence of the forest more than the noise of the <br>city, but you are still a person and occasionally need human <br>contact. You are proud to live by what you hunt, and your <br>skill is your pride. You’ve decided to hunt down monsters for <br>the prestige that prey of that caliber could bring you. <br>Keywords: Archer / Traps / Forest / Smell / Ambush / <br>Track / Capture / Hunt / Trophy.<br>Possessions: A valuable bow / a quiver and arrows <br>/ small traps for animals / my faithful hunting animal / a <br>pickaxe and everything I need to sleep outdoors / supplies <br>and water / chalk with which to mark the trees / a pair of <br>sharp hunting knives.<br>Gift - Poacher: Once you find your prey you won’t let it <br>escape. Once per Scene, you can declare that a target will <br>be your prey. Y ou gain 1 Additional Success to any Check <br>attempting to knock them out, capture them, or follow <br>their tracks. Y our loyal hunting animal can always spend its <br>action to give 1 Additional Success to your Defense Checks. <br>If you reach an Outcome with a Cost, however, your faithful <br>companion will have to deal with the threat in your place.<br>YOUR CONTACT WITH THE BROKEN TALES<br>1-2: Y ou’ve been hunting a monster hiding in the forest for <br>years. Nobody believes you, but you know what you saw. <br>3-4: Some farmer families behave strangely, and you know <br>that whatever they leave in the woods once a month is not <br>a sacrificial goat.<br>5-6: Y ou are devoted to nature and are convinced that <br>plants have a conscience of their own.<br>YOUR BOND<br>1-2: An old shepherd with whom you share cold nights <br>outdoors (Shepherd).<br>3-4: A strange girl who lives alone in the woods (Half Fae).<br>5-6: A butcher to whom you sell your catches (Butcher).</p>","markdown":""},"sort":7200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241737,"modifiedTime":1783973241737,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"CCxxerh8swGa0RnF","name":"Pagina 73","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 73</h2><p>72<br>55 Street Orphan<br>You were born in the gutter and never knew your real parents. <br>You soon realized that you would be spared few hardships in <br>this life. You live day to day, trying to endure the oppression <br>of the rich, and in the darkness of the slums, you have seen <br>creatures that are not human. You have nothing to lose, so <br>you’re not afraid of what you might discover.<br>Keywords: Gang / Safe passage / Escape / Beggar / <br>Disappear in the crowd / Pickpocketing / Innocent look / <br>Aggressive / Free spirit.<br>Possessions: A slingshot and a bag of stones / a wooden <br>club that I know how to use well / a pair of broken shoes / a <br>key to an unknown door / a whistle that I use as a rallying <br>signal for my gang.<br>Gift - Gang:  Y ou can rely on some of your teammates. <br>Create 2 teammates and assign each one a Descriptor that <br>indicates a quality and a flaw. If they are present in the Sce-<br>ne, you can use their Descriptors as your own. Once per <br>Scenario, if you suffer your last Wound, your gang will pull <br>you out of trouble and take you to safety. Y ou can return in <br>the next Scene with 1 Wound healed. In gameplay terms, <br>your teammates are Minor NPCs with 1 Wound.<br>YOUR CONTACT WITH THE BROKEN TALES<br>1-2: Y ou escaped a slave trader with <br>a monstrous face. Y ou’re sure they are <br>not human.<br>3-4: Y ou’ve seen a gang of cultists <br>wandering the slums and kidnapping <br>innocent young people for some dark <br>ritual.<br>5-6: Y ou have a conspicuous mark <br>on your face, which identifies you as <br>an outcast. Y ou only know that the <br>Church has persecuted your parents and that your origins <br>are a mystery.<br>YOUR BOND<br>1-2: An old lady who often leaves you some food on the <br>windowsill (Butcher).<br>3-4: A shady figure you helped elude the guards (Assassin).<br>5-6: A guard who uses you as an informant (Village <br>Militia).<br>56 Alchemist<br>You are a scholar who has <br>abandoned the mundane <br>sciences in search of <br>something greater. Thanks <br>to ancient texts, you excel <br>in alchemy and seek the <br>secret of the philosopher’s <br>stone. The truth that has <br>eluded you lie hidden in <br>the shadows of the Broken <br>Tales.<br>Keywords: Chemist / Scholar / Evaluate / Strange devices / <br>Helper / Strange potions / Analyze / Explosive / Smoke.<br>Possessions: Books and ancient scrolls / tools for <br>experiments / a short, sharp sword / vials with <br>all kinds of substances / stones and pieces of <br>coal / a lighter and oil / a large work tunic. <br>Gift – Alchemy:  Y ou can use your know-<br>ledge and create alchemical reactions. If you <br>take the time to mix, spend 1 Soma and cho-<br>ose from the following effects. 1. Y ou create <br>thick smoke that fills an area with a radius of <br>30 feet; 2. Create a corrosive substance that</p>","markdown":""},"sort":7300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241737,"modifiedTime":1783973241737,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"yVrdpd9GjnYvYZI0","name":"Pagina 74","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 74</h2><p>73<br>slowly erodes metals and other materials. If poured on a <br>living target, roll 1 die: 1-2 nothing happens, 3-5 it inflicts 1 <br>Wound, 5-6 it inflicts 2 Wounds; 3. Create a colored pow-<br>der that can reveal traces and residues of other substances; <br>4. Light a fire even on unsuitable surfaces such as water <br>and glass.<br>YOUR CONTACT WITH THE BROKEN TALES<br>1-2: In one of your books, you read of the miraculous <br>deeds of a powerful wizard and alchemist. Y ou need to find <br>them and have them teach you their secrets. <br>3-4: The Church has involved you in an investigation <br>and, thanks to your gifts, you have discovered traces of an <br>ungodly creature.<br>5-6: Y ou have found the ancient formula to create the <br>Golem, but the last part is indecipherable, and you do not <br>know how to complete the ritual.<br>YOUR BOND<br>1-2: An old friend who provides you with rare items and <br>substances (Smuggler).<br>3-4: A trusted acquaintance who forged your alchemical <br>tools (Blacksmith).<br>5-6: A poor sick person who you use as guinea pigs for <br>experiments (Afflicted).<br>66 Half Fae<br>You feel uncomfortable <br>among people, while the <br>wilderness feels like a <br>much nicer place. Your <br>strange appearance leads <br>others to distrust you in a <br>way that makes you feel <br>not completely human. <br>In the Broken Tales, you <br>may be looking for that <br>part of you that you can’t <br>find among ordinary people. <br>Keywords: Forest Spirit / Animal Friends / Unearthly <br>appearance / Sixth Sense / Mutation / Unnatural Charm / <br>Fleeing / House in the Woods / Fairy Blood.<br>Possessions: A stick that I found in the woods / a large <br>cloak with which to hide from the sight of others / stones with <br>strange engravings that I found by chance / a wooden mask <br>that a poacher gave me / a small animal that follows me as a <br>trusted companion.<br>Gift - Fae Blood:  Y our body and appearance have some <br>special qualities to them. Create a Descriptor that represen-<br>ts your mutation, such as Luminescent Eyes or Pointy Ears. <br>Non-human creatures (including animals) never consider <br>you a threat and will be well disposed towards you, not <br>targeting you for their actions if you do not threaten them <br>first. Y ou can communicate crudely with animals, plants, <br>and non-human creatures.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":7400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241737,"modifiedTime":1783973241737,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Lb0agR27ux1EDvcb","name":"Pagina 75","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 75</h2><p>74<br>YOUR CONTACT WITH THE BROKEN TALES<br>1-2: A Hunter of the Order has discovered you and clearly <br>told you not to be caught again if you do not want your life <br>to take a bad turn.<br>3-4: Strange creatures live in the forest, but they do not <br>reveal themselves to you, perhaps because they fear your <br>human part. <br>5-6: Y ou have seen a group of Hunters of the Order capture <br>and kill someone like you. They called them fae offspring.<br>YOUR BOND<br>1-2: A weird artist who loves to use you as a model for their <br>paintings (Mad Artist).<br>3-4: A young hunter with whom you have become friends <br>(Poacher).<br>5-6: A Hunter of the Order who kept an eye on you. <br>Special: With this result, you can bring into play and use a <br>Hunter of the Order for the rest of the Scenario.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":7500000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241738,"modifiedTime":1783973241738,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"g0vMnZEf3GDWHhfl","name":"Pagina 76","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 76</h2><p>Spoiler<br>! Warning !<br>Go no further if you don’t want to lose your way... <br>This part of the book presents the complete rules to introduce the material in The Broken Ones in <br>a game Campaign.<br>If you want to experience Broken Tales as a player, stop here. After all... would you peek at the <br>last page of a novel you are reading?<br>75</p>","markdown":""},"sort":7600000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241738,"modifiedTime":1783973241738,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"rMTUkAd2KnQpDjQE","name":"Pagina 77","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 77</h2><p>76<br>Like the Hunters from the Core Book, the following <br>list offers issues related to the new Hunters that can be used <br>as Events in the Campaign.<br>Alice of Other Worlds<br>1-2: A former patient from Wonder seeks revenge against <br>the Director. <br>3-4: One of Wonder’s former patients has built a hospital in <br>a grotesque attempt to reproduce Alice’s therapies. <br>5-6: A small village is ravaged by disease without a doctor <br>to take care of it.<br>Beauty and her Beast<br>1-2: A traveling circus is determined to acquire the Beast. <br>3-4: Amelia has been friends with Bellina since they were <br>both innocent children and still sees her as that pure child. <br>5-6: A capricious witch, skilled in creating and shattering all <br>kinds of bonds, gets in the way.<br>Bloodwhite<br>1-2: Karina, Ottone’s sister, is seeking revenge. <br>3-4: An influential cardinal catches Bianca’s gaze and sees <br>divine purity in her. The powerful clergyman is convinced <br>that Bianca should take vows and inspire the whole Church <br>with her purity. <br>5-6: A monster-slayer is on the trail of the “creature” that <br>used to terrorize Lohr.<br>Carlo the Living Puppet<br>1-2: An unscrupulous sorcerer turns children into donkeys <br>to sell them at the livestock market. <br>3-4: Fire-eater the Puppeteer has his eye on Carlo. <br>5-6: The two doctors, Luigi Corvo and Donato Civetta, <br>claim they can cure any disease and bring even the dead back <br>to life.<br>The Broken Ones during a Campaign</p>","markdown":""},"sort":7700000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241738,"modifiedTime":1783973241738,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"SUafvANGtljKfF3x","name":"Pagina 78","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 78</h2><p>77<br>Hatta Carter<br>1-2: An automaton gains consciousness but refuses to coo-<br>perate with Hatta. <br>3-4: A city is upset by one of Hatta’s old, crazy designs. <br>5-6: A young lady seems frozen in time.<br>Iskra the Young Wolf<br>1-2: A pack of wolves who left Greskar’s group sows panic <br>across villages, preying on weak children. They are fouling the <br>honor of the wolves Iskra grew up with. <br>3-4: Irina, a young girl with whom Iskra used to play all the <br>time in the village, recognizes a friend she thought was dead. <br>5-6: A wolf pup has been captured by a group of men who <br>enjoy torturing him. <br>Morgana of the Lake<br>1-2: A young woman wishes to forget her husband and son’s <br>death. <br>3-4: Rumor says there is a magical lake where one can see <br>their past memories by looking at one’s reflection in the wa-<br>ters. <br>5-6: A young woman claims to be called Morgana and appe-<br>ars identical to the Hunter who now serves the Order. <br>OZena the Afflicted<br>1-2: Dose survived Smaragd’s destruction and is now in se-<br>arch of his love, Dorothea. <br>3-4: A villager, who benefited from Henkle’s magic without <br>any drawbacks, has fled Smaragd. <br>5-6: Hilda, the witch Helga’s helper, is seeking revenge for the <br>death of her mistress.<br>Sherazade the Weaver of Tales<br>1-2: Sinbad the Traveler of a Thousand Seas recognizes She-<br>razade and asks her to tell him a story with him as the pro-<br>tagonist. <br>3-4: An actress has grown jealous of Sharazade’s bravery <br>and accuses her of blasphemy, twisting the details of stories <br>to incriminate her. <br>5-6: A good man at death’s door would like to be told a story <br>he remembers fondly from his childhood.<br>Talia the Sleeper<br>1-2: A strange woman daydreams, communicating with Ta-<br>lia. <br>3-4: A servant from Stegeborg survived the castle’s downfall <br>and is now seeking revenge. <br>5-6: A powerful drug with devastating side effects is able to <br>wake Talia for a few hours.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":7800000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241738,"modifiedTime":1783973241738,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"1CRoPocCpoxUQpCg","name":"Pagina 79","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 79</h2><p>78<br>The Gang of Three Pigs<br>1-2: They encounter a mansion belonging to an old mage, <br>said to be impregnable. <br>3-4: A group of Pig Heads fled from Whitehaven and now <br>uses the power of the God Under the Mine to carry out raids. <br>5-6: A group of frightened miners tells of a huge snake head <br>they have discovered in the bowels of the earth.<br>The Knight with a Hundred Heads<br>1-2: A former soldier who believes the Knight with a Hun-<br>dred Head’s uniform is that of a former comrade in arms. <br>3-4: Erlik, an eerie talking bear, seems to have much in com-<br>mon with Ordog. <br>5-6: Passing along an old bridge, the Knight with a Hundred <br>Heads is reminded of a battle he fought, and that some of <br>his comrades in arms had been buried in the vicinity of so-<br>mething the enemy was meant to never find.<br>Yvonne of the Dark<br>1-2: A huge fire is about to burn an orphanage down. <br>3-4: A little boy sees specters for what they truly are. <br>5-6: An old exorcist sets about eradicating every ghost.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":7900000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241738,"modifiedTime":1783973241738,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"XmxoqBFb5QYUzNb1","name":"Pagina 80","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 80</h2><p>79</p>","markdown":""},"sort":8000000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241738,"modifiedTime":1783973241738,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Zm6qr89C7m6amgT6","name":"Pagina 81","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 81</h2><p>80<br>Once upon a time…<br>London’s outskirts. Among the fumes and vapors <br>of newly-built factories, the disappearance <br>of several children has led to widespread <br>discontent among the workers. However, it <br>is only after the disappearance of Gwendolyn <br>Carnarvon, daughter of a titled noble, that the <br>royal family itself decided to turn to the Order. <br>Strange rumors are circulating in the suburbs <br>of London, where it seems that a young gang of <br>hooligans is committing violent acts to slow the <br>creeping spread of modernity, particularly in <br>the form of heartless factories. The Crown has <br>been deeply terrified by the macabre discovery <br>made by police looking into reports of violence <br>in the streets. According to rumors, factory <br>guards had engaged in a clash with the young <br>terrorists. The Crown investigators who tracked <br>down the battlefield were confronted with a <br>scene of unbelievable violence featuring broken, <br>bloody limbs and burst hearts inside shredded <br>rib cages. In great secrecy, the investigation <br>was shortly thereafter entrusted to the Hunters <br>of the Order with the aim of shedding light on <br>the danger that threatens the city and bringing <br>young Carnarvon to safety.<br>A Scenario Inspired by Peter <br>and Wendy (J. M. Barrie)<br>I Don’t Believe<br>Safety Keywords:  <br>Kidnapping / Terrorism</p>","markdown":""},"sort":8100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241738,"modifiedTime":1783973241738,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"gfdtM7W3BrglWGqZ","name":"Pagina 82","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 82</h2><p>81<br>The story that led us here…<br>A powerful fairy, known as the Cauldron Fae, has <br>been residing in London since time immemorial, long <br>before the city became what it is now. Under the false <br>identity of a personable purveyor of pots, she has lived in <br>secret on grounds she considers sacred: a series of caves and <br>galleries under the gardens of the Kensington Palace. The <br>Cauldron Fae is bothered by the modernization overtaking <br>London, slowly poisoning the clear air of the city with <br>smoke and stink. The fairy has begun to surround herself <br>with young orphans and misfits, creating a gang of ruthless <br>killers ready to do anything to please her. At the head of the <br>gang is Pietrik, a young Eastern immigrant who watched his <br>little sister die of fatigue, crushed by inhumane shifts at the <br>factory. Pietrik’s sole purpose in life is now to undermine <br>industrialization. The Cauldron Fae gave Pietrik, as her <br>most trusted servant, a magical object able to animate <br>his shadow so that he can more ably be her servant and <br>guardian. When a group of Crown investigators found the <br>secret passage from the slums to the Kensington Gardens, <br>the Cauldron Fae joined Pietrik on the field, unleashing her <br>great powers. The Cauldron Fae can control the Magic of <br>Disbelief, which allows her to imbue words with truth, but <br>only when expressing concepts of denial. By pronouncing <br>“I don’t believe in guards, ” the bodies of her enemies <br>twisted and then exploded, destroyed by devastating magic. <br>The only way to kill the Cauldron Fae is to use her own <br>magic against her, pronouncing the formula “I don’t believe <br>Mtyrya exists. ” Only Pietrik, however, knows her true name. <br>The young man fell in love with Gwendolyn and, after an <br>initial friendship, decided to kidnap her because she was <br>about to leave for Wales. As a prisoner in the Kensington <br>Gardens, the girl fears for her life, but she is perhaps the <br>only one who can lead Pietrik to reason.<br>The story at the arrival of the <br>Hunters…<br>Pietrik is the leader of his gang, the Lost Boys. They are out <br>of control, striking at a different business in London every <br>night. Only Gwendolyn’s entreaties can dampen the young <br>rebel’s bloodlust. The Cauldron Fae is harnessing power <br>for her greatest spell yet, which will be: “I do not believe <br>that there are people in London. ” The fairy’s goal is to get <br>rid of all the unwelcome humans in her beloved home <br>(including the Lost Boys), saving only Pietrik, to whom she <br>has become attached. To succeed, however, the fairy needs <br>power, which can only be generated by the passionate spirit <br>of young people rebelling against oppressive modernity. <br>For this reason, the Cauldron Fae encourages Pietrik and <br>his followers to strike London’s businesses more and more <br>often. Around the city have been engraved the Seals of the <br>fairy, and only those who already possess one can see the <br>others. The Lost Boys use theirs to activate the other Seals, <br>tap into the Cauldron Fae’s power, and perform small feats <br>of magic.<br>Distraught by the disappearance of his daughter, George <br>Carnarvon sent his best agents into the city. Most <br>disappeared and the remains of the few who were found <br>had been torn by savage wounds. Only at that point was <br>Carnavon willing to admit that the Hunters had skills his <br>men lacked and that made them uniquely suited to confront <br>occult powers. George is concerned for his daughter’s life, <br>and the fact that no one asked for a ransom makes him fear <br>the worst for Gwendolyn.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":8200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241738,"modifiedTime":1783973241738,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"NDyPdNv7zkJ7XoQx","name":"Pagina 83","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 83</h2><p>1<br>82<br>First Scene<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  You have just arrived in <br>London but, despite the exhaustion of your recent journey, <br>Lord Carnarvon has peremptorily summoned you. Tucked <br>away in one of the great homes in the city center, you find <br>yourself at the table with a fifty-year-old nobleman. The <br>puffy, dark circles around his eyes and his pale face leave you <br>with the impression that your host is very concerned about <br>what is happening in London.<br>Place: The London villa of the Carnarvon family.<br>Time: It is the late afternoon of a gloomy autumn day. <br>Initial Situation: George will update the Hunters with <br>all that happened so far. The nobleman will not hide his <br>deep concern for the fate of his daughter Gwendolyn.<br>Information: From the interview with George, the <br>Hunters will obtain the following information.<br> ◆ London is under attack by a large gang of young rebels. <br>The boys, all between the ages of ten and sixteen, hit <br>the most prosperous activities of the city, causing <br>serious accidents, damaging the tools and machinery <br>and, often, even the workers. The gang exhibits a <br>clear penchant for rebellion, focused on the nascent <br>industrial hub of London.<br> ◆ George’s sixteen-year-old daughter, Gwendolyn, was <br>abducted two days ago. The young woman has always <br>been a little rebellious but had never openly revolted <br>against her family. George fears that she has approached <br>the gang of youngsters driven by curiosity and that she <br>has been taken by them against her will. No ransom <br>demand has been made for the young woman, and that <br>makes George fear the worst. A desperate father before <br>anything else, Lord Carnavon will make it clear that <br>finding his daughter is more important to him than the <br>fate of the entire city.<br> ◆ After the clash that ended in a bloodbath the night <br>before, it is clear that the young rioters have something <br>occult on their side. Basil, the only survivor of the <br>attack, said that afterward the young attackers literally <br>disappeared through one of the walls. <br>At the end of the interview, George will be available to lead <br>the Hunters to several places:<br> ◆ To Gwendolyn’s rooms inside the palace, where the <br>Hunters can search for clues to the disappearance of <br>the young woman and interrogate her personal maid: <br>Joanna.<br> ◆ At the Sirens’ Inn, in the lower neighborhoods of <br>London, where Basil rests to recover from his injuries.<br> ◆ At the Skullem Factory, a shipyard that George fears <br>will be the next target of the young rioters.<br>Note: George will be as helpful as possible to the Hunters, <br>but it will be clear that the man is psychologically and <br>physically worn out by the events of the last days. The <br>Hunters can decide whether to keep him by their side or <br>not.<br>Note: In this Scenario, Pietrik and the Lost Boys Gang <br>can use the power of the Seals that the Cauldron Fae has <br>engraved all over London. At least one Seal, to be activated <br>at will, is always present in all the Places of the Scenario.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":8300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241738,"modifiedTime":1783973241738,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"LF2gcTpsvWiHmXnG","name":"Pagina 84","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 84</h2><p>83<br>Threat – Seal of the Cauldron Fae<br>OL Medium 5<br>Descriptor: A magic seal capable of manifesting the magic <br>of the Cauldron Fae.<br>Gift – Seals Everywhere:  At least one Seal of the <br>Cauldron Fae is present in all the Places of the Scenario. <br>Whoever possesses the Gang Seal or Personal Seal Gift  <br>can activate the effect of the Seal of the Cauldron Fae as an <br>additional action; this allows them to teleport to another <br>place featuring a Seal. The Seals are invisible to the human <br>eye and can be used only by those who have a tattooed eye <br>on their hand, placing said tattoo in front of the right eye. <br>Those who use magic can detect the presence of a Seal, but <br>the Seal of Disbelief Scenario Gift is necessary to activate it. <br>Note: Some Places feature more than one Seal to grant <br>the Lost Boys more narrative options in case the Hunters <br>manage to impede access to a Seal or negate the Gift. <br>George Carnarvon<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am the head of the Carnarvon family and my <br>service to the Crown has brought me a great deal of influence. <br>I fear the occult and magic. I can’t sleep due to worry over my <br>daughter’s abduction.<br>Agenda: Stop the gang of rebels that plagues London, but <br>more than anything else find my beloved daughter Gwendolyn.<br>Carnarvon House<br>Descriptor: A rich and large mansion in the heart of <br>London.<br>Joanna called Nana the Servant<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I have been Lady Gwendolyn’s trusted personal <br>servant for over ten years. I saw the young heir grow up and I <br>am as fond of her as if she were my own daughter.<br>Information: Joanna will tell the Hunters that she often <br>heard Gwendolyn chatting with a boy in her room, but <br>when she came in to figure out who it was, she never found <br>anyone. Gwendolyn has always avoided revealing the boy’s <br>identity, convincing Nana that he was some noble son of <br>a good family in the city. Searching Gwendolyn’s room, <br>the Hunters will find some poppy petals under the bed. <br>Nana will say that those flowers can only be found in the <br>Kensington Gardens in London.<br>Seals: There is only one Seal in the Carnarvon villa, <br>inscribed on the east wall of Gwendolyn’s room.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":8400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241738,"modifiedTime":1783973241738,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"EpxjA361Mg5PqmPx","name":"Pagina 85","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 85</h2><p>84<br>The Cauldron Fae’s Lair<br>Descriptor: An extensive maze of caves and galleries stretching beneath all of <br>Kensington’s Gardens. Within it, all kinds of plants and flowers grow luxuriantly <br>thanks to the Cauldron Fae’s power.<br>Threat – Nature Rises Up<br>OL Medium 5<br>Descriptor: Navigating inside the lair without the consent of the Cauldron Fae <br>exposes the intruders to the ire of the many plants. Ivy tentacles and pollen mists rise to <br>block those who walk without their lady’s approval.<br>Mtyrya the Fairy also called the <br>Cauldron Fae<br>OL Hard 7 – Main NPC (2 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am an ancient fairy bound to nature. I hate humans and modernity. Thanks <br>to my power, anything others believe to be impossible, I can make possible.<br>Agenda: Prevent humans from covering my beloved land with dirty, stinking factories / Save <br>Pietrik from the punishment I plan to inflict upon London.<br>Gift – The Magic of Disbelief:  As an action, the Cauldron Fae can formulate a magic <br>sentence including the fragment I don’t believe and make its effect concrete. For example, <br>“I don’t believe in gravity” would allow her to fly, while “I don’t believe the Hunters of the <br>Order exist” would allow her to hurt the Hunters in an attempt to make them disappear. <br>If the statement does not have offensive effects, the duration of the power is generally for <br>the entire Scene. If, on the other hand, the effect is likely to harm a target, it will inflict <br>1 Wound without the possibility of attempting a Defense Check. Those who use magic can <br>try to counteract the Magic of Disbelief, and preventing Mtyrya from speaking words would <br>automatically cancel the Gift’s effect.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":8500000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241738,"modifiedTime":1783973241738,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"e8Ieo3K2ci9awsgG","name":"Pagina 86","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 86</h2><p>85<br>Gift – Ancient Fairy:  The Cauldron Fae is immortal as <br>long as her beloved plants thrive under the Kensington <br>Gardens. The true focus of her power is the rebellious spirit <br>of her young servants. The fairy starts the Scenario with <br>3 Power Tokens and can spend 1 to return from death, <br>mending all the Wounds she has suffered. Each time a <br>factory or equivalent is destroyed in retaliation against <br>modernity, she receives 1 Power Token. The Cauldron <br>Fae can spend 4 Power Tokens to unleash all her power <br>and apply the effect of the Magic of Disbelief Gift to all of <br>London.<br>London’s Slums<br>Descriptor: Wretched alleys and houses where all the poor <br>of London live.<br>Information: In the slums, you can always find 1d6+6 <br>members of the Lost Boys Gang. When he’s not on a <br>mission or at Gwendolyn’s, Pietrik is here too.<br>Seals: Almost every main street in the slums has a Seal <br>somewhere.<br>The Sirens’ Inn<br>Descriptor: A dirty inn in the lower neighborhoods, hiding <br>a clandestine stall. Poor people and prostitutes flock inside to <br>find a roof to rest under.<br>Information: Basil resides at the inn because it is the <br>only one he can afford with the low salary provided by the <br>Carnarvon family. The man will badmouth his employer (if <br>not present) and will tell the Hunters that his companions <br>were literally ripped apart before exploding horribly. The <br>youngsters’ leader (a boy with typical Eastern European <br>features) pronounced the words “I don’t believe in guards” <br>right before the bloodbath. Basil is the only one who <br>wasn’t affected, but he hurt his leg falling down while <br>fleeing (a detail he omitted during George’s account) and is <br>determined to leave London as soon as he can walk again.<br>Pietrik has been watching Basil since he came to the inn, and <br>the Hunters will notice the young man (which corresponds <br>to Basil’s description) after some time there. If cornered, <br>Pietrik will escape thanks to the power of the Seal.<br>Seals: There are two Seals in the Sirens’ Inn, one in the <br>hallway in front of Basil’s room and the other in the main <br>hall near the front door.<br>Basil the Survivor<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am a coward only concerned with making <br>ends meet. <br>Agenda: To get back on my feet and escape from London, <br>away from rebels and magic.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":8600000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241738,"modifiedTime":1783973241738,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"pzX7ptEK3AM9OXPA","name":"Pagina 87","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 87</h2><p>86<br>Pietrik<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a young rebel and I fight the creeping industrialization of London with <br>all my strength.<br>Agenda: Destroy all the factories to avenge my sister’s death / Convince Gwendolyn to <br>join my gang because I have fallen in love with her. <br>Gift – The Needle of Living Shadows: Thanks to the power of the magic needle <br>the Cauldron Fae gave him, once per Scene Pietrik can separate the shadow from <br>his body and make it act like an NPC with its own profile. The shadow has 1 <br>Wound and can slip through the smallest crack. <br>Gift – Personal Seal: Pietrik has the Seal of Disbelief tattooed on the palm <br>of his hand, so once per Scene, he can activate the Gift The Magic of Disbelief <br>(page 84). As with the Gang Seal Gift (page 87), Pietrik can activate any <br>Seal present in London. <br>The Skullem Factory<br>Descriptor: A large shipyard in which metal components for ships are <br>being assembled.<br>Information: Inside the factory, there are two large industrial <br>ovens for metal welding. The goal of the Lost Boys is to blow <br>them up by throwing the magic berries that Pietrik has given <br>out into them. The raid will take place at night and involves 10 <br>Lost Boys, in addition to Pietrik. <br>Seals: The only Seal in the area of the Skullem Factory is <br>located in the alley at the back of the building.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":8700000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241738,"modifiedTime":1783973241738,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"E95qvjxH9E7JfIAQ","name":"Pagina 88","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 88</h2><p>87<br>The Gang of the Lost Boys<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We are young rebels who have lost everything <br>and are ready to die for our leader Pietrik.<br>Agenda: To help Pietrik in his plan for the destruction of <br>London. <br>Gift – Gang Seal:  Each gang member has a tattooed eye <br>on their right hand that allows them to see and use the Seals <br>of the Cauldron Fae scattered throughout London.<br>Gift – Rioter:  Each gang member increases his OL by <br>1 when acting with the support of at least one teammate. <br>Each member has a magic berry that they can throw which <br>will explode on contact, inflicting 1 Wound on all targets <br>within several feet. A Defense Check allows a target to leap <br>away from the blast zone.    <br>Kensington Gardens<br>Descriptor: A large green area in the heart of London. <br>Access to the gardens is prohibited due to ongoing <br>maintenance work. <br>Information: The Kensington Gardens have been long <br>abandoned because the Cauldron Fae uses her magic to <br>create unending problems for the gardeners. No one has <br>entered the gardens for over a year and Pietrik has used an <br>old gardeners’ house as a prison to keep Gwendolyn locked <br>up. The girl hasn’t tried to escape and hopes, so far in vain, <br>to convince Pietrik to give up on his destructive plans. <br>It is possible to descend through a well in <br>the eastern part of the park to access the <br>Cauldron Fae’s Lair. <br>Seals: The Gardens are literally full of <br>Seals.<br>Gwendolyn<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC  <br>(1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am the young heir of <br>the Carnarvon family, but I dream <br>of a life of travel and freedom, <br>exploring the world. I am good at <br>telling stories, and that is how I <br>got closer to Pietrik.<br>Agenda: To convince Pietrik <br>to desist from his revenge. <br>I understand how much <br>pain his heart holds and <br>I would like to welcome <br>him into my family to <br>give him a different <br>future.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":8800000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241738,"modifiedTime":1783973241738,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"bGMiT5b6Ag0QIkdB","name":"Pagina 89","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 89</h2><p>88<br>Scenario Events<br>In this Scenario, there are six Events. As a Storyteller, feel <br>free to create new ones in response to the actions of the <br>Hunters.<br>If the Cauldron Fae reaches 4 Power Tokens:  she <br>will be ready to kill all humans in London but will not do so <br>until she has secured Pietrik safely in her lair.<br>If Pietrik understands the true objective of the <br>Cauldron Fae: he will betray his mistress to try to save <br>Gwendolyn and the Lost Boys.<br>If the Hunters free Gwendolyn: the young woman will <br>tell the sad tale of Pietrik’s past, trying to make the Hunters <br>understand that the boy acts out of resentment and not true <br>evil.<br>If the Hunters capture one of the Lost Boys:  if put <br>under pressure, he will reveal that the whole gang follows <br>Pietrik’s lead and he is the only one who knows the identity <br>of the sorceress who has bestowed powers on everyone. <br>If the Hunters use Gwendolyn as bait for Pietrik:  <br>the young man will give up any involvement with the gang <br>to be with his beloved. <br>If the Lost Boys succeed in destroying the Skullem <br>Factory: one of them will be injured in the explosion and <br>can be captured by the Hunters. <br>Scenario Gifts<br>These Gifts represent special abilities related to the I Don’t <br>Believe Scenario and can be acquired once the conditions <br>are met. A Hunter can only have one Scenario Gift and if <br>they acquire a new one, they will have to forgo the previous <br>one.<br>Seal of Disbelief<br>Requirement: Capture or eliminate a member of the Lost <br>Boys.<br>Y ou studied the strange Seal that unites the entire gang <br>of young rebels and created one just like it on your hand. <br>When you bring your hand over your right eye you can see <br>the Seals of the Cauldron Fae engraved throughout London. <br>By spending 1 Soma you can cross a Seal to get to another <br>Seal whose location you know. Thanks to the Seal, you can <br>perform a Defense Check to prevent the Magic of Disbelief <br>from having an effect on you. <br>Support of a Lord <br>Requirement: Save Gwendolyn from Pietrik’s clutches.<br>Y ou saved the young heir to the Carnarvon family and for <br>this, you were given a medallion bearing the family coat <br>of arms. Receive 1 Additional Success when you use the <br>Carnarvon coat of arms in a context when having a powerful <br>noble’s favor might be useful. Add the Medallion bearing the <br>Carnarvon Coat of Arms and a large sum of money to your <br>equipment.<br>The Challenger (Special Gift for James the <br>Swordsman)<br>Requirement: Face Pietrik or the Lost Boys at least once.<br>The young rioters and their boss remind you of the band</p>","markdown":""},"sort":8900000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241738,"modifiedTime":1783973241738,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"fRUctWjY8P4UxouW","name":"Pagina 90","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 90</h2><p>1<br>2a<br>2b<br>89<br>of cowards who trapped you and are responsible for you <br>losing your hand. Receive 1 Additional Success for every <br>action you take against them if it means you defeat or <br>humiliate them. If you abandon a fight or are forced to <br>retreat, you lose 1 Soma out of shame.<br>The Scenario I Don’t <br>Believe in Scenes <br>FIRST SCENE – The summoning<br>It’s the same one you find on page 82. <br>End of Scene:  After the interview with George, the <br>Hunters can decide whether to collect clues at the <br>Carnarvon villa (SECOND SCENE OPTION A – On <br>Gwendolyn’s trail) or go to the Sirens’ Inn to talk to Basil <br>(SECOND SCENE OPTION B – Basil’s tale).<br>SECOND SCENE OPTION A <br>– On Gwendolyn’s trail <br>Read aloud to the Hunters: George takes you through the <br>private rooms of his villa, to Gwendolyn’s room. Waiting for <br>you is the girl’s personal maid, a thirty-year-old woman with <br>typical Eastern European features. The servant introduces <br>herself as Nana, a nickname Gwendolyn had given her. The <br>room of the young Carnarvon girl is the classic room of a <br>young lady, full of books and maps of the world.<br>Place: Gwendolyn Carnarvon’s bedroom.<br>Time: A bit later in the afternoon of a gloomy autumn day.<br>Information: Speaking with Nana, it will be clear to <br>the Hunters that the servant is sincerely concerned about <br>Gwendolyn’s fate; this should dispel any doubts about the <br>servant’s involvement in the disappearance. Nana will tell <br>the Hunters about the frequent night visits that Gwendolyn <br>received, but without being able to put a face or name to <br>her nightly visitor. At the end of the interview, Nana will <br>give the Hunters the poppy petals she found under the bed. <br>From a quick investigation, the Hunters will discover that <br>those flowers are typical of the Kensington Gardens.<br>End of Scene: The Hunters will move towards the gardens <br>to follow the petals’ trail. Go to the THIRD SCENE – The <br>Gardens.<br>SECOND SCENE OPTION B – <br>Basil’s Tale<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  You easily find the Sirens’ <br>Inn; it is a dive bar in the slums where the poor and drunks <br>belly up at the bar for a cheap beer. You recognize Basil from <br>the leg bandage and the old wooden crutch resting next to <br>his chair. The young man looks drunk, sipping a beer while <br>complaining about the misfortune he had in ending up in the <br>service of Lord Carnarvon.<br>Place: The run-down Sirens’ Inn, full of patrons and poor <br>people.<br>Time: The sun has just set and the large fireplace of the inn <br>casts the patrons’ long shadows on the dirty walls. <br>Information: Talking to Basil, you will get all the <br>information on page 85. During the interview, the <br>Hunters will notice a boy watching them sitting in front of <br>one of the large windows. Once Pietrik understands that</p>","markdown":""},"sort":9000000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241738,"modifiedTime":1783973241738,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"9wnUzqvtj0JogjxX","name":"Pagina 91","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 91</h2><p>3<br>4<br>90<br>the Hunters are investigating the Lost Boys, he will launch an <br>assault supported by 8 of his crew. If the fight turns against <br>them, Pietrik and his comrades will escape thanks to the <br>Seals. However, at least one of the Lost Boys will stay behind <br>and can be captured by the Hunters. After the interrogation, <br>the Hunters will ascertain that the gang’s next target is the <br>Skullem Factory. <br>End of Scene:  The Hunters must run to prevent the <br>impending attack on the factory. Go to FOURTH SCENE – <br>The assault on Skullem.<br>THIRD SCENE –  The Gardens<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  The Kensington Gardens are <br>an architectural and botanical wonder, and even months of <br>abandonment by the gardeners can’t entirely spoil their beauty. <br>Lord Carnarvon got you a key with great ease and you can <br>venture into the park using the main gate. As you step forward, <br>your attention is drawn to a small house in the middle of the <br>park where you clearly see a human figure holding a lantern. <br>It is more than a little suspicious, as no one is supposed to be <br>in the Gardens.<br>Place: The beautiful Kensington Gardens. <br>Time: Night has just fallen.<br>Information: Once at the house, the <br>Hunters will surprise Pietrik as he brings <br>food to Gwendolyn. The young man will <br>try to drive the Hunters out. If it fails, he <br>will flee, flying away (thanks to the power <br>of the Personal Seal Gift). By interrogating Gwendolyn, the <br>Hunters will learn of the attack on the Skullem Factory. <br>End of Scene:  The Hunters must run to prevent the <br>impending attack on the factory. Go to FOURTH SCENE – <br>The assault on Skullem.  <br>FOURTH SCENE –  The assault <br>on Skullem<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  When you reach the factory, <br>the first flames are already devouring the building. Among <br>workers and guards on the run, you clearly see a gang of boys <br>throwing strange berries that explode like bombs when they <br>hit the ground. The youngsters’ targets are the two large ovens, <br>which, if blown up, would intensify the flames, engulfing the <br>entire district.<br>Place: The Skullem Factory, besieged by the Lost Boys.<br>Time: It is late at night, but the flames that lick the building <br>illuminate everything as if it were day.<br>Information: Pietrik, with the support of <br>10 Lost Boys, will fight the Hunters. At the <br>end of the clash, several situations may occur.<br> ◆ If Pietrik is captured by the Hunters, he <br>can be persuaded to speak (using Gwendolyn <br>as a lever will be a great strategy); the young <br>man will reveal the location of the Cauldron <br>Fae’s Lair.<br> ◆ If Pietrik escapes, one of the captured <br>Lost Boys will reveal what Pietrik said: the</p>","markdown":""},"sort":9100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241738,"modifiedTime":1783973241738,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"3KfxLOsf6vtwxIt4","name":"Pagina 92","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 92</h2><p>5<br>91<br>power of the Seals comes from a sorcerer hiding under <br>Kensington Gardens.<br> ◆ In both cases, the captured gang member will reveal that <br>the goal of the Lost Boys is to destroy what is modern in <br>order to bring peace to London. <br>End of Scene: It will be clear for the Hunters that the one <br>who pulls the strings of the whole story hides under the <br>Kensington Gardens. Go to FIFTH SCENE – The Cauldron <br>Fae.<br>FIFTH SCENE –  The Cauldron <br>Fae<br>This Scene has no precise breakdown because it can be <br>approached in different ways by the Hunters. The Cauldron <br>Fae will be willing to compromise to save Pietrik, or fight to <br>the death if the Hunters prove hostile. Whatever happens, <br>it will be clear that the old fairy cannot accept the change <br>that is slowly transforming her beloved city into a large <br>industrial metropolis.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":9200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241739,"modifiedTime":1783973241739,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"1JFFVE2jDZEXJFxo","name":"Pagina 93","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 93</h2><p>92<br>Once upon a time…<br>Strange news comes from far away Iceland: the <br>great volcano Laki has unleashed its full might <br>and has stricken down the poor inhabitants of <br>the small villages on the island, like a divine <br>punishment. Few have managed to escape the fury <br>of fire and ash, but one in particular, the humble <br>logger Heino, tells of strange events in his village <br>and of an ancient power that seems to have taken <br>possession of many young inhabitants. The first <br>rescue expedition was sent to the small village of <br>Hosn, but no news has reached Denmark for over <br>a month. Considering Heino’s delirious tales, the <br>crown has decided to turn directly to the Papacy <br>for help, hoping the Church can determine if the <br>Devil himself could be behind the terrible famine. <br>A small ship has set sail for Iceland, though the <br>island is still shrouded in the fumes of Laki’s fury. <br>Among the crew is a group of Hunters, handpicked <br>to unravel this mystery.<br>A Scenario Inspired by Hansel <br>and Gretel (Grimm Brothers)<br>Hunger Island<br>Safety Keywords:  <br>Cannibalism / Catastrophe / Deprivation</p>","markdown":""},"sort":9300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241739,"modifiedTime":1783973241739,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"YgF7tKKD09ywkDjZ","name":"Pagina 94","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 94</h2><p>93<br>The story that led us here…<br>A few months have passed since the eruption of <br>the volcano Laki, which has wiped out most of the livestock <br>and inhabitants of the island, throwing Iceland into the <br>greatest famine of its history. In the village of Hosn, the <br>residents have found a macabre way to stave off starvation. <br>They sacrifice and feed on the weakest among them. Heino, <br>a poor woodcutter, sensed that his beloved children Hanse <br>and Gréte would be the next victims. Rather than see them <br>served up as meat, Heino led them to the base of Laki, <br>where he hoped they would find a quicker and less painful <br>end. In the mists and fumes of the volcano, however, <br>the two young people did not find death, but an ancient <br>stone, fallen from the sky at the dawn of the world itself. <br>Corrupted by the power enclosed in it, Hanse and Gréte <br>have changed, becoming superhuman beings who need <br>fresh meat to constantly regenerate their bodies. Deciding <br>to spread their new ‘gifts’ , the two children returned to <br>Hosn. Brother and sister infected the other village children <br>with the stone’s power, putting power in new hands. Now <br>adults have become livestock for the children exposed to <br>the power of the stone. The new mutants call themselves <br>Maws, the name by which Hanse and Gréte baptized this <br>new breed of Icelandic people. In one case, however, Hanse <br>granted his sister’s Gréte request for mercy. The two Maws <br>escorted their father to the port of Vík í Mýrdal, putting <br>him on one of the last ships to leave for the continent.<br>The story at the arrival of the <br>Hunters…<br>Most of the island is under the control of the Maws, who <br>lack fresh food and now guard Vík í Mýrdal in the hope of <br>ambushing incoming ships. Berend, captain of the ship of <br>the previous expedition, and Althea, a traveling nun in the <br>service of the Order, are also hiding in Vík í Mýrdal, now <br>a ghost town. The Maws control the only two inhabited <br>places that escaped the fury of the volcano Laki: the port <br>of Vík í Mýrdal and the village of Hosn. They also guard <br>the volcano itself, where the stone is venerated as a deity. <br>The lack of food has made the Maws increasingly aggressive <br>and violent, and even Hanse and Gréte are beginning to <br>struggle to keep them in control. In Hosn, where the few <br>remaining humans are kept in a large cage waiting to be <br>slaughtered, Hanse must increasingly maintain order by <br>force, to prevent the most hungry Maws from massacring <br>the few survivors and consuming all the food stocks in <br>one night. In Vík í Mýrdal, Gréte leads a group of the most <br>faithful Maws, looking for a way to attract new boats to the <br>island.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":9400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241739,"modifiedTime":1783973241739,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"DD9S4HSlGAElX6YR","name":"Pagina 95","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 95</h2><p>1<br>94<br>First Scene<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  After more than a week of <br>sailing, you finally catch a glimpse of the Icelandic coast and the <br>outlines of the port of Vík í Mýrdal. The smoking silhouette of the <br>great volcano stands out on the horizon like a hulking monster <br>looming over the entire island. With a few skillful maneuvers, <br>Captain Arne guides the ship into port, easily navigating the <br>thick blanket of fog and soot that seems to envelop everything. <br>The air is heavy and, around you, the world is a clouded, smoky <br>gray. You can feel a thrill of fear going up your back as you <br>contemplate the unnatural silence surrounding the port. No one <br>is present to welcome you and, at a closer look, the city seems <br>deserted.<br>Place: The port of Vík í Mýrdal, lost in fog.<br>Time: It is early afternoon, even though the fog that covers <br>the whole island means the light is dulled to the point of soft  <br>twilight.<br>Initial Situation: The ship is docked in the port and it is <br>immediately clear to everyone that the city is uninhabited. <br>The ship that brought the previous expedition is docked not <br>far away, looking abandoned as well. <br>Information: When interacting with Captain Arne, the <br>Hunters will learn that the entire crew is quite tense. The sailors <br>are skilled sea wolves, and for this reason deeply superstitious. <br>Only Arne, who comes from a military background, remains <br>cold and calculating at the spectacle of the ghost port. Arne <br>will guarantee the full support of his men to the Hunters: it <br>will be up to them to decide whether or not to make use of <br>the support. <br>Note: In this Scenario the Hunters will travel between Vík <br>í Mýrdal, the village of Hosn, and the volcano Laki. Each <br>journey takes 2 days on foot and must pass through The Mist <br>Roads (page 98).<br>Arne the Captain<br>OL Medium 5 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I once was a military man and I’ve earned the <br>crown’s respect. Now, as a ship’s captain, I serve my country and <br>boast about my crew. <br>Agenda: Do my best to carry out the mission I was entrusted <br>with. However, I won’t put the people under my command at <br>risk.<br>Sailors<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We are sailors under Captain Arne’s orders. We <br>are skilled sea wolves, more comfortable at sea than on land.<br>Agenda: Execute Arne’s orders and avoid in any way having to <br>face the supernatural.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":9500000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241739,"modifiedTime":1783973241739,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"1AN4uPftOk64jk2s","name":"Pagina 96","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 96</h2><p>95<br>The Port of Vík í <br>Mýrdal<br>Descriptor: The large port of a city <br>that was built to be a point of arrival <br>from the mainland. Ships and houses are <br>in a state of complete disuse.<br>Information: Walking around the <br>port and on the ship of the previous <br>expedition, the Hunters can obtain in <br>order the following information:<br> ◆ The city is indeed deserted. Crates <br>still hanging on hoists and torches <br>left untended, so that parts of the <br>docks are charred and burned, <br>suggest that the inhabitants have <br>abandoned what they were doing <br>when disaster struck.<br> ◆ Traces of blood and the remains of <br>devoured humans can be found in <br>the dark recesses of the harbor. It is <br>as if a pack of wild beasts assaulted the inhabitants to <br>drag them into darkness and devour them.<br> ◆ In the small harbor master’s office, the Hunters will <br>find on the front door a message written in blood: the <br>lighthouse is safe. The message is written in poor Latin, <br>with the clear intention of making it unreadable for the <br>natives of the island. It indicates the place where Althea <br>and Berend took refuge, and was written by the nun for <br>a possible group of Hunters. <br>For any information the Hunters receive, <br>you can decide to roll a die or choose <br>what happens:<br>1-2: A group of 8 Maws ambushes the <br>Hunters.<br>3-4: A group of 8 Maws led by Gréte <br>ambushes the Hunters. Gréte will <br>remain on the sidelines to lead the <br>attack and gather information about the <br>newcomers.<br>5-6: Berend watches the Hunters from <br>afar to discern who they are and why <br>they’ve come. He will eventually try to <br>approach them for help, but only when <br>it is safe from the Maws.<br>Gréte<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC  <br>(4 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am the incarnation of <br>the power of the great Maw. My body <br>regenerates thanks to the flesh I eat, my strength and my <br>speed are unbelievable. <br>Agenda: Keep capturing new humans to ensure a future <br>for the Maw’s offspring. Unlike my brother Hanse, I still have <br>a shred of humanity and I wouldn’t want to devour anyone <br>indiscriminately / I want to convince my friend Ina to become <br>a Maw.<br>Gift – Mutant Maw:  As long as they maintain their <br>original appearance, a mutant Maw appears in every way as <br>a common child. When they unleash their power, the body <br>shifts and the mouth widens disproportionately, revealing a</p>","markdown":""},"sort":9600000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241739,"modifiedTime":1783973241739,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"BVsnqw4Bd7bSDLeQ","name":"Pagina 97","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 97</h2><p>96<br>long line of sharp teeth. A mutant is considered to be of a <br>higher OL category for every physical action they perform <br>involving speed, strength, or ferocity. A mutant perceives <br>the smell of human flesh, which they find intoxicating, and <br>for this reason every attempt to hide from their sense of <br>smell receives 1 Penalty. When a mutant begins to devour <br>flesh (human or animal), they cannot stop until they have <br>finished it. Once per Scene, when a mutant Maw inflicts <br>1 Wound by devouring fresh meat, they recover 1 Wound <br>they suffered.<br>Gift – First Maw:  As the firstborn among the Maws, <br>Gréte has learned to manipulate the power that she <br>harbors in her body. During a Scene, Gréte may self-inflict <br>1 Wound to benefit from one of the following effects:  <br>1. Superhuman Strength, if she inflicts 1 Wound with <br>an action and does not devour the target, Gréte can throw <br>it 15 feet away. The target will fall to the ground and suffer 1 <br>additional Wound if they impact an obstacle. Gréte can use <br>her strength to throw one enemy into another, in which case <br>the target can try to dodge the attack with a Defense Check. <br>2. Superhuman Speed , Gréte can make an incredible <br>leap of over 30 feet. She does not need any preparation, <br>and she can take another subject with her while moving. <br>3. Rebirth, Gréte falls into a state of apparent death to <br>regenerate in the next Scene. She wakes up completely <br>healed. Only a highly skilled doctor or someone using <br>magical means is able to discern Gréte is not truly dead.  <br>The Maws<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (2 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: We are a new people, children of the great <br>Maw. Our bodies regenerate thanks to the flesh we eat. Our <br>strength and speed are incredible. <br>Agenda: We obey Gréte and Hanse, they are the firstborns, <br>they know the right path / Satiate our infinite hunger, even at <br>the cost of disobeying the firstborns.<br>Gift – Mutant Maw:  As long as they maintain their <br>original appearance, a mutant Maw appears in every way as <br>a common child. When they unleash their power, the body <br>shifts and the mouth widens disproportionately, revealing <br>a long line of sharp teeth. A mutant is considered to be of a <br>higher OL category for every physical action they perform <br>involving speed, strength, or ferocity. A mutant perceives <br>the smell of human flesh, which they find intoxicating, and <br>for this reason every attempt to hide from their sense of <br>smell receives 1 Penalty. When a mutant begins to devour <br>flesh (human or animal), they cannot stop until they have <br>finished it. Once per Scene, when a mutant Maw inflicts <br>1 Wound by devouring fresh meat, they recover 1 Wound <br>they suffered.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":9700000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241739,"modifiedTime":1783973241739,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"zTbbVo5KauQNKOCk","name":"Pagina 98","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 98</h2><p>97<br>Berend the Crazed Captain <br>OL Medium 5 – Minor NPC (2 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am the captain of the previous expedition <br>and the only one left of my crew. I learned to survive by <br>masking my smell with the stench of rotten fish.<br>Agenda: Wait for someone to come from the mainland to <br>save me.<br>Gift – Stinking Survivor:  Berend managed to avoid <br>being devoured by the Maws, but what he saw happen <br>to his companions scarred his mind forever. The man <br>constantly covers himself with rotten fish because he has <br>discovered the stench conceals him from the Maws. <br>Berend will never be targeted by a Maw unless he <br>takes direct action against them. As long as he <br>is at the port of Vík í Mýrdal, Berend can move <br>with great skill through the alleys and take <br>any companions anywhere in the city without <br>attracting the attention of the Maws. Each <br>time he uses this ability, he rolls 1 die: on 5 <br>or 6, Berend convinces himself that he has <br>seen other survivors and makes noise in an <br>attempt to get their attention. It will be <br>clear to those that accompany him that <br>the whole situation is nothing <br>more than a figment <br>of the poor man’s <br>distressed mind.<br>Vík í Mýrdal’s Lighthouse<br>Descriptor: An old lighthouse in the oldest part of the port <br>of Vík í Mýrdal. Crates of fish have been broken open and <br>spilled around the lighthouse, their contents left to rot in the <br>sun. Now, the air reeks in a nauseating way.<br>Gift – Safe Haven from the Maws: The stacks of rotten <br>fish that Berend and Althea constantly throw at the foot of <br>the lighthouse keep the Maws away. The Maws lose all trace <br>of someone who takes refuge in the lighthouse. While near <br>the lighthouse, Maws reduce their Opposition Level by 1.<br>Information: Althea will have a great deal of information <br>for the Hunters. She has been trapped for a month now, and <br>has taken the opportunity to study the Maws in depth.<br> ◆ The Maws look like children mutated by something. <br>They are strong, fast, and seem to follow the smell of <br>human flesh.<br> ◆ Some desperate people fleeing from the village of Hosn <br>have told them of two “leaders” of the Maws, brother <br>and sister, who apparently are smarter and more <br>powerful than the others.<br> ◆ After overhearing Maws talking to each other, Althea <br>realized that the volcano is a sacred place for those <br>strange beings that humans must not enter.<br> ◆ Both the village and the volcano are two days’ walk <br>from Vík í Mýrdal, but in different directions.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":9800000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241739,"modifiedTime":1783973241739,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"MEa3ADz1LvrsXZqm","name":"Pagina 99","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 99</h2><p>98<br>Althea the Agent of the Order<br>OL Medium 5 – Minor NPC (2 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a nun in the service of the Order and, <br>despite my ecclesiastical background, I have skills as a spy and <br>a fighter. The Order entrusts me with high-risk tasks because <br>it has confidence in my unwavering faith and ruthlessness.<br>Agenda: Solve the mystery of the Maws and provide support <br>to the Hunters of the Order.<br>Gift – Agent of the Order: Althea is talented and trained to support the Hunters. Althea can spend her action to <br>support a Hunter’s action and give them 1 Additional <br>Success in any Check.<br>The Mist Roads<br>Descriptor: All the communication routes between Vík í <br>Mýrdal and the nearby villages are surrounded by a dense, <br>dark fog that does not allow you to see more than a few feet <br>ahead.<br>For each trip on the Mist Roads, you can choose or roll for <br>a Threat/encounter with an NPC.<br>1-2: A crevasse created by the eruption of Laki has <br>opened up, barring the way.<br>Threat – Crevasse in the Mist <br>Descriptor: A crevasse eighteen feet deep, hidden by the <br>dense mist.<br>OL Medium 5<br>Falling into the crevasse will cause 1 Wound. At the bottom, <br>you can find the body of a desperate runaway. As a cost for <br>a Defense Check Outcome, a Hunter may lose equipment <br>that will fall down into the mist.<br>3-4: The mist becomes even thicker, making it <br>impossible to even distinguish the road.<br>Threat – Mist Wall<br>Descriptor: A fog so dense that it is impossible to see <br>anything.<br>OL Hard 7<br>If they fail a Check to stay on the road, the Hunters will get <br>lost and end up in the wrong place.<br>5-6: A group of Maws. A group of 4 Maws who travel in <br>search of fresh meat.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":9900000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241739,"modifiedTime":1783973241739,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"z2t3We17VCcjtaQP","name":"Pagina 100","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 100</h2><p>99<br>The Village of Hosn<br>Descriptor: A small village lost in the hills. Many houses <br>have been burned down, and the stench of corpses hovers in <br>the air.<br>Information: The village is under Hanse’s control. In the <br>small central square, a rudimentary wooden cage was built <br>where the last six inhabitants of the village are trapped. <br>Every day, one inhabitant is taken out to be devoured, but <br>now there are more than twenty Maws and so little flesh is <br>not enough to satisfy their hunger. <br>By saving the inhabitants, the Hunters will be able to obtain <br>some information:<br> ◆ Ina is a little girl who refused to become a Maw. She is a <br>friend of Gréte, who explicitly asked her brother Hanse <br>to keep Ina last, in the hope that she will change her <br>mind and convert. Ina is aware of the friendship that <br>Gréte feels towards her and how this is a weak point <br>within the Maw.<br> ◆ Askell is a young hunter who killed a Maw when Hanse <br>and Gréte took control of the village. As punishment his <br>hands were devoured and now Askell is kept alive only <br>to see all his loved ones die one after the other. He hates <br>the Maws and killing them has become an obsession <br>for him. Askell knows a secret road that allows you to <br>reach the volcano, avoiding the complications of the <br>Mist Roads. <br> ◆ Alba is Askell’s mother. She is now utterly devastated, <br>after seeing her husband Helg eaten alive by the Maws <br>and her son reduced to impotence. Alba has a key to <br>the cellars of the town hall, a shelter from volcanic <br>eruptions where many supplies are stashed. <br> ◆ Enoch is one of the village elders. He was the first to <br>acknowledge the idea of eating the helpless to survive. <br>All the Maws hate him and would attack him without <br>a second thought, if only they had the chance. Hanse <br>keeps him alive, pondering the most convoluted <br>possible way to eliminate him when the time comes.<br> ◆ Erna is a young woman without children. She has <br>always hated living on the island and was only here to <br>follow her husband who has already been devoured <br>by the Maws. Erna has heard Hanse talking to other <br>Maws about a “stone that came from the sky” kept in <br>the volcano, which must be defended at all costs. <br> ◆ Hafnar is a plump businessman who is being fed with <br>the little food left in the village. Hanse’s intention is to <br>fatten up Hafnar to make him more delicious for his <br>Maws. Hafnar possesses a dose of a potent rat poison <br>that he has already used to kill two Maws in the first <br>few days. His intention is to sprinkle his body with <br>the poison on the day he is devoured, to take as many <br>Maws with him as possible.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":10000000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241740,"modifiedTime":1783973241740,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"ljF6MlYWryc6oxlv","name":"Pagina 101","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 101</h2><p>100<br>Hanse<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (4 Wounds)<br>Descriptor:  I am the incarnation of the power of the great Maw. My body <br>regenerates thanks to the flesh I eat. My strength and my speed are unbelievable. <br>Agenda: Keep capturing new humans to ensure a future for the Maw’s offspring. <br>Unlike my sister Gréte, I have no regard for humans and, now that I spared my <br>father to make my sister happy, I just want to protect the stone that came from <br>the sky.<br>Gift – Mutant Maw:  As long as they maintain their original appearance, a <br>mutant Maw appears in every way as a common child. When they unleash their <br>power, the body shifts and the mouth widens disproportionately, revealing a <br>long line of sharp teeth. A mutant is considered to be of a higher OL category <br>for every physical action they perform involving speed, strength, or ferocity. <br>A mutant perceives the smell of human flesh, which they find intoxicating, <br>and for this reason, every attempt to hide from their sense of smell receives <br>1 Penalty. When a mutant begins to devour flesh (human or animal), they <br>cannot stop until they have finished it. Once per Scene, when a mutant Maw <br>inflicts 1 Wound by devouring fresh meat, they recover 1 Wound they suffered.<br>Gift – First Maw:  As the firstborn among the Maws, Hanse has learned <br>to manipulate the power that he harbors in his body. During a Scene, <br>Hanse may self-inflict 1 Wound to benefit from one of the following effects:  <br>1. Superhuman Strength , if he inflicts 1 Wound with an action and <br>does not devour the target, Hanse can throw it 15 feet away. The target <br>will fall to the ground and suffer 1 additional Wound if they impact an <br>obstacle. Hanse can use his strength to throw one enemy into another, in <br>which case the target can try to dodge the attack with a Defense Check.  <br>2. Superhuman Speed , Hanse can make an incredible leap of over 30 <br>feet. He does not need any preparation, and he can take another subject with <br>him while moving. 3. Power of the Stone that Came from the Sky , <br>Hanse can tap into the latent power in his body. Once per Scene, all human <br>subjects in his presence lose 2 Soma or alternatively can resist by taking 1 <br>Wound. Suffering the last Wound for this effect does not cause death, but a <br>loss of consciousness.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":10100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241740,"modifiedTime":1783973241740,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"g1CZcpi9VdeUIPHZ","name":"Pagina 102","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 102</h2><p>101<br>Laki the Volcano<br>Descriptor: A great volcano that dominates all of Iceland. <br>The rock walls have cracked due to the powerful eruptions, <br>creating a series of natural tunnels and galleries. <br>Information: The volcano hides the stone that came <br>from the sky among a maze of tunnels. After the first <br>eruptions, the stone has re-emerged, manifesting its power. <br>To protect the stone, Hanse has left all the Maws that have <br>had issues managing the mutations at the volcano. Those <br>abandoned wretches have grown into Crazed Maws, <br>brainless monsters who wander in search of food. It’s <br>possible for the Hunters to track the Crazed Maws to the <br>stone’s hiding place. Otherwise, the Hunters will face the <br>Threat Daedalus of Tunnels.<br>Threat – Daedalus of Tunnels<br>Descriptor: A series of natural tunnels that change shape <br>according to the tectonic shocks that hit the volcano.<br>OL Hard 7<br>Failing the Check means getting lost, meeting one or more <br>Crazed Maws, or ending up caught in a sudden lava flow, <br>which inflicts 1 Wound and the destruction of one or more <br>pieces of equipment.<br>Crazed Maws<br>OL Medium 5 – Minor NPC (4 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: A mad abomination whose form constantly <br>shifts, as they wander in search of living beings to devour. <br>Agenda: Eat every living thing, except other Maws.<br>Gift – Mutant Abomination:  A Crazed Maw does not <br>feel any pain. For this reason the Wounds it suffers have <br>no narrative effect but are only a counter to understand <br>when the abomination will crumble into a thousand pieces. <br>Tentacles and arms are constantly born from the body of <br>a Crazed Maw, and as a result it can act 2 times during <br>an Exchange. With one of its actions, a Crazed Maw can <br>slam its huge mass to the ground to create a strong tremor. <br>All targets in the immediate vicinity must pass a Defense <br>Check to avoid falling to the ground.<br>Threat – The Stone that Came from <br>the Sky<br>Descriptor: An alien stone, the size of a fist, that thrums <br>with energy. <br>Gift – Alien Stone:  All the powers of the Maws derive <br>from the stone. With its destruction, the mutations will <br>deteriorate, causing the death of all mutants except Hanse <br>and Gréte. The stone has 6 Wounds and has no OL, because <br>it cannot interact directly or defend itself. For each Wound <br>suffered, a spark of the power comes out, affecting the one <br>who inflicted the blow. Whoever suffers this effect can <br>decide between losing 2 Soma or suffering 1 Wound. If the <br>stone is destroyed or stolen, Hanse will be able to unleash <br>all the latent power in him and, by joining with Gréte, give <br>life to the Great Maw.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":10200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241740,"modifiedTime":1783973241740,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Vs3LHOtxEfNke9ED","name":"Pagina 103","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 103</h2><p>102<br>Threat – The Great Maw<br>Descriptor: A colossal titan of flesh and tentacles born from <br>the union of the two first Maws. The creature acts to recover <br>the stone or avenge its destruction, at the cost of destroying the <br>entire island in the process.<br>OL Hard 7<br>Note: The Storyteller must immediately clarify that the <br>Great Maw is a monster so powerful that it cannot be faced <br>in combat. Its ever-growing mass instantly regenerates every <br>wound, and its colossal size is beyond the reach of any magic. <br>Rather than confronting the Great Maw, the Hunters must <br>curb its action as they rescue the survivors.<br>Here is a list of potential situations:<br> ◆ The stone can be used as bait to force the Great Maw to <br>follow it. Throwing it in the middle of the volcano will <br>cause the titan to follow it, burning to death in a lava pit.<br> ◆ One can still leverage Gréte’s consciousness and her <br>sympathy for Ina, making the Great Maw hesitate for a <br>few moments before Hanse regains control.<br> ◆ When a Defense Check against the Great Maw is failed, <br>in addition to suffering 1 Wound, the target will be <br>pushed away by over thirty feet, suffering 1 additional <br>Wound if it impacts something.<br> ◆ With the force of its roar alone, the Great Maw can hurl <br>a human to the ground.<br> ◆ With a tentacle, the Great Maw can “pick up” a house and <br>hurl it at someone.<br> ◆ Escaping the Great Maw is not easy and the survivors of <br>the village will be a burden for the Hunters.<br> ◆ The Great Maw cannot swim and will stop its chase once <br>the Hunters successfully take to the sea.<br>Scenario Events<br>In this Scenario, there are six Events. As a Storyteller, feel free <br>to create new ones in response to the actions of the Hunters.<br>If the Hunters dismantle the Maw packs in Vík í <br>Mýrdal: Gréte will approach the Hunters pretending to <br>be a survivor. The intention of the Maw is to study these <br>new enemies and provide useful information to her brother <br>Hanse.<br>If the Hunters send sailors alone to explore the port <br>of Vík í Mýrdal: in a short time, the poor unfortunate will <br>be attacked and overwhelmed by the Maws.<br>If Gréte understands that the Hunters are here to <br>save the inhabitants:  the Maw could reveal herself and <br>negotiate to save her friend Ina.<br>If the Hunters arrive in Hosn without worrying <br>about being seen: all the Maws will present themselves as <br>common children and ambush the Hunters when their guard <br>is down. <br>If the Hunters steal or destroy the stone that came <br>from the sky:  mad with rage, Hanse will join his sister <br>Gréte to fuse into the Great Maw.<br>If Gréte is cornered by the Hunters:  she will use her <br>gift to appear dead and, as soon as she wakes up, she will run <br>to join her brother.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":10300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241740,"modifiedTime":1783973241740,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"fGwtOutdwBv6m6Y2","name":"Pagina 104","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 104</h2><p>103<br>Scenario Gifts<br>These Gifts represent special abilities related to the Hunger <br>Island Scenario and can be acquired once the conditions are <br>met. A Hunter can only have one Scenario Gift and if they <br>acquire a new one, they will have to forgo the previous one.<br>Stinky<br>Requirement: Meet Berend and learn from him how to <br>mask your scent.<br>Y ou know how to make your scent unrecognizable and <br>confuse enemies and predators. Y ou can spend 1 Soma and <br>cover yourself with a rotting substance that will make you <br>smelly. An enemy who bases their actions on smell (like a <br>Maw) will never target you unless you act directly against <br>them. Y ou gain 1 Additional Success to all Defense Checks <br>you make to defend from an attack carried out by an enemy <br>sensitive to your aroma. Y ou receive 1 Penalty at all Checks <br>with ordinary people when your nauseating smell is a clear <br>obstacle. <br>The Stone that Came from the Sky<br>Requirement: Recover the stone that came from the sky <br>from the slopes of the volcano.<br>Y ou hold an alien stone with great powers, which you can <br>activate by suffering 1 Wound. When you do, choose from <br>one of the following effects. 1. Might: Y our strength triples <br>and you get 1 Additional Success to any Position Check <br>based on sheer strength for the rest of the Scene. 2. Speed: <br>Y our speed triples and you get 1 Additional Success at any <br>Position Check based on speed for the rest of the Scene. <br>3. Energy: Y our body is infused with pure energy and you <br>receive 3 Energy Tokens for the rest of the Scene. Y ou or <br>another nearby magic practitioner can use 1 Energy Token <br>to have 1 Additional Success when using any kind of magic. <br>Y ou can activate more than one effect of this Gift in the same <br>Scene by suffering additional Wounds. Wounds you suffer in <br>this way cannot be recovered in the current Scene.<br>This is My House (Special Gift for the Woman <br>from the Wood)<br>Requirement: Reach the village of Hosn.<br>Y ou remember this place, this is where you lived, and this <br>is where you worked as a baker. With your delicious sweets, <br>you fed the poor children of the village, but then someone <br>whose face you don’t remember poisoned what you created, <br>killing those you cared about. Y ou forgot what you did to <br>keep from succumbing to pain. Now you can decide:<br> <br> Forget what happened again.<br>In this case, deep anger will accompany you throughout your <br>stay on the island. Y ou always get 1 Additional Success when <br>you act to eradicate a threat that puts the life of a helpless <br>human at risk.<br> Remember who you were. <br>Y ou will return to be the witch of your past, but this will <br>mean profoundly changing who you are now. Permanently <br>replace your sheet with that of Katharina the Sweet Witch <br>found at the end of this Scenario.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":10400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241740,"modifiedTime":1783973241740,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"MiCnvCPGUKRfbLN6","name":"Pagina 105","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 105</h2><p>1<br>2<br>Special<br>104<br>The Scenario <br>Hunger Island in <br>Scenes <br>FIRST SCENE –  Arrival at the <br>port of Vík í Mýrdal<br>It’s the same one you find on page 94. While wandering <br>around the port, the Hunters will be attacked by the <br>Maws and then will meet Berend, who will invite them to <br>the lighthouse. Gréte, left in the shadows to observe the <br>situation, will flee to Hosn to warn her brother of the arrival <br>of the Hunters.<br>End of Scene: Berend takes the Hunters to the lighthouse <br>to meet Althea. Go to the SECOND SCENE – The lighthouse.<br>SECOND SCENE –  <br>The lighthouse<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: An excited Berend takes you <br>to the oldest part of the port of Vík í Mýrdal. Crates of fish <br>have been spilled in the area around the lighthouse and now <br>rot in the sun, causing a reek that makes sore vomit rise at <br>the back of your throat. Berend explains, with witty eyes, that <br>the monsters he calls Maws are drawn by the scent of humans <br>and are confused by the smell of rot. With pride, Berend <br>raises his dirty shirt and shows you a hairy torso encrusted <br>with dirt and fish guts. As he starts to pull his pants down, <br>a female voice tells him to stop. Althea, the emissary of the <br>Order who came here before you, comes out of the door of <br>the old lighthouse and yells at the poor madman who led you <br>here.<br>Place: The old lighthouse of the port that Althea and <br>Berend have fortified to keep the Maws away.<br>Time: It is late afternoon as the sun begins its descent, <br>hidden by the dense clouds fed by the fumes of the volcano.<br>Information: Althea will be grateful to the Hunters <br>for their arrival. Although the woman is extremely worn <br>by exhaustion and hunger, she will give the Hunters the <br>information on page 97. Althea will ask the Hunters to <br>accompany her to Hosn, to strike at the “leaders” of the <br>Maws and put an end to the threat they represent. It is clear <br>to the Order’s agent that the island’s stocks of both animals <br>and humans are rapidly depleting, and she fears it’s only <br>a matter of time before the Maws organize themselves to <br>set sail for the mainland. Alternatively, Althea will follow <br>the Hunters to the volcano if that’s where they intend to <br>investigate.<br>End of Scene: The Hunters leave with Althea for Hosn or <br>the Volcano. Go to SPECIAL SCENE – Along the way.<br>SPECIAL SCENE –  Along the <br>way<br>This Scene must be played every time the Hunters set out <br>on a journey. Select one of the effects on page 98.<br>End of Scene: The Hunters arrive at the village of Hosn. <br>Go to THIRD SCENE OPTION A – The village of Hosn or <br>to THIRD SCENE OPTION B – Laki, the Volcano.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":10500000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241740,"modifiedTime":1783973241740,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"5z7AV72r5rncO3BF","name":"Pagina 106","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 106</h2><p>3b3a<br>105<br>THIRD SCENE OPTION A –  <br>The village of Hosn<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  You arrive at Hosn following <br>a little used farm track, convinced that your enemies are posted <br>everywhere. A series of cries and moans draws your attention. <br>In the center of the small town square, a rudimentary wooden <br>cage holds six people prisoner. They seem to be ordinary <br>villagers, emaciated and shaken by the hardships they have <br>endured. Then, the sound of footfalls resonating among the <br>semi-destroyed houses make it clear to you that your enemies <br>are practically everywhere.<br>Place: The small village of Hosn, shrouded in fog.<br>Time: It is a cold day’s dawn and the rays of the sun reflect in <br>the fog, making it look almost like a white veil.<br>Information: Gréte stayed at the village to organize the <br>defenses, while Hanse moved to the volcano. The Maws will <br>first attempt to overcome the Hunters, taking advantage of the <br>numerical superiority. <br> ◆ The weak point of the Maws, however, is to attack without <br>any strategy, running at the Hunters like rabid dogs. <br> ◆ If cornered, Gréte will be willing to compromise by <br>freeing the villagers, with the exception of Enoch.<br> ◆ If released, Ina will try to reason with Gréte, proving to be <br>an asset to the Hunters.<br> ◆ In the village, there are a total of 18 Maws, moving in <br>groups of 6.<br>End of Scene: After freeing the village, talking to prisoners, <br>or interrogating Gréte, the Hunters will clearly understand <br>that the origin of all this is in Laki, where Hanse has retreated. <br>Go to THIRD SCENE OPTION B –  Laki, the Volcano. If, on <br>the other hand, the Hunters come from the volcano, go to the <br>FOURTH SCENE – The Great Maw.<br>THIRD SCENE OPTION B –  <br> Laki, the Volcano<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: Finally, the volcano is no longer <br>just a looming shadow that hangs over all of you since you <br>landed. Now, it stands out in all its grandeur, its top lost among    <br>dense clouds. The earth thrums as if following the beating of a <br>huge heart, which is nothing more than the core of the volcano <br>itself. Among the split rocks, you can see several tunnels that <br>seem to unravel inside the volcano, and grotesque and guttural <br>sounds make you realize that the frequent eruptions are not the <br>worst danger you could encounter.<br>Place: Laki, the Volcano.<br>Time: It is a cold day’s dawn and the rays of the sun reflect in <br>the fog, making it look almost like a white veil.<br>Information: The Hunters will almost immediately come <br>across several Crazed Maws. To get to the center of the <br>volcano, they will have to deal with at least 2, or find a way to <br>follow them to the tunnel where the stone is located.<br> ◆ Hanse is protecting the stone with 2 Crazed Maws to back <br>him up. The boy is willing to bargain with the Hunters for <br>the promise that they will leave the island and leave him <br>and his new people alone.<br> ◆ If cornered, Hanse will throw himself into the volcano <br>carrying the stone with him, and the Hunters will see him <br>burn in the lava.<br> ◆ Hanse will not die in the lava but, consuming all the power <br>of the stone, he will emerge a few hours later filled with <br>anger for the possibilities lost because of the Hunters.<br>End of Scene:  Hunters can move to the village of Hosn <br>to save the remaining inhabitants. Go to THIRD SCENE <br>OPTION A – The village of Hosn. If, on the other hand, the <br>Hunters come from the village, go to FOURTH SCENE – The <br>Great Maw.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":10600000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241740,"modifiedTime":1783973241740,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"6Is8p45ExG9OfK6X","name":"Pagina 107","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 107</h2><p>4<br>106<br>FOURTH SCENE –  The Great Maw<br>This Scene begins after the defeat of both siblings. Hanse, driven mad by the <br>loss of the stone, returns to Hosn as the Hunters prepare to leave. Gréte, who <br>pretended to be dead thanks to her powers, will be reunited with her brother <br>and merge with him into the Great Maw. Play the Great Maw Threat as described <br>on page 102.<br>End of Scene: Hunters manage to escape from the island or end the life of the <br>Great Maw by making it fall into the volcano. Whatever choice they make, only <br>the Hunters can end the danger the Maws represent.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":10700000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241740,"modifiedTime":1783973241740,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"u6v0T8SkCKRMhAz7","name":"Pagina 108","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 108</h2><p>Descriptors and Gifts<br>I am a capable cook and my body has a sweet smell that relaxes whoever <br>is near me. I can tell a lot about people from their food tastes. I deeply <br>hate those who hurt or bully children and the helpless.<br>•  The Sweet Witch: Y ou can spend 1 Soma to offer one of your sweets <br>to someone to make them well disposed towards you. Y ou gain 1 Additional <br>Success to convince and manipulate those who have eaten one of your sweets <br>until the end of the Scene. Y ou can decide that your dessert has an additional <br>effect based on its flavor: <br>1. Marzipan: Whoever eats it will fall into a deep sleep for several hours. <br>2. Candied fruit: The taste of the treat pushes those who are intoxicated to <br>reveal what they cherish the most. <br>3. Cinnamon: Those who eat it will feel the urgent desire to do more than <br>what they are doing, even at the expense of their duty. <br>4. Raisins: The taste of the treat pushes those who are intoxicated to reveal <br>what they hate the most.<br>Other Hunters or particularly capable individuals may require a Position <br>Check to make use of the power of your sweets.<br>I am a capable witch and when I need it, the world around me shapes <br>itself to protect and shelter me. I hate being out in the open and avoid <br>being the center of attention.<br>•  Home Sweet Home: you can spend 1 Soma to draw on your strange <br>witch powers. When you do, choose one of the following effects. <br>1. Create a shelter, for one person, perfectly camouflaged within the <br>environment. It is very difficult to discover your shelter, though some NPCs <br>can come close. At the Storyteller’s discretion, a Defense Check may be made <br>to see if you are discovered. <br>2. Change the texture of an inanimate object into a soft sweet. Y ou can turn a <br>door into marzipan or a sword into colored jelly. <br>3. Make an edible sweet and more nutritious. Whoever consumes your sweet <br>recovers 2 Soma, except yourself.<br>Katharina <br>the Sweet Witch<br>I am a witch specializing in creating magic sweets. I have always used my skills to help all the poor children <br>who cannot afford something good to eat. Giving a little joy to the poor was what warmed my heart the most. But <br>one day, a strange figure called the One Who Plots in the Shadow deceived me by poisoning what I baked with <br>so much love. That day, an entire village lost its future forever with the passing of all the children. I am aware <br>that I am not really guilty of the deaths of so many innocents, but this doesn’t lift the weight from my heart. All <br>I have left is revenge, which I will take as a Hunter of the Order against the one who, on a whim, destroyed <br>everything I cared about.<br>XP<br>Soma<br> 6<br>I love human flesh, a legacy of the alien stone’s power, to which <br>I have been exposed. I can regenerate my body, and my senses are <br>incredibly sharp. I am helplessly attracted to those who have a <br>particular appearance that stimulates my appetite, such as a good <br>smell or velvety skin. <br>•  Dark Ego - Soft and Succulent Flesh:  The truth is that you <br>crave human flesh, especially when raw and taken from evil people. When <br>you inflict a Wound through violent action on someone you deem evil, and <br>if you reach an Outcome with an Increment, you may inflict 1 additional <br>Wound. Once per Scene when you consume human flesh, you recover 1 <br>Wound and the Storyteller will reveal some memories of the victim, giving <br>you contextualized information about what you are looking for..<br>Activator: Blatantly manifest your desire to devour human flesh, regardless of the consequences.<br>Equipment <br>A doll and a wooden soldier, the only memories of the <br>children I cared for / A clean dress and an apron that smells <br>of sweets / A series of incredibly sharp, small pastry knives / <br>A suitcase of fine leather that contains everything I need to <br>produce excellent desserts / A picnic tablecloth / The key to <br>my small pastry workshop. <br>Wounds <br>1.<br>2.<br>3.<br>Extra <br>Wound.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":10800000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241740,"modifiedTime":1783973241740,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"uoW0ZBhlkjqblsuG","name":"Pagina 109","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 109</h2><p>108<br>Once upon a time…<br>Germanic Bavaria. Prince Charles <br>Theodore has summoned the Order after <br>the strange death of his nephew Ottone. <br>He died traveling to the small village of <br>Lohr where he had gone to meet his future <br>wife, Bianca Karenmann. Although official <br>reports speak of a fatal fall from the horse, <br>in truth, the young man’s corpse was found <br>torn apart, his lungs and other organs <br>crushed as if a bomb had exploded within <br>his body. Despite the condolences of Karl <br>and Elsa Karenmann, Prince Charles wants <br>to shed light on his nephew’s death, with the <br>hope that doing so would dispel any shadow <br>of witchcraft and dark rituals. After all, <br>such suspicions had seen Lohr play host to a <br>relentless witch-hunt once before.<br>A Scenario Inspired by Snow <br>White (Grimm Brothers)<br>Bloodwhite’s Heart<br>Safety Keywords:  <br>Gore / Body Horror / False Accusations</p>","markdown":""},"sort":10900000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241740,"modifiedTime":1783973241740,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"PDVKFN5FbNKZy0ei","name":"Pagina 110","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 110</h2><p>109<br>The story that led us here…<br>During the witch hunt that shook the quiet village <br>of Lohr in 1603, a capable and powerful witch named Ursa <br>Radh managed to escape the clutches of the inquisition <br>for fifteen years, until 1618, when the hunt, unfortunately, <br>ended with her capture. While burning at the stake in <br>the village’s public square, Ursa cursed the lineage of the <br>Karenmanns, invoking the curse of the Restless Blood. <br>Karl’s then great-grandfather decided to walk away from <br>Lohr, hoping he would escape the curse, and he did. <br>Later on, his grandson Karl returned to Lohr, tempted by <br>promises of a good political career in the service of Prince <br>Charles Theodore. But his return to Lohr awakened Ursa’s <br>resentful spirit and the curse struck the Karenmann family. <br>Its victim was Bianca, Karl and Elsa’s firstborn daughter. <br>From an early age, she could only be satisfied with raw and <br>bloody meat. The Karenmanns kept their daughter safe <br>from prying eyes, but when Bianca grew old enough, Karl <br>couldn’t help but offer her hand in marriage to Ottone, the <br>Prince’s nephew. Arriving in Lohr, the greedy and spoiled <br>Ottone tried to consummate a relationship with naive <br>Bianca, who unintentionally made him explode to defend <br>herself, thus discovering another of the powers derived <br>from the curse. Panicked, the Karenmann spouses asked <br>Svenn, a skilled huntsman and longtime friend, for help, <br>asking him to secure the young Bianca. The man took <br>Bianca to an old mine where a group of seven Hessian <br>deserters had settled, each of whom had been on the run <br>for years because of war crimes. The seven of them, all <br>suffering from dwarfism, have accepted Bianca into their <br>ranks, swearing to keep her safe, provided the Karenmann <br>family does the same with them.<br>The story at the arrival of the <br>Hunters…<br>Karl and Elsa live in fear that the Prince may send others <br>to investigate and, in particular, the Karenmann couple <br>know about the Order and its agents who once took part <br>in the witch hunt that once befell Lohr. That is why they <br>have commissioned Svenn to prepare a trap to mislead any <br>potential investigation. Svenn targeted Bruna, an old widow <br>who lives apart from the village because many rumors point <br>to her being a witch. Svenn hid a book of witchcraft and a <br>lock of hair recovered from Ottone’s body in Bruna’s house <br>so that any investigation would lead to accusing the woman <br>of witchcraft, diverting attention from Bianca. Regarding <br>the Karenmanns’ offspring, it was announced that she left  <br>for Dresden, to enter a prestigious university. In fact, Bianca <br>lives hidden in the old mine half a day from the village, kept <br>safe by Hessian mercenaries. Bianca and the mercenaries <br>have formed a friendly relationship and the young woman <br>spends her time caring for the soldiers and preparing their <br>meals. Abel, a young man from the village who has always <br>been in love with Bianca, did not believe that the young <br>Karenmann moved to Dresden to study. Her parents’ love <br>and attachment to their daughter are well known and <br>they would never have sent her away so easily. Abel has <br>repeatedly tried to understand the mystery behind Bianca’s <br>disappearance, clashing with the indifference of the village <br>and Svenn’s veiled threats.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":11000000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241740,"modifiedTime":1783973241740,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"IknW27InDjANMguV","name":"Pagina 111","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 111</h2><p>1<br>110<br>First Scene<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: You arrive at the small village <br>of Lohr early in the morning, while most of the inhabitants are <br>busy with the many daily chores. Were it not for the macabre <br>discovery of the body of the young Ottone, Lohr would be the <br>portrait of a happy and carefree village. In front of you, right in <br>the center of the village, the Karenmann family palace stands <br>out in all its splendor.<br>Place: The village of Lohr.<br>Time: The early morning of a beautiful, sunny day.<br>Initial Situation: The Hunters are led to a meeting with <br>Karl and Elsa Karenmann.<br>Information: The Karenmann spouses will welcome the <br>Hunters with open arms, trying to appear as cooperative <br>as possible. From the interview, you can have the following <br>information, much of which is tainted by Karl and Elsa to <br>mislead any investigation.<br> ◆ The body of poor Ottone has already been returned to the <br>Prince’s messengers so that he could be taken to his family <br>to receive the funeral he deserves.<br> ◆ Ottone was found in his room, and it appears that he died <br>during the night. The body was in a gruesome condition.<br> ◆ The Karenmanns have hired Svenn, a skilled huntsman <br>and trusted person who has always provided for the <br>village. Svenn’s house is located a few minutes from the <br>Karenmann palace and the man is waiting for the Hunters <br>to share with them what he has discovered during the last <br>week of investigation.<br> ◆ The Karenmanns will carefully avoid mentioning Bianca. <br>If asked about her, they will say that their daughter has <br>moved to Dresden, eager to forget what happened and to <br>devote herself to her studies.<br>Karl and Elsa Karenmann <br>OL Medium 5 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We are two loving parents who only want what’s <br>best for Bianca. We have great wealth and allies throughout <br>Lohr.<br>Agenda: To have Ottone’s death case closed as soon as possible, <br>placing the blame on Bruna / Protect Bianca from a world that <br>could not accept her for what she is.<br>Karenmann Palace<br>Descriptor: A large and magnificent palace that contrasts <br>with the humble appearance of the rest of Lohr’s dwellings.<br>During the interview, the Hunters will realize that the palace <br>is full of paintings depicting the Karenmann family. In many <br>paintings, a beautiful girl with long black hair, snow-white <br>skin, and a pure and innocent look can be seen. From the <br>paintings the great love that unites Elsa and Karl to their <br>daughter Bianca is clear.<br>The Village of Lohr<br>Descriptor: A small village that is experiencing new prosperity <br>thanks to the Karenmann family.<br>The Hunters may hear some rumors while exploring the <br>village. Choose or roll 1 die:</p>","markdown":""},"sort":11100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241740,"modifiedTime":1783973241740,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"yNNo3KnaB3doppqm","name":"Pagina 112","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 112</h2><p>111<br>1. Ottone quickly showed himself to be a stuck-up, <br>arrogant nobleman. Many are happy that sweet <br>Bianca Karenmann no longer has to marry him.<br>2. In the past, Lohr has been at the center of the largest <br>witch hunt in all of Germany. Several stakes were left <br>in the town square as a warning to all inhabitants.<br>3. The Karenmann family administers the village with <br>care and justice. Father, mother, and daughter have <br>always been inseparable.<br>4. Old Bruna is not well-liked, ever since her husband <br>got sick and then died within a week of a strange <br>illness. Many people think that it <br>was Bruna herself who performed <br>witchcraft on her husband, to <br>punish him for being a drunk.<br>5. In years past, the large mine, <br>located just over half a day’s <br>walk away, provided jobs to <br>the villagers. Since it played <br>out, the mine has become <br>a dangerous place where <br>fugitives and deserters often <br>find shelter for the night.<br>6. Bianca is a girl of rare <br>beauty, sweet and kind to <br>everyone. She has become <br>famous in the village for her <br>commitment to helping the <br>weak and needy. Despite her <br>noble background, she never <br>hesitated to get her hands <br>dirty to help her neighbor.<br>Information: During the visit to the city, Abel will <br>approach the Hunters trying to warn them of the <br>disappearance of Bianca Karenmann, which is suspicious <br>to him.<br>Abel the Young Lover<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am a young baker who has always been in <br>love with Bianca.<br>Agenda: To find Bianca, as I cannot believe that she has <br>abandoned Lohr, nor that her parents would let her go so <br>easily.<br>Svenn’s House<br>Descriptor: A beautiful manor house, now converted <br>into a museum of hunting trophies.<br>Information: Svenn will greet the Hunters <br>with kindness, boasting that he is the man the <br>Karenmann family trusts the most. Svenn will tell <br>them of the doubts he has about Old Bruna and <br>of the fact that some secrets related to the death <br>of Ottone could be hidden in the woman’s house. <br>Svenn will advise the Hunters to act with caution, <br>so as not to alarm the inhabitants of Lohr, but he <br>will make himself available to distract the woman, <br>driving her away from home with an excuse.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":11200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241740,"modifiedTime":1783973241740,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"8UZoqAirdPqAV1JJ","name":"Pagina 113","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 113</h2><p>112<br>Svenn the Skilled Hunter<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a skilled huntsman and I boast of all the <br>prey I have bagged in my long career. I’m a man of the world <br>and I’m used to handling every situation without too many <br>scruples.<br>Agenda: To make Bruna take the blame to divert attention <br>from Bianca / Pretend to help the Hunters to make sure they <br>close the case as quickly as possible.<br>Gift – The Solver:  Svenn takes great care of solving and <br>fixing all the problems of those who offer him a job. Against <br>any attempt at mind control, gathering information, or <br>trying to intimidate him, Svenn’s OL is Hard 7. <br>Bruna’s House<br>Descriptor: A small old house with a <br>garden full of medicinal plants.<br>Information: Bruna lives alone since <br>her husband’s death. Anyone who <br>knows herbs will understand that <br>the woman has good botanical <br>knowledge. Under the bed, <br>Svenn hid a bag with a book of <br>blasphemous rituals and a lock <br>of blond hair that belonged to <br>Ottone.<br>Bruna the Poor Witch<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am a poor old woman to whom life has <br>offered only suffering. Sometimes I manifest strange powers, <br>but I have always concealed this ability out of fear of ending <br>up at the stake.<br>Agenda: To live in peace, seeking acceptance from the <br>inhabitants of Lohr.<br>Gift – Latent Witch:  Bruna has magic abilities, but <br>she never studied and uses her powers unconsciously. If <br>threatened, Bruna will activate her power and the objects <br>in the immediate vicinity will begin to move and then fall <br>upon everyone. Acting in the area affected by this power <br>confers 2 Penalties on each Check due to the uncontrolled <br>magic manifestations. If Bruna is killed, she will curse her <br>killer who, for the rest of the Scenario, will receive 1 Penalty <br>at each Defense Check. A practitioner of magic or someone <br>who can communicate with spirits can soothe Bruna’s soul <br>to undo the curse, but a Position Check will be required <br>against an OL Hard 7. <br>The Surroundings of Lohr<br>Descriptor: The village of Lohr stands on the edge of the <br>great Black Forest and is surrounded by many particular and <br>mysterious places.<br>While wandering around Lohr, the Hunters can reach one <br>of the following places. Roll a die (considering the results <br>from 1-3 as 1) or choose based on the information you want <br>to bring into play. If the Hunters move in free exploration, <br>each place is related to a cardinal direction.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":11300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241740,"modifiedTime":1783973241740,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"FCE6tXIxxG9DlLfb","name":"Pagina 114","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 114</h2><p>113<br>1. To the North of the village flows a river that the <br>inhabitants use to collect water and fish. Far from <br>prying eyes, every morning, Bianca goes to wash <br>the clothes of the Hessian mercenaries. During the <br>afternoon, you may run into them (see “The escort” <br>on the next column). At night, this is the place <br>where Elsa and Bianca meet for a hug.<br>2. Continuing North (past the river) extends a large <br>area that Svenn uses as a hunting ground. The man <br>has scattered traps in the area and it is often possible <br>to find a dying animal, Svenn not even bothering to <br>put an end to its suffering.<br>Threat – Svenn’s Traps<br>Descriptor: A series of dangerous traps cleverly positioned.<br>OL Medium 5<br>Gift – Alarms:  Svenn’s traps are all designed to cause <br>deep wounds, and failing a Defense Check means suffering <br>1 Wound. In addition, they generate a loud noise that can <br>easily alert the Hessian mercenaries in the mine and warn <br>them against potential intruders. <br>3. Further North, after Svenn’s traps, the Hunters will <br>reach the old mine (see the next column).<br>4. To the West of the village, the Hunters will come <br>across a soldier on horseback traveling to Dresden. <br>The soldier, if questioned, will say that he is bringing <br>a dispatch to the city because seven dangerous war <br>criminals have been seen in the area, fleeing after <br>having killed an officer.<br>5.  To the South, the Hunters will come across a <br>small, abandoned house. Inside, there is a thug called <br>Berno. The man is terrified and, if questioned, he will <br>reveal that, two days earlier, he and his companion <br>Folke tried to take advantage of a beautiful young girl <br>with black hair who was washing military uniforms <br>at the river. When Folke touched the young woman, <br>the man’s body first swelled and then exploded into <br>a pool of blood and guts. Berno then ran for his life, <br>without looking back.<br>6. Traveling East, the Hunters will come to the great <br>road that leads out of the forest. The remains of a <br>camp made by the Hessian mercenaries indicate that <br>someone went to the mine after recovering their <br>strength.<br>The Mine<br>Descriptor: A large, abandoned mine riddled with <br>hundreds of tunnels. Hidden by trees and plants, there is a <br>small building that used to house the head of the excavations.<br>Information: Bianca lives in the small building on the <br>top of the mine, but a tunnel dug by the Hessians allows <br>her to descend into the mine at any time. After Folke and <br>Berno’s attempted aggression, the band of Hessians will <br>divide into two groups:<br> ◆ The escort: Includes Wrath, Corpse, and Grinner. <br>They always follow Bianca when she leaves the mine <br>and will act as a guard in frequent late-night meetings <br>with her mother Elsa.<br> ◆ The guardians: Includes Crucible, Stitch, Shadow, <br>and Rookie. This group is working to turn the mine <br>into a new home, as the mercenaries have decided to <br>settle permanently in Lohr.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":11400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241741,"modifiedTime":1783973241741,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"SRdxS6et3RtFKA0c","name":"Pagina 115","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 115</h2><p>7<br>114<br>Moving around the mine without knowing it is difficult. A <br>map of the area that the mercenaries are renovating can be <br>found in the house where Bianca lives. The map is inside a <br>small chest, with a trap built by Crucible.<br>Threat – Safety Deposit Box<br>Descriptor: A small reinforced wooden box engraved with <br>strange runes.<br>OL Medium 5<br>Gift – Get Your Filthy Hands Away!:  Opening the <br>box by failing the Position Check or without using the <br>password, i.e. beer and prostitutes, causes the activation of a <br>strong electric shock that inflicts 1 Wound and alerts Stitch <br>of the attempt to break in. In this case, increase the Our <br>New Home Gift Trench Tokens by 1.<br>Threat – Mine Tunnels<br>Descriptor: A series of intricate passages that all look alike.<br>OL Medium 5<br>Gift – Our New Home:  Start the Scenario with 2 Trench <br>Tokens on this Gift to represent the defenses put in place <br>by the Hessian mercenaries. For each section of mine <br>traversed, the Storyteller must set up a Scene and the <br>mercenaries can spend 1 Trench Token to activate each of <br>these effects once per Scenario. <br>Note: To reach Bianca in the mines, it is necessary to travel <br>at least 2 sections (3 if the Hessian mercenaries use Escape!).<br>1. Escape!: The screams of the Hessians rumble between <br>the tunnels and Bianca moves away from the Hunters by 1 <br>section. <br>2. Boom!: The mercenaries cause a collapse in the passage, <br>overwhelming the Hunters, who will have to pass a Defense <br>Check against OL Hard 7 not to suffer 1 Wound. <br>3. Screw you!:  One or more mercenaries ambush the <br>Hunters from behind, starting a conflict in which at least <br>two of them act first in the Exchange.<br>4. Lights Out!:  Every source of light is blocked and the <br>Hunters find themselves in total darkness. If Shadow is <br>present, he will take advantage of it to attack the Hunters, <br>possibly taking Didi the Rookie with him. <br>The Seven Hessian Mercenaries<br>Seven skilled mercenaries, united by dwarfism syndrome, who <br>have worked with various military forces. Their condition <br>has always put them on the margins of the army, despite the <br>impressive results they’ve obtained on the battlefield. When <br>Siegbold fell ill, his execution was ordered, but the team <br>rebelled by killing all the officers present. Now the seven <br>mercenaries are wanted for war crimes and desertion.<br>Note: To facilitate the management of a group of 7 NPCs, <br>all mercenaries have the same basic profile. However, <br>everyone has an exclusive Gift that characterizes the <br>way they act. In addition, each mercenary has a different <br>ending for his Descriptor. All mercenaries are ex-soldiers <br>accustomed to war and are armed to face hand-to-hand <br>and ranged opponents. <br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (1 Wound)</p>","markdown":""},"sort":11500000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241741,"modifiedTime":1783973241741,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"wIDpChXhlQHxBfiA","name":"Pagina 116","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 116</h2><p>7<br>7<br>7<br>115<br>Descriptor: I am a capable mercenary who has experienced <br>a thousand battles and…[to be completed with the specific <br>Descriptor of each mercenary]<br>Agenda: Protect Bianca to maintain the support of the <br>Karenmann family / Transform the mine into our new home.<br>Dolf called “Crucible”<br>Descriptor: I know alchemy and magic, which I have <br>studied with interest over the years. My glasses are <br>constantly crooked.<br>Gift – Antimagus:  Crucible knows how <br>to create magical interference through <br>the use of vibrations generated by <br>slamming an iron rod on the barrel <br>of his gun. All actions involving <br>the use of spells and magic in his <br>presence receive 1 Penalty.<br>Grimbert called <br>“Wrath”<br>Descriptor: When I <br>get angry, my strength <br>doubles. I chew tobacco all <br>the time.<br>Gift – Warrior’s Fury:  <br>Wrath ignores the first <br>Wound he suffers in each <br>Scene. When he makes <br>an attack, regardless of <br>the outcome, the enemy is <br>overwhelmed by Grimbert’s fury and receives 2 Penalties to <br>their next action.<br>Siegbold called “Corpse”<br>Descriptor: My skin is hard and I have survived many <br>wounds. My body is covered in old, dirty bandages.<br>Gift – Leather Skin:  Corpse can suffer 2 additional <br>Wounds.<br>Bertold called “Stitch”<br>Descriptor: I am a good field doctor. I smell <br>of the alcohol I use to heal wounds and lighten <br>the soul.<br>Gift – It is not the Time to Die, Friend:  <br>Once per Scene, Bertold can heal 1 Wound <br>from a patient which receives care from <br>him. This can also bring someone who has <br>lost their last Wound back into the action. <br>Stani called “Shadow”<br>Descriptor: I am a perfect spy, easily <br>moving through the shadows. I hate <br>sunlight because I suffer from albinism.<br>Gift – Nocturnal:  Stani ignores any <br>penalty derived from effects that reduce <br>the ability to see and perceive an enemy. <br>This also applies to magical shrouds.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":11600000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241741,"modifiedTime":1783973241741,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"p0Tpu0i6NKwNJhw0","name":"Pagina 117","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 117</h2><p>116<br> Didi called “Rookie”<br>Descriptor: I am the youngest in the group and I am good <br>at following orders. I can never stand still, and I speak quickly, <br>words tumbling over each other.<br>Gift – Yes, Sir!: Didi is always where others need him to be. <br>Once per Scene, another mercenary can call Didi to attention, <br>making him appear in the Scene ready to execute any order. <br>Didi can follow a partner in action and imitate his deeds, and <br>thanks to this he can make use of the exclusive Gift of those <br>he is supporting. <br>Hagen called “Grinner”<br>Descriptor: I am good at torture and I know how to make <br>a prisoner talk. A conspicuous scar gives my face a perpetual <br>sneer.<br>Gift – Grim:  Hagen knows how to exploit fear and mind <br>control, so he is completely immune to it. In his presence, his <br>teammates increase their Opposition Level by 1 to resist the <br>effects of fear and mind control.<br>Bianca<br> Karenmann<br>OL Easy 3 – Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I’m a sweet young girl and I just want to live in <br>peace. The power of the curse makes me strong and resilient. <br>It also gives me the power to make living beings explode from <br>within.<br>Agenda: I want what’s best for the whole village of Lohr, even <br>if it means sacrificing myself.<br>Gift – The Curse of Bloodwhite:  Thanks to the power of <br>the curse, Bianca is stronger and more resilient than normal. <br>For this reason, at the end of each Scene she recovers 1 <br>Wound. This effect even allows Bianca to return from <br>death. Bianca’s power can detonate the body of living <br>beings and, once per Exchange, her action can inflict <br>1 automatic Wound to a target. No Defense Check is <br>allowed.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":11700000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241741,"modifiedTime":1783973241741,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"CaVjDLMJxFxUxv8c","name":"Pagina 118","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 118</h2><p>117<br>Scenario Events<br>In this Scenario, there are six Events. As a Storyteller, feel <br>free to create new ones in response to the actions of the <br>Hunters.<br>If the Hunters pay too much attention to Abel:  <br>Svenn will intervene as soon as possible by making the <br>young man disappear. Abel will be imprisoned in a pit in <br>the hunting ground.<br>If the Hunters capture Bianca: Elsa and Karl will call <br>a public assembly, trying to demonstrate to the Hunters <br>how beloved Bianca is and that she does not deserve to be <br>locked up by the Order.<br>If Bianca sees the people she cares about <br>endangered by the Hunters: she will surrender of her <br>own free will, trying to negotiate for the salvation of those <br>she loves.<br>If the Hunters openly declare that they do not <br>believe Bruna is guilty:  Karl and Elsa will make the <br>Hunters understand that they are no longer welcome in <br>Lohr and they will threaten to write a letter to the Prince <br>to complain.<br>If the Hunters defeat or capture at least three <br>Hessian mercenaries: the other mercenaries will try <br>to start a negotiation with them. It will be clear that, for <br>mercenaries, their comrades come first. <br>The first night after the arrival of the Hunters: Elsa <br>will go to the river with Svenn as her escort to meet Bianca <br>and warn her of the presence of the Hunters. <br>Scenario Gifts<br>These Gifts represent special abilities related to the <br>Bloodwhite’s Heart Scenario and can be acquired once the <br>conditions are met. A Hunter can only have one Scenario <br>Gift and if they acquire a new one, they will have to forgo <br>the previous one.<br>Gift – Stake’s Spirit<br>Requirement: Examine the old stakes in the square of <br>Lohr or show interest in the past history of witch-hunting.<br>Y ou are aware of the magical power that resides in the <br>village of Lohr and of the extent of the tragic witch trials <br>it once hosted. Once per Scene, you can open your mind <br>to the spirits of the dead witches. Spend 1 Soma and ask <br>a question about the village, one of the inhabitants, or the <br>surrounding areas. The Storyteller will answer with useful <br>information, but keep in mind that it will be conditioned by <br>the witch’s hatred of this place.<br>Gift – One of Us<br>Requirement: Defeat and spare one or more of the Hessian <br>mercenaries.<br>Y ou defeated the fearsome Hessian mercenaries and <br>earned their respect. Once per Scenario, you can call the <br>team to your rescue, and they will arrive in no time. The <br>Hessian mercenaries will act to help you within their NPC <br>capabilities for the current Scene, and then retreat to start <br>brewing some trouble in your location. This Gift can be <br>maintained in all future Scenarios and does not count <br>towards the maximum of the Gifts you have available.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":11800000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241741,"modifiedTime":1783973241741,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"p5NxynoAITbnNzx0","name":"Pagina 119","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 119</h2><p>1<br>2<br>3a<br>118<br>The Scenario <br>Bloodwhite’s Heart <br>in Scenes <br>FIRST SCENE –  Arrival in Lohr<br>It’s the same one you find on page 110. After the interview <br>with the Karenmanns, the Hunters go to Svenn to talk about <br>his investigation. Before arriving, Abel will intercept the <br>Hunters, revealing his doubts about Bianca’s departure.<br>End of Scene:  The Hunters meet Svenn. Go to THE <br>SECOND SCENE – The huntsman.<br>SECOND SCENE – The huntsman<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: Svenn’s house is a few minutes <br>from the Karenmann palace. With the words of the young Abel <br>still in your head, you find yourself in front of a once lovely <br>mansion. Unfortunately, the trophies of Svenn’s hunting skills <br>spoil its beauty from the entrance: a huge, tacky stuffed bear is <br>placed next to the door. <br>Place: Svenn the huntsman’s house.<br>Time: Mid-morning.<br>Information: Svenn will welcome the Hunters inside <br>the house and will describe everything he has “discovered. ” <br>He’ll also eagerly volunteer to distract Bruna with an excuse, <br>luring her away from her home. When asked about Bianca <br>and Abel, he will say that the young man is the classic loser <br>who fell in love with a girl to whom he should not even speak.<br>End of Scene:  If the Hunters trust Svenn, go to THIRD <br>SCENE OPTION A – Witch hunt , if instead, they decide to <br>search the surroundings of Lohr as requested by Abel, go to <br>THIRD SCENE OPTION B – The river. <br>THIRD SCENE OPTION A –  <br>Witch hunt<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: Entering Bruna’s small and old <br>house isn’t difficult for you. Apart from an abundant garden <br>full of medicinal herbs, little of what you see qualifies as proof <br>that this is the home of a witch. But, maybe you just have to <br>look more closely...<br>Place: Bruna’s crumbling house.<br>Time: It is late afternoon when Svenn sends for Bruna to ask <br>her for advice on some herbs he found in the woods.<br>Information: Searching the house, it will be easy to discover <br>a bag under the bed, inside of which is a book about magic <br>and a lock of blonde hair. Taking the evidence to Svenn, he <br>will confirm that the hair color is the same as that of Ottone’s <br>and that the young scion kept his hair tied in a tail (which, <br>coincidentally, was cut from the corpse).<br> ◆ If the Hunters have no doubts, Svenn will have Bruna <br>removed from the house, and accuse her of witchcraft. <br>Elsa and Karl will congratulate them on the speed with <br>which they have solved the case. <br> ◆ Convinced or not, Abel will approach the Hunters to <br>tell them he made a macabre discovery as he searched <br>the outskirts of the village for tracks. He’ll make an <br>appointment with them after sundown to avoid Svenn’s <br>attention.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":11900000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241741,"modifiedTime":1783973241741,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Njpoc48Z9Bm5ZMiK","name":"Pagina 120","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 120</h2><p>3b<br>119<br> ◆ If they go along, it will be clear to the Hunters that <br>they are no longer welcome in Lohr, and that from this <br>moment on, their stay is no longer viewed favorably by <br>the Karenmanns.<br>End of Scene: Shortly before sunset, Abel will contact the <br>Hunters saying that some very suspicious deserters have <br>settled at the old mine and that the mine would be a perfect <br>place to keep someone in captivity. Go to THE FOURTH <br>SCENE – The mine.<br>THIRD SCENE OPTION B –  <br>The river<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  To the north flows a large <br>river, which separates the inhabited part of the village from <br>the old mine. Abel told you that the mine is now abandoned <br>and that it is often used as a refuge for fleeing deserters and <br>thugs. Your attention is drawn by a melodious voice, a young <br>girl with long black hair is washing military uniforms at the <br>river. Even if you cannot see her well, the resemblance to the <br>daughter of the Karenmanns that you saw in the paintings of <br>the palace is quite striking. Noticing your presence, the young <br>woman flees to the mine while three short, squat men come out <br>of the bush to block your way.<br>Place: The river that flows between the village of Lohr and <br>the abandoned mine.<br>Time: It is early afternoon. <br>Information: The Hessian mercenary escort group (page <br>113) will instruct the Hunters to go somewhere else, making <br>it clear that the mine is now to be considered their property. <br>If they are overwhelmed or outnumbered, the mercenaries <br>will call Rookie for support. However, it is not the intention</p>","markdown":""},"sort":12000000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241741,"modifiedTime":1783973241741,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"asebFuQB5mAr2Fdp","name":"Pagina 121","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 121</h2><p>120<br>of the Hessians to enter into conflict with the Hunters and <br>if asked about who the girl is, they will say that it is a young <br>woman from the village whom they pay to do some chores. <br> ◆ If the Hunters get into a fight, Svenn will arrive after <br>one Exchange, trying to put an end to the hostilities. <br>The huntsman will instruct the Hunters not to seek <br>trouble with the group of mercenaries who are “passing <br>through, ” and will tell the mercenaries that they have <br>a day to “get out of the way. ” The Hunters will catch <br>a clear look of understanding between Svenn and the <br>mercenaries.<br> ◆ If the Hunters return to report, both Svenn and the <br>Karenmanns will attempt to divert attention from the <br>mine, prompting the Hunters to investigate Bruna. <br>End of Scene:  If the Hunters trust Svenn, go to THIRD <br>SCENE OPTION A – Witch hunt , if they decide to <br>investigate the girl at the mine, go to FOURTH SCENE – <br>The mine.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":12100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241741,"modifiedTime":1783973241741,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"7qhJe6THRA18SQBb","name":"Pagina 122","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 122</h2><p>54<br>121<br>FOURTH SCENE –  The mine<br>This Scene can be reached in different ways, but once <br>they get to the mine it will be clear to the Hunters that the <br>Hessians keep Bianca Karenmann with them. The mine <br>must be managed as indicated on page 113, taking into <br>account the intentions and strategies of the Hunters.<br>Place: The old abandoned mine near Lohr.<br>Time: The sun is setting.<br>Information:<br> ◆ The Hessians will fight to the death if necessary, but <br>Bianca herself will surrender if the Hunters seem to be <br>getting the better of the situation.<br> ◆ Bianca will confess to everything if faced with the <br>staging that her parents created to save her, especially <br>if this can prevent an innocent woman like Bruna from <br>an unjust accusation.<br>End of Scene:  The Hunters retrieve Bianca Karenmann <br>and return to Lohr, go to the FIFTH SCENE – The trial.<br>FIFTH SCENE –  The trial<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  When you return to Lohr <br>with Bianca, all eyes of the village are on you. The smiles and <br>greetings with which the inhabitants welcome Bianca are a <br>clear sign of how much the daughter of the Karenmanns is <br>loved and esteemed. Arriving at the central square, Elsa and <br>Karl await you with a group of armed guards. There is no <br>hatred in their eyes, but only the concern given by a parent’s <br>love for their daughter.<br>Place: The central square of Lohr, near the old stakes <br>where witches were bound and burned still stands as a <br>warning to all the inhabitants.<br>Time: The sun has just risen, after a night of clashes at the <br>mine.<br>Information: Elsa and Karl will go all-in by asking the <br>Hunters not to imprison their beloved daughter. The two <br>nobles will be supported by the testimonies of the villagers. <br>It will quickly become clear that everyone considers Bianca <br>a pure and kind soul.<br>End of Scene: It will be up to the Hunters to decide the <br>fate of Bianca Karenmann.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":12200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241741,"modifiedTime":1783973241741,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"ji1jJKkma5LUoO0T","name":"Pagina 123","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 123</h2><p>122<br>Once upon a time…<br>The Papal State. Father Cristoforo, ministering <br>to the city of Capodimonte, wrote to the Papacy <br>to request the intervention of a group of Hunters. <br>Several years ago, the formerly abandoned <br>convent on Martana Island became the home of <br>a mysterious cult called the House of Roses. It is <br>sponsored by the rich Dionysus Gonsalva, heir to <br>the family that has always lived in Capodimonte, <br>a town on the shores of Lake Bolsena. Many <br>young girls in the area have left their families to <br>go to Martana Island, severing all ties with their <br>past. It seems that this blasphemous cult is led by <br>a mysterious priestess, but access to the island is <br>prohibited by order of the Gonsalva family. Given <br>the excellent relations between the Gonsalva <br>family and the Papacy, the Hunters must go to <br>Capodimonte and seek permission to access the <br>island.<br>A Scenario Inspired by <br>Beauty and the Beast <br>(Jeanne-Marie Leprince de <br>Beaumont)<br>The House of Roses<br>Safety Keywords:  <br>Animalistic Savagery / Cult / <br>Brainwashing / Drugs / Reduced <br>Inhibitions</p>","markdown":""},"sort":12300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241741,"modifiedTime":1783973241741,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"E3dPsHwcbLHuKZdW","name":"Pagina 124","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 124</h2><p>123<br>The story that led us here…<br>Dionysus Gonsalva is a young noble, victim of a <br>curse that has deformed his body and made him monstrous. <br>He is always in search of a bride, as he has been through <br>several over the years. The marriage has always ended in <br>blood when the bride first sees her prospective husband and <br>rejects Dionysus in horror. Bellina Cantalupo (known as <br>Bella) is a humble but ambitious servant who arrived at the <br>Gonsalva court in service to Marianna De Rossi, Dionysus’ <br>most recently deceased wife. Bella soon sensed the distress <br>of her lord and, without a second thought, worked her way <br>into his good graces to become his secret lover. Despite the <br>disgust she feels for Dionysus, Bella beguiled her lord with <br>the promise of true love. She also convinced him to move <br>to the old, abandoned monastery of Martana Island. The <br>two then founded the House of Roses, a place to welcome <br>young girls in search of a life away from the poverty that <br>plagues the current era. In the House of Roses, the young <br>novices are cared for and pampered, unaware that once <br>a month, one of them will be sacrificed to Dionysius to <br>appease his distorted need for love. Bella even arranged for <br>her two sisters, Francesca and Letizia, to join her in the cult. <br>She had always envied their beauty and planned for both of <br>them to be torn apart by her captive lover. Francesca, the <br>older sister, saw the true nature of Dionysus when he was <br>unleashed against Letizia. She escaped and now roams the <br>island, hunted by the servants of Dionysus, waiting for the <br>chance to escape.<br>The story at the arrival of the <br>Hunters…<br>Capodimonte. Pietro Gonsalva, head of the noble family, <br>receives more and more complaints from the population <br>due to the continuous disappearance of young girls, who <br>flee to the House of Roses in search of a comfortable life. <br>Mere months after its foundation, the House of Roses <br>has become so famous as to attract young people from all <br>over Italy. Although Pietro does not know what is really <br>happening on Martana Island, the delusional letters of <br>his son Dionysus have made him worried. Now the old <br>nobleman hopes that an outside authority (such as the <br>Hunters) will take care of the situation.<br>Francesca hides in the dense vegetation of the island, <br>unable to leave it by swimming because the waters of the <br>lake are too cold in the middle of winter. The poor fugitive <br>keeps an eye on the pier in the hope of being able to secretly <br>embark on one of the ships that, after unloading the new <br>arrivals, returns to Capodimonte. In the House of Roses, <br>Bellina is consumed with anger at her sister’s escape and <br>now has total control over Dionysus’ psyche, treating him <br>like an animal. Bellina is surrounded by faithful servants, <br>all brainwashed to serve her as a goddess, and maintains <br>control over the island thanks to a pack of trained mastiffs <br>that obey Dionysus due to his bestial curse.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":12400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241741,"modifiedTime":1783973241741,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"iPaOerGnyLIg8ipU","name":"Pagina 125","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 125</h2><p>1<br>124<br>First Scene<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  Capodimonte is a rich city <br>near Lake Bolsena that, thanks to the huge investments of the <br>noble Gonsalva family, has grown quite prosperous. After a <br>few minutes’ walk, you come across the church of San Carlo, <br>the smallest in the city, amidst small shops packed with busy <br>apprentices. Now you just have to decide whether to enter to <br>meet Father Cristoforo or first introduce yourself to the noble <br>Pietro Gonsalva, the regent of the city.<br>Place: The rich and prosperous city of Capodimonte.<br>Time: It is a cold morning.<br>Initial Situation: Hunters can decide who to meet and in <br>what order between the noble Pietro Gonsalva (at the city’s <br>fortress) and Father Cristoforo (in the small church of San <br>Carlo). Both men will have information about the House of <br>Roses, bringing a different point of view to the attention of <br>the Hunters.<br>Capodimonte<br>Descriptor: A rich and prosperous city protected by the Papal <br>State.<br>Pietro Gonsalva Regent of <br>Capodimonte<br>OL Medium 5 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am a rich and powerful nobleman, and I have <br>managed to ingratiate myself with the Papal State. I love being <br>in charge, but over time I’ve learned to trust those who are more <br>experienced than I am.<br>Agenda: Preserve the House of Roses because it is the first <br>place where Dionysus appears to be restrained / Not to lose the <br>advantageous agreements made with the Church.<br>Information from the conversation with Pietro:  <br>The Regent of Capodimonte will welcome the Hunters with <br>all honors, praising their importance to the Church and for <br>humanity’ salvation. Pietro is sincerely respectful of the work <br>of the Order. <br> ◆ Pietro will say that the island was once a monastery and <br>that, thanks to the efforts of his son Dionysus, it has now <br>returned to a renewed splendor.<br> ◆ Martana Island has become a place of worship, where <br>people can take refuge and contemplate God.<br> ◆ Pietro cares a lot about the House of Roses because <br>his son Dionysus is suffering from a rare disease that <br>covers his whole body with hair and, unfortunately, his <br>monstrous aspect is not accepted by society. To Pietro, it</p>","markdown":""},"sort":12500000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241741,"modifiedTime":1783973241741,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"RJEBh9JVUYndo3wv","name":"Pagina 126","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 126</h2><p>125<br>seems the island is the only place Dionysus has ever <br>been judged for the good he can do and not for his <br>fearsome appearance.<br> ◆ At the end of the interview, it will be clear to the Hunters <br>that Pietro has no idea of what life is like on the island, <br>he has never been there and, because of the many <br>diplomatic involvements around it, he has no interest <br>in discovering more. For the reasons mentioned above, <br>Pietro will make sure the Hunters understand that the <br>House of Roses must remain active.<br> ◆ With great generosity, Pietro will offer the Hunters a <br>boat that will take them to the island in the afternoon.<br>Father Cristoforo<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am a humble provincial priest and I have <br>been responsible for the religious education of the Gonsalvas <br>for years. <br>Agenda: I have reason to believe that the House of Roses is <br>a place of blasphemy and damnation, so I want the Church <br>to investigate.<br>Information from the conversation with <br>Cristoforo: The humble priest will welcome the Hunters <br>in the small church of San Carlo. The man will show <br>reverence to the work of the Order and will seem aware of <br>who the Hunters really are.<br> ◆ Cristoforo will say that the island once was a <br>monastery where the residents dedicated themselves to <br>blasphemous rites. The Church intervened by putting <br>them all at the stake.<br> ◆ Martana Island is a name on the lips of many young <br>people, who tell of a place of feasts and pleasures far <br>from the severe but holy eye of God. Many young women <br>go out of their way to get to sail to the island. <br> ◆ Cristoforo taught the ways of God to the unfortunate <br>Dionysus, being troubled by the savagery that the young <br>man struggled to control. <br> ◆ At the end of the interview, it will be clear to the Hunters <br>that Cristoforo does not really know what is happening on <br>the island, but he is firmly convinced that it is nothing good.<br> ◆ Trying not to be overheard by prying ears, Cristoforo will <br>tell the Hunters that a couple of faithful friends have a small <br>boat and can take the Hunters to the island at night, landing <br>on a little-used beach. <br>Martana Island<br>Descriptor: A small island in the center of Lake Bolsena. Covered <br>mostly by dense vegetation, the island includes a sanctuary, a <br>small pier, and a mansion recently built by the Gonsalvas.<br>There are five locations available on the island:<br> ◆ The Pier: Where all ships arriving from Capodimonte dock. <br>The pier is under the control of Bella and her worshippers. <br>If the Hunters accept Pietro Gonsalva’s transportation offer, <br>they will arrive there in the late afternoon.<br> ◆ The White Beach: A small beach of rocks and earth to the <br>east of the island. It is located on the opposite side of the <br>island from the few inhabited places. If the Hunters accept <br>Father Cristoforo’s offer of transportation, they will reach <br>the beach at night.<br> ◆ The Sanctuary: All the young people who have become <br>prisoners of the House of Roses live here.<br> ◆ The Mansion: The House of Roses is a sumptuous villa that <br>Dionysus had built for Bella.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":12600000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241741,"modifiedTime":1783973241741,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"h5AxcOf18ipq00o1","name":"Pagina 127","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 127</h2><p>126<br> ◆ The Forest: A large wooded area where Dionysus’ <br>Mastiffs roam. In the thick of the forest, there is a <br>mass grave where Bella dumps the bodies of the <br>Beast’s unfortunate victims.<br>The Pier<br>Descriptor: A small pier with a watchtower.<br>Information: At the pier there are always 8 Servants, <br>armed and ready to welcome every arrival. In the guard <br>tower there are 6 other Servants equipped with firearms.<br>Bella’s Servants <br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We are young people in the service of Bella <br>and we are trained to defend the House <br>of Roses. <br>Agenda: Follow all of Bella’s <br>orders to the letter. <br>Gift – For Our Lady:  The Servants are brainwashed <br>and totally dependent on Bella. Every attempt to scare or <br>mentally manipulate them receives 2 Penalties. If Bella <br>is targeted by a threat, once per Exchange, a Servant can <br>sacrifice themselves to take the hit in her place. <br>The White Beach<br>Descriptor: A small beach of pebbles and earth hidden <br>among the dense vegetation.<br>Information: Docking at the beach without the <br>necessary precautions will attract 1d6+2 Mastiffs.<br>The Forest<br>Descriptor: A large wooded area that almost entirely <br>covers Martana Island.<br>Information: The forest is overrun by mastiffs loyal to <br>Dionysus. Avoiding them requires overcoming the Pack of <br>Mastiffs Threat. In case of a Failure, 8 Mastiffs will appear <br>and surround the intruders. At the center of the forest is <br>a mass grave where the bodies of Dionysus’ victims are <br>dumped. Francesca hides in the pit to escape the hungry <br>dogs.<br>Threat – Pack of Mastiffs<br>OL Medium 5 <br>Descriptor: We patrol the forest, looking for intruders. No <br>one can escape our sense of smell.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":12700000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241741,"modifiedTime":1783973241741,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"XgtTLh3zAAWc7msh","name":"Pagina 128","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 128</h2><p>127<br>Dionysus’ Mastiffs<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We are big and fierce mastiffs loyal to our <br>leader, Dionysus.<br>Agenda: Hunt down any intruders arriving on the island.<br>Gift – Pack:  Any action taken while surrounded by 2 <br>or more Mastiffs receives 1 Penalty. A Mastiff can use its <br>action to howl and alert Dionysus, who will arrive within <br>2 Exchanges.<br>Francesca Cantalupo<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am Bellina’s sister, the eldest of three.<br>Agenda: Flee the island to return to my father / Avenge <br>Letizia’s death and punish Bellina for always being a selfish, <br>jealous child.<br>The Sanctuary<br>Descriptor: An ancient monastery converted into a small <br>pleasure town. <br>Information: 20 Handmaids and 10 Servants are <br>always present in the Sanctuary. All the inhabitants of the <br>Sanctuary live surrounded by food and pleasures of the <br>flesh, in a state of constant and perverse ecstasy. Bella adds <br>drugs to both food and drinks so that the inhabitants of the <br>Sanctuary lose their inhibitions.<br>Threat – The Food of the Gods<br>OL Medium 5 <br>Descriptor: All the food in the Sanctuary is tainted with a <br>powerful drug that loosens one’s inhibitions.<br>Gift – The Drug of the True Self:  Whoever eats food <br>treated with this powerful drug loses all inhibition. Anyone <br>who fails the Defense Check to resist the effect receives 2 <br>Drug Tokens. During a Scene, the Storyteller can spend 1 <br>Drug Token to activate one of the following effects. 1. The <br>True Self: Immediately activates the Hunter’s Dark Ego <br>without them suffering the Wound generated by not using <br>the Activator. 2. Dulled Senses: The Storyteller decides <br>what type of Outcome the Hunter is aiming for after they <br>have declared an action. <br>Bella’s Handmaids <br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We are young girls loyal to our lady. We are <br>ready to have a good time – anytime.<br>Agenda: We have tasted happiness in the House of Roses <br>and we will not allow anyone to take us back to our former, <br>miserable lives.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":12800000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241741,"modifiedTime":1783973241741,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"3wwKxp8oqhU7rcTs","name":"Pagina 129","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 129</h2><p>128<br>The Mansion also known as the <br>House of Roses<br>Descriptor: A large and rich mansion, with a wide garden, <br>a hedge maze, and beautiful red roses.<br>Information: Bella lives in the Mansion where 8 Servants <br>are executing any of their lady’s wishes. Dionysus lives in <br>the cellars of the estate and only goes out at night or when <br>his Mastiffs get his attention.    <br>Threat – Hedge Labyrinth<br>OL Medium 5 <br>Descriptor: A large labyrinth of hedges and roses that <br>extends throughout the estate garden. <br>Gift – Secret Passage:  Bellina and Dionysus know a <br>series of secret passages to avoid wasting time in the maze. <br>Anyone else might need several hours to negotiate it.   <br>Bellina Cantalupo known as Bella<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a cunning manipulator and the only queen of the House of Roses. I <br>take advantage of the power I wield whenever I have the chance.<br>Agenda: Increase the influence of the House of Roses at any cost / Getting rid of <br>Dionysus, but without destroying the House of Roses.<br>Gift – Manipulative:  During a Scene, if Bella has enough time to talk to a <br>subject, she will learn a secret about them, such as a Descriptor or <br>their Gift. Bella is immune to any kind of mental manipulation <br>or fear. <br>Gift – My Beast:  If Bella is in danger, Dionysus will come <br>to her rescue within 1 Exchange. To help Bella, Dionysus <br>can free himself from any kind of impediment, whether <br>physical or mental. Nothing can stop Dionysus, who <br>will break through doors and walls if necessary.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":12900000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241741,"modifiedTime":1783973241741,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"WGA0g81nz6kPwRL7","name":"Pagina 130","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 130</h2><p>129<br>Dioniso Gonsalva called the <br>Beast<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (4 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a young man afflicted by a curse <br>that turned me into a fierce beast. Only Bella’s scent <br>keeps my incredible ferocity in check.<br>Agenda: I would like to live alone with Bella <br>in this paradise, and I only tolerate the House <br>of Roses for the sake of my love for her / I <br>would like to show the full extent of my love <br>to Bella, but until she gives herself to me, I <br>will have to take my frustration out on <br>her handmaids.<br>Gift – The Beast:  Dionysus can <br>act twice during an Exchange. When <br>moving, Dionysus can jump up to thirty <br>feet and easily destroy any obstacle. <br>When acting to save Bella, Dionysus <br>increases his Opposition Level by 1.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":13000000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241741,"modifiedTime":1783973241741,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"sjxzWPh8qNr9fXXf","name":"Pagina 131","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 131</h2><p>130<br>Scenario Events<br>In this Scenario there are five Events. As a Storyteller, feel free <br>to create new ones in response to the actions of the Hunters.<br>If the Hunters capture Bella:  the Lady of the House of <br>Roses will threaten to unleash Dionysus’ wrath on all the <br>innocents on the island. Bella will demand that the Hunters <br>release her, while trying to negotiate a deal that works for <br>everyone.<br>If the Hunters kill Dionysus:  Bella will thank them by <br>telling them that it was all the fault of the mad nobleman <br>who forced her to do everything. Her aim is to escape the <br>judgment of the Church by passing herself off as a victim.<br>If the Hunters find Francesca:  the young woman will <br>describe how all the Handmaids ignore what truly happens <br>to Bella’s chosen ones. Francesca will tell the Hunters who <br>Bellina really is, and how she brainwashed everyone on the <br>island thanks to her position of power and the drugs in the <br>food.<br>If the Hunters officially show up at the pier:  Bella <br>will welcome them with all honors by offering them food <br>and drinks. Bella’s purpose is to gather information about <br>the newcomers and then feed them to Dionysus one by one.<br>If the Hunters accuse Bella or Dionysus:  Bella will <br>seek an advantageous agreement by mentioning that the <br>Gonsalva family is one of the greatest supporters of the <br>Papacy, and that a scandal could end the huge subsidies that <br>Pietro regularly pays to Rome. <br>Scenario Gifts<br>These Gifts represent special abilities related to the The <br>House of Roses Scenario and can be acquired once the <br>requirements are met. A Hunter can only have one Scenario <br>Gift and if they acquire a new one, they will have to forgo the <br>previous one.<br>Gift – Faithful Mastiffs<br>Requirement: Have defeated one or more of Dionysus’ <br>Mastiffs.<br>Y ou defeated the Mastiffs, proving you are a worthy pack <br>leader. Y ou gain 1 Mastiff who follows you as a faithful <br>companion. Y ou can spend 1 Soma to assign a task to your <br>Mastiff for the rest of the Scene. 1. Find: The Mastiff can <br>track an object or a person if you are able to provide it with <br>a sample of its smell; 2. Defend: The Mastiff stands in your <br>defense, granting you 1 Additional Success in all Defense <br>Checks. In case of an Outcome with a Cost, the Mastiff  <br>will die taking the blow in your place as a Cost; 3. Attack: <br>The Mastiff attacks the enemy you point to, reducing their <br>Opposition Level by 1 for the course of the Exchange. Each <br>time you use this effect, roll a die. With 4+ the Mastiff is <br>killed in the action. If your Mastiff is killed, you can get <br>another one at the beginning of the next Scene.<br>Gift - Uncovering Deceptions<br>Requirement: You know how to expose a charlatan and lay <br>bare lies.<br>All NPCs who possess a Descriptor, Gift, or Agenda that has <br>to do with lying or deceiving others reduce their Opposition <br>Level by 1 in your presence. When you’re around, you also <br>weaken their followers: once per Scene you can prevent a <br>subject from using a Gift that depends on using or sacrificing <br>a follower.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":13100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241742,"modifiedTime":1783973241742,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"XbFlvO4KBf39KELA","name":"Pagina 132","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 132</h2><p>1<br>2a<br>131<br>The Scenario The <br>House of Roses in <br>Scenes <br>FIRST SCENE –  Arrival at <br>Capodimonte<br>It’s the same one you find on page 124. The Hunters will <br>go first to interview Pietro Gonsalva and then to Father <br>Cristoforo.<br>End of Scene:  Hunters can decide whether to land on <br>the island through the passage offered by Pietro, go to <br>SECOND SCENE OPTION A – The pier. Or land secretly <br>thanks to the help of Cristoforo, go to SECOND SCENE <br>OPTION B – The White Beach.<br>SECOND SCENE OPTION A <br>– The pier<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: In less than an hour’s sailing, <br>you can already see the shape of Martana Island looming in <br>front of you. The boat arrives in a small covered port, where <br>you find a large group of men with smiling faces waiting for <br>you, though it’s difficult to ignore the weapons they carry. <br>A young girl with wavy brown hair seems to be the person <br>in charge, and when you get off the boat, she greets you, <br>smiling. “I am Bella Cantalupo, and I serve my lord Dionysus <br>Gonsalva so that the House of Roses may be a place of peace <br>and prayer. Please be our guests for at least one night. ” Bella <br>beckons you to follow her to what appears to be a completely <br>renovated monastery.<br>Place: Martana Island’s pier.<br>Time: It is almost time for dinner.<br>Information: Bella will be extremely helpful with the <br>Hunters, trying to answer all their questions. The woman’s <br>goal is to impede the investigation and pass the House of <br>Roses off as a place of worship and peace.<br> ◆ If the Hunters ask her about Dionysus, Bella will say <br>that her master shuns situations in which there are <br>many people because of his appearance. Bella takes <br>care of everything, but if the Hunters want to, she will <br>set up an interview with Dionysus.<br> ◆ Bella will highlight the peace and prosperity in which <br>servants and handmaids live, and all the young people <br>will be helpful and happy.<br> ◆ Bella will invite the Hunters to stay for the night and <br>organize a banquet in their honor. The Hunters will <br>be asked to stay within Sanctuary so as not to risk <br>provoking the many mastiffs that Dionysus breeds in <br>the forest.<br> ◆ The Mansion is reserved for Dionysus, and for this <br>reason it is inaccessible to the Hunters. Sneaking into <br>it, you will find ample supplies of Mandrake and other <br>herbs useful to produce drugs. <br> ◆ Bella will watch the Hunters closely, always maintaining <br>her fake, friendly smile. <br>End of Scene:  After talking to Bella and seeing the <br>Sanctuary, the Hunters will be invited to a banquet set up <br>just for them. Go to THIRD SCENE OPTION A – Welcome <br>guests.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":13200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241742,"modifiedTime":1783973241742,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Xh4CffxLzKUbyg0G","name":"Pagina 133","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 133</h2><p>3a 3b<br>2b<br>132<br>SECOND SCENE OPTION B  – <br>The White Beach<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: You land on a small beach of <br>pebbles and mud. As soon as you step off the boat, the sailors <br>hastily set sail once more, making the sign of the cross. Only a <br>few seconds pass before you hear growls and howls. Apparently, <br>a wolf or dog pack is moving towards you, attracted by your <br>smell.<br>Place: A small beach on Martana Island.<br>Time: It is almost time for dinner.<br>Information: A group of 8 Mastiffs will try to intercept <br>the Hunters and, if the clash begins, they will immediately <br>howl to summon Dionysus. The beastly lord of the island <br>will attack without hesitation but will flee after suffering 2 <br>Wounds. If, on the other hand, the Hunters manage to hide <br>from the pack of Mastiffs, they will see Dionysus coming and <br>will be able to observe him in all his savagery. Dionysus will <br>remain for a few minutes before leaving and returning to the <br>Mansion.<br>End of Scene:  Having faced or avoided the Mastiffs, the <br>Hunters will come across the mass grave, go to THIRD <br>SCENE OPTION B – Unwanted guests.<br>THIRD SCENE OPTION A –  <br>Welcome guests<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  The banquet Bella has set up <br>for you is sumptuous to say the least. Wine and delicacies of <br>all kinds cover the great table of the Sanctuary, while around <br>you, servants and handmaids dance and sip wine, indulging <br>in the pleasures of the evening. Even Bella seems particularly <br>euphoric, inviting you to enjoy the fine things her generous lord <br>Dionysus has to offer. <br>Place: The Sanctuary of the island.<br>Time: The sun has just gone down.<br>Information: Bella will try to drug the Hunters to lower <br>their defenses and discover how much of a threat they are. If <br>the Hunters insist on meeting Dionysus, Bella will ask that <br>only one of them go, since her lord is not accustomed to being <br>seen by many people at once. If the Hunters consent, the <br>chosen one will be taken to the Mansion’s rose garden, where <br>Dionysus will attack, trying to kill them. If the Hunters keep <br>a low-profile during dinner, at some point Bella will be called <br>away by a servant to deal with an emergency. The Hunters <br>will be able to see concern in the eyes of the young woman, <br>since Dionysus is having one of his fits and needs to consume <br>one of the handmaids to appease himself. Bella will take a <br>girl with her, saying goodbye to the Hunters. Following Bella <br>will require overcoming two groups of 8 Servants, which the <br>woman will put on the road between the Sanctuary and the <br>Mansion.<br>End of Scene:  The Hunters now clearly understand that <br>something dark animates Bella’s actions, and they arrive at <br>the Mansion to witness the sacrifice, go to the FOURTH <br>SCENE – The sacrifice.<br>THIRD SCENE OPTION B – <br>Unwanted Guests<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  You have overcome the <br>terrible Mastiffs patrolling the forest and, as you cross the <br>rugged woodland, a nauseating smell draws your attention. A <br>little more than ten meters away, a large grave contains the <br>bodies of a multitude of young girls, all horribly mutilated, as <br>if a ferocious creature had devoured them. Suddenly, one of the <br>girls seems to be moving, making a soft cry.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":13300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241742,"modifiedTime":1783973241742,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"WTav3pKDj3SbrPPA","name":"Pagina 134","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 134</h2><p>4<br>5<br>133<br>Place: The mass grave in the middle of the island’s Forest.<br>Time: It is night, and a soft moonlight filters through the <br>branches of the trees.<br>Information: It will be possible to find Francesca within <br>the pit, looking worn and on the edge of madness. The young <br>woman will describe all the crimes Bellina has committed and <br>how Letizia was sacrificed to the fury of Dionysus. The young <br>woman’s only wish is to run away but, if the Hunters play on <br>her anger, she will ask to follow them to avenge her dead sister. <br>Francesca’s voice is known to the Mastiffs, and within a short <br>time, a pack of 8 will reach the pit, led by Dionysus. In the <br>event of a confrontation, the beastly noble will do everything <br>he can to kill Francesca. As in the previous clash, Dionysus <br>will flee as soon as he receives the second Wound.<br>End of Scene: Once Bellina’s faults have been discovered, the <br>Hunters can move to the Mansion to capture her. Go to THE <br>FOURTH SCENE – The sacrifice.<br>FOURTH SCENE – The sacrifice<br>There are two ways to get to this Scene.<br>From the banquet: The Hunters follow Bella and catch her <br>red-handed as she prepares to feed Dionysus an unsuspecting <br>handmaid.<br>From the grave:  The Hunters arrive at the garden of <br>the Mansion led by Francesca just as Bella prepares to feed <br>Dionysus an unsuspecting handmaid.<br>Place: The rose garden of the Mansion.<br>Time: It is night, and only the full moon illuminates the small <br>labyrinth of hedges and roses.<br>Information: The ritual consists of bringing the handmaid <br>to the center of the maze of hedges, and then letting Dionysus <br>unleash his desires. Only Bella and Dionysus are present at the <br>rite, since none of the servants or handmaids must discover <br>the truth. If the Hunters intervene, Bella will not hesitate to <br>unleash Dionysus against them. While they battle, she will <br>flee to the Sanctuary to stir up all the servants and handmaids <br>against the Hunters, accusing them of having been sent by the <br>Papacy to end the House of Roses.<br>End of Scene:  After facing Dionysus, the Hunters must <br>handle Bella who sends all the inhabitants of the island against <br>them. Go to SCENE FIVE – Face to face.<br>FIFTH SCENE – Face to face<br>This Scene can have many variables, based on what the <br>Hunters have discovered so far. There will be 20 Servants and <br>20 Handmaids in the Scene.<br>Place: The Sanctuary.<br>Time: It is late at night and the only light is cast by the banquet <br>bonfires.<br>Information: Bella will use all her influence to cast the <br>Hunters in a bad light, also accusing them of the attempted <br>(or successful) murder of Dionysus, the one who has been <br>supporting everyone at the House of Roses. Bella will make <br>the Hunters understand that she is willing to come to terms <br>with them, but her power of manipulation is very strong and <br>she can do with the innocents who live on the island as she <br>likes.<br>End of Scene: Bella will be determined not to lose the power <br>she has gained and has an entire island at her command. The <br>Hunters will have to play their cards well to put an end to the <br>House of Roses once and for all.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":13400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241742,"modifiedTime":1783973241742,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"2l1A4C8KkSg3nY5x","name":"Pagina 135","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 135</h2><p>134<br>Once upon a time…<br>The Hunters are sent to Sweden to <br>investigate the mysterious Stegeborg <br>Castle. The property, once run by the <br>Schwernis family, has been abandoned <br>for decades. The surrounding villages <br>had survived the departure of the noble <br>family, remaining populated and lively. <br>However, in the last few weeks, they <br>have gone ominously silent. Strange <br>lights have been seen coming from <br>the Stegeborg Castle, and seers in the <br>service of the Order have received a dark <br>omen. Something evil, hidden within <br>the meandering corridors of Stegeborg, <br>has been awakened. Now, everyone <br>will pay for the sins of one man. The <br>Hunters must go to Stegeborg and face <br>the danger the seers have foretold.<br>A Scenario Inspired by Sleeping <br>Beauty (Charles Perrault)<br>Stegeborg’s Quiet<br>Safety Keywords:  <br>Incest / Physical and Psychological <br>Abuse / Rape / Body Horror</p>","markdown":""},"sort":13500000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241742,"modifiedTime":1783973241742,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"19hIeeTsYCDcePqq","name":"Pagina 136","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 136</h2><p>135<br>The story that led us here…<br>The last member of the Schwernis family, former <br>lords of Stegeborg, remains in the castle. Talia never left  <br>when the castle was abandoned fifty years ago, and instead <br>was bound in eternal slumber. Talia had always submitted <br>to her father Alexander and mother Alexandra, twins <br>united in a perverse relationship. The couple was obsessed <br>with their daughter, who was the last of their children. <br>Each of the previous pregnancies had ended with the birth <br>of deformed children, all of whom had been smothered <br>by their disappointed parents. Talia represented the pure <br>beauty Alexander and Alexandra had been longing for. <br>Their dreams realized, they withdrew within the walls of <br>the castle and hid themselves from the rest of the world. <br>In her stone prison, Talia suffered all kinds of abuse at her <br>parents’ hands, finding support only in Carabosse, the old <br>cook of the castle. Unbeknownst to Talia, Carabosse was <br>once a powerful witch who escaped the great inquisition of <br>1645 in France. When Talia bled for the first time, her father <br>tried to force himself on her. The young woman fought <br>back and, unintentionally, pushed Alexander out of one <br>of the castle towers, causing his death. Crazed with pain, <br>Alexandra tried to kill her daughter, but was stopped by <br>Carabosse. The witch was moved with compassion for all of <br>Talia’s pain, and cast her last and greatest spell: she froze the <br>Stegeborg Castle in time. Talia, asleep in the underground <br>crypt, was imbued with the witch’s power so that she could <br>now move objects or grow plants merely through force of <br>will. Alexandra was transformed into a monster and forced <br>to be her daughter’s guardian for eternity. Talia’s wish <br>covered Stegeborg with ivy and brambles, a symbol of its <br>separation from the rest of the world. <br>The young woman, forever asleep, waits for someone pure <br>of heart and capable of breaking the magic that once saved <br>her, only to deliver her to a life of fading dreams. <br>Fifty years later, Accursio De Celeste, a renowned mercenary <br>and researcher, went to Stegeborg, attracted by rumors of a <br>rich treasure hidden in the castle’s dungeons. Overcoming <br>uncounted dangers, the man reached the dungeons to <br>discover the sleeping body of Talia, who was so impressed by <br>so much courage and skill that she decided to let him come <br>even closer. But Talia’s dreams were once more shattered <br>by the darkness of the human soul. Like her father fifty <br>years earlier, Accursio tried to abuse the beautiful Sleeper. <br>Anger and resentment once again overcame Talia’s mind, <br>animating the castle and cursing the entire village next to it. <br>In one night, all the inhabitants were killed or assimilated <br>by the castle, becoming monsters and prisoners. Accursio <br>took refuge in the Master Tower, waiting for his chance to <br>escape. Her soul forever scarred, Talia’s will is now out of <br>control, expanding beyond the walls of Stegeborg, in a slow <br>but inexorable attempt to assimilate the whole world.<br>The story at the arrival of the <br>Hunters…<br>The village near the castle is nothing more than a ghost town <br>where Georg, the only survivor of Talia’s fury, takes refuge <br>from the Quiet Guards: men and women merged with the <br>furnishings of the castle and transfigured into monsters, <br>now serving the Sleeper. Accursio lives in the Master Tower <br>of the castle where Talia’s power struggles to reach since <br>it is there that Alexander tried to rape his daughter. The <br>memory of so much pain weakens her abilities. Accursio <br>is aware that he cannot escape on his own, since the tower <br>has a single exit to the inner courtyard of the castle, and <br>Talia’s power can reach him there. Alexandra, now reduced</p>","markdown":""},"sort":13600000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241742,"modifiedTime":1783973241742,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"299AX3ZM5mMMYHLF","name":"Pagina 137","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 137</h2><p>1<br>STEGEBORG<br>136<br>to a deformed monster, wanders through the castle and waits <br>for someone to end her life. She had trusted Accursio, and <br>now that the man has proven as despicable as Alexander, <br>Alexandra has resigned herself to the idea that no one can <br>ever give Talia peace and thus put an end to the curse. A few <br>villagers led by a woman named Lisbet are kept alive inside <br>the castle, in the rooms that once belonged to the Schwernis <br>family. Talia holds them hostage, forcing them every night to <br>keep her company by reading stories and singing songs.<br>First Scene<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  It is almost sunset when you <br>glimpse the first houses of the village of Stegeborg. The imposing <br>shape of the castle looms over the small village, casting its great <br>shadow as if to swallow it. While an old stray dog raises its ears <br>in your direction, the unnatural silence that accompanies your <br>footsteps does not bode well.<br>Place: The small village of Stegeborg, devastated by the fury <br>of Talia.<br>Time: It is almost sunset, but the sky is clear and there is still <br>plenty of light.<br>Initial Situation: It’s apparent the village has suffered some <br>sort of disaster as soon as the Hunters arrive there. Doors <br>and windows are literally crumbling, while dozens of corpses <br>lie in the streets. On the wrists and neck of the bodies, one <br>can see the clear marks of something that seized them tightly <br>and dragged them with incredible force. Moving around the <br>village will immediately attract the attention of the Quiet <br>Guards, who will converge on the Hunters. There are a total of <br>10 Guards in town. Georg took refuge in the church, but the <br>fear of being captured led him to stay there for days and he <br>almost died of hunger. <br>Information: Saving Georg will yield some information. <br>The man arrived in Stegeborg a few years ago and does not <br>know the history of the Schwernis well. He does know that <br>fifty years earlier something so upset the noble family they <br>packed up and left in a single night, disappearing. Georg will <br>also reveal that, a week ago, an Italian treasure hunter named <br>Accursio De Celeste passed through the village, asking for <br>information about the castle. That same evening, he went <br>there, never to return. Soon after, all hell broke loose, and the <br>plants in the village came to life, dragging and strangling its <br>inhabitants. Georg survived by fleeing to the church. He hid <br>there, afraid to move after witnessing several villagers being <br>transformed into Quiet Guards.<br>Important note: Thanks to her Sleeping Spirit Gift, Talia <br>can interact with all the Places in the Scenario. Depending <br>on the actions of the Hunters, the Sleeper can be an ally or an <br>enemy. On page 142, you can find instructions for managing <br>the Sleeping Spirit Gift.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":13700000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241742,"modifiedTime":1783973241742,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"jt7nOIWEBMTRrhiK","name":"Pagina 138","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 138</h2><p>STEGEBORG<br>137<br>The Village of <br>Stegeborg<br>Descriptor: A small village at the foot of Castle Stegeborg, <br>devastated by the fury of Talia.<br>Georg the Survivor <br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I’m a poor laborer without a family. I once was <br>living in the streets.<br>Agenda: Escape from Stegeborg as soon as possible, so I can <br>leave what I saw behind me and start a new life.<br>The Quiet Guards <br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We are the poor inhabitants of the village, fused <br>with some of the castle’s furnishings. Our transformations <br>have driven us to madness and we blindly obey the will of <br>Talia.<br>Gift – Quiet Guards:  A Quiet Guard no longer possesses <br>a mind and acts as an object under the control of Talia. That <br>is why they cannot be mentally manipulated or frightened <br>in any way. Each Quiet Guard is a human body fused with a <br>part of the castle. Roll a die or choose a mutation.<br>1. Tools: The Guard’s arms are an agglomeration of tools, <br>such as shears and hammers. When attacking, the Guard is <br>considered to have an OL Medium 5.<br>2. Grating: The Guard’s body is covered with metal grates <br>and frames. It can suffer 1 additional Wound.<br>3. Chains: Ropes and chains hang from the Guard’s body. <br>With a single action, the Guard can interact with 2 targets.<br>4. Door: The Guard’s body is a huge pile of metal doors <br>and hinges. When defending itself, the Guard is considered <br>to have an OL Medium.<br>5. Fireplace: Burning embers are kept ablaze within the <br>Guard’s stomach. Once per Scene, the Guard’s attack inflicts <br>1 additional Wound.<br>6. Plates:  The Guard’s body is a cluster of plates and <br>glasses embedded in the living skin. When the Guard is <br>eliminated, it explodes into a thousand shards, inflicting <br>1 Wound to the one who dealt the last blow unless they <br>succeed a Defense Check.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":13800000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241742,"modifiedTime":1783973241742,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"J8DmdjWiYqznuOEx","name":"Pagina 139","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 139</h2><p>138<br>The Castle’s Courtyard<br>Descriptor: A large inner courtyard, which was once a <br>lavish garden. Now, ivy and brambles infest every crevice, <br>forming a real forest.<br>Threat – Forest of Animated <br>Brambles<br>Descriptor: Brambles and ivy animated by Talia’s ability. <br>We act to capture and strangle any intruders. We are guarding <br>the courtyard, waiting to end Accursio’s life.<br>OL Hard 7<br>Gift – Forest of Brambles:  The mass of brambles acts <br>under the magical power of Talia and can perform 1d6 <br>actions per Exchange. Each individual action can be used <br>in a different way. 1. Attacking:  Whip at or strangle a <br>target and inflict 1 Wound; 2. Ensnaring:  Immobilize <br>a target, preventing it from acting; 3. Manipulating: <br>Manipulate objects or the setting to open or close passages;  <br>4. Communicating:  Take the shape of rudimentary <br>letters. The Forest cannot be destroyed unless it is <br>completely set on fire and, even then, it will regenerate <br>within a few minutes. By inflicting 1 Wound, it’s possible <br>to hack away some branches and slow down the plants’ <br>growth, for example, to free an ensnared target. If Accursio <br>is present the Forest of Animated Brambles will focus on <br>capturing him, devoting at least half its actions to that <br>purpose.<br>Information: Access to the courtyard is easy, as the large <br>drawbridge of the castle is lowered. From the Courtyard, <br>you can access the Master Tower and the Main Court.<br>The Master Tower<br>Descriptor: A large six-story fortified tower, with barred <br>windows. The large main door is walled by brambles and <br>plants.<br>Information: Talia has blocked the only exit with her <br>Forest of Animated Brambles and attempting to force it will <br>activate its Threat (see previous column). By inflicting a <br>total of 3 Wounds to the brambles, you can open the door. <br>Accursio has taken refuge on the third floor where, slowly, <br>he is sawing the bars out of a window with the intention <br>of stretching a rope to the walls and escaping. Accursio <br>is the only one, besides Alexandra, who has a key to the <br>Dungeons.<br>Accursio De Celeste <br>Mercenary and Researcher of Renowned Fame<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a skilled adventurer and treasure hunter, <br>and I have no qualms about doing what it takes to get what <br>I want. <br>Agenda: Escape from Stegeborg while keeping the secret of <br>what I have done, as well as keeping the treasure I have found <br>/ Take advantage of the arrival of the Hunters in Stegeborg to <br>appease the fury of Talia. <br>Gift – Good at Escaping:  Accursio is skilled at making <br>himself scarce when things get bad. Increase his OL by 1 <br>for all actions involving fleeing or avoiding a menace. Once <br>per Scene, Accursio can move away from a place without <br>anyone being able to stop or see him. To do this, however, <br>it is necessary that something happens that can attract the</p>","markdown":""},"sort":13900000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241742,"modifiedTime":1783973241742,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"DI9WWvHVy81mez1h","name":"Pagina 140","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 140</h2><p>Master<br>Tower<br>Arrival<br>DrawbridgeCourtyardEntry Hall<br>Formal Dining <br>Room<br>Kitchens<br>Fireplace<br>&lt; Pantry<br>&lt; Staircase to cellars<br>&lt; Upwards stairsServants’ ChambersServants’ Chambers<br>Connection CorridorConnection Corridor<br>Guard RoomGuard Room<br>139<br>general attention for a few moments, such as a fight or a <br>sudden event.<br>Main Court <br>Descriptor: The largest block of rooms and halls of the castle. <br>Despite the passing of time, it’s still possible <br>to see faded hints of past splendors and <br>beauty.<br>Information: The Hunters enter <br>the castle by its entry hall, a <br>large room with several pieces of furniture on which visitors <br>could leave coats and weapons. From the entry hall, you can <br>access the Formal Dining Room and the Servant’s Chambers. <br>Use the map of Stegeborg to see what the Hunters are up <br>against. Some rooms on the map do not have pre-established <br>encounters. As with Events, feel free to create content in <br>accordance with the Hunters’ choices.<br>First <br>floor</p>","markdown":""},"sort":14000000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241742,"modifiedTime":1783973241742,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"3o3sbWn5K8ilbNgU","name":"Pagina 141","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 141</h2><p>Noble Rooms<br>Tapestry Room<br>Balcony Balcony &lt; Balcony<br>&lt; Balcony<br>Fireplace<br>Guard Room<br>&lt;<br>Staircase to <br>first floor<br>140<br>Formal Dining Room<br>A large and lavish ballroom where there are 6 Quiet Guards.<br>Kitchens<br>The great kitchens of the castle. By crawling up inside the fireplace’s <br>chimney, you can reach the Noble Rooms on the second floor. By <br>inspecting the Kitchens, you can see that meals are still being prepared. <br>From the Kitchens, one can access the Cellars (page 141).<br>Servants’ Chambers<br>Upon entering the Servant’s Quarters, the Hunters will find the bodies <br>of servants half melded with walls and sinking into the floor, frozen in <br>expressions of terror. Getting too close to the walls will rouse the servants, <br>animating them.<br>Connection Corridor<br>A large corridor in the east wing of the castle. From the large, barred <br>windows, the Hunters will notice the figure of a man moving in the <br>Master Tower. It is Accursio, working hard on his escape.<br>Threat – Walls of Memory<br>Descriptor: Bodies and stone come alive to hold intruders in <br>a crazy embrace.<br>OL Easy 3<br>Gift – The Horror Sculpted in the Stone:  When the <br>Walls of Memory come alive, surprised targets receive 1 <br>Penalty to any potential Defense Check. The walls grab a <br>target and whisper words of despair and suffering in their <br>ears. Those who hear them must decide whether to lose 1 <br>Soma or suffer 1 Wound before freeing themselves.<br>Second <br>floor</p>","markdown":""},"sort":14100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241742,"modifiedTime":1783973241742,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"x6wnCJSEEwN0pex5","name":"Pagina 142","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 142</h2><p>141<br>The Guard Room<br>A narrow, small chamber tucked between the two floors <br>of the castle, divided into two by a wooden weapon rack. <br>A large, barred door leads to the Noble Rooms. Trying <br>to open the door without Talia’s permission activates the <br>Phantom Weapons Threat, which will attack the intruders <br>as long as they remain in the room.<br>Threat – Phantom Weapons<br>Descriptor: A series of weapons that float in the air, ready <br>to strike at unwelcome visitors.<br>OL Medium 5<br>Gift – Blade Storm:  When this Threat is activated, 1d6 <br>different targets will be attacked by a blade during each <br>Exchange. If there are more attacking blades than targets, <br>each target receives 1 Penalty to Defense Checks to avoid <br>being hit. Two additional attacking blades impose 2 <br>Penalties to Defense Checks to all targets, and so forth.<br>The Tapestry Room<br>A large and sumptuous room covered with tapestries and <br>paintings depicting the Schwernis family. Almost all the <br>paintings are untouched, but the largest on the north wall <br>is ruined. It’s possible to make out that the painting depicts <br>a family: father, mother, and daughter. The parents are <br>so similar that they look like twins. The husband’s face is <br>obscured by old blood, while the mother’s body has been <br>warped by cuts and stains making it look like a monster. <br>The daughter, a cold and sad figure in the pose, has two <br>scratches on her eyes, making them appear closed.<br>Cellars<br>In the large Cellars of the castle, the old barrels and piles of <br>dirt are home to Alexandra. The monster will not hesitate <br>to attack any intruder. Here a large metal hatch allows <br>access to the Dungeons of the castle. The hatch is locked <br>with Talia’s magic, but it can be opened with her key. There <br>are two copies. One is in the possession of Alexandra and <br>the other is held by Accursio.<br>Alexandra the Mother<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (5 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a monster, deformed in body and mind. <br>The curse that keeps me alive means that I cannot forget <br>what I have done. Now, with my misshapen mouth, I can <br>only grunt and whine, preventing me from imploring the <br>forgiveness of my daughter.<br>Agenda: After more than fifty years of a cursed existence, <br>I have come to understand the damage my sins have done. <br>Unable to beg for her forgiveness, I show my daughter how <br>much I regret the past by doing anything she asks of me.<br>Gift – Deformed Orc:  Alexandra is a huge monster with <br>herculean strength. She can act twice during an Exchange, <br>but not consecutively. The curse makes Alexandra resistant <br>to magic. Any action using magic that involves her receives <br>1 Penalty.<br>Information: Upon her death, Alexandra’s body <br>will reverse to that of a gorgeous middle-aged woman. <br>Alexandra is the only one, besides Accursio, who has a key <br>to the Dungeons.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":14200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241742,"modifiedTime":1783973241742,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"M4XgWYbaCbyGvX9z","name":"Pagina 143","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 143</h2><p>Talia<br>Talia<br>142<br>Noble Rooms<br>Descriptor: A series of rich and beautiful rooms, preserved <br>despite the years passed.<br>Information: The only survivors of the village are held <br>prisoner in this part of the castle. Talia has Alexandra pick up <br>Lisbet every night to take her to the Dungeons and read her a <br>story. Lisbet is a young mother and her two children, Marita <br>and Lars, are among the prisoners. Lisbet realized that Talia <br>is nothing but a wounded spirit, so she tries to comfort the <br>girl by slowly gaining her trust. Lisbet’s hope is that sooner or <br>later, Talia will release her and all the other prisoners.<br>Lisbet<br>OL Medium 5 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am a young widow and I settled in the village <br>to start anew. I have experienced many misfortunes in my life, <br>which have forced me to become stubborn and strong-willed. <br>However, I’ve managed to stay kind and generous.<br>Agenda: To save all the prisoners by convincing Talia to do <br>the right thing. <br>The Dungeons<br>Descriptor: A series of tunnels and galleries full of barred <br>doors leading to the treasure room.<br>Talia the Sleeper <br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a young girl put to sleep for eternity by the <br>magic of Carabosse. The whole castle responds to my will and, <br>thanks to my powers, I can see and hear everything.<br>Agenda: Revenge myself on Accursio, who betrayed my trust <br>the way so many others have / Finding peace through death, or <br>assimilating everything I can with my power.<br>Gift – Sleeping Spirit:  Talia can literally manipulate the <br>entire castle as she pleases. During each Exchange, she can <br>perform up to 3 of the following actions. 1. Manipulate: <br>Move or reshape an object of the castle into something else; <br>2. Attack:  Throw and move objects to inflict 1 Wound;  <br>3. Reject:  Prevent people from moving, entering, or <br>leaving by manipulating objects, or even the castle itself. <br>Talia cannot speak, but she can use Manipulate to write or <br>compose rudimentary messages through objects. Talia can <br>concentrate all 3 actions into one with devastating effects. It <br>can collapse an entire wing of the castle or open a deep well <br>in the ground. The effects of this action are wide-ranging and, <br>at the discretion of the Storyteller, may remove one or more <br>Hunters who fail a Defense Check from the Scene.<br>Information: Next to Talia’s sleeping body, one can find her <br>diary, written with a pen manipulated by her hair. It tells the <br>Sleeper’s whole sad story.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":14300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241742,"modifiedTime":1783973241742,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"pZJkXvpLKGyK1TiR","name":"Pagina 144","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 144</h2><p>143<br>Note: Talia’s Gift, Sleeping Spirit, can be used in <br>countless ways throughout the Scenario. Below is a <br>set of suggestions for the Storyteller. Extracts of Talia’s <br>diary are on page 148.<br>Talia can:<br> ◆ Leave messages on pictures and furniture or send <br>the Hunters a page from her diary.<br> ◆ Lock and open doors to provide guidance.<br> ◆ Move the curtains on the windows to illuminate a <br>dark room.<br> ◆ Distort the paintings in the Tapestry Room so <br>her tragedy is better understood.<br> ◆ Lock the drawbridge to prevent someone from <br>escaping.<br> ◆ Withdraw the brambles from outside the castle, <br>pulling them in through the windows.<br> ◆ Use one of the prisoners as a warning.<br> ◆ Draw the Hunters’ attention to one of Accurio’s <br>belongings that has been left in the castle, and <br>which can hint at his presence.<br> ◆ Open a well in the treasure room as a way of warning <br>the Hunters away.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":14400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241742,"modifiedTime":1783973241742,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Ya2Gm8af1RdweilN","name":"Pagina 145","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 145</h2><p>144<br>Scenario Events<br>In this Scenario there are six Events. As a Storyteller, feel free <br>to create new ones in response to the actions of the Hunters.<br>At dawn on the day following the arrival of the <br>Hunters: Accursio will finish sawing the bars and will try to <br>escape by descending from the walls. Talia will unleash her <br>abilities and will capture him, taking him to the dungeons to <br>punish him.<br>If the Hunters manage to rescue Accursio from <br>Stegeborg: Talia will give into her fury, killing all the <br>prisoners except Lisbet. Now, the new target of the Sleeper’s <br>hatred will be the Hunters.<br>If the Hunters show interest in the history of the <br>Schwernis family:  Talia will ease the pressure on the <br>intruders, trying to guide them to the Tapestry Room.<br>If the Hunters make it clear to Lisbet that they are <br>there to save her:  the woman will say that she has read <br>some pages of Talia’s diary and that the spirit acts only out of <br>pain and trauma.<br>If the Hunters find a way to communicate with <br>Alexandra: she will ask them to save Talia from herself by <br>helping her to feel hope once more. Then she will drive the <br>Hunters to kill her by attacking them, so she can finally be <br>free from the curse.<br>If the Hunters reveal themselves to Accursio: he will <br>tell them that a spirit roams in the castle and that perhaps <br>something the adventurer stole has enraged it. The scoundrel <br>will seem sincerely repentant and will deliver what he has <br>stolen to the Hunters so that they can bring it back to the <br>basement and “appease” the spirit.<br>Scenario Gifts<br>These Gifts represent special abilities related to the Stegeborg’s <br>Quiet Scenario and can be acquired once the requirements <br>are met. A Hunter can only have one Scenario Gift and if they <br>acquire a new one, they will have to forgo the previous one.<br>Adept of the Quiet<br>Requirement: To have witnessed a manifestation of Talia’s <br>abilities within the castle.<br>Y ou realize that having a calm spirit prevents the castle from <br>perceiving you as a threat. Receive 1 Additional Success in <br>all Defense Checks you make against a manifestation of the <br>power of Stegeborg or a creature associated with the powers <br>of spirits.<br>The Castle’s Secrets<br>Requirement: Learn the secret passages of the castle from <br>Accursio or Lisbet.<br>Y ou know some of the many secret passages that connect the <br>whole castle. During a Scene, you can spend 1 Soma to find <br>a passage from one place to another in the castle, as long as <br>you have been there before. Y ou can’t leave the castle walls <br>with this Gift.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":14500000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241742,"modifiedTime":1783973241742,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"4Wb77g4JwMQT930H","name":"Pagina 146","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 146</h2><p>3a<br>1<br>2<br>145<br>FIRST SCENE –  Arrival at the <br>Village<br>It’s the same one you find on page 136.<br>End of Scene: After learning from Georg what happened <br>to the village and Accursio’s disappearance, the Hunters <br>continue their investigation at the castle. Go to the SECOND <br>SCENE – The Castle’s Courtyard.<br>SECOND SCENE – The Castle’s <br>Courtyard<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  After crossing the large <br>drawbridge, you finally arrive at the castle’s immense garden. <br>Brambles and ivy cover everything, and Georg’s description of <br>the havoc the plants caused in the village sounds more like <br>a story made up to frighten children. Two lights attract your <br>attention. One comes from the third floor of the large Master <br>Tower to your left. The second light shines from the second <br>floor of the castle. All the windows have thick bars and you <br>soon understand that the entrance doors of the two structures <br>are the only way to access the buildings.<br>Location: The large inner garden of the castle.<br>Time: Night has now fallen, a light coming from the tower <br>and one from the second floor of the castle shine in the dark.<br>Information: Talia will follow the actions of the Hunters <br>to understand their intentions and then animate the castle to <br>close them in by raising <br>the drawbridge. See <br>the Animated Bramble <br>Forest Threat on page <br>138.<br>End of Scene:  To <br>escape from the animated <br>brambles, the Hunters can <br>decide to enter the tower, <br>go to THIRD SCENE <br>OPTION A – Master Tower, <br>or the castle, go to THIRD SCENE OPTION B – Main Court.<br>THIRD SCENE OPTION A –  <br>Master Tower<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  When you eventually enter <br>the tower, the brambles seem to recoil as if frightened of the <br>place. A call for help comes from the stairs. It seems whoever <br>inhabits the third floor has witnessed your escape and is <br>descending at a rapid pace towards you.<br>Place: The old Master Tower, where Talia killed her father <br>to defend herself fifty years earlier.<br>Time: It is night and only Accursio’s lantern’s light <br>illuminates the bare, gray rooms of the tower.<br>Information: Accursio will ask the Hunters for help, but <br>he will soon understand that they too can do little against <br>the power of Talia. The cunning adventurer will tell the <br>Hunters that an evil spirit resides in the castle and that, <br>The Scenario Stegeborg’s <br>Quiet in Scenes</p>","markdown":""},"sort":14600000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241742,"modifiedTime":1783973241742,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"kX9nDnaJ8lHoRb0g","name":"Pagina 147","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 147</h2><p>3b<br>4<br>146<br>in his search of treasures, he must have inadvertently <br>awakened it. Appearing repentant, Accursio will ask the <br>Hunters to do something to save him since they are here <br>to solve the mystery. However, he will refuse to leave the <br>Tower, pointing out that the thorns almost killed him <br>when he tried to escape. To help the Hunters, Accursio will <br>show them one of the secret passages leading directly to <br>the Noble Rooms on the second floor. He will explain to <br>the Hunters that from there you can descend into a large <br>fireplace, reach the Kitchens, and then descend into the <br>Cellars where the evil spirit is located, avoiding most of the <br>dangers of the castle. <br>End of Scene:  Following Accursio’s directions, the <br>Hunters enter the castle through a secret passage, go to the <br>FOURTH SCENE – Noble Rooms.<br>THIRD SCENE OPTION B –  <br>Main Court<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  When you finally enter the <br>castle, the brambles seem to settle and still once more as if <br>nothing had happened. In front of you is the huge castle of <br>Stegeborg, a maze with over one hundred rooms.<br>Place: The gloomy and abandoned castle of Stegeborg.<br>Time: It is night and only the light brought by the Hunters <br>illuminates the large dust-covered rooms.<br>Information: When exploring the castle, the Hunters <br>will pass through various Places (presented on page 139) <br>in the following order:<br>Servants’ Chambers (page 140)<br>Tapestry Room (page 141)<br>Guard Room (page 141)<br>Talia will observe the Hunters and can intervene thanks to <br>her Sleeping Spirit Gift (page 142).<br>End of Scene:  Past the Guard Room, the Hunters will <br>have access to the second floor, go to the FOURTH SCENE <br>– Noble Rooms.<br>FOURTH SCENE – Noble Rooms<br>Note: The Hunters can reach this Scene after exploring the <br>castle or thanks to the secret passage indicated by Accursio. <br>In the second case, before setting up this Scene, they will <br>go through the Tapestry Room (page 141) and then the <br>Guard Room (page 141).<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: You close the big door behind <br>you and you can hear the clang of the ghostly weapons that <br>still slam on the heavy wrought iron reinforcements. This <br>area of the castle seems illuminated and in fact, within a few <br>moments, some human figures stare at you from the bottom <br>of a large dining room. A woman with a thin and tired face <br>raises a hand in greeting.<br>Place: The castle’s main room, where the Schwernis family <br>lived.<br>Time: It is past midnight.<br>Information: Lisbet will welcome the Hunters, telling <br>them that all the prisoners are kept alive by a monster that <br>lives in the cellars, which regularly brings food and water. <br>Lisbet is often taken to the castle’s basement by the creature <br>to read or sing old stories to a girl who seems frozen in <br>perpetual sleep. Talking to Lisbet, the Hunters will also <br>discover:<br> ◆ The monstrous creature that feeds the prisoners moves <br>freely around the castle and possesses incredible <br>strength.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":14700000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241743,"modifiedTime":1783973241743,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"dRqgkmfLLQpQcNev","name":"Pagina 148","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 148</h2><p>5<br>6<br>147<br> ◆ From the large fireplace in the dining room, you can <br>go downstairs to the Kitchens. From there you can <br>reach the Cellars where you can find the hatch for the <br>Dungeons. If the Hunters have spoken to Accursio, <br>they will then have confirmation that the man was not <br>lying.<br> ◆ Lisbet will say that the sleeping girl seems unutterably <br>sad and, despite what she has done in the village, Lisbet <br>cannot help but feel compassion for her rather than <br>hatred.<br>End of Scene:  Hunters can wait until Alexandra arrives <br>to ambush her or climb down the chimney and face her <br>directly in the Cellars. Go to THE FIFTH SCENE – The <br>Castle’s Orc.<br>FIFTH SCENE – The Castle’s Orc<br>Note: This Scene kicks off when the Hunters face <br>Alexandra.<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  What stands before your <br>eyes is a grotesque creature with vaguely human features. <br>An old noble woman’s dress dangles from its shape like a rag, <br>soiled with blood and ichor. The being is short of breath, but <br>its muscles are tense and powerful. Only the eyes glow with <br>a deep light of suffering and madness, protruding from the <br>deformed face, which is dotted with pustules and bubbles. <br>The being roars with all its anger before hurling itself against <br>you.<br>Place: The castle cellars or the dining room where all the <br>prisoners are kept.<br>Time: A few hours left until dawn.<br>Information: Alexandra will fight to the death, in the <br>hope that the Hunters will end her life, freeing her from the <br>curse. Once she’s killed, she’ll turn back into the beautiful <br>woman she once was. Around her neck, she wears a chain <br>with the key to the Dungeons’ trapdoor.<br>End of Scene:  Hunters can descend into the Dungeons <br>and finally meet Talia. Go to SCENE SIX – The Sad Sleeper.<br>SIXTH SCENE –  The Sad <br>Sleeper<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  You pass down a few <br>long corridors before arriving at the castle’s large treasure <br>room. The door is wide open, and an unnatural green light <br>illuminates the entire room. The strange glow radiates from <br>a young girl floating in the air, asleep in an unnatural torpor. <br>Her skin is as cold and pale as that of a corpse. Only the very <br>long blond hair that lashes and moves unsettlingly allows you <br>to understand that this being is alive.<br>Place: The treasure room of the castle.<br>Time: The sun begins to rise as Accursio attempts his great <br>escape.<br>Information: Talia’s reaction will vary depending on <br>what the Hunters have done so far. Shortly after the Hunters <br>arrive, Accursio will be carried into the room by a group of <br>Quiet Guards and dragged in front of Talia to be executed.<br>End of Scene: The Hunters will be key to tipping the scales <br>in the epilogue of the sad story of the Sleeper of Stegeborg.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":14800000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241743,"modifiedTime":1783973241743,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"P585YNoFieb39r5P","name":"Pagina 149","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 149</h2><p>148<br>Talia’s <br>diary<br>Page 1 <br>How long will this captivity last? My parents say it is <br>for my own good, but in the meantime, sixteen years of <br>my life have passed without me ever setting foot outside <br>these walls. Father finally quieted my complaints by <br>giving me the keys to the Master Tower. I love spending <br>hours and hours in the tower, studying the villagers. <br>They go about their daily tasks, never knowing that I <br>sit here in a gilded cage and watch, longing to join in <br>their normal lives.<br>Page 2<br>My mother got very angry with the cook. Apparently, <br>she’s not as good a cook as Mother thought. The <br>problem is, Mother can be quite unreasonable. More <br>than once, I have seen her take out a fit of bad temper <br>on the servants. My father does nothing to stop her. On <br>the contrary, he seems to enjoy watching my mother <br>mercilessly wielding her authority to misuse the <br>servants. In the end, the cook ran away, leaving the <br>castle. My mother started calling her terrible names, <br>saying that such terrible food would have shamed <br>the whole Schwernis family. At dinner, my father <br>whispered something in my mother’s ear, running his <br>finger down her throat, and then together they laughed <br>rudely. I felt a shiver down my spine.<br>If I were a magician I would turn my mother into a <br>monster, because that’s what she is. Even if she looks <br>like a noblewoman, her soul is black and overflowing <br>with evil.<br>Page 3<br>The new cook is called Carabosse. She is a foreigner. <br>With the rumors about Mother’s cruelty, I don’t <br>wonder why no one in the village wants to work at the <br>castle anymore. Carabosse has a sweet face like that of <br>a loving grandmother, but also deep green eyes, which <br>seem to shine. She says she hails from the east and, if <br>I remember correctly, the prelate of the village on his <br>last visit spoke to my father of many witches fleeing <br>from the numerous stakes that are in use in Eastern <br>Europe. If Carabosse really is a witch, I hope she uses <br>magic and turns me into a bird. It would be nice to be <br>able to fly beyond these walls, above the clouds.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":14900000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241743,"modifiedTime":1783973241743,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"1rZEolV7S7IeRSzK","name":"Pagina 150","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 150</h2><p>149<br>Page 4<br>Mother caught me. Some servant must have tattled on <br>my little visits to the village at night. Or maybe it was <br>the villagers who betrayed me, despite all the coins I <br>gave them... They too are just bloody selfish. Now, every <br>single window in the castle has a thick metal grate, and <br>the transformation from a palace to prison is complete. <br>My parents say this is for my own good, that the world <br>outside the castle is dangerous for a pure soul like mine. <br>That I am the daughter they have always desired, their <br>most precious treasure. But their intentions stifle my <br>soul, drowning it in utter darkness. Only Carabosse <br>understands me, but she seems to grow more and <br>more tired and sick. My father often stares at me with <br>frightening eyes, whispering the word “desired. ” <br>Page 5<br>I’ve discovered the truth and it ruined me. My father <br>and mother are twin siblings. Their love has never been <br>blessed by God and their obsession with a daughter has <br>led them to so many miscarriages. What remains of my <br>brothers and sisters is in the basement, too deformed <br>to survive. When my mother learned what I had <br>discovered, I was sure she would kill me. Instead, she <br>smiled, a sweet smile like I have never seen on her face <br>before. She said I am ready, that I am old enough to run <br>the family. I have been living in this room for a week <br>now, but tomorrow my father will return and a strange <br>feeling grips my heart. I am afraid because no one is <br>coming to save me.<br>Page 6<br>It happened. Mom is devastated by grief, but I don’t <br>regret what I did. When my father tried to… I can’t even <br>write it down. I fought back with all my might. I pushed <br>him away from me, but I didn’t mean for him to fall <br>down the tower. But even though I didn’t intend it, I felt <br>relieved. And at that very moment, I realized that my <br>soul had been forfeited. Now I’m waiting for my mother <br>to decide my fate. She howled in sorrow for the three <br>nights after Father’s fall, cursing God and promising me <br>infinite suffering as punishment for taking away the love <br>of her life.<br>Today, Carabosse came to bring me dinner, gave me a <br>caress on the head, and told me that all this will end. <br>“Sleep, my little one”... were her last words. And with <br>that one kind gesture, I let myself go to sleep. The only <br>real means at my disposal was to escape the walls of <br>Stegeborg.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":15000000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241743,"modifiedTime":1783973241743,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"pLhESiLs7aGqBuSR","name":"Pagina 151","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 151</h2><p>150<br>Once upon a time…<br>Vigo, a Galician port city. The Hunters were <br>summoned by the Countess of Vigo herself to <br>investigate two dangerous assassins with very <br>particular methods. Several mutilated bodies <br>have been found in recent weeks: three handsome <br>young girls, whose faces were removed by the two <br>murderers. An old spinner from the port saw two <br>cloaked figures wandering through the alleys of <br>the lower city, and that is why the Countess firmly <br>believes that this is the work of a pair of murderers <br>and not a single individual. It is not the first time <br>that something like this has happened. Ten years <br>ago, similar murders had disturbed the city, never <br>to be solved. The murders included ritualistic <br>elements using blood and flesh that brought to <br>mind the blackest of magic. The Countess fears <br>that, whatever hand held the knife, something dark <br>has come to hunt the people of Vigo. A ceremony <br>commemorating the ten-year anniversary of the <br>Count and the Countess is to be held soon, and the <br>shadow of the murders darkens what should be a <br>day of celebration for the whole city.<br>A Scenario Inspired by Cinderella (Charles Perrault)<br>In your Eyes, with <br>your Feet<br>Safety Keywords:  <br>Murder / Torture / Mutilation</p>","markdown":""},"sort":15100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241743,"modifiedTime":1783973241743,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"aZavZBzICdYSleCE","name":"Pagina 152","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 152</h2><p>151<br>The story that led us here…<br>Ten years ago, Maria Di Bello, a wealthy widow who <br>had always been faithful to the King of Spain, lived in Vigo <br>with her three daughters. The elder two were the fruit of her <br>relationship with her beloved husband, while the youngest <br>was the unfortunate result of a one-night stand with a ship <br>captain. Maria had always loved everyone the same way: <br>Francisca the elder, Marta the middle daughter, and Cinder <br>the youngest. Cinder had been named for the strange gray <br>hair she had inherited from her father, strikingly contrasting <br>the intense blond hair of her mother and sisters. When the <br>current Count Azul of Vigo reached marrying age, Maria <br>offered all her daughters. Cinder was immediately rejected <br>due to her hair, described as “horrible” by the noble Azul. <br>Resentful and envious, Cinder turned to the Kind Mother, a <br>powerful witch residing in the port of Vigo who had hidden <br>her identity behind the curious name. With the Mother’s <br>help, Cinder committed several murders, removing skin <br>and hair from the victims and reshaping her body to look <br>exactly as Count Azul desired. Her mother and sisters <br>noticed the change, and Cinder was forced to silence them. <br>With her death near at hand, Maria appealed to what little <br>humanity she knew her daughter still had, asking her to at <br>least spare her sisters. Cinder agreed, but to ensure their <br>silence she maimed them both, digging out an eye and <br>cutting off one of their feet. One-eyed and lame, the two <br>sisters fled the city in hopes of a new life. <br>But fate was not kind to Francisca and Marta and, after <br>ten years as beggars and outcasts, they returned to Vigo. <br>Fueled by resentment and transformed by hate for their <br>cruel sister, the two have sworn revenge. In this, they are <br>supported by the now elderly Kind Mother, whose tongue <br>Cinder cut out after she asked the new Countess for one too <br>many favors. The ambition and ruthless cruelty of Cinder <br>has therefore forged a strange alliance, formed by all the <br>women she has wounded along the bloody road to a life of <br>luxury at the court of Vigo.<br>The story at the arrival of the <br>Hunters…<br>Cinder presents herself to the Hunters under the false <br>name of Princesca, the identity she used to seduce Azul. <br>The woman has many powers, such as enslaving animals <br>or disguising her appearance, as she has learned the art of <br>magic from the Kind Mother. The last remaining piece of <br>evidence that could link Cinder to her crimes is a pair of <br>glass slippers that the Kind Mother had created for her ten <br>years earlier. Clicking the heels of the magical slippers can <br>confuse or bewitch people. They were used to commit the <br>murders ten years ago, as Cinder bewitched her victims <br>so she could dissect them alive without interference. The <br>shoes fit Cinder’s feet perfectly, proving her involvement. In <br>addition, every night at midnight, Princesca returns to her <br>original appearance for a few minutes, revealing her true <br>identity before the magic recovers.<br>Francisca and Marta each wear a glass slipper and have <br>staged a return of the killer for two reasons: to put Cinder <br>under pressure, and to attract the attention of the Hunters <br>of the Order so that they shed light on the wicked actions <br>of their sister. The objective of the two is to be caught by the <br>Order and then try to bring the Hunters to their side.<br>Meanwhile, the Kind Mother plots her revenge. The old</p>","markdown":""},"sort":15200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241743,"modifiedTime":1783973241743,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Zt9LelRUqOd0TviE","name":"Pagina 153","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 153</h2><p>1<br>152<br>witch is helping Francisca and Marta only to destabilize <br>Cinder. Once the Hunters begin closing in on Cinder, the <br>Kind Mother will ask the Countess to use magic to return <br>her tongue, promising to deal with the Hunters in return. <br>However, having regained speech, and consequently the <br>ability to perform magic, the Kind Mother will instead be <br>able to take revenge on that wretched girl who, ten years <br>earlier, trampled on everyone for her own gain.<br>Nota: In this Scenario, two NPCs have a double identity.<br>Cinder poses as Princesca, the Countess of Vigo. The <br>Kind Mother poses as the Old Port spinner. <br>Keep in mind that either name may be used without <br>explanation when discussing these characters.<br>First Scene<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  You are led by a servant to <br>the great reception hall of the noble Vigo palace. The rich decor <br>and the large number of servants at work suggest that Count <br>Azul of Vigo is among the richest nobles in all of Galicia. <br>You are greeted by the Count himself, a handsome man in <br>his forties, and his wife Princesca. According to rumors still <br>circulating, she is a girl of humble origins picked from among <br>many candidates for her incredible beauty.<br>Place: The magnificent palace of Count Azul of Vigo.<br>Time: It is a hot summer morning.<br>Initial Situation: After a quick presentation by Count <br>Azul, Princesca will take the floor. The Countess will <br>explain what happened (the discovery of three corpses) and <br>how they were killed, which sadly recalls the events that <br>transpired ten years ago. From the interview, Hunters can <br>obtain the following information:<br> ◆ Ten years earlier, a murderer terrorized Vigo by killing <br>six young girls and removing parts of their skin and <br>hair. All the victims had in common were their blond <br>hair and their beauty.<br> ◆ The killer’s actions culminated in the massacre of an <br>entire family. Maria, Francisca, Marta, and Cinder Di <br>Bello were all killed the same night. This was the last <br>act of the killer before he disappeared forever. Note <br>that the other two victims were commoners killed <br>by Cinder so she could steal their beauty. They are <br>unrelated to the Di Bello family, and not important to <br>the current investigation. <br> ◆ In the last week, the bodies of three prostitutes who <br>frequented the port were found. All were known for <br>their beauty and a healthy head of blonde hair. Each of <br>them had the skin from their faces removed.<br> ◆ An old spinner who lives near the harbor is the only <br>witness. She told the guards of two black-clothed <br>figures who lured one of the victims into the shadows. <br>The girl followed the figures as if hypnotized, as if <br>sorceries and dark arts were involved.<br> ◆ As lord and lady of Vigo, Princesca and Azul instruct <br>the Hunters to unravel the mystery and thus put an end <br>to the murderer’s ten-year slaughter.<br> ◆ In a day, it will be the wedding anniversary of Azul and <br>Princesca and to celebrate the occasion there will be <br>a party in the summer palace located just outside the</p>","markdown":""},"sort":15300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241743,"modifiedTime":1783973241743,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"rmAZLkGdFM1JUuMJ","name":"Pagina 154","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 154</h2><p>153<br>city. The only obvious concern of the Count is <br>not to appear weak in front of his noble guests. <br>During the interview, it will be clear to the Hunters <br>that it is Princesca who holds the reins of the city, <br>and that her husband Azul is only a rich brat with <br>little concern for the sufferings of his subjects. It <br>will also be apparent that Princesca is nervous when <br>speaking to the Hunters. If asked about it, she will <br>deflect by reminding them of her (overly vague) <br>humble beginnings and highlighting how lucky she <br>was to marry the Count.<br>After the interview, Princesca will reveal to the <br>Hunters where to find the old spinner and the last <br>corpse. They’re both in the port area. <br>The Palace of Count Azul <br>of Vigo<br>Descriptor: A sumptuous noble palace in the city <br>center.<br>The Count Azul of Vigo<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am a rich and bored nobleman who <br>cares only about social position. <br>Agenda: To waste time between parties and <br>pleasures, leaving the burden of leadership to my wife <br>Princesca.<br>Cinder Known to all as <br>Princesca of Vigo<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC  <br>(3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am Cinder and, thanks to <br>magic, I pretend to be the attractive and kind <br>Princesca. Thanks to the power of the Kind <br>Mother, I control the entire city. I am cold and <br>determined and I won’t let anyone stand in <br>my way. <br>Agenda: Gain wealth and power by <br>manipulating my stupid husband / Solving <br>the mystery of the new killer who behaves <br>exactly as I did ten years ago. <br>Gift – Kind Magic:  Cinder is able <br>to use the magic that the Kind Moth-<br>er taught her. As an action, Cinder <br>can cast one of the following spells.  <br>1. Animal Servants:  A group of <br>animals (up to 6 subjects) blindly <br>obeys the will of Cinder, even per -<br>forming suicidal actions. Cinder <br>has used this power many times <br>on a pair of doves until they <br>have been completely enslaved <br>(see The Doves on page 154);  <br>2. Transmutation:  An ob -<br>ject or a portion of the envi-<br>ronment mutates to be trans-<br>formed into something else. <br>The mutation lasts through-</p>","markdown":""},"sort":15400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241743,"modifiedTime":1783973241743,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"0Gcaycu88vbLNfUX","name":"Pagina 155","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 155</h2><p>154<br>out the Scene and cannot affect living beings; 3. Wish: A <br>subject (other than the one casting the spell) can express a <br>wish and it will come true. The Storyteller will decide the <br>nearest mechanical effect to accomplish the wish, whether <br>it is a new Descriptor, to heal one or more Wounds, or to <br>obtain a Gift. The effect of Wish cannot bring the dead back <br>to life, it only affects the subject who expresses it and lasts <br>until midnight.<br>Gift – Beauty Wish:  Thanks to the power of magic, <br>Cinder can assume any appearance she wants. The effect <br>lasts until midnight and usually Cinder uses it to maintain <br>the appearance of Princesca.  <br>The Doves<br>OL Medium 5 – Minor NPC  <br>(1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We are two doves enslaved by the power of <br>Cinder. Magic has permanently broken our will and we <br>defend our mistress from all danger. <br>Gift – Go for the Eyes:  The Doves are skilled at hitting <br>the enemies’ weak spots. When a Dove manages to inflict a <br>Wound, it inflicts 1 additional Wound. In case of a positive <br>Outcome in a Defense Check, once per Scene, the Dove’s <br>attack will still inflict 1 Wound. This Gift cannot be used <br>more than once against the same target <br>during the Scenario.<br>The Port of Vigo<br>Descriptor: The great city’s port where ships from all over <br>the world are docked. The alleys in front of the port are a <br>crossroads of taverns, shops, and leisure houses. Even in the <br>middle of the night, there’s always life in the harbor. <br>Information: The Old Spinner resides in a small house <br>in the eastern part of the pier, while the last corpse was <br>found in the western area.<br>East of the pier:  The Hunters will be able to meet the <br>Kind Mother, who will present herself as an old silent <br>seamstress. Cinder knows that the spinner is the Kind <br>Mother, but gives no sign that she knows. The old witch <br>will communicate with the Hunters with some difficulty <br>and give them a brooch she found near the alley where <br>she saw the two cloaked silhouettes pass. The brooch bears <br>the coat of arms of the Di Bello family: the Kind Mother <br>herself will give directions to the Di Bello house, located in <br>the upper quarters of the city. The old witch will not follow <br>the Hunters, as she does not want to be seen by Francisca <br>and Marta.<br>West of the pier:  The Hunters will find Eduardo and <br>Felipe, two guards at the service of the Count of Vigo, <br>guarding the crime scene. The body of the young prostitute <br>(known as Estella) was moved to the icebox of an old fish <br>warehouse nearby.<br> ◆ The two guards will tell the Hunters that no one has <br>claimed her body. She is most likely one of the many <br>poor people just trying to get by. <br> ◆ Examining Estella’s body will confirm the removal <br>of all facial skin, performed with insane care. A very</p>","markdown":""},"sort":15500000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241743,"modifiedTime":1783973241743,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"A5kO6UjtHxBLWdwP","name":"Pagina 156","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 156</h2><p>155<br>precious ring was inserted in the young woman’s right <br>eye orbit. The ring has the coat of arms of the Countess <br>of Vigo engraved on it. The object was placed there by <br>Francisca and Marta to draw attention to Cinder. <br>The Kind Mother Known to all <br>as the Old Spinner<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am an old and powerful witch whose tongue <br>Cinder cut out. I can no longer use my magic, but I still have <br>potions and magic items to use for my purposes.<br>Agenda: Put Cinder under pressure so she asks for my help, <br>make her use Wish to give me back my tongue, and then use <br>my magic to take revenge on her. <br>Gift – Kind Magic:  As an action, the Kind Mother can <br>cast one of the following spells. 1. Animal Servants: A <br>group of animals (up to 6 subjects) blindly obeys the will <br>of the Kind Mother and even performs suicidal actions; <br>2. Transmutation:  An object or a portion of the <br>environment mutates to be transformed into something <br>else. The mutation lasts throughout the Scene and cannot <br>affect living beings; 3. Wish: A subject (other than the <br>one casting the spell) can and will express a wish. The <br>Storyteller will decide the nearest mechanical effect to <br>accomplish the wish, whether it is a new Descriptor, to heal <br>one or more Wounds, or to obtain a Gift. The effect of Wish <br>cannot bring the dead back to life, it only affects the subject <br>who expresses it and lasts until midnight. Note: The Kind <br>Mother cannot use this Gift unless she first finds a way to <br>heal her severed tongue.<br>Gift – Witch’s Treasures:  The Kind Mother possesses <br>a large number of magical objects and potions, which she <br>can use or give to her allies. Once per Scenario, she can <br>make use of each of these effects. 1. Potion: If ingested, <br>a potion bestows a Descriptor that provides an incredible <br>ability, such as flying or being invisible for the duration <br>of the Scene. No potion can grow her tongue back. 2. <br>Heirloom: The Kind Mother can get a hold of a Treasure <br>of the Order (page 5) that has not already been found <br>and is not in the possession of the Hunters.<br>Eduardo and Felipe<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We are two guards who are content to leave <br>thinking to other people. We do as we’re told while doing as <br>little as possible.    <br>The Di Bello Family <br>House<br>Descriptor: A large, abandoned villa in the bourgeois <br>districts of Vigo.<br>Information: Francisca and Marta live in the house <br>their mother abandoned. The two sisters traveled around <br>the world for a long time, but it was in mystical Prague <br>they underwent the strange rite that sewed their bodies <br>together. Now, the two women act as one creature, each <br>wearing on her foot one of the glass slippers that the Kind <br>Mother gave them. Francisca and Marta will be hostile to <br>the Hunters until they discover their identity. At that point,</p>","markdown":""},"sort":15600000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241743,"modifiedTime":1783973241743,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"TVBvoYPAyEZm9el0","name":"Pagina 157","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 157</h2><p>156<br>the sisters will fall at their feet, begging them to expose <br>Cinder, who has escaped the consequences of her crimes <br>for ten years, hiding under the false identity of Princesca.<br> ◆ The two sisters are willing to do anything to get revenge <br>on Cinder, including going to prison or even giving up <br>their lives.<br> ◆ They will reveal to the Hunters that Cinder uses magic <br>to alter her appearance. Ten years earlier their mother <br>Maria had discovered the deception when she surprised <br>Cinder at the stroke of midnight, the moment each day <br>when she must recast her transfiguration spell.<br>Francisca and Marta the Vengeful <br>Sisters<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (4 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: We are two poor sisters sewn together in one <br>body. We move with perfect coordination and cooperate <br>effortlessly, each aiding the other against any danger. <br>Agenda: Discredit Princesca and reveal to everyone that <br>she is Cinder, our despised sister.<br>Gift – The Razor-sharp Glass Slippers:  Thanks to <br>the magical slippers the Kind Mother gave them, at every <br>step Francisca and Marta can click the glass heels and create <br>a resonance that generates a state of confusion in subjects <br>within forty feet. When a Hunter acts under the influence <br>of the Slippers, they must perform a Defense Check against <br>OL Medium 5 or lose their action for the Exchange. This <br>effect is considered mental manipulation. Once per Scene, <br>the two sisters can click their heels and cause a vibration <br>that damages the minds of those within reach. All affected <br>subjects must pass a Defense Check against OL Hard 7 or <br>suffer 1 Wound. Activating the Slippers is considered a free <br>additional action for the sisters. <br>Gift – As One Body:  Francisca and Marta can act twice <br>during an Exchange, once for each sister.<br>Count Azul of Vigo’s <br>Summer Residence<br>Descriptor: A beautiful villa in the countryside of Galicia.<br>Information: The feast for the tenth wedding anniversary <br>of Azul and Princesca is being held in the villa. Noblemen <br>and wealthy bourgeois are among the guests at the reception, <br>while a large troupe of acrobats has the task of brightening <br>up the evening with songs, dances, and juggling. A skilled <br>animal tamer has been arranged at the explicit request of <br>Princesca, who will therefore always have animals (a tiger <br>and a bear) to control with magic if need be.<br> ◆ Talking to the guests during the reception, the Hunters <br>will discover that after ten years, many are still <br>wondering how a girl of humble origins could steal the <br>heart of Count Azul.<br> ◆ At the stroke of midnight, before the great final toast, <br>Princesca will fake being dizzy to get away for those <br>few minutes she needs to cast her transfiguration spell.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":15700000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241743,"modifiedTime":1783973241743,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"SeSg0kE2qD452Qku","name":"Pagina 158","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 158</h2><p>157<br>Akim the Tamer<br>OL Medium 5 – Minor NPC <br>(2 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a brave and skilled <br>tamer. The tiger Tasha and the bear <br>Berto are both dear to me, as they obey <br>my every command.<br>Agenda: Perform and amaze the <br>audience with my animals / Prevent <br>anyone from harming Tasha and <br>Berto, whom I consider as my children.<br>Scenario Events<br>In this Scenario, there are six Events. As a Storyteller, feel <br>free to create new ones in response to the actions of the <br>Hunters.<br>If the Hunters keep Princesca informed of the <br>investigation: the clever woman will quickly understand <br>that someone is framing her and will send Eduardo and <br>Felipe to deal with the Kind Mother. If the Hunters don’t do <br>something, the old witch won’t escape her fate. <br>If the Hunters defeat Francisca and Marta: the two <br>sisters will tell them everything they know, imploring the <br>Hunters to help expose Cinder.<br>If the Hunters unmask Cinder:  The Countess will <br>use the power of her magic to escape and run to the Kind <br>Mother for her help. Once she regains her voice thanks to <br>Cinder’s use of Wish, the Kind Mother will assist Cinder <br>to eliminate the Hunters and then take her time making <br>Cinder pay. <br>If the Hunters understand who the Kind Mother <br>really is: The witch will offer her aid in exchange for her <br>life and will seek their help in regaining her voice. <br>If the Hunters seek the support of Azul:  The Count <br>will pretend to be a fool and will even avoid taking measures <br>against Cinder once she has been unmasked. The man is <br>so willfully ignorant that he will ban the Hunters from the <br>city in order to keep his wife where she is, managing all the <br>responsibilities so he can lead a life of laziness. <br>If the Hunters trap Cinder during the anniversary <br>party: The woman will use magic to take control of Tasha <br>and Berto, sending them against the Hunters. Akim will <br>hinder the Hunters if they try to harm his beloved animals. <br>Cinder will try to escape to the Kind Mother by taking <br>advantage of the chaos. <br>Tasha the Tiger<br>OL Medium 5 – Minor <br>NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a fast and <br>aggressive, though trained, tiger.<br>Berto the Bear<br>OL Medium 5 – Minor NPC  <br>(3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a strong and massive trained <br>bear.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":15800000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241743,"modifiedTime":1783973241743,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"PBuhOQ9GWreQwh9t","name":"Pagina 159","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 159</h2><p>158<br>Scenario Gifts<br>These Gifts represent special abilities related to the In your Eyes, <br>with your Feet Scenario and can be acquired once the conditions <br>are met. A Hunter can only have one Scenario Gift and if they <br>acquire a new one, they will have to forgo the previous one.<br>Gift – Kind Blessing<br>Requirement: Show a sincere interest in solving the mysterious <br>murders in Vigo to the Kind Mother.<br>A powerful witch has blessed you with protection against magic <br>and sorcery. Receive 2 Additional Successes when you make a <br>Defense Check against a magic effect. The first time you inflict 1 <br>Wound on a target using magic, the blessing dissipates until the <br>next Interlude.<br>Note: The Storyteller can offer this Gift to the Hunter who has met <br>the requirements without revealing who the witch who casts the <br>blessing is. Simply, the Hunter will become aware that someone is <br>trying to help them.<br>Gift – The Razor-sharp Glass Slippers (Treasure of <br>the Order)<br>Requirement: Defeat Francisca and Marta.<br>Obtain the Treasure of the Order The Razor-sharp Glass Slippers, <br>see page 25 of the Treasury of the Order.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":15900000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241743,"modifiedTime":1783973241743,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"qot9eJhHHz38T4NX","name":"Pagina 160","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 160</h2><p>1<br>2a 2b<br>159<br>The Scenario Through your <br>Eyes, with your Feet in <br>Scenes<br>FIRST SCENE –  The Regents of <br>Vigo<br>It’s the same one you find on page 152. The Hunters will <br>talk to Azul and Princesca.<br>End of Scene:  The Hunters can decide whether to <br>interrogate the Old Spinner, go to SECOND SCENE <br>OPTION A – The Old Spinner. Or examine the body of the <br>last victim, go to SECOND SCENE OPTION B – The crime <br>scene.<br>SECOND SCENE OPTION A <br>– The Old Spinner<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: The port of Vigo is very busy <br>and represents the heart of the city. Its importance can be seen <br>clearly in the constant flow of goods and the ships crowded at <br>the docks. Following the directions given by Princesca, you <br>come to a small house in one of the alleys right next to a large <br>fish market, each fisherman setting up his stall directly on his <br>docked boat. You find the door to the small open dwelling, <br>and when you enter you see the figure of an old lady sewing. <br>The woman opens her mouth as if to greet you, but no <br>sound emerges. It quickly becomes clear her tongue has been <br>removed, leaving only a stump behind in her mouth. <br>Place: A small house that the spinner also uses as a <br>tailoring workshop. <br>Time: It is late morning and the smell of fresh fish coming <br>from the fishermen’s ships tickles the nostrils. <br>Information: The Kind Mother will welcome the <br>Hunters, trying to make herself understood to the best of <br>her ability, and will give the same information presented <br>on page 155. <br>End of Scene: Having obtained the brooch and directions <br>to the house of the Di Bello family, the Hunters can go there <br>to investigate. Go to THIRD SCENE – The old house of the <br>Di Bello family. Or examine the body of the last victim, go <br>to SECOND SCENE OPTION B – The crime scene.<br>Note: For correct management of the clues, the Hunters <br>must go to an interview with the Old Spinner before the <br>THIRD SCENE – The old house of the Di Bello family.<br>SECOND SCENE OPTION B – <br>The crime scene<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  The port of Vigo is very <br>busy and represents the heart of the city. Its importance can <br>be seen clearly in the constant flow of goods and the ships <br>crowded at the docks. Following the instructions given by <br>Princesca, you arrive at an old warehouse that is now being <br>used as a morgue. Two men who look quite drowsy guard the <br>front door.<br>Place: An old warehouse in the western part of the port. <br>Time: It is late morning. A large ship from the Americas is <br>docking at the port.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":16000000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241743,"modifiedTime":1783973241743,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"I4kkK20ZB1cpgCh0","name":"Pagina 161","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 161</h2><p>3<br>160<br>Information: Eduardo and Felipe will be well disposed <br>towards the Hunters, letting them in to examine the body <br>of the victim. They can discover the information on page <br>155. <br>End of Scene: With all the doubts that the ring can put in <br>the minds of the Hunters, there are still some fundamental <br>clues missing. They can go and talk to the Old Spinner. Go <br>to SECOND SCENE OPTION A – The Old Spinner. Or, if <br>they’ve been there already, they can head to the THIRD <br>SCENE – The old house of the Di Bello family.  <br>THIRD SCENE –  The old house <br>of the Di Bello family<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  The house of the Di <br>Bello family is an elegantly imposing villa that, despite its <br>abandonment, stands out among the houses of the upper <br>districts of Vigo. Sun-bleached curtains in the second-floor <br>windows have been disturbed, perhaps by new occupants of <br>the long-abandoned home.<br>Place: The grand, abandoned house of the Di Bello family.<br>Time: It is just past noon.<br>Information: Francisca and Marta are in the house. As <br>soon as the Hunters enter, they will be attacked by the sisters. <br>Once defeated, the two women will reveal their identities <br>and the whole story of Cinder, asking for the Hunters’ help <br>in unmasking their sister. The two will suggest that the <br>Hunters confront Cinder during the wedding anniversary <br>party that will be held the following evening.<br> ◆ The two sisters will confess that they are using the <br>same methods and plan that Cinder used ten years <br>earlier. They will also say that they put the ring in the <br>victim’s eye (if the Hunters have found it) to guide the <br>investigation towards the Countess.<br> ◆ The two sisters will say they were helped by an old <br>witch who gave them the slippers. The woman left  <br>them the shoes without saying a word, so the sisters <br>could not see her face.<br>End of Scene:  It will now be clear to the Hunters that <br>the Countess hides a secret, go to the FOURTH SCENE – <br>Unmasking the Countess.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":16100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241743,"modifiedTime":1783973241743,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Azv4wLX2A1Yv2E9K","name":"Pagina 162","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 162</h2><p>4<br>161<br>FOURTH SCENE –  Unmasking the <br>Countess<br>This scene can develop in many ways and in many possible places, so <br>it’s presented below with different tips for managing your Scenario.<br>If the Hunters want to unmask Cinder: The best way will be to <br>catch her red-handed while casting the spell to alter her appearance <br>at midnight. If they wish to, the Hunters will be welcome to attend <br>the reception. Once unmasked, Cinder will stir up the beasts of <br>Akim against the Hunters, then try to flee to the Kind Mother <br>for help.<br>If the Hunters tell everything to Princesca: The Countess <br>will thank them, trying to dismiss them as soon as possible, and <br>then move her guards to arrest her sisters and the Kind Mother. <br>If the Hunters do nothing, the three women will disappear into <br>the dungeons of the castle never to be seen again.<br>If the Hunters attempt to expose the Kind Mother:  <br>The old witch will try to play on their pity to avoid being <br>handed over to the Order. The old woman’s primary goal  is <br>to regain her tongue thanks to Cinder’s magic. Once she has <br>done that, she will try to eliminate every potential witness, <br>Hunters included.<br>End of Scene:  However the Scene goes, once again the <br>fate of the unfortunate protagonists of this story will be in <br>the hands of the Hunters.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":16200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241744,"modifiedTime":1783973241744,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"dJEdVkgoSWw9TYs1","name":"Pagina 163","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 163</h2><p>162<br>Once upon a time…<br>Prague is a great city recovering from war, after <br>Fredrick the Great’s recently failed siege. Ostromir <br>Malý, the Bohemian regent of Prague, has sent <br>an urgent request for help to the Order. The <br>nobles charged with rebuilding Prague are being <br>murdered in a way that has shocked the city, one <br>each night and all by the same hand. Each corpse <br>has been found with a body part removed and a <br>message scrawled on the walls reading, “I will stay <br>with you always. ” Ostromir has commissioned <br>the well-known alchemist Konstantin Svoboda to <br>construct a new guardian for the city – a Golem <br>– but the construction has been delayed. Until <br>its completion, the Hunters have been called on <br>to track down the noble-stalking killer, while the <br>commoners of the city, enthralled, watch like the <br>audience at a play.<br>A Scenario Inspired by The <br>Happy Prince (Oscar Wilde) by <br>Tommaso De Benetti<br>I Will Stay with You Always<br>Safety Keywords:<br>  <br>Body Horror / Murder / Torture</p>","markdown":""},"sort":16300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241744,"modifiedTime":1783973241744,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"lO8ZjIA586ib1uSx","name":"Pagina 164","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 164</h2><p>163<br>The story that led us here…<br>In the city of Prague stood a statue called the Happy <br>Prince, so-called for its extraordinary beauty: the body of <br>the statue was covered with a thin layer of gold and the eyes <br>were sapphires. On the hilt of the sword are set beautiful <br>rubies. One quiet evening, a young swallow on his yearly <br>migration to Egypt decided to rest under the sculpture. The <br>Prince saw the way the ordinary people of Prague suffered <br>from hunger and fear in the half-ruined city, and the statue <br>wept with pity. The Prince’s tears moved the bird to feel <br>the same compassion for the commoners of the city. The <br>Prince convinced the swallow to take the precious things <br>from his body and bring them to those in need. “The living <br>think that gold can make them happy, ” said the Prince, and <br>on hearing that, the swallow consented. Day after day the <br>swallow stripped the statue of everything that was valuable <br>to give that wealth to the people of Prague, who were <br>ground endlessly beneath the bootheels of the powerful. <br>Doing so, however, took so long that winter arrived. The <br>swallow could no longer reach Egypt to be reunited with <br>his flock. He decided to stay near to the Prince, who the <br>bird now loved, until one sad day the cold froze the swallow <br>into a grim little statue. Being powerless to save his friend <br>finally broke the Prince’s heart. Now worthless, the statue <br>was removed and handed over to Konstantin Svoboda, the <br>alchemist, for his experiments. For some reason, the lump <br>of lead at the statue’s heart refused to melt.<br>At the request of God Himself, an angel descended from <br>Paradise to retrieve the two most precious things Prague <br>had to offer: the Prince’s heart and the body of the <br>swallow. But the angel returned to Heaven empty-<br>handed, for in both the heart of the Prince and the spirit <br>of the swallow pity had been replaced by hatred for the <br>way Prague had rewarded their generosity.<br>The story at the arrival of the <br>Hunters…<br>Deemed unworthy of Paradise, the spirit of the swallow <br>instead possessed the body of Alexandr Pták, known <br>professionally as Alexandr the Bird. He was a circus <br>acrobat whose trademark was long flights through the <br>air during the dangerous stunts that made up his act. <br>Alexandr, who officially disappeared a few weeks ago, is <br>now almost completely under the control of the spirit. <br>With the little lucidity he had left, the acrobat returned <br>to Černobog, the young son of a seamstress to whom <br>the swallow had donated two rubies. Černobog’s mother <br>died from hardship and deprivation she suffered in <br>making a noble’s party dress. The boy had long been <br>considering retaliation against the client who had made <br>such unreasonable demands. Černobog and Alexandr <br>overcame their communication barriers to reach an <br>agreement. First they would recover the Prince’s body <br>and then they would dedicate themselves to avenging his <br>memory. They arrived at the laboratory of Konstantin, <br>the alchemist in charge of building the Golem. <br>Konstantin was desperate. Despite all the resources that <br>had been provided to him, the work couldn’t proceed <br>without the essential missing ingredient, which is, <br>unfortunately for him, human flesh. The regent had <br>threatened to expel him from Prague in the absence of <br>developments, but the arrival of Černobog and Alexandr <br>seemed providential.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":16400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241744,"modifiedTime":1783973241744,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"i2zsOqNdWKM2uS9k","name":"Pagina 165","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 165</h2><p>1<br>164<br>Although Černobog had been ready to pay for it with a <br>ruby, the Prince’s body had already been melted down. <br>His lead heart, however, is still relatively intact. Konstantin <br>thus proposes a pact: Černobog will invest the ruby to buy <br>the old circus from which Alexandr comes, which will <br>become the new secret laboratory of the alchemist. Then <br>the boy and Alexandr will be able to devote themselves <br>to their revenge, each time taking a piece of the body of <br>the victims as part of their bargain with the alchemist. In <br>return, Konstantin will rebuild the Prince, unleashing him <br>during the upcoming dance at Prague Castle...<br>Note: This Scenario presents an investigation in which <br>Hunters have a wide range of options on how to proceed. <br>The initial presentation of the places corresponds to the <br>Read aloud to the Hunters of the Scene Tree mode. This <br>method makes it easier for Hunters to review the clues and <br>overall situation at the beginning of each Scene.<br>First Scene<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  The regent of Prague, <br>Ostromir Malý, welcomes you in his brightly lit study, located <br>inside the castle of the city, a fortified complex recently <br>renovated by Empress Maria Theresa of Habsburg. Behind his <br>slick desk of fine wood, the short, ragged little Ostromir almost <br>disappears. He welcomes you with a certain enthusiasm and <br>you immediately notice how nervous he is: after introducing <br>himself he begins to compulsively clean his glasses, while <br>trying in vain to attract the attention of two servants in order <br>to offer you refreshment. Without even letting you speak, <br>he tries to fill the silences with bizarre questions about the <br>nature of the Order, but he doesn’t seem really interested in <br>your answers. Around a marble table, seated on chairs lined <br>with red satin, there are three other people: an old man with <br>a long beard and gray mustache, a gentleman in his forties <br>with thick brown hair, and a gorgeous blonde girl in elegant <br>clothes. Ostromir introduces them respectively as Konstantin <br>Svoboda, a well-known alchemist, Bartoloměj Novotný, <br>assistant to the director of the National Theater, and Beáta <br>Czernin, a member of one of the noble families of the city.  <br>He then invites you to sit on empty chairs and, sinking into <br>his, begins to explain the situation.         <br>Place: A beautiful room in Prague Castle, too big for a <br>modest presence like that of Ostromir. In addition to the <br>table where much of the conversation will take place after <br>the arrival of the Hunters, there’s a beautiful display of <br>golden chandeliers hanging from the ceiling, large mirrors <br>with precious frames, fine carpets on polished floors, and, <br>on the walls, huge tapestries darkened by time. <br>Time: Late afternoon, an ideal time for tea.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":16500000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241744,"modifiedTime":1783973241744,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"vrvjk8zS31nxPHwg","name":"Pagina 166","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 166</h2><p>165<br>Initial Situation: Ostromir appears obviously nervous as <br>if he knows how much his success depends on the Hunters’ <br>help. <br>Information: From the interview with Ostromir, <br>Konstantin, Bartoloměj, and Beáta, the following <br>information can be obtained:<br> ◆ Someone is killing (or trying to kill) prominent <br>people in Prague. The connection between the cases is <br>obvious, as the words “I will stay with you always” have <br>been found written on the wall with various substances <br>at the crime scenes. <br> ◆ Beáta found her murdered lover in her rooms, wearing <br>a dress he’ d bought for her. He was found missing an <br>arm.<br> ◆ Bartoloměj found the theater director, Gabriel Černý, <br>lying with one leg severed on the stage where a new <br>show was to be performed just a few hours later. <br> ◆ Konstantin seems to have escaped the killer through <br>a coincidental routine change (he had been delayed <br>longer than usual in a nearby tavern), but his alchemical <br>lab was devastated.<br>Hunters can now choose where to start their investigations.<br>Ostromir Malý<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I rule Prague on behalf of Empress Maria <br>Theresa and, after the failed siege, I hold the city’s fate in the <br>palm of my hand. The recent murders are complicating my <br>life, though so far the noble families support my authority.<br>Agenda: Capture the assassin who is causing panic among <br>the nobles / Avoid a popular uprising.<br>Beáta Czernin the Noblewoman<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am part of the city’s elite and I take advantage <br>of it. Sometimes, my vanity and arrogance unexpectedly <br>cause annoyances. <br>Agenda: Distancing myself from my late lover Danek in the <br>eyes of my husband and family / Finding out which monster <br>may have murdered him in this way.<br>The Alchemical <br>Laboratory<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  You reach the workshop <br>from a small staircase on one side of Haštalská, the street <br>in Prague that runs alongside the Church of St. Castulus. A <br>stone corridor leads you to what looks like the entrance to <br>a cell, protected by a wooden door reinforced by large iron <br>bars. Konstantin pulls out a large key that he hangs on his <br>neck and makes his way inside the laboratory, where the <br>soft light of lanterns hanging on the wall illuminates a cold <br>space similar to a tomb. Built of red brick and furnished with <br>wooden tables and benches, the workshop houses hundreds <br>of stills, bottles, and parchments abandoned on dusty shelves. <br>Dried plants and other esoteric trinkets hang from the ceiling. <br>In the center of the room is a forge, which Konstantin uses <br>to process minerals of various kinds, while in the corner an <br>elegant wooden desk is covered with paperwork, inks, and <br>pens for writing. What strikes you most is the almost total <br>devastation of a wing of the laboratory, now a pile of rubble, <br>glass, and split wooden boards. On the ground, a dry puddle <br>of god-knows-what emits a nauseating stench. Konstantin</p>","markdown":""},"sort":16600000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241744,"modifiedTime":1783973241744,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"KOMMILHnd9CDIHM5","name":"Pagina 167","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 167</h2><p>166<br>apologizes for the mess, saying he didn’t have the strength to <br>fix it, “now that he’s alone. ” On the wall, written in smears <br>with dark mineral powders, you see: “I will stay with you <br>always. ” <br>Descriptor: An underground laboratory with a large forge <br>and esoteric trinkets. The east wing is a pile of rubble and on <br>the wall in front of you can clearly be read the phrase: “I will <br>stay with you always.”<br>Information: Depending on their ability to ask questions <br>and examine clues, Hunters can access some or all of the <br>following information:<br> ◆ Anything that was broken or stolen had little value, <br>with the exception of a lead heart that belonged to an <br>old statue that was recently removed from the city. <br>Konstantin says that the heart was the subject of his <br>studies, as he had not been able to melt it. <br> ◆ Konstantin is working on a secret project on behalf <br>of the city of Prague (the Golem), which he is very <br>reluctant to talk about. Apparently, it’s not proceeding <br>as planned. <br> ◆ A few days ago, a man who was in charge of cleaning <br>was fired: Georg Slanina, who lives in the nearby <br>rookery. Konstantin claims he was often intoxicated, <br>which is true. The real reason for the dismissal, not to be <br>revealed to the Hunters directly, was to allow Alexandr <br>to recover the Prince’s heart and stage the devastation <br>of the laboratory without inconvenient witnesses.<br>Konstantin Svoboda the Alchemist<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am one of the most prominent alchemists in <br>Prague. My brilliant experiments could easily backfire on me. <br>Agenda: Create a Golem thanks to my alchemical studies <br>and prove that no noble title or institutional position can <br>possibly compare to my alchemical knowledge. <br>Gift – The Secrets of Metal:  Konstantin knows arcane <br>words that allow him to control metal. Any action against <br>him involving a metal weapon or bludgeoning tool receives <br>1 Penalty. Starting from moderate amounts of raw materials, <br>Konstantin can also forge various metal objects with <br>unusual properties. The Storyteller must create a Descriptor <br>that outlines this property (for example: The alloy of this <br>dagger violently repels other metals). <br>Gift – The Secrets of Flesh:  Once per Scene, when a <br>metallic body is in the vicinity of warm flesh, whether it’s still <br>attached to the body or only recently removed, Konstantin <br>can utter some arcane words, forcing the two elements to <br>merge. The procedure causes 1 immediate Wound, and 1 <br>additional Wound during the painful medical procedure <br>necessary to untangle flesh and metal.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":16700000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241744,"modifiedTime":1783973241744,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"rOnEhWTf3s7bPBYj","name":"Pagina 168","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 168</h2><p>167<br>The Rookery<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  As you enter the rookery, <br>you realize that you are being spied on: tired and hostile faces <br>observe you from half-open balconies; mothers hurriedly pick <br>up the children playing in the street and the men spit on the <br>ground when they pass you by. On several street corners, you <br>notice men and women in brightly colored but worn clothes, <br>looking hungry and cold, asking for alms while standing on <br>their heads, juggling, or performing other little tricks.<br>Descriptor: A maze of old houses with faded walls. Weary <br>and hostile faces watch those who pass, while the poor and <br>hungry ask for alms along the streets.<br>Information: Depending on their ability to ask questions <br>and examine clues, Hunters may discover some or all of the <br>following information: <br> ◆ The general sentiment of the population with regard <br>to the recent murders, rumor of which has spread, is of <br>ill-concealed approval. The blank, unconcerned gazes <br>of any commoners interviewed makes it clear they <br>think the nobles deserved it. <br> ◆ This is a good point of contact between the Hunters <br>and some artists of the Circus of the Azure Sun. See <br>the section Cibulka Tavern for available information. <br> ◆ If they visit Georg, the characters find him drunk in his <br>house, and very aggressive. If subdued or persuaded to <br>speak, Georg will say that Konstantin is at his wits’ end <br>as the project he is leading on behalf of the city is not <br>going well. <br> ◆ The attic where Josef Slezák lived (see page 169) <br>burned down two days earlier. By convincing a couple <br>of soldiers to grant them access, the Hunters will <br>discover that the writer seems to have bought a huge <br>amount of wood, with which he feverishly filled the <br>stove until it exploded. The embers set fire to the rest <br>of the attic, devouring the roof of the house and Josef <br>himself. <br> ◆ If the Hunters are looking for him, Černobog (see <br>page 172) is not at home, as he is now permanently <br>stationed at the Circus of the Azure Sun. By breaking <br>in, however, they will be able to access his rooms. <br>There, the boy still keeps his mother’s sewing tools <br>and the notebook where she noted expenses and <br>orders, including that for Danek Brzobohatý (one of <br>the victims, details on page 168). On the front of the <br>notebook, there is the name of the woman: Hedvika <br>Potměšil.<br>Georg Slanina the Helper <br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I work very hard. I like to drink, and when I <br>do, I become a beast. <br>Agenda: Supporting my daughter, who now has to sell <br>matches on the street / Understanding why Konstantin fired <br>me.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":16800000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241744,"modifiedTime":1783973241744,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"o9J2jlaAAYhvkqGc","name":"Pagina 169","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 169</h2><p>168<br>Cibulka Tavern<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  Cibulka’s entrance is <br>blackened by dirt, soot, and the effects of bad weather. You <br>cross a stone arch and, pushing a heavy wooden door, you find <br>yourself in a tavern built under sturdy red brick arches, with <br>solid wood tables and stools. Despite the slightly suffocating <br>atmosphere caused by the smoke from the kitchens and the <br>faint light from the torches, the climate seems jovial. The <br>smell of meat and beer mixes with the sweat of the patrons <br>and the smell of urine in the corners. Cibulka is a place <br>where workers and merchants mix, without paying too much <br>attention to the social class. You make your way through the <br>noise, looking for valuable information.      <br>Descriptor: A dark tavern, built under massive, red brick <br>arches. The smell of meat and beer mixes with the smell of <br>sweat and urine.<br>Information: Depending on their ability to ask questions <br>and examine clues, Hunters may discover some or all of the <br>following information:<br> ◆ Several patrons can confirm that on the evening of the <br>intrusion Konstantin was in Cibulka until late. This is <br>rare, as he usually leaves the place in the late afternoon <br>to devote himself to his lab work during the night. <br> ◆ At a table, you can find several members of the Circus <br>of the Azure Sun, which had been put up in a field <br>near the walls of Prague. They seem disconsolate and <br>complain about the lack of work and prospects, even if <br>they continue to order food and drinks. If questioned, <br>they will reveal that the circus was purchased roughly a <br>week earlier with a single ruby. The owner of the Circus <br>of the Azure Sun sold everything, tents, and animals, <br>without thinking twice. Most of the performers were <br>fired shortly after by the new owner, a strange boy <br>named Černobog Potměšil. <br> ◆ Some claim to have seen Konstantin and Bartoloměj <br>engaged in a heated discussion at one of the tables a <br>few nights ago. <br>The Czernin Family Palace<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: As you climb the stairs that <br>line the large fountain in front of the baroque palace of the <br>Czernin, you can only wonder how many rooms it contains <br>beneath its massive roof. “Here you can see the damage from <br>cannonfire during the siege, ” says a laconic servant as he <br>guides you through the majestic halls that lead to the room <br>where Danek’s body was found. When you arrive, Beáta <br>welcomes you, and apologizes for the absence of her husband, <br>who is apparently “indisposed. ” The room has not been <br>touched: on the canopy bed lies the rotting corpse of Danek <br>Brzobohatý, conspicuously lacking an arm. The man’s body <br>has cuts and abrasions all over his torso. He is dressed in an <br>elegant woman’s dress, now completely ruined.    <br>Descriptor: A large castle in the Baroque style, which still <br>bears the marks of the siege of Prague.<br>Information: Depending on their ability to ask questions <br>and examine clues, Hunters may discover some or all of the <br>following information:<br> ◆ Beáta admits that the dress was a gift for her which, <br>apparently, Danek had ordered a few weeks earlier. She <br>would have worn it to the upcoming ball organized by <br>the regent at Prague Castle. <br> ◆ On the dress, if examined carefully, the initials H.P . <br>(Hedvika Potměšil, mother of Černobog) can be found.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":16900000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241744,"modifiedTime":1783973241744,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"ef78lFYPd4juyrXl","name":"Pagina 170","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 170</h2><p>169<br>Beáta doesn’t know exactly how Danek got his dress, but <br>she suggests he probably used a common seamstress, <br>since in her opinion the dress is not even that beautiful. <br> ◆ If the body is examined carefully, it will be clear that the <br>cuts and abrasions were caused by a whip, while the arm <br>was removed with a hacksaw. With the right knowledge, <br>it will be possible to discover that the whip is similar to <br>those used to tame animals, while the hacksaw is of high <br>quality, as might be in the possession of certain men of <br>science. <br>The Theater<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: You’re led inside the impressive <br>theater that stands out in front of the waters of the Vltava <br>river. A warm light is reflected on the golden mezzanines, and <br>beautiful red drapes lend the auditorium an extraordinary <br>elegance. This place is only for those who can afford it. Although <br>the murder happened several hours ago, nothing has been <br>touched while awaiting the Order’s investigation. The body of <br>the theater director Gabriel Černý is on Cleopatra’s throne, <br>missing a leg. The puddle of now-dried blood has stained the <br>stage. Bartoloměj looks at it with concern and declares: “We will <br>get back on our feet, and we will bring the audience back to the <br>theater even after this horrible tragedy. ”   <br>Descriptor: A large theater richly furnished, reserved only for <br>the wealthiest in Prague.<br>Information: Depending on their ability <br>to ask questions and examine clues, <br>Hunters may discover some or all of the <br>following information: <br> ◆ The corpse is missing a leg, which <br>has been severed cleanly, but <br>the man appears to have died of <br>strangulation. An analysis might <br>suggest that a large reptile, such as <br>a Boa constrictor, was used. Such <br>an animal is incredibly exotic in <br>Prague (it comes, in fact, from the <br>Circus of the Azure Sun). <br> ◆ At the time of the murder, all <br>the staff, including the actors, had <br>returned home. Since the script had <br>arrived late, Gabriel was finalizing the <br>last details, something he often did.<br> ◆ Bartoloměj had a deep disagreement with <br>the director, especially about the opening show: <br>a reinterpretation of Anthony and Cleopatra by <br>Shakespeare, which Gabriel Černý had commissioned <br>from “a hack of a writer” named Josef Slezák. Bartoloměj <br>had repeatedly advocated instead for a focus “on the <br>masterpieces of various Bohemian artists. ”<br> ◆ Some janitors say that Konstantin and Bartoloměj have <br>met a couple of times lately to go drinking together, in a <br>place called Cibulka. <br> ◆ To be revealed only after the visit to the alchemical <br>laboratory and after some pressuring: on the night of the <br>murder, Bartoloměj agreed to leave a side entrance to <br>the theater open, at Konstantin’s request. The alchemist <br>argued that he could “resolve the problem. ” Unless the <br>Hunters have Konstantin with them, the alchemist is <br>already hiding at the Circus of the Azure Sun.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":17000000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241744,"modifiedTime":1783973241744,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"7cUIoMqUd5RNq9ko","name":"Pagina 171","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 171</h2><p>170<br>Bartolomej Novotný the Assistant <br>Director of the Theater<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am the young and ambitious assistant of <br>Gabriel Černý. Our differences were known. <br>Agenda: Make sure I am not blamed for the murder / <br>Make sure it doesn’t turn out that I facilitated the murder. <br>The Circus of the Azure Sun<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  Just outside the walls of <br>Prague, a battered blue and white tent stands in a muddy <br>field. Some smaller tents are surrounded by wooden wagons, <br>while a secondary tent connected to the larger one acts as <br>a shelter from the weather for animals. There is a strange <br>silence, as if the field had been abandoned, except for a <br>subdued metallic sound coming from the animal tent.<br>Descriptor: A dilapidated tent in the middle of a muddy <br>field. Wooden carriages and abandoned animal cages.<br>The camp is not actually abandoned, and at several hours <br>of the day it’s possible to see a young boy hanging around <br>the tents (Černobog). Konstantin spends every free <br>moment in the animal tent, where he is assembling the <br>Prince, while the main tent is mostly empty, except for the <br>presence of a huge nest made up of brushes and mud built <br>a few meters from the ground, and accessible only through <br>the stairs or the ropes of the acrobats. <br>Information: Entering the Circus of the Azure Sun <br>without being seen by Černobog is difficult but, once <br>inside, Hunters can access some or all of the following <br>information:<br> ◆ There is a large basin containing human remains, <br>still wearing some uniforms of the Circus of the <br>Azure Sun. These are the artists who did not leave the <br>circus after the acquisition of Černobog, now simple <br>spare parts for the Prince. It will be possible to find a <br>hacksaw nearby. <br> ◆ On a desk you can find an invitation to the dance at <br>Prague Castle, under the name Konstantin Svoboda. <br>On another sheet there seems to be a rudimentary <br>map of the city, with a path traced (the one Konstantin <br>plans to use to get the Prince to the Castle). <br> ◆ The nest, suspended in the center of the tent, is made <br>up of mud and branches and is extremely similar to <br>that of a swallow. It’s big enough to accommodate a <br>human being. This is where Alexandr rests when he’s <br>not out murdering someone. <br> ◆ Approaching the circus at night, the Hunters will be <br>able to see strange lights coming from the animal tent: <br>Konstantin is in fact finalizing the preparations before <br>activating the Prince.<br>Refer to the Events section of the Scenario to better manage <br>the situation. <br>^</p>","markdown":""},"sort":17100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241744,"modifiedTime":1783973241744,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"zwCQukLqgLKY2Vol","name":"Pagina 172","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 172</h2><p>171<br>The Prince<br>OL Medium 5 – Minor NPC <br>(6 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a Golem of blood <br>and flesh. There is only hatred in my <br>broken heart. <br>Agenda: Killing and tearing apart the ungrateful <br>people of Prague / I prefer to take my revenge on the <br>rich and powerful above all others. <br>Gift – Broken Heart:  Once per Scene, the Prince can <br>emit a freezing scream of pain that affects all living beings <br>in the area, causing 1 Penalty to any action against him. <br>Gift – Tornado of Blades:  The Prince’s body is <br>composed of arms, legs, and heads held together by a <br>metal structure. Any limb that can hold a blade <br>does. The Prince can start spinning, hitting <br>each opponent on his way in a single <br>attack, inflicting 1 Wound on anyone <br>who fails a Defense Check.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":17200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241744,"modifiedTime":1783973241744,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"TAjNQX2z9gn3tozg","name":"Pagina 173","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 173</h2><p>172<br>Aleksandr Pták<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am divided between who I was before and <br>the spirit who took possession of my body. I have the urge to <br>kill, but since my mind is clouded, I don’t always know why.<br>Swallow’s Agenda: Finding an ally in the people I helped <br>in my previous life / Restoring the Prince, my only true love / <br>Avenging wrongs suffered. <br>Alexandr’s Agenda: Finding peace and freeing myself <br>from the spirit that possesses me. <br>Gift – Swallow’s Flight:  Aleksandr can easily climb <br>anywhere and perform inhuman leaps. As he does, his OL <br>increases by 1. If he hits someone plunging down from <br>above, he can automatically escape the enemy’s threat range <br>with a long jump. <br>Gift – What is Yours is Mine:  As an additional action, <br>Aleksandr can steal any object in the hands of another <br>character with extreme ease. A Hunter can avoid the theft  <br>by succeeding in a Defense Check.          <br> <br>Cernobog Potmešil The Child<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: The rubies I received allowed me to recover <br>from the fever that had plagued me and, thanks to them, I <br>am now strong and healthy, but at what price? I feel anger <br>and resentment towards those who live on the shoulders of <br>the poor people of Prague. <br>Agenda: Avenge my struggling mother / Make sure the rich <br>pay for their crimes.<br>Gift - The Ruby of Hate:  Černobog uses one of the two <br>rubies he obtained from the Swallow as bait to achieve <br>his goals. When he distracts someone with the ruby, he <br>prevents the use of a Gift for the duration of the Scene. If <br>the ruby is crushed, Černobog suffers 1 Wound.<br>Prague Castle<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: On the evening of the party, <br>you are greeted in the majestic ballroom of Prague Castle. <br>A cascade of crystal chandeliers illuminates white arches <br>finished with gold, while large mirrors magnify the already <br>remarkable size of the room, full of people dressed elegantly. <br>You hear your name announced aloud, and everyone seems <br>intrigued by your presence. Ostromir introduces you to the <br>various families of the city, but despite the superficially happy <br>atmosphere, the tension is palpable. <br>Descriptor: The great and magnificent Prague Castle.<br>When the ball is at its busiest, a wall will be violently <br>destroyed by a large creature of flesh and metal crashing <br>^^</p>","markdown":""},"sort":17300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241744,"modifiedTime":1783973241744,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"tVTNdsGr0yQZYnip","name":"Pagina 174","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 174</h2><p>173<br>in: the Prince. Behind him will follow Konstantin, drunk <br>with power, cursing Ostromir and those who lacked faith in <br>him. Konstantin will try to control the Prince, as much as <br>possible, directing the creature first towards Ostromir and <br>then against the others. <br>Refer to the Events of the Scenario for other potential <br>situations at Prague Castle. <br>In the event that all threats have already been eradicated, <br>you can use the dance as an epilogue, changing the vibe: <br>the aristocracy can go back to sleeping peacefully, even if <br>the ordinary people of Prague see this return to normality <br>as an additional sign of contempt that sooner or later will <br>result in open rebellion.<br>Scenario Events<br>In this Scenario there are five Events. As a Storyteller, feel <br>free to create new ones in response to the actions of the <br>Hunters.<br>The second night since the beginning of the <br>investigation in Prague:  there is rumor of another <br>murder of a prominent citizen (the Captain of the soldiers, <br>known for harassing the population). The details are left to <br>the Storyteller, but this is a good time to have the Hunters <br>near the crime scene and stage a chase with Alexandr on <br>the rooftops of the city. <br>The dance in Prague Castle will be held the third <br>night after the arrival of the Hunters:  unless <br>Konstantin’s plan is stopped. The Hunters will be invited as <br>guests of honor by Ostromir himself.  <br>If Konstantin is discovered or killed:  Konstantin <br>will try to turn the Prince against the Hunters. Lower the <br>Prince’s OL by 1 if Alexandr’s only murders are those of <br>Danek and Gabriel. If Konstantin is killed before activating <br>the Prince, the Hunters will only have to worry about <br>Alexandr and Černobog. The ball at Prague Castle can also <br>be used as a trap to attract remaining threats. <br>In case the Prince is eradicated, but not the others: <br>Alexandr and Černobog will attempt a desperate move to <br>infiltrate Prague Castle during the ball to kill Ostromir and <br>every other possible aristocrat. Konstantin, if alive, will flee <br>the city knowing he has lost everything. <br>If the Hunters prowl around Prague without <br>concealing their identity:  the less affluent classes <br>will be generally hostile towards the Hunters, especially <br>since word has spread that they are working for the hated <br>Ostromir Malý. More than a few thugs will be happy to <br>block their way, accusing them of protecting the powerful. <br>Even some soldiers, knowing their Captain will protect <br>them from repercussions, could hinder the Hunters or turn <br>violent against the population in the area of the rookery.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":17400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241744,"modifiedTime":1783973241744,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"odkHAzGBCzbosE5f","name":"Pagina 175","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 175</h2><p>1<br>2<br>3a<br>4<br>5<br>3b<br>174<br>The Scenario I Will Stay with You Always in Scenes <br>FIRST SCENE –  The call of <br>Ostromir<br>It’s the same one you find on page 164, but there’s only <br>Konstantin present. The other two cases are mentioned, <br>but Ostromir says that Beáta and Bartoloměj will only be <br>available the next day. <br>After the interview with Ostromir, Konstantin will lead the <br>Hunters to the alchemical laboratory (page 165).<br>End of Scene: It will be clear that vital clues are hidden in <br>the poor neighborhoods of Prague. Go to THE SECOND <br>SCENE - The rookery and Cibulka.<br>SECOND SCENE – The rookery <br>and Cibulka<br>Suggest that Hunters go and ask some questions in the <br>rookery or tavern (page 167). They’ll find clues there.<br>End of Scene:  From here on, let the Hunters decide <br>whether to go first to Beáta THIRD SCENE OPTION A <br>– The Czernin family palace or Bartoloměj THIRD SCENE <br>OPTION B – The theater.<br>THIRD SCENE OPTION A –  <br>The Czernin family palace <br>The Scene takes place as described on page 168.<br>End of Scene:  Hunters can collect further clues by <br>interrogating Bartoloměj THIRD SCENE OPTION B – The <br>theater, or go to FOURTH SCENE – The circus.<br>THIRD SCENE OPTION B –  <br>The theater<br>The Scene takes place as described on page 169.<br>End of Scene:  Hunters can collect additional clues by <br>interrogating Beáta THIRD SCENE OPTION A – The <br>Czernin family palace, or go to FOURTH SCENE – The <br>circus.<br>FOURTH SCENE –  The circus<br>The Hunters will arrive at the circus during the night. They <br>will see the lights in the animal tent, and they will encounter <br>Černobog, Konstantin, and the Prince. Aleksandr isn’t <br>there, but he still poses a threat.<br> <br>End of Scene: The Hunters are invited to the ball, go to <br>the FIFTH SCENE – Prague Castle. <br>FIFTH SCENE –  Prague Castle<br>At this point the only threat left is Aleksandr, who in a last <br>desperate attempt will break into a window with the sole <br>aim of killing Ostromir.<br>End of Scene: the final clash will be against Aleksandr.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":17500000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241744,"modifiedTime":1783973241744,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"5M6F6HT0Vt2HcKuu","name":"Pagina 176","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen - Pagina 176</h2><p>Villager’s Sheet<br>PLAYER:<br>Name:<br>Age:<br>Role:<br>Description:<br> <br> <br> <br> <br>Your contact with the Broken tales:<br> <br> <br>DISTINGUISHING FEATURES: <br> <br>Your Bond: <br> <br>• Gifts:<br> <br> <br> <br> <br> <br> <br>Descriptor:<br>Descriptor:<br> <br> Possessions <br>1.<br>2.<br>3.<br> Wounds <br>XPSoma<br>Broken Tales The Village</p>","markdown":""},"sort":17600000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241744,"modifiedTime":1783973241744,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"librarySlug":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen-2022-06-29","category":"The Broken Ones","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","sourcePath":"C:\\Users\\Gamer\\Documents\\Broken Tales KS [ENG]\\bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf"}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241744,"modifiedTime":1783973241744,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"gt1LcuBZ9RVuznwx","name":"bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen","pages":[{"_id":"yG82vJIhEhZL3JkI","name":"PDF local","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h1>bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen</h1><p><strong>Archivo:</strong> bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf</p><p><strong>Paginas:</strong> 26</p><p><a href=\"systems/broken-tales/assets/source-pdfs/bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen-2022-06-14.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Abrir PDF dentro de Foundry</a></p>","markdown":""},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241744,"modifiedTime":1783973241744,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"IWV9Mf5L7fbQaAY8","name":"Pagina 1","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 1</h2><p>Alice  <br>of Other Worlds</p>","markdown":""},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241744,"modifiedTime":1783973241744,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"8f8V4i9tDj2yMR33","name":"Pagina 2","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 2</h2><p>Descriptors and Gifts<br>I am a skilled physician and psychiatrist, and <br>diagnosing illnesses is simple. My work has made me <br>particularly cold and detached.<br>• Physician: Once per Scenario, when you take the <br>time to treat an injury, you may heal 1 Wound suffered <br>by one of your patients, also bringing them back from <br>apparent death or unconsciousness. Y ou may spend 1 <br>Soma to reassure and calm someone who is frightened or <br>experiencing any negative feeling. If you do, you receive <br>1 Additional Success to any Check involving interactions <br>with that patient for the remaining of the Scenario. <br>Cheshire, my faithful trained lynx, is the most <br>trustworthy of companions – a shadow keeping <br>me safe from threats. Cheshire’s attachment is an <br>obsession and she may even threaten those who don’t <br>want to hurt me.<br>• Cheshire the Lynx: Cheshire is an NPC fully <br>under your control, with the following profile:<br>OL Medium 5 – (2 Wounds) <br>Descriptor: I am a big, short-tempered wild lynx and I only <br>live to serve Alice.<br>Gift - Two Souls: Y ou share your soul with Cheshire, and <br>you can see and feel through her senses. Y ou can spend <br>1 Soma to make Cheshire immaterial for an action and <br>allow her to cross any obstacle.<br>I am a young doctor who has dedicated her whole life to the treatment of mental illnesses. I understand <br>them, for I am suffering from one as well, and only those who burned themselves while playing with <br>fire can understand its dangers. After a dark period during which I managed a sanatorium, the Order <br>stripped me of all academic honors and degrees, reducing me to the status of a criminal. But it didn’t <br>take long for them to understand the extent of my studies and the magnitude of my abilities. After <br>possessing the Pope himself, I struck a deal with the Order. They will allow me to continue my studies, <br>but I may only study the creatures they fight. And perhaps, through the distorted minds of the Broken <br>Tales, I can prove that the worlds I visited as a child are real and not the ramblings of a mad mind.<br>Alice of<br>Other Worlds<br>As a child I traveled to other worlds and my mind can perceive and see <br>things beyond common perception. Memories of my childhood haunt me, <br>and I often get lost in visions of the past.<br>• Dark Ego - Alice of Other Worlds: As an action, you may spend <br>1 Soma to try to possess the body of a person or animal that is looking into <br>your eyes. Particularly powerful individuals may require a Position Check for <br>you to succeed. Y ou can act through the body you possess and continue to use <br>your Gifts and Descriptors, but you receive an additional Descriptor created <br>by the Storyteller and representing the abilities of the body you are possessing. <br>The possession ends at the end of the Scene, when the possessed body suffers 1 <br>Wound, or you decide to return to your body of your own volition. While you <br>control someone else’s body, your original body is inert and at the mercy of the <br>world. Y ou cannot possess Broken Tales or supernatural creatures. Y our mind is <br>not easy to control, so you gain 1 Additional Success for Defense Checks against <br>any kind of mind control and magic. <br>Activator: You notice a detail that does not match what you consider normal.<br>XP<br>Soma<br> 5<br>Equipment <br>A valuable doctor’s coat / Books about the human psyche / <br>A watch, a gift from someone I met on my travels / A lucky <br>rabbit’s foot / A set of sharp scalpels / A doctor’s bag / A deck <br>of cards which is missing the queen of hearts.<br>Wounds <br>1.<br>2.<br>3.<br>Extra <br>Wound.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241745,"modifiedTime":1783973241745,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"x77r8EnOjcxm9FeQ","name":"Pagina 3","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 3</h2><p>Beauty  <br>and her Beast</p>","markdown":""},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241745,"modifiedTime":1783973241745,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"zZYgdWF0hvXs25Sq","name":"Pagina 4","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 4</h2><p>Beauty  <br>and her Beast<br>Descriptors and Gifts<br>Dionysus follows me and protects me like a faithful beast, <br>and responds to all my commands. As useful as this is, I feel <br>disgusted every time he comes near me.<br>• The Beast: Dionysus is an NPC fully under your control, <br>with the following profile:<br>OL Medium 5 – (Wounds: as Bella’s current value) <br>Descriptor: I am a powerful and feral beastman. Only Bella’s scent <br>keeps me under control.<br>Gift - Monstrous:  If he intends to kill someone, Dionysus may <br>act twice in each Exchange. Once per Scene, Dionysus can break <br>or lift even a large object with extreme ease. <br>During Scenes, you decide how Dionysus acts. Any Wound one <br>of you suffers also applies to the other. When Dionysus is within <br>a few steps, you receive 1 Penalty to each Check due to the strong <br>disgust you feel for him.<br>I am charismatic and affable. My innate air of superiority <br>fascinates simple people. I love having all my eyes on me.<br>• The Beauty: Once per Scene, when you meet a new subject, <br>you may spend 1 Soma and declare that you have met them in the <br>past and that you made some kind of deal with them. Create, in <br>agreement with the Storyteller, an Agenda for them representing <br>the deal. If you take the time to talk to someone, the Storyteller <br>must reveal a clue about their current Agenda or a drawback of <br>one of their Descriptors. When someone shows a strong interest <br>in you, Dionysus, if present, loses the use of the Monstrous Gift  <br>because of the strong jealousy and shame he feels for himself.<br>I am Bellina Cantalupo, but everyone calls me Bella. I was once a servant to the bride of the monstrous Dionysus <br>Gonsalva. I played my cards well, charmed the nobleman, and rose to power. Unfortunately, the Order got in the <br>way and sabotaged everything I had built. As a punishment, I was magically bound to Dionysus and now our <br>souls are intertwined. I feel his pain and his beastly instincts. Dionysus perceives, in turn, my disgust for him, <br>but it doesn’t affect the mad love he feels for me. I serve the Order in the hope of gaining its grace and being <br>released from this punishment. But, deep down in my heart, I still long for the power that I was denied being born <br>a peasant, but that I know I deserve.<br>I am linked to Dionysus and we share pain and perceptions. He will <br>always know where I am and vice versa. For me, that’s the most <br>humiliating part of the curse.<br>• Dark Ego - Beasts in Body and Soul: When you reveal your <br>true nature everyone is horrified. One is a beast in body, while the other <br>is a beast in her soul. Y ou receive 3 Savagery Tokens that you can spend <br>during the Scene to: <br>1. Inflict 1 additional Wound, if Dionysus spends an action to help you in <br>the attack. The Wound will be a strikingly bloody gash.<br>2. Have a minor NPC lose their action as they are intimidated, having <br>witnessed the fury of Dionysus.<br>3. If Dionysus is not present in the Scene, he can appear immediately <br>(possibly tearing a new opening in the environment, demolishing any <br>possible obstacle) to support you. <br>4. Perform a second action in the Exchange, if Dionysus spends one of his <br>to open the way for you.<br>Activator: Unleash the feral power of Dionysus, or humiliate or betray <br>someone, revealing your true nature.<br>Equipment <br>A leather whip and metal needles / A noble dress / Fine <br>dresses and jewelry / A rose that never fades / A bag <br>with dried meat with which to keep Dionysus’ hunger at <br>bay / Soaps and feminine perfumes / A poisoned stiletto <br>that I keep hidden for any eventuality.<br>Wounds <br>1.<br>2.<br>3.<br>Extra <br>Wound.<br>XP<br>Soma<br> 6</p>","markdown":""},"sort":400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241745,"modifiedTime":1783973241745,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"4mmDySn590vKPvsh","name":"Pagina 5","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 5</h2><p>Bloodwhite</p>","markdown":""},"sort":500000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241745,"modifiedTime":1783973241745,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"tofbyHr3MqIJskIU","name":"Pagina 6","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 6</h2><p>Descriptors and Gifts<br>I am a mutant and can alter my body as I wish. The Order uses <br>my unique abilities to support other Hunters. When it changes, <br>my body emits a particular hormone that arouses those close <br>to me.<br>• Mutant: Y ou start the Scenario with 3 Mutation Tokens. <br>Y ou may spend 1 Mutation Token to modify a part of your body, <br>such as turning your arms into wings or your skin into a thick <br>carapace. Create a Descriptor that represents the mutation. Y ou <br>gain 1 Additional Success whenever you take advantage of your <br>mutation. Whenever you change shape, the Storyteller can decide <br>that the hormone emitted by your body bewilders the mind of an <br>NPC nearby, creating a specific Agenda for them that leads them <br>to seek you in some way. Y our mutations remain until the end of <br>the Scene. Once per Scenario, the Storyteller can declare that this <br>Gift is activated without you realizing it and give you 1 Mutation <br>Token.<br>My touch is capable of mutating other beings with devastating <br>results. The flesh deforms before it explodes. When I am in the <br>grip of strong emotions, I lose control of my power and I am <br>afraid to touch the people I care about.<br>• Mutagenic Touch: Y ou can inflict 1 Wound to a living <br>being with the touch of your hand. If you kill the target this way, <br>it will explode in a gruesome way, scaring everyone present. The <br>most impressionable NPCs, at the Storyteller’s discretion, will <br>then try to avoid any confrontation with you. When you achieve <br>an Outcome with an Increment with your touch and kill someone, <br>your body assimilates part of the exploded flesh, and you may <br>recover 1 Mutation Token or 1 Soma.<br>I am a good girl and believe in the power of love and justice. My <br>pure gaze reaches the hearts of the people close to me. I try to <br>avoid those that look at me with disgust, believing me to be a <br>monster.<br>• Dark Ego - Pure Innocence:  When you appeal to the <br>purity of your heart, even the foulest spell is broken. When you <br>activate your Dark Ego during a Scene, you become immune to <br>any effect of fear or mind control, and all subjects you consider evil <br>lower their Opposition Level by 1 in your presence. Y ou can spend 1 <br>Mutation Token to give 1 Additional Success to the first action of all <br>allies who admire you for who you are.<br>Activator: Open your heart and appeal to the goodness of those close to <br>you, revealing who you are, or sacrifice something of yourself for others.<br>XP<br>Soma<br> 5<br>Equipment <br>A precious dress / A swallow-shaped hair clip, a <br>gift from my mother / An old gun, a gift from a <br>group of seven mercenaries who defended me for <br>a long time / The coat of arms of my noble family <br>/ A few small animals from the woods that follow <br>me, attracted by my smell.<br>Wounds <br>1.<br>2.<br>3.<br>Extra <br>Wound.<br>Bloodwhite<br>Starting at my birth, I have been called strange, an abomination or, at best, a mutant. And indeed, <br>my body is unlike any other and I possess abilities that my beloved parents have always called <br>“special”. All the inhabitants of Lohr, the city where I lived, have always shown me kindness,  so <br>I grew up driven by a great desire to help others. My family has gone to great lengths to protect <br>me, even resorting to crime to keep me safe. The arrival of the Order upset everything and, after <br>being captured, I was offered a deal which I couldn’t refuse. By entering the service of the Order, <br>I spared my family any trial and all their crimes are forgiven. After a lifetime of being protected, <br>it is my turn to protect them.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":600000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241745,"modifiedTime":1783973241745,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"nST1fVyRAmhYvD7o","name":"Pagina 7","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 7</h2><p>Carlo<br>the Living<br>Puppet</p>","markdown":""},"sort":700000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241745,"modifiedTime":1783973241745,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"4mUcgG87XJLfIg5U","name":"Pagina 8","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 8</h2><p>I am a puppet who has been animated by a magic ritual and though I remember a life, it is a lie. The spell gave me <br>memories of a childhood and feelings for the one I once called “father,” but none of it was true. Now, my only wish is <br>to become a real child. That desire has led me to trust dishonest people and commit crimes of which I was not even <br>aware. Everyone has always deceived me and promised things they couldn’t give me, starting with my father. But <br>the Order has forgiven me for my misdeeds, standing in the role of a new father figure: honest, straightforward, and <br>understanding. If I do everything I am told, I will be rewarded. I will finally become a real child… or maybe I lie to <br>myself as easily as everyone else?<br>I am an animated puppet and my body is made of wood. I don’t feel <br>pain, nor do I fear most things that would kill a real person. Only fire <br>scares me because it’s the only thing that could really end my life.<br>• Dark Ego - Soulless Puppet: Y our body is made of wood and <br>so you ignore any penalty derived from dangers that would affect a living <br>being. Y ou receive 1 Additional Success to all your Defense Checks. Y ou <br>can communicate with other puppets or toys who can tell you something <br>at the Storyteller’s discretion. If you stay still, you will pass as a common <br>puppet in the eyes of those who see you and you cannot be discovered <br>except with special skills or magic.<br>Activator: Make obvious use of the wooden properties of your body to perform <br>an action, or have your nose grow dramatically (i.e. when you accumulate <br>the third Lie Token), proving to everyone that you are not human.<br>XP<br>Soma<br> 6<br>Equipment <br>A school coat / An old textbook / A map to the famous <br>Field of Miracles / A small bag with some junk taken <br>from the stomach of a fish / A miraculous medicine, <br>gift of a Fairy.<br>Wounds <br>1.<br>2.<br>3.<br>Extra <br>Wound.<br>Carlo the LivingPuppet<br>Descriptors and Gifts<br>My life is animated by the magic of lies, and for this reason <br>I am skilled at recognizing and using both falsehoods and <br>magic. Even if admitting it is hurtful, my own life is a lie and <br>I move only because I pretend to be a real child.<br>• Lies: When you tell a lie, you can temporarily make it a <br>reality. Create a Descriptor that represents your lie and concerns <br>something about you that you pride yourself on, such as: I have the <br>strength of five men, or I can fly through the air. The Descriptor <br>remains throughout the Scene, and you gain 1 Additional Success <br>the first time you use it for an action. Each time you make use of this <br>Gift you receive 1 Lie Token. Y our nose will grow in proportion <br>to the amount of Lie Tokens you have. During the Scenario the <br>Storyteller can spend 1 Lie Token to give you 1 Penalty on a Check, <br>describing how your clumsy puppet body prevents you from <br>performing at your best. With every Lie Token spent, your nose <br>shrinks closer back to normal.<br>I want to prove that I am a good boy, and that is why I strive <br>to perform every task that is assigned to me. I naively tend to <br>trust adults blindly, even if I just met them.<br>• Always in the Middle of Trouble: Once per Scene, <br>when you face a danger or problem arising from a previous choice <br>you have made, you recover 1 Soma and get 2 XP . When you do <br>what an NPC asks and trust them without asking questions, you <br>can discard 1 Lie Token.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":800000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241745,"modifiedTime":1783973241745,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"qK0urBt1Cfm50KQh","name":"Pagina 9","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 9</h2><p>Hatta<br> Carter</p>","markdown":""},"sort":900000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241745,"modifiedTime":1783973241745,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"vkXvriizEaGWq6Ul","name":"Pagina 10","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 10</h2><p>I am an eccentric (although most would say crazy) inventor, always pursuing my next masterpiece. Time is my obsession <br>and to fight it, I build strange clocks with (insane) magical properties. In the past, I helped the noble (hateful) Alice of Other <br>Worlds in the design of her sanatorium (and she imprisoned me as a thank you) and I was accused (despite my most sincerely <br>altruistic intentions!) of being her accomplice because of it. The Order imprisoned me (again!), but when I showed them my <br>brilliant inventions, they did not hesitate to take me (under duress) into the ranks of their Hunters. Many (if not all) believe that <br>I am mad. But what they do not understand is that only those who are able to see “beyond” reality can actually shape it. <br>Even though I pretend everything is fine, I am aware of my <br>madness <br>and I count on it to always find incomprehensible solutions to any <br>problem. Sometimes, I convince myself of things that aren’t true.<br>• Dark Ego - Mad like a Hatter:  When you give free rein to <br>your madness, reality bends itself to prove you right. Declare something <br>crazy such as That door leads to the opposite side of town, or This pair <br>of glasses allows you to see ghosts and create a Descriptor. Y our madness <br>must always concern an object and its crazy use. Y ou cannot directly affect <br>or interact with living beings. Suffer 1 Wound caused by the fatigue of <br>turning your madness into reality. Y our madness lasts throughout the <br>Scene. If at least one subject is amazed by what you do with your madness, <br>you gain 1 Soma.<br>Activator: Behave and talk like a crazy person, not worrying about the <br>reactions of those around you.<br>XP<br>Soma<br> 6<br>Equipment <br>A valuable and improbably tall top hat / Evening <br>clothes / Watchmaker’s shirts and glasses / A <br>complete set of over twenty watches / My precious <br>toys / A modified gun that can shoot multifunction <br>bullets / A fancy tea set.<br>Wounds <br>1.<br>2.<br>3.<br>Extra <br>Wound.<br>Hatta<br>     Carter<br>Descriptors and Gifts<br>I am obsessed with time and when I can plan an action out, I can <br>complete it half the time a normal person would need. Sometimes <br>I lose focus on what I am doing, using twice as much time to <br>complete the simplest actions.<br>• Time Watches:  When you want to use time to your <br>advantage, you can twist the stem on one of your watches and choose <br>from the following. <br>1. Slow the World Down: Receive 1 Additional Success to your <br>next Position Check.<br>2. Speed up the Hatter:  Y ou can act immediately (unless you <br>have already done so during the Exchange) by interrupting anyone’s <br>action, regardless of what else might be happening in the narrative. <br>When you use your watches, you gain 1 Time Token. During the <br>Scenario, the Storyteller can spend 1 Time Token to freeze you a few <br>seconds in time and give you 2 Penalties to a Defense Check. If you <br>take an Interlude and drink some good tea, you can discard all the <br>Time Tokens you have accumulated.<br>I am a good toymaker and the small automata I build can <br>perform the most varied tasks. All my creations have a touch <br>of my madness and sometimes they don’t work exactly as they <br>should.<br>• Playmates: Y ou own three automated dolls, The Little <br>Hatter, The Hare, and The Dormouse. Each automaton can perform <br>small tasks, such as picking up and carrying items or delivering a <br>message. Each doll has a special ability.<br>The Little Hatter can explode, inflicting 1 Wound to everyone <br>within ten feet of it. <br>The Hare can always find a way, even through narrow places or <br>closed doors. <br>The Dormouse can fall asleep and deactivate to discard 1 Time <br>Token. <br>During Interludes, repair all automata.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":1000000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241745,"modifiedTime":1783973241745,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"HV2N3jygZWLzhaAY","name":"Pagina 11","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 11</h2><p>The Knight with<br>a Hundred<br>Heads</p>","markdown":""},"sort":1100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241745,"modifiedTime":1783973241745,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"GYsWa4vAB8AQMODf","name":"Pagina 12","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 12</h2><p>XP<br>Soma<br> 7<br>Equipment <br>A worn and colorful military uniform / My trusty <br>dueling saber / A pair of finely made guns / A large <br>tricorn hat covering my head / A pocket watch / A <br>braid of hair which belonged to the one I loved / A <br>letter from a comrade fallen in battle / A large scarf <br>with which to wrap my face and hide my missing <br>head.<br>Wounds <br>1.<br>2.<br>3.<br>Extra <br>Wound.<br>I was a skilled and feared cavalryman, veteran of uncounted battlefields. After my military service ended, I <br>retired to private life with my beloved family. But I could not leave the battle behind so easily and one of my enemies <br>found my home, murdering my family and removing my head. In a twist of fate, my trusty horse Ordog revealed <br>himself to be an evil spirit who brought me back from the dead with his magic, allowing me to pursue a vendetta <br>against my murderers. Headless and with no past, I killed many enemies, reliving their memories while carrying <br>out my revenge. Now that justice has been served, I will work with the Order as a Hunter for eternity. I have no <br>home to return to and I have to keep Ordog distracted, so he doesn’t steal the soul of some other poor devil.<br>I am an immortal knight and I do not feel fatigue or pain. My body <br>regenerates quickly. I don’t have a head and I have to disguise this fact <br>so as not to frighten ordinary people.<br>• Dark Ego - The Headless Knight: Y ou are an immortal <br>vengeful spirit. When you suffer your last Wound, you dissolve into <br>thin air to return at the beginning of the next Scene having recovered 2 <br>Wounds, and the Storyteller receives 1 Sleep Token. <br>Y ou can wear the head of someone you’ve beheaded, making it yours <br>for the remainder of the Scene. Y ou will receive some of your victim’s <br>memories through a flashback and a Descriptor that represents their <br>abilities. The Storyteller will relate this information to you.<br>Activator: Reveal who you are and show everyone that you don’t have a <br>head, or Ordog unveils a glimpse of his true nature.<br>Descriptors and Gifts<br>I am a swordsman and a Hussar knight with finely honed <br>combat skills. Ordog is more than a common horse and he <br>often saved me with his magic. Sometimes I wonder who the <br>real Hunter of the Order is.<br>• Ordog the Trusty Horse: Ordog is a strange horse-<br>shaped entity. He can speak and is uncannily smart, but he is very <br>sarcastic and capricious. Ordog will always know how to find you <br>and will overcome all obstacles to reach you. When you ask for his <br>help, Ordog will manifest his magical power and the Storyteller <br>will create a Descriptor that will allow him to do incredible things, <br>such as fly or pass through the walls. The Storyteller has full <br>control of Ordog’s will and whims, so expect to have to promise <br>him something or convince him of your reasons.<br>I am a tenacious defender and in my previous life, I always <br>stood my ground, never retreating. The memory of my loved <br>ones makes me melancholic and I cannot forgive those who <br>hurt families.<br>• The Bridge: When you protect a place or honor an oath <br>you have taken, nothing can overwhelm you. Once per Scene, you <br>may declare an oath in which you swear to defend something and <br>gain 3 Oath Tokens. As long as you act to fulfill your oath, you can <br>spend 1 Token to:<br>1. Resist being separated from what you are defending.<br>2. Gain 1 Additional Success for a Defense Check.<br>3. Inflict 1 additional Wound to an enemy, but only if this allows <br>you to eliminate them. If you do, you must decapitate them. <br>If you break your oath, the magic that animates you weakens and <br>the Storyteller gains 1 Sleep Token that they can spend at any time <br>to have you automatically fail a Check.<br>The Knight with <br>a Hundred<br>Heads</p>","markdown":""},"sort":1200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241745,"modifiedTime":1783973241745,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"PoeNW8Xj5IfvxTDG","name":"Pagina 13","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 13</h2><p>Iskra<br>the Young<br>Wolf</p>","markdown":""},"sort":1300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241745,"modifiedTime":1783973241745,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"xFtCnXiqo1adl8bZ","name":"Pagina 14","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 14</h2><p>Descriptors and Gifts<br>When I am calm, I still look like a small and helpless child <br>and, thanks to this, adults tend to underestimate me. I struggle to <br>behave like a normal child, but I can’t keep my wolfish side leashed <br>forever.<br>• The Red Hood:  Y ou can spend 1 Soma to look exactly like <br>a common child. Create a Descriptor that contains one of the words <br>Pretty, Small, or Sweet. As long as you maintain your disguise, no <br>adult will notice you or consider you a potential danger. Receive 2 <br>Additional Successes to the first action you take when you decide to <br>drop your disguise and reveal who you are.<br>I perform my best when I’m cooperating with my hunting <br>companions. I quickly learn the strengths and weaknesses of the <br>pack. I follow every order of anyone I consider more important <br>than me within the pack, without hesitation or remorse.<br>• Pack: When you coordinate and act with one or more of your <br>teammates against a common threat, you both get 1 Additional Success <br>for your Position Check. At the end of the Scene, if you have resolved <br>a significant issue thanks to the collaboration with your companions, <br>you recover 1 Soma.<br>Iwas abandoned by my mother in a large forest and survived by joining a pack of werewolves. After <br>a year of honing my predatory skills, I tracked down the woman I once called “Mother” and sank <br>my fangs into her throat. My pack was dismantled by a group of Hunters and the Order captured me. <br>After another year of education and training, I finally found in the Order my new pack and made the <br>Hunters my trusted hunting companions. I serve the Order with strength and dedication, happy to do <br>everything the alpha Hunter asks of me.<br>Iskra the<br>    Young<br>Wolf I am a wolf child and I defend myself with fangs and claws. My <br>sense of smell is infallible. I’m young and I know little about the <br>world, so I am easily intimidated when I face something I don’t <br>know.<br>• Dark Ego - The Young Wolf: Unleash your feral side, ready to bite anyone who opposes your pack. If you get an Outcome with an <br>Increment on a Position Check, you can spend the Increment to take an <br>additional action immediately. Y ou can also inflict 1 Wound on yourself <br>to perform an additional action after your normal action. Y ou can’t <br>perform more than 3 actions per Exchange. Y ou may spend 1 Soma <br>to memorize the smell of a person you are interacting with. Y ou will <br>always recognize them and it will be easy for you to follow their tracks <br>even after a long time.<br>Activator: Give free rein to your feral side or fulfill a task for your pack with your wolf skills.<br>XP<br>Soma<br> 6<br>Equipment <br>A red cape of fine workmanship, embroidered with the <br>coat of arms of the Order / A wolf mask carved in wood <br>/ A broken clay doll, a memento of one of my few happy <br>memories of my mother / A fang from the leader of my <br>old pack / A rag doll depicting a well-dressed girl, a gift  <br>from my beloved grandmother.<br>Wounds <br>1.<br>2.<br>3.<br>Extra <br>Wound.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":1400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241745,"modifiedTime":1783973241745,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"KZA1GJthyJF28dgY","name":"Pagina 15","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 15</h2><p>The Gang<br>of three Pigs</p>","markdown":""},"sort":1500000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241745,"modifiedTime":1783973241745,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"XdOHMNseJ7K9LM34","name":"Pagina 16","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 16</h2><p>The Gang<br>of three Pigs<br>Descriptors and Gifts<br>We are a gang and we use numerical superiority <br>to overcome our human limitations. Our faces <br>are always covered by a pig’s head mask, <br>intimidating ordinary people.<br>• Gang: Y ou can act as three independent <br>characters using all the same Descriptors, Gifts and <br>Soma. Each gang member has 1 single Wound, for a <br>total of 3. Each of you is skilled at something.<br>The eldest gains 1 Additional Success in actions <br>involving repairing or tampering with the <br>environment. <br>The middle brother gains 1 Additional Success in <br>actions to construct or tamper with objects.<br>The youngest gains 1 Additional Success in actions <br>not related to any kind of obligation or duty towards <br>the gang or the current mission.<br>Thanks to the flesh of the God Under the Mine, <br>our body is able to regenerate. We do not fear <br>pain or disease. Preserving the God’s meat is an <br>obsession for us, and is more important than <br>anything else.<br>• Eating the Divine: By eating the flesh, <br>you can regenerate your bodies and even return <br>from death. At the end of each Scene, each member <br>recovers their Wound as long as at least one of the <br>Brothers is still alive to activate the power of this Gift. <br>Once per Scenario, one of you can spend 1 Soma to <br>heal immediately from 1 Wound and come back to <br>life instantly.<br>We are three brothers who renounced their names to become emissaries of the God Under the Mine. We <br>were a group of anarchists and rebels, but the Order captured us, forcing us to become Hunters. We carry with <br>us the last piece of the God Under the Mine, an ancient and powerful creature. We keep the remains of the God a <br>secret so that the Order won’t get their grubby hands on it. By feeding on it, our bodies can regenerate and even <br>return from death, effectively making our gang immortal.<br>We are capable builders and there is no building that we cannot fortify or infiltrate. We <br>are very protective of what we think is ours.<br>• Dark Ego - Our Home:  When you arrive in a new location, you can take the <br>time to examine, alter, and repair it. Y ou may use one of the following options for each <br>present gang member.<br>1. Escape route:  Detail a Descriptor that represents an escape route that only you <br>may open.<br>2. Trap: Detail a Descriptor that describes how your trap activates and hurts intruders. <br>Those who enter the perimeter will trigger it, suffering 1 Wound. Skilled and attentive <br>individuals may require a Position Check to fall into your trap.<br>3. Improvement: Create a Descriptor that represents an improvement you make to <br>the environment. Y ou get 1 Additional Success when you make use of your improvement <br>during an action.<br>4. Alter: Detail a Descriptor that represents a new feature of the site that only you can <br>activate.<br>Activator: Take time to work on a location and make it your own.<br>Equipment <br>Pig’s head masks / Carpenter’s tool bags / Lots of bricks / <br>Lots of wood / Lots of dried straw / Picks and hammers / <br>Miners’ lanterns / Heavy leather work coats / A reinforced <br>case containing the flesh of the God Under the Mine / <br>Three keys.<br>Wounds <br>1.<br>2.<br>3.<br>Extra <br>Wound.<br>XP<br>Soma<br> 6</p>","markdown":""},"sort":1600000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241745,"modifiedTime":1783973241745,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"CRrywZSKULRmPoK1","name":"Pagina 17","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 17</h2><p>Morgana<br>     of the Lake</p>","markdown":""},"sort":1700000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241745,"modifiedTime":1783973241745,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"gsrIwoI5Zjir58kZ","name":"Pagina 18","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 18</h2><p>I am a young illusionist who has lost her memory. That is why I journey as a Hunter, looking for clues <br>about my past. Often, in my dreams, I see a powerful sorcerer and a great witch forging an alliance to <br>defeat me, overwhelming me with their joined power. I don’t know who they are, but my natural ability <br>to read the threads of fate tells me that they are responsible for my condition. After years of making a <br>living as an illusionist and soothsayer, an old man named Ambrose took me into the Order. He told me <br>that I would find a way to put my power to good use there.<br>My body contains immeasurable magical power, but someone has locked <br>it away. However, I can perform great magic when I manage to unleash it. <br>I can sense any magic active around me and the feeling sends a bone-deep <br>shiver through my body, making it difficult to mask my affinity.<br>• Dark Ego - The Supreme Fairy:  Y ou can unleash your true <br>fairy essence and alter reality itself. When you do this, you suffer 1 Wound <br>and choose an effect:<br>1. Making the Unreal a Reality:  One of your illusions becomes <br>real. If necessary, the Storyteller must create an ad hoc profile.<br>2. Supreme Fairy: Y ou may replicate a Gift with a magical effect you <br>have witnessed at least once during the Scenario, for the duration of the <br>Scene.<br>3. Lady of Destiny:  Y ou can change the fate of a Minor NPC by <br>rewriting its Descriptor and Agenda. This may not affect particularly <br>powerful NPCs or enemies, at the Storyteller’s discretion.<br>Activator: Evoke your true potential when experiencing a strong emotion or <br>when you find yourself in a magically charged location, and let yourself be <br>flooded with power.<br>XP<br>Soma<br> 5<br>Equipment <br>A practical, street artist’s dress / A silver headband, a gift  <br>from someone I have forgotten / A small diary where I <br>transcribe my dreams / An ancient coin engraved with the <br>word Camelot / Two wooden dolls I hold in my sleep, a witch <br>and a warlock.<br>Wounds <br>1.<br>2.<br>3.<br>Extra <br>Wound.<br>Morgana <br>     of the Lake<br>Descriptors and Gifts<br>I have always had an intuitive understanding of destiny. <br>Dreams and visions may come over me uncontrollably, giving <br>me a glimpse of the right thread to follow. I often see things <br>I’ d rather not and live with the pain of finding out what will <br>happen in the future of someone I care about.<br>• Weaver of Destiny: Once per Scene, you can give a goal <br>to an ally, such as Defeat that enemy  or Retrieve that item. As <br>long as your ally acts to fulfill the destiny you have indicated to <br>them, they get 1 Additional Success to all their actions. However, <br>if at the end of the Scene you have not achieved your goal, you will <br>both suffer 1 Wound due to the magical backlash of destiny. When <br>faced with one or more choices, you can spend 1 Soma and ask the <br>Universe to help you decide. Choose a Keyword such as enemy, <br>danger, or something else and the Storyteller will tell you which <br>of the possibilities in front of you is the most related to the word <br>you have chosen.<br>I am a skilled illusionist. Thanks to my power, I can conjure <br>tricks of light and mirages. I am hopelessly attracted to mirrors <br>and sleights of hand.<br>• Illusion: Y ou may spend 1 Soma to create up to three <br>illusions and move them as you like. Create a Descriptor that <br>represents your illusions. Every illusion is a distortion of the <br>visual field. Y ou may make them more believable by adding 1 <br>element, choosing from between sound, smell, or tactility. Y our <br>illusions are realistic, but they will be exposed if closely examined. <br>Alternatively, you may spend 1 Soma to create three illusory <br>copies of yourself to confuse watchers. Y ou gain 3 Additional <br>Successes for the first Defense Check you make. Y ou then subtract <br>1 Additional Success (down to zero) for each additional Defense <br>Check you must take.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":1800000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241745,"modifiedTime":1783973241745,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"OsscEu9WKNBpV4dT","name":"Pagina 19","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 19</h2><p>OZena<br>the Suffering</p>","markdown":""},"sort":1900000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241745,"modifiedTime":1783973241745,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"3lIu1etJY3LQRJfa","name":"Pagina 20","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 20</h2><p>OZena<br>the Suffering<br>Descriptors and Gifts<br>I trained to be an efficient fighter and assassin, taking <br>advantage of the magical shoes  I took from my first <br>victim. The disease that afflicts me disfigures my face and I <br>am ashamed of my condition.<br>• The Silver Shoes: When you move, you can teleport <br>for short distances, and this allows you to automatically elude <br>any attempt to impede or prevent your movements. Y ou need to <br>see where you intend to reappear. If you’re holding someone’s <br>hand, you can spend 1 Soma to bring them with you. Once <br>during the Scenario, you may make a longer trip, even of <br>several miles, but only to a place that you have seen at least once <br>before.<br>I have been leading a band of followers for a long time and I <br>know how a leader should behave. I’m good at imposing my <br>will on others. Even though I am often offered loyalty, being <br>a stranger far from my home in time and space makes it <br>difficult to trust others.<br>• Experience of a Dark Journey: Y ou have <br>accomplished many missions with strange companions and <br>have learned something from each of them. Y ou can invoke <br>each of these effects once per Scenario.<br>1. Tough as Tin:  Ignore 1 Wound you should suffer from <br>physical damage. <br>2. The Bravery of a Lion: Y ou gain 2 Additional Successes <br>when you throw yourself against a great danger without caring <br>about the consequences.<br>3. The Brain of a Genius Scarecrow: The Storyteller <br>will provide you with useful information about a place, <br>personality, or event you are dealing with. The information you <br>gain is always useful to what you’re doing.<br>I am a young American girl from 1939. Because of a magic tornado, I crashed into Broken Europe with a <br>strange doctor named Norman Henkle. I am suffering from a rare form of OZena, which disfigures my face <br>and has blighted my life ever since I was a child. Dr. Henkle deceived me with the promise of a cure and a way <br>back to my time, asking me to become a witch hunter. I committed crimes, even murders, until the Order put <br>an end to my madness. I was forgiven and found in the Order a new home that I don’t want to run away from. <br>Even if sometimes the memories of my “past in the future” resurface, making me homesick... What if the Order <br>is deceiving me as Henkle did? Am I always meant to be just a pawn in someone else’s game?<br>I am a person out of her time and largely immune to those who use spells and <br>magic. I have a natural talent for fighting those who use magic. I hate witches <br>and sorcerers because, despite their power, they can’t heal me.<br>• Dark Ego - From Another World: As a creature displaced in time, you <br>are naturally resistant to magic. Y ou gain 2 Additional Successes when defending <br>yourself from a danger associated with magic. When you inflict 1 Wound on a <br>being associated with magic, you prevent them from using their powers (Gifts and <br>Descriptors) during their next action. Blocking the powers of particularly powerful <br>opponents and Hunters may require a Position Check. When you touch a magic or <br>enchanted object, you can spend 1 Soma to temporarily interrupt its power. The <br>duration of this effect is decided by the Storyteller.<br>Activator: Reveal that you’re from another time through a gesture or a word. <br>Alternatively, act threatening towards a magical being.<br>Equipment <br>A green cape with a wide and drooping hood / A blade of <br>modern design / A bag full of small objects from my time / A <br>mask of delicate workmanship that depicts a suffering face / My <br>trusty silver shoes / A series of stilettos hidden in my blond <br>hair / The medal of my dear deceased dog.<br>XP<br>Soma<br> 6<br>Wounds <br>1.<br>2.<br>3.<br>Extra <br>Wound.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":2000000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241746,"modifiedTime":1783973241746,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"4kmzNVvL2SGqJ7q7","name":"Pagina 21","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 21</h2><p>Sherazade<br>the Weaver<br>of Tales</p>","markdown":""},"sort":2100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241746,"modifiedTime":1783973241746,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"KVfuGWLFKqYhGXsH","name":"Pagina 22","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 22</h2><p>Descriptors and Gifts<br>I know over a thousand stories and from each one I draw <br>a lesson with which to face dangers. I’ d do anything to <br>learn a new story.<br>• The Tale: Y ou start each Scenario with 3 Story Tokens. <br>Once per Scene, you may tell a short story. If you do, spend <br>1 Story Token and declare a Keyword that appears in your <br>narrative, then mark it down on your Sheet. During the <br>Scenario, if a Keyword you have marked is introduced during <br>a Scene by the Storyteller (for example, the Keyword is Soldier <br>and you come across Soldiers), erase the word to get 1 XP and <br>2 Additional Successes for either your next action or that of <br>one of your allies. When you learn an interesting new story, <br>you receive 1 Story Token.<br>I know the delicate art of flattery and I know how to best <br>compliment others to make them feel good. I will not <br>tolerate those who use violence.<br>• Words Like Honey: Y ou can speak beautiful words <br>to bring out a memory, an emotion, or a fear. Spend 1 Story <br>Token and choose one Keyword. Each NPC or Hunter who <br>has listened to you and is connected to the Keyword will <br>be overwhelmed by their emotions and will have to create <br>a relevant Descriptor and keep it throughout the Scene. <br>Particularly powerful subjects and Hunters who oppose your <br>power may require a Position Check. Y our allies receive 1 <br>Additional Success in the first action they take when using <br>any Descriptor created by this Gift.<br>I am the greatest storyteller that has ever lived, having learned my skills after serving a <br>wealthy sultan for many years. I can’t remember why I left, but I suddenly found myself in <br>Europe, where I used my skills against the Order and the Hunters. After my defeat, I was <br>forgiven, for it was clear to my jailers that a dark force had clouded my mind. I serve the Order <br>to regain my freedom, but also to find the one who corrupted my heart, forcing me to do harm. <br>I hate violence in all its forms and all I wish to do is brighten people’s hearts through stories <br>and poems.<br>Sherazade <br>the Weaver of <br>Tales<br>My stories become reality. Shadows, those ubiquitous reflections of <br>reality, can interact with me. A life among the shadows in my bedroom <br>has made it hard for me to bear sunlight.<br>• Dark Ego - One Thousand and One Nights:  One of the <br>characters in a story you told during the Session comes to life as a Shadow. <br>Create a Descriptor for them, ensuring it is driven to support you. The <br>Shadow could, for example, fly or walk on water. The Shadow thus created <br>will be at your service and will do whatever you order with an OL Medium 5 <br>and 1 Wound. For each Story Token you decide to spend, you can summon <br>an additional Shadow. Y our Shadows do not speak and cannot act in places <br>where there is more light than darkness.<br>Activator: Manifest your affinity for the shadows or tell a dark story full of <br>fear and monsters.<br>XP<br>Soma<br> 6<br>Equipment <br>Precious oriental dresses / A veil of red silk with which to cover <br>my face / A huge storybook / Incense and perfumes / A bag <br>full of gifts given by adoring nobles, who had been enthralled <br>by the stories I told / A small dagger coated with poison / The <br>comb with which I brushed the hair of my beloved sister / <br>The egg of a strange creature that was given to me as a gift by <br>Sinbad, the Traveler of a Thousand Seas.<br>Wounds <br>1.<br>2.<br>3.<br>Extra <br>Wound.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":2200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241746,"modifiedTime":1783973241746,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"ragT9fdeiwnLv0dC","name":"Pagina 23","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 23</h2><p>Talia the<br>Sleeper</p>","markdown":""},"sort":2300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241746,"modifiedTime":1783973241746,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"kgURswSDrSxGUWL9","name":"Pagina 24","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 24</h2><p>Talia<br>the Sleeper<br>Descriptors and Gifts<br>My body floats, carried by my power, ignoring obstacles of all <br>kinds. I can use my very long hair as if it were my hands. I <br>travel in a heavy nun’s habit and wear a mask to hide my true <br>condition from the world.<br>• The Cloak: Y our large nun’s cloak floats to defend you from <br>the world and contains many small items that you can manipulate. <br>Thanks to this Gift you are able to float and hover in the air, but <br>always at a speed equal to the pace of a human. Once per Scene, <br>you may:<br>1. Hide an object inside your cloak, hiding it from everyone (even <br>when searching through magic).<br>2. Extract from your cloak an object that you need. It can be rare <br>and peculiar, but not magic or unique.<br>I can communicate with those who are asleep  or <br>understand their desires and fears through dreams. I hate <br>it when there are too many people around. The buzz of their <br>lives reminds me of what I can’t have.<br>• In the Dream: Once per Scene, you can freely <br>communicate with a subject who is unconscious through a <br>dream. Alternatively, you may choose to spend 1 Soma to “read” <br>the dreams of a conscious subject. The Storyteller will reveal all or <br>part of the subject’s Agenda to you through the narration of one <br>of their dreams. Particularly powerful subjects and Hunters may <br>require a Position Check to be able to capture their dreams.<br>I am a cursed daughter, born from a forbidden love, destined to sleep forever. However, <br>my mind is alert and I perceive what is happening in the world around me. The curse that <br>afflicts me allows me to manipulate objects, which is why the Order kept me alive after saving <br>me from the castle that was my home and prison. As a Hunter, I am committed to ending <br>injustice and I hope to find a cure for my curse. However, the only thing I truly wish to find is <br>someone who won’t break my heart.<br>I can move objects with the power of thought alone. Through this power, <br>I am able to manifest my presence in the world. My real body is immobile <br>and locked in eternal sleep, at the mercy of the world. I long for the <br>least caress, which would remind me of being alive.<br>• Dark Ego - The Sleeping Will:  Y ou can use your power to <br>manipulate the objects around you. Y ou can make small items float or <br>throw them like weapons. Y ou can affect your surroundings up to 30 feet <br>away. Y ou can act up to 3 times in an Exchange, manipulating the world <br>around you, but you cannot act more than once against the same target. <br>Once per Scene, you can focus all 3 actions on a single large object (like a <br>house) and manipulate it to your liking.<br>Activator: Shed your cloak, revealing your helpless body or exposing yourself <br>to others by manipulating the world around you.<br>Equipment <br>A large nun’s cloak / A long hood with a veil hiding my face / <br>Objects and small things that float under my cloak / A piece <br>of ivy that has remained clinging to my left arm / The diary <br>in which I wrote about my sad life before the curse.<br>XP<br>Soma<br> 7<br>Wounds <br>1.<br>2.<br>3.<br>Extra <br>Wound.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":2400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241746,"modifiedTime":1783973241746,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"kOtWhzorwULiH1EB","name":"Pagina 25","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 25</h2><p>Yvonne<br>of theDark</p>","markdown":""},"sort":2500000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241746,"modifiedTime":1783973241746,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"BlfcXJgH5bMhpmex","name":"Pagina 26","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen - Pagina 26</h2><p>I am the spirit of a poor child who was burned to death by a wicked man. After my death, I <br>wandered restlessly through Paris until the Order found me and taught me how to control my new <br>form. Now, my life has meaning and I act as a Hunter in the hope of helping those who, like me, have <br>endured suffering caused by a cruel world. Although I can’t remember why, I have a deep dislike for <br>servants of the Church and for any who would pretend to be charitable without really helping others.<br>I am a ghost, but the Order has taught me how to make my body solid and tangible. <br>I can become ethereal for short moments and exploit my condition to my advantage. <br>Even though I mostly keep to myself, I suffer when I realize I’m on my own.<br>• Dark Ego – Solitary Ghost:  When you decide to take on your ghostly <br>form, you receive 1 Solitude Token and become intangible. Y ou cannot have any kind <br>of physical interaction with the world (not even talking) and no one can touch you, <br>except through magic. However, you do not become invisible to the human eye and so <br>those who see you will understand that you are a ghost. In the form of a specter, your <br>affinity to fire is more intense and you gain 1 Additional Success in any action involving <br>the flames you are manipulating. In addition, you can spend 1 Soma to ignite a flame <br>from thin air and set something on fire. The effect of this Gift lasts until you decide to <br>stop it, but the Storyteller can spend 1 Solitude Token to force you to remain ethereal <br>for a few more minutes. When you take an Interlude or spend time with someone who cares about you, remove all Solitude Tokens. When you use this Gift without satisfying <br>the Activator, you can ignore the Wound and take 1 Solitude Token instead.<br>Activator: React angrily when the world ignores you or makes it clear to you that no one cares about you.<br>XP<br>Soma<br> 6<br>Equipment <br>A worn-out cape / A bag full of candles / A tinderbox and dry sticks <br>/ Alcohol and other flammable substances / Some coins received as <br>charity / A small rosary donated by someone I don’t remember.<br>Wounds <br>1.<br>2.<br>3.<br>Extra <br>Wound.<br>Yvonne<br>of the Dark<br>Descriptors and Gifts<br>I died with my beloved candles in my hand and <br>was reborn with the power to control fire. I hate <br>staying in the darkness and I always want at least <br>a small source of light.<br>• Light the Flame: Y ou can manipulate fire, as <br>long as there is already a flame in the environment. <br>Decide whether to increase or decrease its size or <br>intensity, as well as the direction it burns. Y ou can <br>also manipulate the flame to hit something within <br>nine feet of it. Y ou gain 1 Additional Success to each <br>action you take while manipulating fire. The first time <br>you use this Gift in a Scene, the Storyteller may decide <br>that your action will spread the flames in some way.<br>I have no choice but to remain in my childish <br>body for eternity. I have a sweet smile and <br>people often feel protective towards me. Animals <br>perceive me for who I really am and they act up <br>in my presence.<br>• Innocent Smile: When you talk to someone, <br>you can spend 1 Soma to provoke their sympathy (the <br>Storyteller will evaluate whether or not the subject is <br>sensitive to your influence) to create an Agenda in <br>which the target feels somehow responsible for you. <br>During a Scene, if the location is crowded, you can <br>act or move without anyone noticing.</p>","markdown":""},"sort":2600000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241746,"modifiedTime":1783973241746,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"librarySlug":"bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen-2022-06-14","category":"The Broken Ones","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf","sourcePath":"C:\\Users\\Gamer\\Documents\\Broken Tales KS [ENG]\\bt-tbo-sheets-eng-final-screen [2022-06-14].pdf"}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241746,"modifiedTime":1783973241746,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"y5iiiwXRK5I9W7WI","name":"The Newcomer's Crown","pages":[{"_id":"3FO6wZyTwHF9CmKy","name":"PDF local","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h1>The Newcomer's Crown</h1><p><strong>Archivo:</strong> The Newcomer's Crown [2022-06-28].pdf</p><p><strong>Paginas:</strong> 1</p><p><a href=\"systems/broken-tales/assets/source-pdfs/the-newcomer-s-crown-2022-06-28.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Abrir PDF dentro de Foundry</a></p>","markdown":""},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241746,"modifiedTime":1783973241746,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"TrUgSXPhqTFZEURD","name":"Pagina 1","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>The Newcomer's Crown - Pagina 1</h2><p>The Newcomer’s Crown<br>Once upon a time, an old and dissipated king was served by a <br>company of knights, also old and tired. Although in the past the <br>kingdom had been an example of courage and righteousness, <br>now it was nothing more than a land lost to pleasure and <br>laziness. To fight his ennui, the king called a tournament in <br>which anyone could participate. The dissolute ruler’s intent was <br>to cruelly laugh while his knights were beating on some poor <br>peasant attracted by the idea of becoming a noble. On the day <br>of the tournament, however, only the knights had entered. The <br>people were discouraged by fear, despite the fact that the grand <br>prize, nobility, could change their lives forever. However, shortly <br>before the start of the tournament, a mysterious challenger <br>appeared, a small boy with a wooden sword. The king and <br>his knights laughed heartily, warning the fool not to enter his <br>name. In response, the young man said he wanted to become a <br>knight, and what better way to achieve his dream than winning <br>a tournament?<br>Taking pity, the king sought an excuse to prevent the young <br>man’s death at the edge of some random blade. “If you don’t <br>have a helmet to protect your head, I’m afraid you can’t <br>participate. ” The young man did not lose heart. Instead, he took <br>a small wicker basket, like those used as cradles, and put it on <br>his head. “I am ready, Your Majesty, ” replied the young man.<br>The king began the tournament… and the knights fell one after <br>the other. With absolute courage, against all expectations, the <br>young man defeated all the challengers before the stunned gaze <br>of the king. “ And now that I have demonstrated my bravery, can <br>you make me a knight?”<br>The king, visibly amazed, smiled. He thought about it for a <br>moment and then shouted, “ Arrest this young man! He’s the <br>Devil himself!” The guards grabbed him. Realizing the danger, <br>the boy begged the king for mercy. But the king certainly could <br>not allow true courage and purity of heart to sprout in his <br>kingdom, proving how unworthy he was to sit at its head. <br>And so it was that the young man’s head was lopped off by the <br>headsman’s ax, leaving the small basket as the only memory of <br>his courage and his purity, soiled with blood.<br>Keywords: Purity / Attempt / Challenge / Tournament / <br>Courage / Unexpected<br>Gift - The Newcomer’s Crown:  The Hunter who wears <br>the small basket as a helmet is infused with purity and <br>courage. When facing a threat for the first time, the Hunter <br>gets 1 Additional Success at both the first Position Check and <br>the first Defense Check they must perform. Once per Scene, <br>when they take an action where they do not have a relevant <br>Descriptor, they still get 3 Base Successes. Once per Scene, <br>when the Hunter fails a Position Check, they gain back 1 <br>Soma.<br>The Newcomer’s Crown<br>Inspired by the Arthurian Myth</p>","markdown":""},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241746,"modifiedTime":1783973241746,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"librarySlug":"the-newcomer-s-crown-2022-06-28","category":"Adventures","sourceFile":"The Newcomer's Crown [2022-06-28].pdf","sourcePath":"C:\\Users\\Gamer\\Documents\\Broken Tales KS [ENG]\\The Newcomer's Crown [2022-06-28].pdf"}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241746,"modifiedTime":1783973241746,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"7ulIzrjrUfWkuQqo","name":"Broken Tales - Bookmarks","pages":[{"_id":"pTHUFxwRBJeMmurB","name":"PDF local","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h1>Broken Tales - Bookmarks</h1><p><strong>Archivo:</strong> Broken Tales - Bookmarks [2022-06-30].pdf</p><p><strong>Paginas:</strong> 1</p><p><a href=\"systems/broken-tales/assets/source-pdfs/broken-tales-bookmarks-2022-06-30.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Abrir PDF dentro de Foundry</a></p>","markdown":""},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241746,"modifiedTime":1783973241746,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"c8NZitnlFgb6Pmv1","name":"Pagina 1","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"content":"<h2>Broken Tales - Bookmarks - Pagina 1</h2><p>Bookmark<br>Additional Descriptors<br>Story Gifts<br>Wounds<br>Notes<br>Soma    XP<br>Once upon a time...<br>Sheet<br> ←<br> ←<br>Additional Descriptors<br>Story Gifts<br>Wounds<br>Notes<br>Soma    XP<br>Once upon a time...<br>Sheet<br> ←<br> ←</p>","markdown":""},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1783973241746,"modifiedTime":1783973241746,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"librarySlug":"broken-tales-bookmarks-2022-06-30","category":"Sheets and Support","sourceFile":"Broken Tales - Bookmarks [2022-06-30].pdf","sourcePath":"C:\\Users\\Gamer\\Documents\\Broken Tales KS [ENG]\\Broken Tales Sheets ENG\\Broken Tales - Bookmarks [2022-06-30].pdf"}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":17